eel drive system)|quattro]]\n|{{convert|140|PS|kW bhp|0|abbr=on}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|9.7&nbsp;sec\n|{{convert|128.7|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2.0 TDI\n|{{convert|170|PS|kW bhp|0|abbr=on}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{no|}}\n|8.6&nbsp;sec\n|{{convert|141.7|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2.0 TDI quattro\n|{{convert|170|PS|kW bhp|0|abbr=on}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{no|}}\n|8.5&nbsp;sec\n|{{convert|139.2|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2.5 [[V6 engine|V6]] TDI <ref group=\"B7\" name=\"25TDI\">Only available for model year 2005. No [[Diesel particulate filter|DPF]] available for this engine. In 2006 replaced by the 2.7 V6 TDI engine.</ref>\n|{{convert|163|PS|kW bhp|0|abbr=on}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{no|}}\n|8.8&nbsp;sec\n|{{convert|141.1|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2.7 V6 TDI <ref group=\"B7\" name=\"NEWTDI\" />\n|{{convert|180|PS|kW bhp|0|abbr=on}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|8.4&nbsp;sec\n|{{convert|142|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|3.0 V6 TDI quattro <ref group=\"B7\" name=\"30TDI\">Only available for model year 2005. In 2006 replaced by a stronger version of the same engine.</ref>\n|{{convert|204|PS|kW bhp|0|abbr=on}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{no|}}\n|7.2&nbsp;sec\n|{{convert|146|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|3.0 V6 TDI quattro <ref group=\"B7\" name=\"NEWTDI\">Not available before model year 2006.</ref>\n|{{convert|233|PS|kW bhp|0|abbr=on}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|{{yes|\u2713}}\n|6.8&nbsp;sec\n|{{convert|152.25|mi/h|0|abbr=on}}\n|}\n\n<references group=\"B7\" />\n\n===Safety===\nThe Audi A4 offers many standard safety features, including [[Robert Bosch GmbH|Bosch]] ESP&nbsp;8.0 [[electronic stability control|Electronic Stability Programme]] (ESP) with [[anti-lock braking system]] (ABS), side [[airbag]]s in the seats, 'sideguard' curtain airbags, and its optional [[quattro (four wheel drive system)|quattro]] four-wheel drive system. It also received the [[Insurance Institute for Highway Safety]] (IIHS) \"Top Safety Pick For 2007\".<ref>IIHS.org [http://www.iihs.org/ratings/ratingsbyseries.aspx?id=558 IIHS-HLDI: Audi A4] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011091113/http://www.iihs.org/ratings/ratingsbyseries.aspx?id=558 |date=11 October 2007 }}</ref><ref>IIHS.org [http://www.iihs.org/ratings/tsp_archive.html TOP SAFETY PICK past winners] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070520111723/http://www.iihs.org/ratings/tsp_archive.html |date=20 May 2007 }}</ref> EuroNCAP crash test results from the B6 apply to the B7 model. \n{{clear}}\n\n=={{anchor|B8}}B8 (''Typ'' 8K; 2008\u20132016)==\n{{Infobox automobile\n|name = Fourth generation (B8/8K)\n|image = 2009 Audi A4 (8K MY10) 2.0 TDI sedan (2015-07-09) 01.jpg\n|production = October 2007\u20132015\n|model_years = 2008\u20132016\n|assembly = {{Unbulleted list |Germany: [[Ingolstadt]] |Germany: [[Neckarsulm]] |India: [[Aurangabad, Maharashtra|Aurangabad]] ([[Audi India]]; CKD)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.automobilesreview.com/auto-news/audi-starts-production-audi-a4-india/5106/|title=Audi A4 CKD assembled in India too}}</ref> |China: [[Changchun]] ([[FAW-VW]]) |Indonesia: [[Purwakarta]] ([[Garuda Mataram Motor|Garuda Mataram]])}}\n|designer = Julian H\u00f6enig (exterior: 2004, 2005)<ref>http://www.julianhoenig.com/art/about_files/portfolio.pdf</ref><br>Ingo Von Bargen (interior: 2005)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.carbodydesign.com/archive/2007/11/07-audi-a4-design/|title=Audi A4: the design|work=carbodydesign.com}}</ref>\n|body_style = 4-door [[sedan (automobile)|saloon/sedan]],<br/>5-door Avant ([[station wagon|estate/wagon]])\n|platform = [[Volkswagen Group B platform#B8|Volkswagen Group MLB platform]]\n|related = [[Audi A5]]<br/>[[Audi S4#B8|Audi S4 (B8)]]<br/>[[Audi RS4#B8|Audi RS4 (B8)]]\n|engine = {{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Inline-four petrol engine\n|1 = 1.8L [[turbocharger|T]][[gasoline direct injection|FSI]] [[inline-four engine|I4]]\n|2 = 2.0L T[[gasoline direct injection|FSI]] I4\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V6 petrol engine\n|1 = [[List of Volkswagen Group petrol engines#3.0 V6 24v TFSI 213-245kW|3.0L]] [[V6 engine|V6]] [[Supercharger|T]][[Fuel Stratified Injection|FSI]]\n|2 = 3.2L [[V6 engine|V6]] [[gasoline direct injection|FSI]]\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V8 petrol engine\n|1 = 4.2L [[V8 engine|V8]] FSI\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Inline-four diesel engine\n|1 = 2.0L [[Turbocharged Direct Injection|TDI]] I4\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V6 diesel engine\n|1 = 2.7L V6 [[Turbocharged Direct Injection|TDI]]\n|2 = 3.0L V6 [[Turbocharged Direct Injection|TDI]]\n}}\n|transmission = {{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Manual Transmission\n|1 = 6-speed [[manual transmission|Manual]]\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Automatic Transmission\n|1 = 6-speed [[automatic transmission|Tiptronic]]\n|2 = 8-speed [[automatic transmission|automatic]]\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Dual-clutch Transmission\n|1 = 7-speed [[Direct-Shift Gearbox|S tronic]]\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Continuously Variable Transmission\n|1 = 8-speed [[continuously variable transmission|Multitronic]]\n}}\n|wheelbase = {{convert|2808|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br/>allroad: {{convert|2805|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br/>LWB: {{convert|2869|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n|length = {{convert|4703|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br/>allroad: {{convert|4721|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br/>LWB: {{convert|4763|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n|width = {{convert|1826|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br/>allroad: {{convert|1841|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n|height = {{convert|1427|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br/>Avant: {{convert|1436|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br/>allroad: {{convert|1495|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br/>LWB: {{convert|1426|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n|weight =\n|sp = uk\n|predecessor =\n|successor =\n}}\n{{Multiple image | align = left | direction = vertical | width =\n| image1 = Audi A4 allroad quattro Phantomschwarz.JPG\n| image2 = Audi A4 allroad 2.0 TFSI quattro S tronic Gletscherwei\u00df Heck.JPG\n| caption2 = allroad quattro (pre-facelift)\n}}\n\n[[File:2012 Audi A4 B8 interior.jpg|thumbnail|left|Interior]]\nAudi released the first official pictures of the [[Volkswagen Group B platform#B8|B8]] series A4 in August 2007, and unveiled the car to the public at the September 2007 [[Frankfurt Motor Show]]. [[sedan (automobile)|Saloon/sedan]] and Avant ([[station wagon|estate/wagon]]) models are offered. The Avant was unveiled to the public at the March 2008 [[Geneva Motor Show]]. For North America destined models, the B8 continued in production for the 2016 model year, while Europe began deliveries on the 2016 B9 model.\n\nThe B8 A4 is built on a variant of the [[Volkswagen Group MLB platform|Audi Modular Longitudinal Platform]], a platform which is also used in the [[Audi A5]] [[coup\u00e9]]. While prior A4 chassis were limited in [[wheelbase]] due to the relationship between the engine, transmission and front axle, the MLP allows for a reduced front overhang, resulting in a greater wheelbase length without the same increase in overall length.<ref>{{Citation | last =Monticello | first =Mike | title =2009 Audi A4 3.2 Quattro | journal =[[Road & Track]] | volume =60 | issue =2 | page =104 | date =October 2008 | url = | doi = | id = }}</ref> This effectively redistributes the centre of gravity slightly rearwards, improving handling by better balancing vehicle mass between the front and rear axles. The estimated static front:rear weight ratio of the B8 A4 is approximately 55:45, depending on body style and engine. The relocation of the steering rack in front of the axle also improves handling over previous A4 platforms.{{Citation needed|date=March 2009}} Key to the implementation of MLB is the novel mounting of the [[Differential (mechanical device)|differential]] in front of the clutch. This is achieved by driving the flywheel/clutch remotely by means of a 'top hat' shaped drive plate, between which the differential lay shaft passes, whilst power transmission to the final drive is via an inclined transfer shaft which runs the length of the transmission unit. Whilst the platform retains Audi's \"overhung\" engine mounting position, the front axle is now 152mm further forward than the previous B6/B7 generation platform.<ref>{{cite book|title=Audi A5 \u2013 Self Study Programme|date=January 2007|publisher=Audi AG|page=30|url=http://training.avme.net/admin/Upload/SSP/4801_392%20Audi%20A5%20generell.pdf|accessdate=5 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105113255/http://training.avme.net/admin/Upload/SSP/4801_392%20Audi%20A5%20generell.pdf|archive-date=5 January 2015|url-status = dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The transfer shaft, however, has the effect of creating a large \"bulge\" on one side of the transmission tunnel, which on right-hand drive versions forces the pedals to be badly offset, which has attracted criticism from the British motoring press in particular.\n\nThe B8 A4 has increased in wheelbase by {{convert|160|mm|in|1}} and in length by {{convert|117|mm|in|1}} over the prior B7, which has allowed for increased rear seating legroom. Although the overall dimensions have increased, the kerb weight has dropped some 10%. The boot (trunk) has also increased to {{convert|480|L|cuft|1}} for the saloon (sedan) version. The A4 Avant will have a maximum capacity of {{convert|1430|L|cuft|1|abbr=on}} with the rear seats folded down.\n\nReception has been mixed, with praise for the Audi A4's increased size, giving it best-in-class rear legroom and trunk space in the compact executive car segment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iol.co.za/motoring/latest-launches/audi-a4-replacement-hot-and-cool-1.852835|title=Audi A4 replacement: Hot and cool|last=Rutherford|first=Mike|date=6 November 2007|work=iol.co.za|accessdate=11 May 2011}}</ref> Its inline-4 2.0 TFSI engine, while efficient providing plenty of torque, was considered lacking and less refined compared to 6-cylinder engines of lighter rivals who posted faster acceleration times. However, the [[Audi S4]] [[sports sedan]] has been well-received for its V6 3.0 TFSI engine's power and efficiency.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/12/27/automobiles/27ulrich-best.html?pagewanted=2&_r=1&sq=Ford%20Taurus%20disappointing&st=cse&scp=1 | work=The New York Times | title=A Holiday From Wishful Thinking | first=Lawrence | last=Ulrich | date=27 December 2009 | accessdate=2 May 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/02/08/automobiles/autoreviews/08audi-a4.html?_r=1&pagewanted=2 | work=The New York Times | first=Lawrence | last=Ulrich | title=A Class Act Matures in Size and Price | date=8 February 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newcartestdrive.com/review-intro.cfm?Vehicle=2009_Audi_A4&ReviewID=4525 |title=2009 Audi A4 Review, Prices, Photos |publisher=New Car Test Drive |accessdate=11 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe B8 A4 was facelifted in early 2012.\n\nDuring a model cycle changes are made to integrate new technologies and to keep the model competitive. These changes are referenced based on the model year (MY) of the car.\nIn Australia, the B8 has undergone 2 revisions leading to three variants, the B8, B8 MY10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ozaudi.com/forums/showthread.php/19978-MY10-changes-for-Australian-Audi-range |title=MY10 changes for Australian Audi range |publisher=Ozaudi.com |date= |accessdate=2011-05-16}}</ref> and B8 MY11.\n\n===Body types===\n{{Multiple image | align = left | direction = vertical | width = 200\n| image1 = Audi A4 B8 2.0 TDI 20090906 rear.JPG\n| caption1 = Sedan (pre-facelift)\n| image2 = 2009-2010 Audi A4 (8K) 2.7 TDI Avant (2011-01-12).jpg\n| caption2 = Avant (pre-facelift)\n| image3 = Audi A4L B8 02 China 2012-04-14.jpg\n| caption3 = A4L (pre-facelift)\n}}\n\n====Saloon / Sedan ====\nAudi released the first official pictures of the [[Volkswagen Group B platform#B8|B8]] series A4 in August 2007, and unveiled the car to the public at the September 2007 [[Frankfurt Motor Show]]. [[sedan (automobile)|Saloon/sedan]] and Avant ([[station wagon|estate/wagon]]) models are offered.\n\n====Avant====\nThe Avant station wagon / estate was presented at the March 2008 [[Geneva Motor Show]].\n\n====A4L====\nThe A4L is a long-wheelbase version for the Chinese market, with a {{convert|60|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} longer wheelbase and length.<ref>PaulTan.org [http://paultan.org/archives/2008/11/17/new-extended-audi-a4l-for-the-china-market/ New extended Audi A4L for the China market]</ref> The vehicle was presented at the 2008 Guangzhou Motor Show. The production version then went on sale in January 2009. Launch models included a 2.0 TFSI with 132&nbsp;kW (180&nbsp;hp) and the 3.2 FSI with 195&nbsp;kW (265&nbsp;hp).<ref>{{cite web|last=Filipponio |first=Frank |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2008/11/17/audi-intros-long-wheelbase-a4-for-china/ |title=Audi intros long-wheelbase A4L for China |publisher=Autoblog.com |date=17 November 2008 |accessdate=2010-10-20}}</ref>\n\n====A4 allroad quattro====\nThe '''A4 allroad quattro''' features a wider track, increased ground clearance, quattro permanent [[four-wheel drive]], a distinctive radiator grille, stainless steel underbody guards and roof rails.\n\nThe A4 allroad quattro was made available in early summer 2009.<ref name=\"allroad-pr\">{{cite web|url=http://www.audi.com/com/brand/en/company/news/models_and_services.detail.2009~02~the_audi_a4_allroad.html |title=The Audi A4 allroad quattro: A Vehicle that knows no Boundaries |date=15 February 2009 |work=www.audi.com |publisher=Audi AG |accessdate=2009-02-23 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090221142116/http://www.audi.com/com/brand/en/company/news/models_and_services.detail.2009~02~the_audi_a4_allroad.html |archivedate=21 February 2009 |url-status = live}}</ref>\nThe car was unveiled in 2009 [[Geneva Motor Show]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Paukert |first=Chris |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2009/03/04/geneva-2009-new-audi-a4-allroad-debuts-reportedly-may-come-to/ |title=Geneva 2009: New Audi A4 Allroad debuts, reportedly may come to U.S. after all |publisher=Autoblog.com |date=3 April 2009 |accessdate=2010-10-20}}</ref>\n\n===Specifications===\n\n====Body styles====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Body !!Sedan !!Avant !!A4L!!allroad quattro\n|-\n|Year ||2011\u2013||2010\u2013||2009||\n|-\n|Luggage capacity||{{convert|480|L|cuft|1}} with the rear seats in the upright position, and {{convert|962|L|cuft|1|abbr=on}} with the seats folded||{{convert|490|L|cuft|1|abbr=on}} with the rear seats upright, and {{convert|1430|L|cuft|1|abbr=on}} with the seats folded||?||\n|-\n|Curb weight||{{convert|1410|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} to {{convert|1690|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}||{{convert|1470|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} to {{convert|1695|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}||?||\n|}\n\nThe A4-based convertible models were replaced by the [[Audi A5|A5/S5]] Cabriolet.\n\n====Powertrain====\nThe B8 powertrain options are the following: engines, transmissions and drivelines:<ref>Audi.co.uk [http://www.audi.co.uk/etc/medialib/cms4imp/audi2/uk/Products/a4/pdf.Par.0045.File.pdf The new Audi A4, A4 allroad and S4 range, Pricing and Specification Guide, Valid from April 2009, Edition 6.1. 04/09] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120225053823/http://www.audi.co.uk/etc/medialib/cms4imp/audi2/uk/Products/a4/pdf.Par.0045.File.pdf |date=25 February 2012 }}</ref> <small>(All United Kingdom specification unless stated otherwise).</small><ref>Audi South Africa [http://www.audi.co.za/specs/?rid=a4 A4 specifications] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090713205119/http://www.audi.co.za/specs/?rid=a4 |date=13 July 2009 }}</ref><small>(for South Africa specification).</small><ref