2013\n|{{convert|1968|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on}} 16v I4 turbo\n|{{convert|120|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} @4200\n|{{convert|290|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} @1750\u20132500\n|-\n|2.0 TDI e||CAGB||2009\u2013\n|{{convert|1968|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on}} 16v I4 turbo\n|{{convert|136|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} @4200\n|{{convert|320|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} @1750\u20132500\n|-\n|2.0 TDI e||CA||2012\u2013\n|{{convert|1968|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on}} 16v I4 turbo\n|{{convert|163|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} @4200\n|{{convert|380|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} @1750\u20132500\n|-\n|2.0 TDI, 2.0 TDI quattro||CAGA||2007\u2013\n|{{convert|1968|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on}} 16v I4 variable geometry turbo\n|{{convert|143|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} @4200\n|{{convert|320|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} @1750\u20132500\n|-\n|2.0 TDI, 2.0 TDI quattro||CAHA||2008\u2013\n|{{convert|1968|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on}} 16v I4 variable geometry turbo\n|{{convert|170|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} @4200\n|{{convert|350|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} @1750\u20132500\n|-\n|2.7 TDI||CAMA/CGKA||2007\u2013\n|{{convert|2698|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on}} 24v V6 turbo\n|{{convert|190|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} @3500\u20134400\n|{{convert|400|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} @1400\u20133250\n|-\n|3.0 TDI quattro||CAPA/CCWA||2007\u2013\n|{{convert|2967|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on}} 24v V6 turbo\n|{{convert|240|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} @4000\u20134400\n|{{convert|500|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} @1500\u20133000\n|}\n\nThe [[quattro (four wheel drive system)|quattro]] permanent [[four-wheel drive]] system uses the latest [[Torsen]] T-3 centre [[differential (mechanical device)|differential]], with a default 40:60 front to rear asymmetric torque distribution ratio (used first on the [[Audi RS4#B7|B7 RS4]]) as standard. (Previous A4 quattro models split torque with a default front:rear 50:50). The additional torque bias applied to the rear wheels helps mimic the driving dynamics of rear wheel drive cars.\n\nAudi was reported to stop offering 3.2L V6 models in 2010 model year,<ref>{{cite web|last=Lavrinc |first=Damon |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2009/04/22/audi-dropping-3-2-liter-v6-from-2010-a3-a4-and-tt/ |title=Audi dropping 3.2-liter V6 from 2010 A3, A4 and TT |publisher=Autoblog.com |date=22 April 2009 |accessdate=2010-10-20}}</ref> but still offers them as of August 2011 (Germany).\n\nAll [[petrol engine]]s use [[gasoline direct injection|Fuel Stratified Injection]] (FSI), and all [[diesel engine]]s use the [[common rail]] fuel delivery (with a pressure of {{convert|1600|bar|psi}}), with [[piezoelectricity|piezo]] [[fuel injection|injectors]] of their [[Turbocharged Direct Injection]] engines.\n\nWith the 2012 facelift (the B8.5) came additional 163ps TDIe and TDI Ultra engines, the latter requiring the addition of [[adblue]] allowing for cleaner running, both of which fell into the lower emissions tax bracket for the UK, yet presenting a significant performance improvement over the base 136ps and mid-range 143ps models.<ref>https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-review/audi/a4/first-drives/audi-a4-20-tdie</ref>\n\n====Transmissions====\nIn 2009, Audi announced the seven-speed [[dual clutch transmission|dual-clutch]] [[Direct-Shift Gearbox|S tronic]] transmission as option for A4 in UK and European markets.<ref>AutoBlog.com [http://www.autoblog.com/2009/02/06/audi-a4-and-a5-get-s-tronic-gearbox-abroad-u-s-still-waiting/ Audi A4 and A5 get S tronic gearbox abroad, U.S. still waiting]</ref>\n\nAll A4L models include Speed 8 [[multitronic]] [[Continuously variable transmission|continuously variable]]/[[manual transmission]], except for A4L 3.2 FSI quattro, which includes Tiptronic [[automatic transmission]].\n\nVolkswagen settled a class-action lawsuit in 2013 involving the failures of the CVT transmission in its Audi A4 and A6 automobiles for model years 2002\u20132006<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenationaltriallawyers.org/2013/10/audi-cvt-suit-settlement-given-green-light/|title=Audi CVT Suit Settlement Given Green Light|work=The National Trial Lawyers}}</ref>\n\n====Performance====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 90%\"\n|-\n! Vehicle model, transmission !! Acceleration 0-{{convert|100|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}} (s)<br><small>(saloon)</small> !! top speed <small>(saloon)</small> !! [[emission standard|CO<sub>2</sub> emissions]] (g/km) <small>(saloon)<br>(Directive<br>80/1268/EEC)</small> !! notes\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 2.0 TFSI, 6-speed [[manual transmission|Manual]]\n| 6.9\n| {{convert|250|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}<br><small>(elec. limited)</small>\n| 149\n| \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 1.8 TFSI, 6-speed [[manual transmission|Manual]]\n| 8.6\n| {{convert|225|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}\n| 164\n| \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 1.8 TFSI, 8-speed [[Multitronic]] [[continuously variable transmission|CVT]]\n| 8.6\n| {{convert|250|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}\n| 169\n| \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 2.0 TFSI, 8-speed [[Multitronic]] [[continuously variable transmission|CVT]]\n| 8.2\n| {{convert|236|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}\n| 167\n| Aus/NZ/ZA<br>only\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 2.0 TFSI, 8-speed [[Multitronic]] [[continuously variable transmission|CVT]]\n| 6.9\n| {{convert|241|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}\n| 167\n| \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 2.0 TFSI [[quattro (four wheel drive system)|quattro]],<br>6-speed [[manual transmission|Manual]]\n| 6.6\n| {{convert|246|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}\n| 169\n| \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 2.0 TFSI [[quattro (four wheel drive system)|quattro]],<br>7-speed [[Direct-Shift Gearbox|S tronic]]\n| 6.5\n| {{convert|241|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}\n| 172\n| \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 3.2 FSI, [[Multitronic]] [[continuously variable transmission|CVT]]\n| 6.5\n| {{convert|250|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}<br><small>(elec. limited)</small>\n| 194\n| \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 3.2 FSI quattro, 6-speed [[manual transmission|Manual]]\n| 6.0\n| {{convert|250|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}} <small>(elec. limited)</small>\n| 213\n| \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 3.2 FSI quattro, 6-speed [[automatic transmission|Tiptronic]]\n| 6.1\n| {{convert|250|km/h|mph