luetooth audio streaming - applicable to 2012 facelift onwards, B8.5 models)\n*Electronic hand brake\n*Speed sensitive [[power steering]] ('[[servotronic]]' \u2013 on some models)\n\nOptions:\n*Audi Lane Assist ([[lane departure warning system]]);\n*Audi Side Assist ([[blind spot monitor]]);\n*[[autonomous cruise control system|Adaptive Cruise Control]] (ACC);\n*[[Advanced Key]] (keyless entry and start);\n*[[Bang & Olufsen]] sound system (505W);\n*Advanced parking system front and rear with [[backup camera|reversing camera]];\n*Navigation system with full MMI with {{convert|7|in|mm|adj=on}} screen;\n*[[Adaptive headlamp|Adaptive headlights]] (with cornering technology);\n*Audi Drive Select;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.automoblog.net/2009/03/26/2009-audi-a4-review/|title=2009 Audi A4 3.2 quattro sedan Review|publisher=Automoblog.net}}</ref>\n\n===Safety===\n\n====Euro NCAP====\nThe Audi A4 (B8) [[Euro NCAP]] crash tests ratings (pre-2009 testing):<ref name=\"EuroNCAP.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.EuroNCAP.com/tests/Audi_A4_2008/320.aspx|title=Audi A4|accessdate=2008-05-29|work=EuroNCAP.com| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080531020807/http://www.euroncap.com/tests/Audi_A4_2008/320.aspx| archivedate= 31 May 2008 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n* Adult occupant = {{rating|5|5}}\n* Child occupant = {{rating|4|5}}\n* Pedestrian = {{rating|2|4}}\n\nEuro NCAP (2009 testing):<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euroncap.com/results/audi/a4/2009/350.aspx|title=Audi A4|work=euroncap.com}}</ref>\n* Overall = {{rating|5|5}}\n* Adult occupant = 93%\n* Child occupant = 84%\n* Pedestrian = 39%\n\n====Insurance Institute for Highway Safety (IIHS)====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+IIHS scores:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iihs.org/ratings/ratingsbyseries.aspx?id=558 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-10-28 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011091113/http://www.iihs.org/ratings/ratingsbyseries.aspx?id=558 |archivedate=11 October 2007 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n|Moderate overlap frontal offset\n|Good\n|-\n|Small overlap frontal offset\n|Good (2017 models)\n|-\n|Side impact\n|Good\n|-\n|Roof strength\n|Good\n|}\nHead and seat restraints\nGood\n\n====NHTSA====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+[[National Highway Traffic Safety Administration|NHTSA]] 2012 A4 saloon FWD:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.safercar.gov/Vehicle+Shoppers/5-Star+Safety+Ratings/2011-Newer+Vehicles/Vehicle-Detail?vehicleId=6350|title=2012 Audi A4 4 DR FWD|work=safercar.gov}}</ref>\n|-\n|Overall:\n|{{rating|4|5}}\n|-\n|Frontal Driver:\n|{{rating|3|5}}\n|-\n|Frontal Passenger:\n|{{rating|4|5}}\n|-\n|Side Driver:\n|{{rating|4|5}}\n|-\n|Side Passenger:\n|{{rating|5|5}}\n|-\n|Side Pole Driver:\n|{{rating|5|5}}\n|-\n|Rollover:\n|{{rating|5|5}}\n|}\n\n===A4 TDI concept e (2008)===\nIt includes a [[common rail]] {{convert|1968|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on}} TDI diesel engine rated at {{convert|120|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|290|Nm|lbft|abbr=on}}, a [[start-stop system|stop-start system]] and [[regenerative brake|regenerative braking]]. It can achieve a fuel consumption of 3.99L/100&nbsp;km (58.95 mpg<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.automobilemag.com/auto_shows/2008_paris/0810_audi_a4_tdi_concept_e/index.html |title=AutomobileMag.com |publisher=AutomobileMag.com |date= |accessdate=2010-10-20}}</ref>) and CO<sub>2</sub> output of 105 g/km. It can accelerate 0-{{convert|100|km/h|mph|abbr=on}} in 10.7 seconds, with top speed of {{convert|206|km/h|mph|abbr=on}}.\n\nOther features include [[electric motor]]-based power steering, revised [[aerodynamics]], low-rolling resistance 225/45R17 tyres, and electric actuation of the rear brakes.\n\nThe car was unveiled in [[Paris Motor Show]].<ref>AutoBlogGreen.com [http://www.autobloggreen.com/2008/10/02/audi-unveils-a4-tdi-concept-e/ Audi unveils A4 TDI concept e]</ref>\n\n===Facelift (2012\u20132015)===\n{{Multiple image | align = left | direction = vertical | width =\n| image1 = Audi A4 Avant 2.0 TDI Ambiente (B8, Facelift) \u2013 Frontansicht, 17. Mai 2012, Velbert.jpg \n| image2 = Audi A4 Avant 2.0 TDI (B8, Facelift) \u2013 Heckansicht, 25. Februar 2012, Ratingen.jpg\n| caption2 = Avant (facelift)\n| image3 = Audi A4 2.0 TDI Ambition (B8, Facelift) \u2013 Heckansicht, 30. Juli 2012, Ratingen.jpg\n| caption3 = Sedan (facelift)\n}}\n{{Multiple image | align = right | direction = vertical | width =\n| image1 = Audi A4 B8 Facelift allroad quattro 2.0 TFSI S tronic Phantomschwarz.JPG\n| image2 = Audi A4 B8 Facelift allroad quattro 2.0 TFSI S tronic Phantomschwarz Heck.JPG\n| caption2 = Allroad quattro (facelift)\n}}\n\nThe facelift model Audi A4 came in 2011. It features redesigned LED headlamps and tail lights, front air dam with fog lamps, and closely set twin exhausts. Interior changes include bluetooth connectivity for audio streaming (nav equipped models only) and a redesigned ignition key. Controls for air-conditioning, infotainment, and power windows gain chrome clasps. Other detail interior changes include larger steering column stalk switches first seen in the D4-series [[Audi A8]] and a simplified layout for the HVAC control panel \u2013 for example the temperature setting for the heated seats is now directly set by a single button and is no longer controlled using the MMI dial. The A4 includes radio with eight speakers as standard, while MMI navigation system with voice dialogue is optional. A new \"Drive Select System\" allows drivers to choose comfort, dynamic, individual, or efficiency modes for fuel efficiency. Power output of the 1.8 TFSI engine is 170 BHP and 320 Nm of torque \u2013 up 10 BHP and 70 Nm from the previous versions. Electro-mechanical power steering is standard.\n\nIn Europe, the wide range of Audi A4 saloon and Avant estate are available with the 1.8 TFSI, 2.0 TFSI gasoline engine, as well as 2.0 TDI, 2.0 TDIe, and 3.0 TDI diesel motor. Trim levels are Attraction, Ambition, and Ambiente. In the UK, the A4 range is offered in SE, SE Technik, Technik, S line, and Black Edition model grades. All wheel drive quattro are offered in most engine and grade combinations.\n\nFor North America, the facelift model Audi A4 sedan is only offered with 2.0 TFSI gasoline engine. Model grades are Premium, Premium Plus, and Prestige. The Avant was discontinued, leaving the Allroad quattro as the only station wagon body style. For the 2016 model year, the A4 and S4 continued in B8 production. The B9 A4 would not reach the North American market until the 2017 model year, while the S4 variant would not be available until the 2018 model year.\n\n{{clear}}\n\n=={{anchor|B9}}B9 (''Typ'' 8W; 2016\u2013present)==\n{{Infobox automobile\n|name = Fifth generation (B9/8W)\n|image = 2017 Audi A4 (8W) sport quattro sedan (2018-10-19) 01.jpg\n|production = 2015\u2013present<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.audi-mediacenter.com/en/4328 |title=High tech all the way \u2013 the new Audi A4 and A4 Avant |publisher=Audi AG |website=www.audi-mediacenter.com |date=4 September 2015 }}</ref>\n|model_years = 2016\u2013present\n|assembly = \n|designer = Frank Rimili<br/>R\u00fcdiger M\u00fcller (interior)\n|body_style = 4-door [[sedan (automobile)|saloon/sedan]],<br/>5-door Avant ([[station wagon|estate/wagon]])\n|platform = [[Volkswagen Group MLB platform#MLBevo|Volkswagen Group MLBevo platform]]\n|engine = {{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Inline-four petrol engine\n|1 = 1.4L [[Turbocharger|T]][[gasoline direct injection|FSI]] [[inline-four engine|I4]]\n|2 = 2.0L T[[gasoline direct injection|FSI]] I4\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V6 petrol engine\n|1 = 3.0L V6 [[Turbocharger|T]][[gasoline direct injection|FSI]]\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Inline-four diesel engine\n|1 = 2.0L [[Turbocharged Direct Injection|TDI]] I4\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V6 diesel engine\n|1 = 3.0L V6 [[Turbocharged Direct Injection|TDI]]\n}}\n|transmission = 6-speed [[manual transmission|manual]]<br> 7-speed [[Direct-Shift Gearbox|S-tronic]]<br/> 8-speed Tiptronic\n|wheelbase = {{convert|2820|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n|length = {{convert|4726|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n|width = {{convert|1842|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n|height = {{convert|1427|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n|weight =\n|related=[[Audi A5#Second generation (2016\u2013present)|Audi A5]]<br>[[Audi Q7#4M|Audi Q7]]\n|predecessor =\n|successor =\n}}\n\nThe next-generation B9 version of the A4 was revealed in June 2015 \u2013 the fifth model to carry the A4 badge, and the ninth generation of the Audi 80/A4 series overall. Pre-production versions were released to the motoring press, whilst the official launch occurred at the [[Frankfurt Motor Show#2015|Frankfurt Motor Show]] in September 2015. The B9 is slightly larger than the outgoing B8, but Audi claims the new A4 is around {{convert|120|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} lighter than its predecessor.<ref name=\"autocar.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/new-cars/2015-audi-a4-revealed|title=2015 Audi A4 - latest pictures and details - Autocar|author=|date=|website=www.autocar.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n<gallery widths=\"200px\">\n2017 Audi A4 (8W) sport quattro sedan (2018-10-19) 02.jpg|Sedan / Saloon\nAudi A4L B9 003 China 2017-03-22.jpg|A4L\n2018 Audi A4 Avant S Line TDi S-A 2.0 Rear.jpg|Avant\nAudi A4 Avant B9 IMG 1973.jpg|Avant (facelift)\n2018 Audi A4 Allroad Quattro Front.jpg|Allroad quattro\n2018 Audi A4 Allroad Quattro Rear.jpg|Allroad quattro\n2015 Audi A4 B9 2.0 TFSI quattro 185 kW S line Interieur Innenraum Cockpit.jpg|Interior\nAudi A4 Allroad Quattro B9 at IAA 2019 IMG 0285.jpg|Allroad quattro (facelift)\nAudi A4 Allroad Quattro B9 at IAA 2019 IMG 0297.jpg|Allroad quattro (facelift)\n</gallery>\n\n===Engines===\n\nSeven engines are available from launch, three petrols and four diesels.<ref name=\"autocar.co.uk\"/> All are available in both the A4 Saloon and A4 Avant. The figures below are for the saloon only.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"