ef>{{cite web|url=http://www.audiworld.com/news/06/032706/content.shtml |title=Three Generations of Audi A4 DTM Cars |publisher=Audiworld.com |date=27 March 2006 |accessdate=1 June 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Australian Super Touring Championship===\n[[Brad Jones (racing driver)|Brad Jones]] won the [[Australian Super Touring Championship]] in both [[1996 Australian Super Touring Championship|1996]] and [[1998 Australian Super Touring Championship|1998]] driving an A4.\n\n===BTCC===\n[[File:Audi Quattro A4 - Flickr - exfordy.jpg|thumb|[[Frank Biela]] won the 1996 British Touring Car Championship driving an A4]]\nThe A4 was used in the 1996\u20131998 and 2011-2015 [[British Touring Car Championship]] seasons.\n[[File:Rob Austin racing, 2012 BTCC Audi A4.jpg|thumb|[[Rob Austin]]'s 2012 BTCC Audi A4]]\n\n===ETCC===\nThe A4 was used in the 2000\u2013[[2001 European Super Touring Championship season]].\n\n===Italian touring cars===\nA4 drivers won the [[Italian Superturismo Championship]] in 1995 and 1996.\n\n===STCC===\nDrivers in an A4 won the 2001, 2002, 2003 and [[2006 Swedish Touring Car Championship season]].\n\n===STW===\nThe A4 was entered into the [[1995 Super Tourenwagen Cup season]].\n\n===RTCC===\nThe car was used in the 2006 [[Russian Touring Car Championship]].\n\n===SCCA===\nThe A4 was used in the [[SCCA World Challenge]] for several years.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Volkswagen Group China]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Audi A4}}\n* [http://www.audi.com/en/models/a4.html Audi A4] at Audi International website\n\n{{Audi}}\n{{Audi vehicles timeline (Europe)}}\n{{Audi vehicles timeline (North America)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n\n[[Category:Audi vehicles|A4]]\n[[Category:Compact executive cars]]\n[[Category:Euro NCAP large family cars]]\n[[Category:Sedans]]\n[[Category:Station wagons]]\n[[Category:Convertibles]]\n[[Category:Vehicles with CVT transmission]]\n[[Category:All-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Front-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 1994]]\n[[Category:1990s cars]]\n[[Category:2000s cars]]\n[[Category:2010s cars]]\n[[Category:Hybrid electric cars]]\n[[Category:Touring cars]]\n", "name_user": "TKOIII", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eB9 (Typ 8W; 2016\u2013present):cats", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Audi_A4"}
{"title_page": "Luiz Fernando Carvalho", "text_new": "{{infobox person\n| name = Luiz Fernando Carvalho\n| image    =\n| imagesize =\n| birth_name = Luiz Fernando Carvalho de Almeida\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1960|7|28|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality =\n| alias =\n| yearsactive = 1985\u2013present\n| occupation       = Film director, screenwriter, novelist\n| known_for        = [[Film]]s and [[Television program|TV series]] based on [[List of Brazilian writers|Brazilian writers]]\n| notable_works   =  ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'', ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|Os Maias]]'', ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Dois Irm\u00e3os]]''\n| children = \n}}\n\n'''Luiz Fernando Carvalho''' (born July 28, 1960 in [[Rio de Janeiro]]) is a [[Brazil]]ian filmmaker and television director, known for works closely linked to literature that constitute a renovation in Brazilian audiovisual aesthetics.<ref>Carter, Eli Lee [http://escholarship.org/uc/item/589368qf#page-3 \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho: An Auteur of Brazilian Television\"], ''UCLA Electronic Theses and Dissertations'', 2013. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref> He has already brought to the screen works by [[Ariano Suassuna]], [[Raduan Nassar]], [[Machado de Assis]], [[E\u00e7a de Queir\u00f3s]], [[Roland Barthes]], [[Clarice Lispector]], [[Milton Hatoum]], [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]] and [[Graciliano Ramos]], among others.\n\nSome critics compare Luiz Fernando Carvalho's productions to the Brazilian Cinema Novo<ref name=\"Sukman\">{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=lavoura+arcaica&anyword=&noword=&exactword=Mario+Peixoto&decadaSelecionada=&anoSelecionado=&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title=Um cineasta que est\u00e1 entrando para o clube dos poetas|author=Hugo Sukman|publisher=OGlobo|date=28 October 2001|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Com Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho respeita uma tradi\u00e7\u00e3o que vai de Mario Peixoto a Ruy Guerra}}</ref> and icons of film history such as [[Luchino Visconti]] and [[Andrei Tarkovski]].<ref name=\"Piza\">{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,lavoura-arcaica-estreia-sabado-no-canada,20010822p2443|title=\"Lavoura Arcaica\" estr\u00e9ia s\u00e1bado no Canad\u00e1|author=Daniel Piza|date=22 August 2001|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Um parentesco com o estilo e a espiritualidade do cinema dos russos Tarkovski e Sokurov}}</ref> His work is characterized by visual and linguistic experimentation<ref name=\"Ismail\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrissima/2016/10/1822788-quinze-anos-depois-filme-lavoura-arcaica-ainda-e-corpo-estranho.shtml|title=Quinze anos depois, filme \"Lavoura Arcaica\" ainda \u00e9 corpo estranho|author=Ilana Feldman e Ismail Xavier|date=16 October 2016|publisher=Ilustr\u00edssima/Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> and exploration of the multiplicity of Brazil's cultural identity.<ref>[http://www.lanacion.com.ar/395562-luiz-fernando-carvalho-talento-made-in-brasil \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho, talento made in Brasil\"], ''La N\u00e1cion'', 11 May 2002. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref><ref name=\"MariaRita\">{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/maria-rita-kehl-velho-chico-reinaugura-um-desejo-de-utopia-20210647|title='Velho Chico' reinaugura um desejo de utopia|author=Maria Rita Kehl|date=1 October 2016|publisher=OGlobo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=O Brasil de Benedito Ruy Barbosa e Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u00e9 agreste. \u00c9 pobre, remediado, devastado e esperan\u00e7oso}}</ref> The baroque style<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diplomatique.org.br/uma-novela-shakespeareana-neorrealista-e-barroca/|title='Uma Novela Shakespearana, neorrealista e barroca|author=Helcio Kovaleski|date=15 March 2016|publisher=Le Monde Diplomatique Brasil|access-date=13 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Coelho\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1411200117.htm|title='Lavoura' e os ind\u00edcios de uma obra prima|author=Marcelo Coelho|date=14 November 2001|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Lavoura Arcaica\" tem todas as raz\u00f5es para ser excessivo, barroco, quase ostentat\u00f3rio em sua riqueza estil\u00edstica. O filme consegue traduzir visualmente toda a beleza liter\u00e1ria do livro de Raduan Nassar}}</ref><ref name=\"Ilana\">{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/dois-irm%C3%A3os-arqueologia-da-mem%C3%B3ria-alegoria-da-destrui%C3%A7%C3%A3o-45b5723b88cd|title=Dois Irm\u00e3os: arqueologia da mem\u00f3ria, alegoria da destrui\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Ilana Feldman|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Na obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, o barroco \u00e9 um conceito norteador de uma pesquisa de linguagem: busca conceitual pela brasilidade presente nos opostos, nas contradi\u00e7\u00f5es e nos contrastes deste pa\u00eds}}</ref> of overlays and interlacing of narrative genres, the relation to the moment in Time,<ref name=\"Mata\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/critica/ult569u395.shtml|title=Em \"Lavoura Arcaica\", Carvalho faz retrato do tempo|author=Tiago Mata Machado|date=23 October 2001|publisher=FolhaOnline|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> the archetypal symbols of the Earth and the reflection on the language of social and family melodrama<ref name=\"Inacio\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1511200125.htm|title=Longa \u00e9 exce\u00e7\u00e3o exemplar no cinema do pa\u00eds|author=In\u00e1cio Ara\u00fajo|date=15 November 2001|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> are features of the director's poetic language.\n\nThe filmmaker's works have met with both critical and public acclaim. He directed the film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'' (2001)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://journals.openedition.org/cinelatino/2104|title=Du go\u00fbt du public selon Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Sylvie Debs|date=1 June 2008|publisher=Cin\u00e9mas d\u2019Am\u00e9rique latine|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/archives/article/2003/07/09/a-la-gauche-du-pere-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho_327204_1819218.html|title=\"A la gauche du p\u00e8re\", de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Florence Colombani|date=9 Julho 2003|publisher=Le Monde|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>, based on the homonymous novel by [[Raduan Nassar]], cited by the critic [[:fr:Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9]] in the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]] as a \"ground-breaking promise of renovation, of an upheaval not seen in Brazilian cinema since [[Glauber Rocha]],<ref name=\"Cahiers\">Tess\u00e9, Jean-Philippe [http://www.cineressources.net/articles_periodiques/resultat_f/index.php?pk=85803&param=F&textfield=a+la+gauche+du+pere&rech_type=F&rech_mode=exact&pageF=1&pageP=1&type=FOR&pk_recherche=85803 \" Les pieds dans la terre\"], ''Cahiers du Cin\u00e8ma'', July\u2013August 2003. Retrieved on 19 April 2017.</ref><ref>Tess\u00e9, Jean-Philippe [http://www.chronicart.com/cinema/a-la-gauche-du-pere/ \"On peut ais\u00e9ment voir dans cette grande fresque charnelle la plus belle d\u00e9couverte du cin\u00e9ma br\u00e9silien depuis Glauber Rocha, au moins parce que Luiz Fernando Carvalho partage avec le r\u00e9alisateur de Antonio das mortes un go\u00fbt pour la puissance du lyrisme\"], ''Chronicart'', 6 July 2003. Retrieved on 19 April 2017.</ref> which won over 50 national and international awards.<ref name=\"Montreal\">{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,montreal-premia-a-ousadia-de-lavoura-arcaica,20010905p2499 |title=Montreal premia a ousadia de \"Lavoura Arcaica\"|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=5 September 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The telenovelas ''[[Renascer|Renascer (Rebirth)]]'' (1993) and ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'' (1996), by screenwriter [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, are recognized as benchmarks of Brazilian television drama and achieved some of the highest audience ratings of the 1990s.<ref>Hopewell, John [https://variety.com/2016/tv/global/rodrigo-santoro-globo-velho-chico-1201725234/ \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho (\u2018The King of the Cattle\u2019) returns with a rural romantic saga packing political overtones\"], ''Variety'', 8 March 2016. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv-pesquisa.com.puc-rio.br/mostraregistro.asp?CodRegistro=23342&PageNo=25|title=Renascer deu aula de dire\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|date=6 November 1993|publisher=Jornal do Brasil|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nThere is a marked contrast between the director's television works: from the pop design of the 60s in the series ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Ladie's Mail (Correio Feminino)]]'' (2013) to the classic rigor of the mini-series ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|The Maias (Os Maias)]]'' (2001), the urban references of the working-class suburbs in the mini-series ''[[:pt:Suburbia|Suburbia]]'' (2012) to the playfulness of the soap ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' (2014), the aesthetic research of the Sert\u00e3o (backcountry) in ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' (2016) to the Brazilian fairytale of the mini-series ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]'' (2005) and the realistic universe of family tragedy in ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' (2017).<ref>Carter, Eli Lee [http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S1983-68212014000100004&script=sci_arttext&tlng=pt \"Rereading Dom Casmurro - aesthetic hybridity in Capitu\"], ''University of Virginia'', 2014. Retrieved on 18 April 2017.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1080/13569325.2014.958660| title=Afinal, o que Querem as Mulheres?: Luiz Fernando Carvalho's Metafictional Critique of Brazilian Television Fiction| journal=Journal of Latin American Cultural Studies| volume=23| issue=4| pages=363\u2013379| year=2014| last1=Carter| first1=Eli Lee}}</ref>\n\nThe director's production process is renowned for identifying new talent from all over Brazil and for training actors,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,freud-explica,635078|title=Freu Explica|author=Patricia Vilalba|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=11 November 2010|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Freud explica: \"O processo de ensaios para filmar com Luiz Fernando \u00e9 um dos diferenciais do diretor, que o p\u00f4s em posi\u00e7\u00e3o de sonho de consumo de qualquer ator comprometido com seu of\u00edcio\"}}</ref> revealing new stars of the dramatic arts such as [[Leticia Sabatella]], [[Eliane Giardini]], [[Bruna Linzmeyer]], Johnny Massaro, [[Irandhir Santos]], [[Simone Spoladore]], [[Caco Ciocler]], [[Marcello Antony]], Marco Ricca, [[Isabel Fillardis]], [[Giselle Iti\u00e9]], Emilio Orciollo Netto, Sheron Menezes, Jackson Antunes, [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]], [[Eduardo Moscovis]], Jackson Costa, [[Leonardo Vieira]], Cac\u00e1 Carvalho, Luciana Braga, Julia Dalavia, Renato G\u00f3es, Cyria Coentro, Marina Nery, J\u00falio Machado, B\u00e1rbara Reis, Lee Taylor, Zezita de Matos, Mariene de Castro and Lucy Alves, among others. The director's actor coaching technique has given rise to a method recounted in the book ''O processo de cria\u00e7\u00e3o dos atores de Dois Irm\u00e3os'' (''The creation process of the actors in Dois Irm\u00e3os''), by the photographer Leandro Pagliaro.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/entretenimento/tv/noticia/2017/01/dois-irmaos-livro-registra-cenas-da-preparacao-do-elenco-da-minisserie-9303834.html/|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\": livro registra cenas da prepara\u00e7\u00e3o do elenco da miniss\u00e9rie|author=Roger Lerina|date=12 January 2017|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/literatura,fotografo-registra-o-intenso-processo-de-ensaio-da-serie-dois-irmaos,10000098867|title=Fot\u00f3grafo registra o intenso processo de ensaio da s\u00e9rie 'Dois Irm\u00e3os'|author=Ubiratan Brasil|date=9 January 2017|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box|width=40%|align=right|quote=\"There is a concrete promise of renovation, of a palpitation not seen in Brazilian cinema since [[Glauber Rocha]]. (...) At first, one is left with nothing but fragments torn from a visual magma. But soon the chaos resolves itself, the film unrolls in all its richness like a barbaric poem verging on hallucination, of extraordinary power. (...) Never, however, does its return to the underlying myths obscure or accelerate the predominance of the sensations. If the film is possessed of such enchanting force, it is because Luiz Fernando Carvalho knows that everything starts there, in this first way of being born into the world, of allowing oneself to be ravished by it, to savor every twist of it...\"|source=\u2014Les Cahiers du Cin\u00e8ma, by [[:fr:Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9]] on his critic about ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''<ref name=\"Cahiers\"/>}}\n\n== Early Career: 1980s ==\nLuiz Fernando Carvalho studied architecture and literature. He started out in cinema at 18 in a number of roles: audio technician, assistant director, screenwriter, short film editor and director. His first TV work came in the early 80s, as assistant director of noteworthy mini-series, such as ''[[O Tempo e o Vento]]'', based on the work of [[\u00c9rico Ver\u00edssimo]], directed by [[Paulo Jos\u00e9]], and ''[[:pt:Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas|Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]'', from the work of [[Guimar\u00e3es Rosa|Jo\u00e3o Guimar\u00e3es Rosa]], in which he started to direct his first scenes, still as assistant director to Walter Avancini.\n\n=== ''The Waiting (A Espera)'' ===\nHe wrote and directed the short ''The Waiting (A Espera)'', based on the book ''[[A Lover's Discourse: Fragments]]'' (''Fragments d'un discours amoureux'') by [[Roland Barthes]]. Launched in 1986, the film collected the following awards: Best Short Film, Best Actress ([[Marieta Severo]]) and Best Cinematography ([[Walter Carvalho]]) at the 13th [[Festival de Gramado]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivaldegramado.net/vencedores?vencedores=30|title=Lista de vencedores do Festival de Gramado de 1986|publisher=FestivaldeGramado.net|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104050/http://www.festivaldegramado.net/vencedores?vencedores=30|archive-date=15 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Best Short Film ([[Golden Shell]]) at the [[San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival]] (Spain); and the Special Jury Award at the Ste Ther\u00e8se Festival (Canada).\n\n== 1990s ==\n=== ''Sweet River (Riacho Doce)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Riacho Doce (miniss\u00e9rie)}}\nEarly in the 90s, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed a 40-chapter mini-series written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]], based on the work of [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]] and starring [[Vera Fischer (actress)|Vera Fischer]], Osmar Prado, Sebasti\u00e3o Vasconcelos, [[Carlos Alberto Riccelli]] and [[Fernanda Montenegro]], with costumes by Beth Filipecki. The then inhospitable island of Fernando de Noronha (PE) served as the scene for the story, which is set in a small fishing village in the Northeast of Brazil.\n\n=== ''The Cangaceiro's Revenge (Os Homens Querem Paz)'' ===\nIn 1991, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed an adaptation of a script by Brazilian TV pioneer P\u00e9ricles Leal, with costumes by Beth Filipecki. The telefilm was shot in the town of Canind\u00e9, Cear\u00e1, and reached the finals of the 34th [[New York Television Festival]]. This marked the television debut of actress [[Leticia Sabatella]]. The critic Rodrigo Fonseca affirmed that his first memory of Let\u00edcia Sabatella on TV was also when he discovered the existence of the \"genius of direction that is Luiz Fernando\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mulheresdocinemabrasileiro.com.br/site/entrevistas_depoimentos/visualiza/164/Rodrigo-Fonseca-Leticia-Sabatella|title=Let\u00edcia Sabatella, por Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=Mulheres do Cinema Brasileiro|access-date=14 April 2017|quote=Foi quando eu tomei contato com a exist\u00eancia desse g\u00eanio da dire\u00e7\u00e3o que \u00e9 o Luiz Fernando}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Stone on Stone (Pedra Sobre Pedra)'' ===\n{{Main|Pedra Sobre Pedra}}\nIn 1992, he directed the telenovela written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]], considered to have reached the 6th largest audience in Brazilian television history.<ref name=\"Audiencia\">{{cite web|url=http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0,,EMI63532-9531,00.html |title=Aguinaldo Silva divulga lista das novelas com maior audi\u00eancia da hist\u00f3ria |date=10 March 2009 |publisher=Revista Quem |access-date=14 April 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304045233/http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0%2C%2CEMI63532-9531%2C00.html |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>  Notable cast members included: [[Lima Duarte]], [[Renata Sorrah]], Armando B\u00f3gus, [[Eva Wilma]], [[Paulo Betti]], [[Andr\u00e9a Beltr\u00e3o]], Pedro Paulo Rangel and [[Eduardo Moscovis]]. Certain characters are regarded as landmarks in TV drama: Sergio Cabeleira (Osmar Prado) and the photographer Jorge Tadeu ([[F\u00e1bio Jr.]]).\n\n=== ''The Tale of Our Lady of Light (O Auto de Nossa Senhora da Luz)'' ===\nWhile filming [[Pedra sobre Pedra]], Luiz Fernando Carvalho came up with a significant sequence inspired by [[Ariano Suassuna]]'s  Armorial Movement (Movimento Armorial) . The enormous success of the sequence, confirmed by the record number of requests by viewers for a rerun, was decisive in transformation of the material into a telefilm, with additional scenes written by Braulio Tavares and interpreted by the actor and musician [[Antonio N\u00f3brega]]. It competed for the [[International Emmy Award]] in 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/especiais/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz-curiosidades.htm|title=Curiosidades do Auto de Nossa Senhora da Luz|publisher=Mem\u00f3ria Globo|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104038/http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/especiais/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz-curiosidades.htm|archive-date=15 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Rebirth (Renascer)'' ===\n{{Main|Renascer}}\nThe 1993 soap, written by [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, met with critical and public acclaim and was the most watched in the 90s and 4th in audience ratings in the history of Brazilian television.<ref name=\"Audiencia\"/> It was also shown in several other countries. As directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, it is regarded as among the symbols of renovation of the aesthetics of the genre in the 90s.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KkJNHsGCYFkC&pg=PA219&lpg=PA219 |last=Jacob de Souza |first=Maria Carmen |title=Telenovela e representa\u00e7\u00e3o social: Benedito Ruy Barbosa e a representa\u00e7\u00e3o do popular na novela Renascer|publisher=E-papers|year=2004 |page=219 |isbn=978-85-87922-90-8|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, um dos mais expressivos representantes contempor\u00e2neos dessa tend\u00eancia autoral da dire\u00e7\u00e3o de telenovela, fez de Renascer seu sucesso mais exemplar}}</ref> The character Buba, interpreted by [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]], caused a national controversy, as it was the first time that the discussion of gender had been addressed in a telenovela. It received the APCA Award for Best Novela, Best Actor ([[Antonio Fagundes]]), Best Supporting Actor (Osmar Prado), Best Supporting Actress (Regina Dourado), Best Male Breakthrough Performance (Jackson Antunes).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/6/02/ilustrada/21.html/|title=\"Renascer\" domina premia\u00e7\u00e3o de cr\u00edticos|author=Ana Beatriz Brisola|date=2 June 1994|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> [[Leonardo Vieira]], Jackson Antunes, Cac\u00e1 Carvalho, Marco Ricca, [[Isabel Fillardis]] and [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]] were among the talents revealed in this work. The television entrepreneur [[:pt:Boni|Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio de Oliveira]], considered the plot \"well structured by Benedito, with a well-crafted first part, masterfully directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho\".<ref>{{cite book |last=Oliveira |first=Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio |date=2011 |title=O Livro do Boni |language=pt |location=S\u00e3o Paulo |publisher=Casa da Palavra |isbn=978-85-7734-226-6}}</ref> According to Marilia Martins, few novelas had a first chapter directed with such polish and skill as ''Rebirth''.\n\n=== ''A Woman Clothed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Uma mulher vestida de sol}}\nIn 1994, the telefilm directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho marked the first appearance of [[Ariano Suassuna]]'s works on television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/3/09/ilustrada/2.html|title=Ariano Suassuna prepara estr\u00e9ia na TV|author=Marcelo Migliaccio|date=9 March 1994|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=10 April 2017}}</ref> Based on the writer's unpublished novel of the same name, the script was the work of Ariano himself, in partnership with the director. Director of photography Dib Lufti, costumes by Luciana Buarque and art production by Lia Renha. Scenography by the artist Fernando Velloso, from the [[Grupo Corpo]] dance group, music by Ant\u00f4nio Madureira, a member of the Armorial Quintet (Quinteto Armorial). With ''A Woman dressed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'', the director commenced his exploration of the limits of television language, combining elements of the popular theater of the Northeast. Luiz Carlos Vasconcelos's Grupo Piolim participated and the cast included Tereza Seiblitz, Lineu Dias, Sebasti\u00e3o Vasconcelos, Ana L\u00facia Torre, [[Raul Cortez]] and the then novice actor Floriano Peixoto. According to the researcher of Literature H\u00e9lio Guimar\u00e3es, the work gave rise to an impasse at the TV station: was Lu\u00edz Fernando Carvalho too big for the Globo screen?<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/7/14/ilustrada/9.html|title=\"Mulher Vestida de Sol\" desafia o padr\u00e3o de realismo da Globo|author=H\u00e9lio Guimar\u00e3es|date=14 July 1994|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)}}\nOne year after ''A Woman dressed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'', in 1995, Luiz Fernando Carvalho resumed his connection with the writer [[Ariano Suassuna]], this time transforming the play ''[[:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)|The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)]]'' into a telefilm . The director continued his search for a hybrid language for television, as a way of criticizing the naturalism of the novelas. Art production and costumes by Yurika Yamasaki and the artist Dantas Suassuna, participation of [[Antonio N\u00f3brega]], [[Patr\u00edcia Fran\u00e7a]], [[Ary Fontoura]] and [[Marieta Severo]]. According to the critic Rog\u00e9rio Durst, the telefilm was a major feat of TV drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=artigo&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=A+Farsa+da+Boa+Pregui%C3%A7a&anyword=&noword=&exactword=sofisticada&decadaSelecionada=1990&anoSelecionado=&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title= Uma sofisticada op\u00e7\u00e3o popular|author=Rog\u00e9rio Durst|publisher=O Globo|date= 7 December 1995|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)'' ===\n{{Main Article|O Rei do Gado}}\n''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'', 1996, the director's next collaboration with the author [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/novela-de-forte-cunho-social-rei-do-gado-de-benedito-ruy-barbosa-volta-ao-ar-nesta-segunda-15009118|title= Novela de forte cunho social, 'O rei do gado', de Benedito Ruy Barbosa, volta ao ar nesta segunda|author=Nat\u00e1lia Borde |publisher=Revista da TV/OGlobo|date=12 January 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> became the novela with the 9th largest audience in Brazilian television history.<ref name=\"Audiencia\"/> It was rescreened three times,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2015/02/19/diretor-explica-por-que-terceira-reprise-de-rei-do-gado-faz-tanto-sucesso/|title=Diretor explica por que terceira reprise de \"Rei do Gado\" faz tanto sucesso|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=19 February 2015|publisher=UOL|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2015/02/1582950-reprise-de-o-rei-do-gado-chega-a-bater-novelas-ineditas-em-audiencia.shtml|title=Reprise de 'O Rei do Gado' chega a bater novelas in\u00e9ditas em audi\u00eancia|author=Fernanda Reis|date=1 February 2015|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> outrating other productions of the time, and was sold to over 30 countries. It marked the debut of [[Marcello Antony]], [[Caco Ciocler]], [[Mariana Lima]], Emilio Orciollo Netto and [[Lav\u00ednia Vlasak]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1996/10/20/revista_da_folha/3.html|title= Vidas com rumo|publisher=Revista da Folha|date=20 October 1996|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>  Other significant aspects of the novela were its social criticism and sensitive approach to the Landless Workers Movement (movimento dos sem-terra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/direto-da-fonte/a-televisao-brasileira-tem-dado-claros-sinais-de-esgotamento-de-seu-modelo/|title=A televis\u00e3o brasileira tem dado claros sinais de esgotamento de seu modelo|author=Thais Arbex|date=16 December 2013|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote= Rei do Gado foi a primeira novela a abordar o conflito dos sem-terra e a reforma agr\u00e1ria}}</ref> The actors Jackson Antunes and [[Ana Beatriz Nogueira]] stand out in this context. The cast included [[Antonio Fagundes]], [[Patricia Pillar]], [[Leticia Spiller]] and [[Raul Cortez]] with guest appearances in the early stages by [[Tarcisio Meira]], [[Eva Wilma]] and [[Vera Fischer (actress)|Vera Fischer]]. The character Ti\u00e3o Galinha, interpreted by Osmar Prado, is a landmark of his career. The novela received the Certificate of Merit at the [[San Francisco International Film Festival]] and the APCA Award for Best Actor ([[Raul Cortez]]), Best Supporting Actor (Leonardo Br\u00edcio), Best Supporting Actress (Walderez de Barros) and Best Male Breakthrough Performance ([[Caco Ciocler]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/novelas/o-rei-do-gado/premios.htm|title=Pr\u00eamios de'O Rei do Gado'|publisher=Mem\u00f3ria Globo|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328091627/http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/novelas/o-rei-do-gado/premios.htm|archive-date=28 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Fernando de Barros e Silva wrote, in the Folha de S.Paulo, \"The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado) swallows up Brazilian cinema\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.folha.uol.com.br/resultados/?q=O+Rei+do+Gado+engole+o+cinema+nacional+&site=&periodo=acervo&x=14&y=13|title=O Rei do Gado engole o cinema nacional |author=Fernando de Barros e Silva|date=7 July 1996|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to critic Rogerio Durst, the novela is \"a dramatic epic with first class special appearances and superb photography\".\n\nTiao Galinha belongs to another soap opera: \u201cRenascer\u201d.\n\n=== ''Giovanna and Henrico (Giovanna e Henrico)'' ===\nThe quality of the first seven chapters of ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'', showing the decline of the coffee cycle and Brazil's participation in World War II, prompted The Globo Network's International Division to transform the first part of the novela into the mini-series ''Giovanna and Henrico'', with [[Let\u00edcia Spiller]] and Leonardo Br\u00edcio playing the lead couple. The production was selected as hors-concours at the [[Banff World Media Festival]], in Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq150522.htm|title='O Rei do Gado' ganha pr\u00eamios em festivais|author=Cristina Padiglione|date=15 May 1997|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos)'' ===\n{{Main Article|:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos}}\nBefore the end of the 90s, Luiz Fernando Carvalho had already started on research for the feature film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''. Together with the author of the novel, [[Raduan Nassar]], he traveled to the Lebanon to familiarize himself with Mediterranean culture. The material collected during the trip was used to produce the documentary ''[[:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos|May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos)]]'', screened on GNT in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1997/12/14/tv_folha/16.html |title='Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos' estr\u00e9ia no GNT|author=Mariana Scalzo|date=14 December 1997 |access-date=29 March 2017}}</ref> In the opinion of critic Rodrigo Fonseca, the documentary \"honed to the limit of tragic fatality its investigation of time\".\n\n== 2000s ==\n=== ''To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)'' ===\n{{Main Article|To the Left of the Father}}\nIn 2001, the director made his first feature film, ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'', in which he was responsible for directing, screenplay and editing, with cinematography by Walter Carvalho, art direction by Yurika Yamazaki and costume design by Beth Filipecki.<ref name=\"Sukman\"/><ref name=\"Piza\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.almirdefreitas.com.br/almir/Lavoura_Arcaica___Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho.html|title=Com Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho vence o desafio de levar a literatura de Raduan Nassar para o cinema|author=Almir de Freitas|publisher=Revista Bravo!|access-date=17 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170418082444/http://www.almirdefreitas.com.br/almir/Lavoura_Arcaica___Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho.html|archive-date=18 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The cast included [[Selton Mello]], [[Raul Cortez]], [[Simone Spoladore]], [[Leonardo Medeiros]], [[Caio Blat]] and [[Juliana Carneiro da Cunha]]. Aiming to maintain the connection with the poetic prose of [[Raduan Nassar]]'s book, the director elected to film without a defined script, based entirely on the actors' improvisations on the theme.<ref name=\"Mata\"/><ref name=\"Coelho\"/><ref name=\"Inacio\"/> This involved intensive coaching of the cast, secluded on a farm for four months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1408200518.htm|title=Mergulho em Raduan Nassar conduz a pequena obra-prima|author=Jos\u00e9 Geraldo Couto|date=14 August 2005|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> The film's creation and production process was discussed in the book ''About To the Left of The Father'' (\"Sobre Lavoura Arcaica\"), in which the director is interviewed by Jos\u00e9 Carlos Avellar, Geraldo Sarno, Miguel Pereira, Ivana Bentes, Arnaldo Carrilho and Liliane Heynemann, launched in Portuguese, English and French by the publisher [[:pt:Ateli\u00ea Editorial|Ateli\u00ea Editorial]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.atelie.com.br/publicacoes/autor/luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title= Sobre Lavour'Arcaica \u2013 O filme|author=Luiz Fernando Carvalho |publisher=Atelier Cultural |year=2002|isbn=978-85-7480-140-7|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> It was success with the critics<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=pagina&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=Lavoura+Arcaica&anyword=&noword=&exactword=colheita&decadaSelecionada=2000&anoSelecionado=2001&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title=Uma colheita espl\u00eandida|author=Luciano Trigo|publisher=RioShow|date=28 October 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.folha.uol.com.br/resultados/?q=Filme+radicaliza+linguagem&site=&periodo=acervo&x=22&y=15|title=Filme radicaliza linguagem|author=Jos\u00e9 Geraldo Couto|publisher=Ilustrada/Folha de S.Paulo|date=24 September 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20011125-39485-spo-151-cd2-d3-not/busca/Lavoura+Arcaica|title=Convuls\u00f5es|author=Daniel Piza|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=25 November 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.lanacion.com.ar/395562-luiz-fernando-carvalho-talento-made-in-brasil|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, talento made in Brasil|author=Diego Batle|publisher=La Nacion|language=spanish|date=11 May 2002|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> and the public, reaching 300 thousand viewers with just two copies, one in Rio de Janeiro and the other in S\u00e3o Paulo. It is considered one of the [[Abraccine Top 100 Brazilian films|100 best Brazilian films of all times]], according to the Brazilian Film Critics Association (Abraccine).<ref>{{cite web |url= https://abraccine.org/2015/11/27/abraccine-organiza-ranking-dos-100-melhores-filmes-brasileiros/ |title= Abraccine organiza ranking dos 100 melhores filmes brasileiros |access-date= 26 October 2016 |author= Andr\u00e9 Dib |date= 27 November 2015 |publisher= abraccine.org}}</ref> It had a successful career in a number of national and international festivals, receiving over 50 awards at the [[Montreal World Film Festival]],<ref name=\"Montreal\"/><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.ffm-montreal.org/en/awards/16-awards-of-the-montreal-world-film-festival-2001.html/|title = 16 Awards of the Montreal World Film Festival 2001|website=FFMMontreal.org|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=n.d.|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Rio Film Festival]], the [[S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival]], the [[Grande Pr\u00eamio do Cinema Brasileiro|Grand Prix for Brazilian Film]], the [[Bras\u00edlia Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq2911200111.htm|title = Bras\u00edlia celebra \"Lavoura\" e \"Samba\"|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=29 November 2001|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Havana Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1512200135.htm|title = \"Lavoura\" ganha pr\u00eamios em Havana|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=15 December 2001|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Cartagena Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1103200214.htm|title = \"Lavoura Arcaica\" ganha Festival de Cartagena|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=11 March 2002|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Guadalajara International Film Festival]], the [[Buenos Aires International Festival of Independent Cinema]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pagina12.com.ar/diario/espectaculos/6-4799-2002-05-06.html|title=Una met\u00e1fora sobre los que no tienen lugar en la mesa social|author=Ana Bianco|language=spanish|publisher=P\u00e1gina 12|date=1 May 2002|access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> among others. In the opinion of writer and psychoanalyst Renato Tardivo, author of ''Porvir que vem antes de tudo \u2013 literatura e cinema em Lavoura Arcaica'', the film is one of the most important works of Brazilian cinema \u201cof all times\u201d.<ref>{{cite book |last=Tardivo |first=Renato Cury  |title=Porvir que vem antes de tudo: uma leitura de lavoura arcaica - literatura, cinema e a unidade dos sentidos |publisher=Universidade de S\u00e3o Paulo (USP)|date=2009 |url= http://www.teses.usp.br/teses/disponiveis/47/47134/tde-11122009-110032/pt-br.php}}</ref> The critic Carlos Alberto de Mattos described it as the first work of art of the Brazilian cinema in the 21st century.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carmattos.com/2016/10/13/festival-do-rio-lavoura-arcaica/|title=Festival do Rio: Lavoura Arcaica|author=Carlos Alberto de Mattos|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|date=25 November 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The film was acclaimed by the critics of various countries and, according to the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]], ''To the Left of the Father'' is a \"barbarous poem verging on hallucination, of extraordinary power\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.chronicart.com/cinema/a-la-gauche-du-pere/|title=Critique:A La Gauche du P\u00e8re|author=Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|language=French|publisher=Chronicart|date=6 July 2003|access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"allocine.fr\">{{cite web| url=http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=46949.html|title=Critiques:A La Gauche du P\u00e8re|publisher=AlloCin\u00e9|language=French|access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"allocine.fr\"/><ref>{{cite web| url=http://next.liberation.fr/cinema/2003/07/09/pere-de-tous-les-vices_439245|title=P\u00e9re de touts les vices. Relecture saisissante d'un monstre de la litt\u00e9rature br\u00e9silienne|author=Didier Peron|language=French|date=9 July 2003|publisher=Liber\u00e1cion|access-date=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The Maias (Os Maias)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)}}\nA 2001 production, this mini-series based on the homonymous novel by [[E\u00e7a de Queir\u00f3s]] and adapted by Maria Adelaide Amaral was another landmark in the director's career.<ref>Elena Corr\u00eaa, \"Linguagem po\u00e9tica que remete a outra \u00e9poca. Roteiro fiel e dire\u00e7\u00e3o inconfund\u00edvel\", em \"O Globo\" (11 de janeiro de 2001)</ref> The Maias portrays the decadent Portuguese aristocracy in the second half of the 19th century, through the tragic story of a traditional Lisbon family. Costumes by Beth Filipecki and direction of photography by Jos\u00e9 Tadeu Ribeiro. In the opinion of writer [[Luis Fernando Ver\u00edssimo]], \"the extraordinarily mobile camera of Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u201cvisited\u201d, more than portrayed, the frivolous Lisbon of the time and all the novel's atmospheres. But beneath it all, there was this majestic progression, from the first scene to the denouement, the moving camera conducting us like a slow tragic theme tune that recalls a symphony. No TV camera has ever been so complicit and seductive, never has TV been so romantic\".<ref>{{cite book |last=Wajnman |first=Solange  |title=Miniss\u00e9ries hist\u00f3ricas e a comunica\u00e7\u00e3o por objetos. Notas sobre os figurinos e cen\u00e1rios de 'Primo Bas\u00edlio' e \"Os Maias\"  |publisher=Universidade de Santa Maria (UFSM)|date=2011|url= https://periodicos.ufsm.br/animus/article/viewFile/4125/2624}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observatoriodaimprensa.com.br/artigos/qtv31012001991.htm|title=Os Maias|author=Luis Fernando Ver\u00edssimo|date=26 January 2001|publisher=Observat\u00f3riodaImprensa.com.br|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Para Os Maias, Carvalho escolheu um andamento que, na m\u00fasica, seria chamado de \u2018andante majestoso\u2019, que pode impacientar a gera\u00e7\u00e3o videoclipe, mas est\u00e1 perfeito, e era o ritmo preferido de Lean e Visconti.}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria)'' ===\n{{Main|Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria}}\nOver two seasons, ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]'' (2005), a mini-series in which he was also responsible for creation and script, consolidated the director's linguistic research.<ref>\"Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria - segunda jornada \u00e9 uma joia lapidada com meticulosidade por um artista barroco, que n\u00e3o tem medo de abra\u00e7ar o excesso de refer\u00eancias universais e regionais para recriar a realidade brasileira com rigor e paix\u00e3o\", in \"Correio Braziliense\" (15 October 2005)</ref>  His co-writers were Luis Alberto de Abreu and Carlos Alberto Soffredini, basing themselves on a selection of stories taken from popular Brazilian oral storytelling tradition,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq0901200511.htm|title=Carvalho invoca a cultura popular em micross\u00e9rie|author=Valmir Santos|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|date=9 January 2005|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\"\"Diretor associa \"Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria\" a uma busca pela identidade brasileira\"}}</ref> collected by the writers [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]], [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]] and [[Silvio Romero]]. Art direction by Lia Renha, guest artist Raimundo Rodriguez, direction of photography by Jos\u00e9 Tadeu Ribeiro and costumes by Luciana Buarque. The 60 marionettes that represented the animals were produced by the Grupo Giramundo, from Minas Gerais state. The work marked the start of the partnership between the director and psychoanalyst Carlos Byington, as advisor on the mythological dramatization of the text. The mini-series was conceived under a 360\u00ba dome, scrap from a rock show stage. The sound track, by Tim Rescala, was based on cirandas (traditional dances) by [[Heitor Villa-Lobos]], [[C\u00e9sar Guerra-Peixe]] and [[Francisco Mignone]]. Designer Jum Nakao was responsible for some of the costumes, with animation of the stop-motion scenes by Cesar Coelho, founder of the [[Anima Mundi (event)|Anima Mundi festival]]. It received the 2005 APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Critics' Choice Award, the ABC Best Photography Award, the Contigo Award for Best Director and Best Child Actress and the Brazil Quality Award (Pr\u00eamio Qualidade Brasil ) for Best Director, Television \u2013 Best Special Project, Best Author and Best Breakthrough Actress, and reached the finals of the 2005 [[International Emmy Award]], in the categories Best Mini-Series and Best Actress.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u54506.shtml|title=Atriz mirim de \"Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria\" \u00e9 indicada ao Emmy\"|publisher=Folha Online|date=21 October 2005|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> It was nominated Hors Concours by the [[Banff World Media Festival]], in Canada (2006), and the [[International Public Television Screening Conference|Input International Board Taipei]] (2005). Compared with ''To the Left of the Father'' on account of its innovative television language, it caught the attention of critics and public by its novel, theatrical and playful language in transporting the universe of popular culture to a sophisticated television production, without losing its authenticity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=pagina&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+maria&anyword=&noword=&exactword=&decadaSelecionada=2000&anoSelecionado=2005&mesSelecionado=10&revistaoglobo=on|title= Em Busca da nossa inf\u00e2ncia brasileira|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|publisher=Revista OGlobo|date=9 October 2005|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=As imagens de Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria s\u00e3o raras. Tudo escapa ao padr\u00e3o global: \u00e9 fic\u00e7\u00e3o que tem coragem de se revelar como fic\u00e7\u00e3o, \u00e9 uma TV que tem a ousadia de buscar nas origens do cinema a reinven\u00e7\u00e3o da linguagem}}</ref> The critic Nilson Xavier considers it one of the most poetic, original and beautiful productions of recent years.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.teledramaturgia.com.br/hoje-e-dia-de-maria/ |title=Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria|author=Nilson Xavier|publisher=Site Teledramaturgia |access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9, in the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]], the mini-series was very ambitious and formally very well produced, following other noteworthy projects such as ''The Maias (Os Maias)''.\n\n=== ''Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)'' ===\n{{Main Article|:pt:A Pedra do Reino}}\nIn 2007, the director's third production based on the works of [[Ariano Suassuna]] brought to the TV the ''Romance d'A Pedra do Reino e o Pr\u00edncipe do Sangue do Vai-e-Volta''. The mini-series is regarded as yet another aesthetic innovation by the director, as in ''To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)'' and ''Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria)''. The script was the work of Luiz Fernando Carvalho, in collaboration with Luis Alberto de Abreu and Braulio Tavares, direction of photography by Adrian Teijido, scenography by Jo\u00e3o Irenio Maia, editing by Marcio Hashimoto and costumes by Luciana Buarque. Colorist Sergio Pasqualino. Regional artists, coordinated by the artist Raimundo Rodriguez, assisted with the art production. Music by Ant\u00f4nio Madureira (Quinteto Armorial) and Marco Ant\u00f4nio Guimar\u00e3es ([[Uakti (band)|Uakti]]). The cast was the fruit of the director's extensive search for talent throughout the backcountry (sert\u00e3o) of the Northeast. Television debut of the actors [[Irandhir Santos]] and Mayana Neiva and the singer Renata Rosa, among many others. It was filmed in the town of Tapero\u00e1, where [[Ariano Suassuna]] spent his childhood. During the coaching process, the team and cast attended lectures, out in the sert\u00e3o, by the actress [[Fernanda Montenegro]], the psychoanalyst Carlos Byington and the writer himself. [[Ariano Suassuna]] affirmed that Luiz Fernando Carvalho's recreation of his ''Romance d\u2019A Pedra do Reino'' resulted in an \"extraordinarily beautiful work that moved him as author and individual, as a spectator\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.revistacinetica.com.br/pedradoreinoilana.htm|title=A Pedra do Reino:A opera mundi de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Ilana Felman|publisher=Revista Cin\u00e9tica|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://ricardocalil.ig.com.br/index.php/2007/06/06/triunfo-da-imaginao/comment-page-1|title=Triunfo da Imagina\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Ricardo Calil|publisher=iG |date=6 June 2007|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=A Pedra do Reino segue mesmo a l\u00f3gica dos sonhos, com del\u00edrios visuais de intenso brilho e elipses de tempo, com desorienta\u00e7\u00f5es espaciais e suspens\u00f5es de sentido}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/leia-critica-da-microsserie-pedra-do-reino-4182728|title=cr\u00edtica da micross\u00e9rie 'A Pedra do Reino|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=O Globo|date=16 June 2007|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=\u201cA Pedra do Reino\u201d eleva \u00e0 en\u00e9sima pot\u00eancia um questionamento autoral onipresente nas hist\u00f3rias de Carvalho desde que rodou \u201cOs homens querem paz\u201d, um especial, exibido em 1991}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/07/24/diretor-de-a-pedra-do-reino-adaptara-fernando-e-isaura-para-a-tv.amp.htm|title=Diretor de \"A Pedra do Reino\" adaptar\u00e1 \"Fernando e Isaura\" para a TV|author=Andr\u00e9ia Rocha|publisher=UOL|date=24 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2017/11/1934597-editora-lanca-dois-volumes-de-obra-postuma-de-ariano-suassuna.shtml|title=Nova Fronteira lan\u00e7a dois volumes de obra p\u00f3stuma de Ariano Suassuna|author=Claudio Leal |date=11 November 2017|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=\"Portando nomes reais ou acrescidos de sobrenomes ficcionais, amigos surgem em ep\u00edgrafes e s\u00e3o incorporados pelo escritor como personagens dos di\u00e1logos sobre a cultura brasileira e seu projeto liter\u00e1rio. As atrizes Inez Viana e Marieta Severo , os diretores Aderbal Freire Filho e Luiz Fernando Carvalho, os poetas Jos\u00e9 Laurenio de Melo e Ad\u00e9lia Prado se situam entre esses interlocutores de Dom Pantero na \"Autobiografia Musical, Dan\u00e7arina, Po\u00e9tica, Teatral e V\u00eddeo-CinematoGr\u00e1fica\"}}</ref>\n\n=== Quadrante Project (Projeto Quadrante) ===\nBased on ''[[:pt:A Pedra do Reino|Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)]]'' (2007), the director set up the Quadrante Project with the intention of making a series of regional drama programs to rediscover the Brazilian imaginary through adaptations of literary texts of authors from each Brazilian state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1712200617.htm|title=Sert\u00e3o \u00e9 \"semente\" de \"A Pedra do Reino\"|author=Esther Hamburguer|publisher=Revista Cult|date=17 December 2006|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> Similarly, local actors act out the texts. The richness of the project lay in the discovery of regional talent: authors, actors, composers, artists in general. The project recognized the human potential of each regional culture, looking beyond the simplistic image of a postcard. In addition to ''Stone of the Kingdom'', the Quadrante is made up of the mini-series [[Capitu]] (2008), based on the book ''[[Dom Casmurro]]'', by [[Machado de Assis]], and ''Dois Irm\u00e3os'' (2017), by [[Milton Hatoum]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2017/01/dois-irmaos-retoma-antigo-projeto-artistico-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-e-tem-primeiro-capitulo-deslumbrante|title=Dois Irm\u00e3os retoma antigo projeto art\u00edstico de Luiz Fernando Carvalho e tem primeiro cap\u00edtulo deslumbrante|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio da Televis\u00e3o|date=9 January 2017|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Capitu'' ===\n{{Main|Capitu}}\nIn 2008, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed and finalized the script for this adaptation of the book ''[[Dom Casmurro]]'', by [[Machado de Assis]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Carter |first=Eli Lee  |title=Rereading Dom Casmurro - aesthetic hybridity in Capitu  |publisher=University of Virginia|date=2014|url= http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S1983-68212014000100004&script=sci_arttext&tlng=pt}}</ref> The mini-series was written by Euclydes Marinho in collaboration with Daniel Piza, Luis Alberto de Abreu and Edna Palatnik. Art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez, photography by Adrian Teijido and costumes by Beth Filipecki. Colorist Sergio Pasqualino. It marked the TV debut of actors [[Let\u00edcia Persiles]] and Michel Melamed, among others. The mini-series was filmed in the abandoned Autom\u00f3vel Clube building, in downtown Rio de Janeiro, and the whole scenographic universe was created from newspaper and recycled material. The opening credits scene was conceived by the director and created by the designer Carlos B\u00eala.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/2475349/|title=Abertura de Capitu|author=Carlos B\u00eala|publisher=Vimeo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The production is part of the Quadrante Project and was the director's tribute to [[Machado de Assis]] on the centenary of his death. It received the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Critic's Choice Award (2009), ABC Best Photography Award  (from the Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Cinematografia) and the [[Creative Review]] award in the Best in Book and Design and Art Director categories. In the opinion of critic Gustavo Bernardo, the mini-series deserves \"to be viewed and reviewed countless times, at least because each fragment of a scene is precious for its beauty\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/prosa/post/a-capitu-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-145085.html|title=A Capitu de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Gustavo Bernardo|publisher=O Globo|date=9 December 2009|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to theatre director [[:pt:Gabriel Villela|Gabriel Villela]], Luiz Fernando Carvalho produces works of art on the screen, calls on the viewer's vivacity so that he accepts nothing masticated, but masticates along with Casmurro.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq0808200923.htm|title=\"Capitu\" traduz para TV modo de narrar de Machado de Assis|author=Gabriel Villela|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|date=8 August 2009|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> For Randall Johnson, director of the UCLA Latin American Institute, \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho is today, without doubt, the director whose work is the most authorial of all TV and cinema production in Brazil\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/curso-na-universidade-da-california-debate-obra-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-3144586|title=Curso na Universidade da Calif\u00f3rnia debate obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|publisher=Revista da TV/OGlobo|date=24 May 2009|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://renatofelix.wordpress.com/2009/08/27/entrevistas-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Entrevistas: Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Renato Felix|publisher=Blog do Renato Felix|date=27 August 2009|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Trata-se um ensaio sobre a d\u00favida. N\u00e3o absolvo Capitu e n\u00e3o a condeno}}</ref>\n\n== 2010s ==\n\n=== ''After all, what does a woman want (Afinal, O Que Querem as Mulheres?)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Afinal, o Que Querem as Mulheres?}}\nIn 2010, Luiz Fernando Carvalho created, directed and wrote the mini-series inspired by [[Sigmund Freud]]'s: famous question \"What does a woman want?\". [[Jo\u00e3o Paulo Cuenca]], Cecilia Giannetti and [[:pt:Michel Melamed|Michel Melamed]] collaborated on the script. As well as acting in the production, Melamed created the opening sound track. Direction of Photography Adrian Teijido, costumes by Beth Filipecki and art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez. The director launched actress [[Bruna Linzmeyer]]\u2019s career in this production. Osmar Prado shared the part of Freud with a model animated by Cesar Coelho, founder of the [[Anima Mundi (event)|Anima Mundi festival]], using the stop-motion technique.  The opening vignette features the work of German artist [[Olaf Hajek]], who also produced special illustrations for the mini-series by invitation of the director.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/17214632|title=Abertura da miniss\u00e9rie \"Afinal, o que querem as mulheres?\"|author=Alexandre Romano|publisher=V\u00edmeo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> It received the ABC award (Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Cinematografia) for Best Photography. According to columnist Patr\u00edcia Kogut, \"it is an oneiric journey, a visual poem that blends realities, full of references to times past, to what has been experienced, to what lingers in memory\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2010/11/critica-afinal-que-querem-as-mulheres-340331.html|title=Cr\u00edtica: Afinal, o que querem as mulheres?|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=13 November 2010|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Carter |first=Eli Lee  |title=Afinal, o que Querem as Mulheres?: Luiz Fernando Carvalho's Metafictional Critique of Brazilian Television Fiction |journal=Journal of Latin American Cultural Studies |volume=23 |issue=4 |pages=363\u2013379 |date=2014|doi=10.1080/13569325.2014.958660 }}</ref>\n\n=== ''Suburbia'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Suburbia}}\nIn 2012, Luiz Fernando Carvalho inaugurated in TV drama a production in which all the protagonists are of African descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://televisao.uol.com.br/critica/2012/11/01/seriado-olha-com-realismo-mas-carinho-para-a-dura-vida-no-suburbio.htm|title=Seriado olha com realismo, mas carinho para a dura vida no sub\u00farbio|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=1 November 2011|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/suburbia-uma-entrevista-com-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Suburbia: uma entrevista com Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Luiz Zanin|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=3 November 2012|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> The mini-series, created and written by the director in partnership with Paulo Lins, counted on the collaboration of Adrian Teijido (Photography), Luciana Buarque (Costumes), Marcio Hashimoto (Editing) and Sergio Pasqualino (Colorist). It also marked the start of another research cycle, in which the director focused on realist aesthetics, which influenced the language as a whole, but mainly in the choice of non-actors for the main parts. The nearly 40 actors launched in the mini-series include artists of the groups N\u00f3s do Morro and [[:pt:Afroreggae|Afroreggae]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2012/12/critica-naturalidade-e-ausencia-de-pose-o-mundo-de-suburbia.html|title=Naturalidade e aus\u00eancia de pose: o mundo de 'Suburbia'|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=3 December 2012|access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> \u00c9rika Januza, until then secretary of a school in the interior of Minas Gerais state, was chosen to play the main character of the story. Guest appearance by Fabr\u00edcio Boliveira, Rosa Marya Colin, Haroldo Costa, Maria Salvadora, Paulo Tiefenthaler and Dani Ornellas, among others. In 2012, the Globo network took the series up again for a second season in 2013 due to its satisfactory audience ratings. Later, however, the director Luiz Fernando Carvalho chose to cancel the new season. In the opinion of anthropologist Luiz Eduardo Soares, the work was a \"reconstructive reading of the carioca society, producing a superb result \".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/luiz-eduardo-soares-escreve-sobre-intensidade-da-forma-em-suburbia-6733970|title=Luiz Eduardo Soares escreve sobre a intensidade da forma em 'Suburbia'|author=Luiz Eduardo Soares|publisher=O Globo|date=15 November 2011|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Ladie\u2019s Mail (Correio Feminino)''===\n{{Main|:pt:Correio Feminino}}\nA mini-series in eight episodes, created and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho based on women's journals written by [[Clarice Lispector]] in the 1950s and 1960s, under the pseudonym Helen Palmer. The visual language and narrative were based on 60s pop art and design,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/quero-um-novo-ciclo-na-tv-diz-luiz-fernando-carvalho-10375021|title='Quero um novo ciclo na TV', diz Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=O Globo|date=16 October 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> from the costumes to the lighting and set; all filmed in a single light box, which changed color according to the subjects addressed. Adapted by Maria Camargo, the series was shown in 2013 as part of the program Fant\u00e1stico,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/luiz-fernando-carvalho-dirige-serie-correio-feminino-estreia-deste-domingo-do-fantastico-10543381|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho dirige s\u00e9rie Correio Feminino, estreia deste domingo do Fant\u00e1stico|author=Zean Bravo|publisher=O Globo|date=27 October 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> with costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie and Luciana Buarque, photography by Mikeas and edited by Marcio Hashimoto. The actress [[Maria Fernanda C\u00e2ndido]] played Helen Palmer narrating all the episodes. In the cast, [[Luiza Brunet]] interpreted the mature woman, and [[:pt:Alessandra Maestrini|Alessandra Maestrini]], the young woman. The adolescent is [[Cintia Dicker]], an international model whose acting career was launched in the mini-series. In the opinion of critic Patricia Kogut, the series is \"inspired, pleasant, in good taste and unpretentious, like Clarice's texts as Helen Palmer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2013/11/correio-feminino-faz-leitura-inspirada-de-clarice-lispector.html|title='Correio feminino' faz leitura inspirada de Clarice Lispector|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=5 November 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Alexandre and Other Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)}}\nA 2013 telefilm, with script by Luis Alberto de Abreu and Luiz Fernando Carvalho<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/prosa/post/a-consciencia-dos-sonhos-por-luiz-fernando-carvalho-518115.html|title=A consci\u00eancia dos sonhos - Diretor de 'Alexandre e outros her\u00f3is', especial de TV baseado nas hist\u00f3rias infantojuvenis de Graciliano Ramos, examina dimens\u00f5es m\u00edtica, ut\u00f3pica e humana na obra do alagoano|author=Luiz Fernando Carvalho|publisher=OGlobo|date=14 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> based on two stories by the Alagoan writer [[Graciliano Ramos]]. Luiz Fernando Carvalho's coaching and directing of the actors revealed a new code of interpretation to [[Marcelo Serrado]] and [[Ney Latorraca]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://atarde.uol.com.br/cultura/televisao/noticias/1555977-ney-latorraca-e-destaque-em-alexandre-e-outros-herois|title=Ney Latorraca \u00e9 destaque em 'Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is'|date=16 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=A Tarde|author=Roberta Pennafort}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/2013/12/1383371-ney-latorraca-renasce-em-especial-na-tv-alexandre-e-outros-herois.shtml|title=Ney Latorraca renasce em especial na TV 'Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is'|author=Gislaine Gutierre|publisher=Folha Online|date=10 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Ele (Luiz Fernando Carvalho) me tirou totalmente da zona de conforto}}</ref> as well as a harmony in the quality of the interpretations. Direction of photography by Mickeas, art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez and costumes by Luciana Buarque. Incidental sound track by Tim Rescala. Opening theme by the Pernambucan Siba. The cast of the TV special, a finalist in the 2014 [[International Emmy Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/finalista-do-emmy-internacional-alexandre-outros-herois-pode-ter-mais-episodios-em-2015-14233742|title=Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is \u00e9 finalista do Emmy Internacional|date=14 October 2014|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=Revista da TV|author=Nilton Carauta}}</ref> also included Fl\u00e1vio Bauraqui, Fl\u00e1vio Rocha, Marc\u00e9lia Cartaxo and Luci Pereira.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/opiniao/direcao-seca-faz-a-qualidade-tecnica-de-alexandre-e-outros-herois-1577#ixzz4dl00ba3T|title=Dire\u00e7\u00e3o 'seca' faz a qualidade t\u00e9cnica de Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is|date=19 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV|author=Raphael Scire}}</ref> Critic Patricia Kogut considered the telefilm a miniature work of art on television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2013/12/alexandre-e-outros-herois-uma-pequena-obra-prima-na-globo.html|title='Alexandre e outros her\u00f3is': uma pequena obra-prima na Globo|date=20 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=O Globo|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|quote=Trata-se de uma viagem horizontal pela cultura popular, sem o olhar estrangeiro, ou a entroniza\u00e7\u00e3o daquilo que \u00e9 simples. Essa \u00e9 uma das maiores virtudes do programa adaptado por Lu\u00eds Alberto de Abreu e com a clar\u00edssima assinatura de Luiz Fernando Carvalho. N\u00e3o vimos a alta cultura caindo na tenta\u00e7\u00e3o popularizante e sim uma produ\u00e7\u00e3o abertamente popular e ao mesmo tempo elegante e requintada, com ambi\u00e7\u00e3o art\u00edstica e dona de um universo est\u00e9tico pr\u00f3prio, original}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2013/12/25/luiz-fernando-carvalho-lembra-que-ha-lugar-para-graciliano-ramos-na-tv/|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho lembra que h\u00e1 lugar para Graciliano Ramos na TV|author=Mauricio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=25 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)'' ===\n{{Main|Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o}}\nThis 2014 production marked the director's return to the telenovela format after 12 years of dedicating himself to mini-series and more authorial projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/serafina/2014/04/1445086-luiz-fernando-carvalho-critica-novelas-tradicionais-e-cruza-conto-de-fadas-e-hq.shtml|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho critica novelas tradicionais e cruza conto de fadas e HQ|author=Sylvia Colombo|publisher=Serafina|date=27 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://televisao.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/07/31/e-preciso-renovar-mais-e-copiar-menos-diz-diretor-de-meu-pedacinho.htm|title=\u00c9 preciso renovar mais e copiar menos, diz diretor de Meu Pedacinho|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' was written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, with art production by Marco Cortez, art work by Raimundo Rodriguez and costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie. The critics praised various aspects, from the harmony of the quality of acting to the editing, direction, costumes, scenography and aesthetics, inspired by Westerns and Japanese manga (comics).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/entretenimento/noticia/2014/07/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-estetica-que-deu-certo-4564521.html|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o: A Est\u00e9tica que deu certo|author=Vanessa Scalei|publisher=Zero Hora|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2014/08/01/meu-pedacinho-do-chao-fugiu-do-obvio-surpreendeu-e-encantou/|title=Meu Pedacinho do Ch\u00e3o fugiu do \u00f3bvio e surpreendeu|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=1 August 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/opiniao/cinco-motivos-para-tornar-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-inesquecivel-4268|title=Cinco motivos para tornar Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o inesquec\u00edvel|author=Raphael Scire|publisher=UOL|date=30 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/05/linda-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-dissolve-duvidas-da-estreia.html|title='Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o' dissolve d\u00favidas na estreia|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=27 May 2014|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o \u00e9 uma das grandes produ\u00e7\u00f5es da nossa TV. Segue linda, artesanal dentro do poss\u00edvel e \u00e9 carregada principalmente por sua hist\u00f3ria. Dentro daquele ambiente on\u00edrico e l\u00edrico, h\u00e1 dramas e conflitos s\u00e9rios. Eles capturam a aten\u00e7\u00e3o do p\u00fablico com for\u00e7a. E a beleza dos cen\u00e1rios e figurinos n\u00e3o dissimula nem diminui esses recados}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,meu-pedacinho-de-chao-nao-se-acomoda-e-faz-nevar-no-rio,1531589|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o n\u00e3o se acomoda e faz nevar no Rio|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=21 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Luiz Fernando Carvalho's direction of the actors revealed a new code of interpretation, noted by the critics, to actors such as [[Juliana Paes]] and [[Rodrigo Lombardi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/04/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-estreia-com-marca-do-diretor.html|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o estreia com marca do diretor|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o estreia com marca do diretor (...) Juliana Paes, madura, exuberante, respondeu bem \u00e0 m\u00e3o forte da dire\u00e7\u00e3o. Mostrou que avan\u00e7ou um passo na sua trajet\u00f3ria de atriz}}</ref> The team's creative process and cast coaching to shape the aesthetics of ''My Little Plot of Land'' took place at TVLi\u00ea, known as Galp\u00e3o, which operated from 2013 to 2017. The space brought together all the creative teams and was conceived by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, at Projac, for collaborative project creation and talent training. In addition to ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'', the works ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Female Messages (Correio Feminino)]]'', ''[[:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)|Alexander and Other Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)]]'', ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|The Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' were created in the Galp\u00e3o. The whole process of creation and production of the novela in the Galp\u00e3o is described by the journalist Melina Dalboni in the book ''Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o'', which has drawings, sketches and photos by the director and the team (published by Casa da Palavra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2015/02/13/livro-prolonga-a-experiencia-dos-fas-de-meu-pedacinho-de-chao/|title=Livro prolonga experi\u00eancia dos f\u00e3s do Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=13 February 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Sets and costumes were envisaged through the playful eye of childhood,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/conheca-detalhes-da-criacao-de-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-trama-com-universo-onirico-ar-de-fabula-12586431|title=Conhe\u00e7a detalhes da cria\u00e7\u00e3o de 'Meu pedacinho de ch\u00e3o', trama com universo on\u00edrico e ar de f\u00e1bula|author=Nat\u00e1lia Castro|publisher=Revista da TV|date=26 June 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> and according to the columnist Patr\u00edcia Kogut, contributed to a beautiful invented universe, far different from what we are used to seeing on TV.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/07/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-deixara-sua-marca-na-historia-da-televisao.html|title=Cr\u00edtica: Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o deixar\u00e1 sua marca na hist\u00f3ria da TV|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The houses were faced with recycled cans, based on the work of artist Raimundo Rodriguez. The costumes, the subject of an exhibition, mixed technological fabrics and plastic material.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2014/12/exposicao-exibe-figurino-da-novela-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-no-rio.html|title=Exposi\u00e7\u00e3o exibe figurinos de Meu Pedacinho do Ch\u00e3o|publisher=G1|date=27 December 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Cesar Coelho, of the Anima Mundi Festival, used stop-motion and time-lapse techniques for all the animation. The novela received the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Award for Best Actor ([[Irandhir Santos]]); Contigo Magazine Award for Best Child Actor (Tom\u00e1s Sampaio) and Best Director; the Extra television award  for Best Costumes and Best Makeup (Rubens Lib\u00f3rio); and the Quem Magazine award for Best Actor ([[Irandhir Santos]]), Best Supporting Actor (Johnny Massaro) and Best Author ([[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]]). The critic Cristina Padiglione regards the novela as worthy of a standing ovation, and in the opinion of Alexandra Moraes \"the images, at first sight childish, gain relevance with colors and effects of dramatic intent. Good performances and the firm hand of the director give the plot meaning\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/cristina-padiglione/isso-nao-e-um-pedacinho-de-chao-e-um-latifundio/|title=Isso n\u00e3o \u00e9 um 'pedacinho' de ch\u00e3o, \u00e9 um latif\u00fandio|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2014/04/1437903-critica-cores-e-filtros-reforcam-trama-em-meu-pedacinho-de-chao.shtml|title=Cr\u00edtica: Cores e filtros refor\u00e7am trama em 'Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o'|author=Alexandra Moraes|publisher=Ilustrada - Folha de S.Paulo|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Old River (Velho Chico)'' ===\n{{Main|Velho Chico (telenovela)}}\nIn 2016, ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' marked Luiz Fernando Carvalho's return to prime time,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/09/velho-chico-folhetim-classico-mas-com-muita-renovacao.html|title='Velho Chico': folhetim cl\u00e1ssico, mas com muita renova\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u201cVelho Chico, como outras obras de Carvalho, provou que a ind\u00fastria cultural da televis\u00e3o tamb\u00e9m pode ter ares de artesanato. N\u00e3o \u00e9 pouco\"}}</ref> directing the novela written by [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and Bruno Luperi, which again carried the imprint of the new esthetic in TV drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omelete.uol.com.br/series-tv/entrevista/velho-chico-stanley-kubrick-da-tv-brasileira-diretor-luiz-fernando-carvalho-fala-sobre-a-novela/|title=\"Stanley Kubrick da TV brasileira\", diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho fala sobre a novela|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=14 March 2016|publisher=Omelete.com.br|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2016/01/1734731-a-maior-funcao-da-televisao-e-criar-cidadaos-diz-luiz-fernando-carvalho.shtml|title='A maior fun\u00e7\u00e3o da televis\u00e3o \u00e9 criar cidad\u00e3os', diz Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=L\u00edgia Mesquita|date=31 January 2016|publisher=Ilustrada|work=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=24 February 2016}}</ref> The novela was divided into two phases,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/06/velho-chico-tem-cenas-para-amarrar-o-presente-ao-passado.html |title='Velho Chico' tem cenas para amarrar o presente e o passado|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|date=15 June 2016|publisher=O Globo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> with direction of photography by Alexandre Fructuoso and costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie. Highlights were the photography<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,diretor-luiz-fernando-carvalho-fala-sobre-a-fotografia-peculiar-da-novela-velho-chico,10000064739|title=Diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho fala sobre a fotografia peculiar da novela 'Velho Chico'|author=Luis Carlos Merten|date=25 July 2016|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho e a fotografia viscontiana da novela \u2018Velho Chico\u2019}}</ref> and acclaimed performances by the actors [[Antonio Fagundes]], Lucy Alves, [[Domingos Montagner]], Lee Taylor, [[Marcos Palmeira]], [[Chico Diaz]], Renato G\u00f3es, [[Rodrigo Lombardi]], [[Dira Paes]], [[Irandhir Santos]], [[Fabiula Nascimento]], Julia Dalavia, Cyria Coentro, Barbara Reis, Julio Machado, Umberto Magnani, [[Camila Pitanga]], [[Christiane Torloni]], [[Marcelo Serrado]], Gabriel Leone, Giulia Buscaccio, Mariene de Castro, G\u00e9sio Amadeu, Jos\u00e9 Dumont, Marc\u00e9lia Cartaxo and others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/coluna/noticia/2016/12/quem-fez-festa-dos-telespectadores-em-2016.html|title=Quem fez a festa dos telespectadores em 2016|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=29 December 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u201cVelho Chico trouxe um vento novo para a faixa das 21h (...) Entre os destaques desse elenco estiveram novatos e veteranos, numa mistura de atores que encantou o p\u00fablico. Domingos Montagner, tragicamente morto perto da loca\u00e7\u00e3o, impressionou mais uma vez, como o Santo. Marcos Palmeira esteve no melhor papel da sua carreira. Antonio Fagundes, depois de ajustes no personagem, fez um coronel grandioso. Chico Diaz, Lucy Alves, Fabiula Nascimento, Zezita Matos, Christiane Torloni, Julia Dalavia, Renato G\u00f3es e tantos outros brilharam\"}}</ref> The cast was of a uniformity rarely seen in novelas, resulting in countless awards for its actors, including the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Award for Best Actress for Selma Egrei and the Critics' Choice Award for [[Domingos Montagner]](posthumous) and the production also won Best Supporting Actress (Selma Egrei), Best Supporting Actor (Irandhir Santos), Best Breakthrough Actress (Lucy Alves) and Best Breakthrough Actor (Lee Taylor),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/velho-chico-justica-selma-egrei-e-marco-ricca-sao-premiados-na-apc|title='Velho Chico', 'Justi\u00e7a', Selma Egrei e Marco Ricca s\u00e3o premiados na APCA|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Telepadi|date=30 November 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2016/11/1837325-aquarius-velho-chico-rita-lee-e-montagner-levam-premios-da-apca.shtml|title='Aquarius', 'Velho Chico', Rita Lee e Montagner levam pr\u00eamios da APCA|publisher=Folha Online|date=30 November 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> with Veja Rio's Carioca of the Year Award going to Luiz Fernando Carvalho for the renovated aesthetic of prime time television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vejario.abril.com.br/cidades/luiz-fernando-carvalho-cria-uma-nova-estetica-para-o-horario-nobre/|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho cria uma nova est\u00e9tica para o hor\u00e1rio nobre|author=Sofia Cerqueira |publisher=Veja Rio|date=10 December 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The team's creative process and cast coaching lasted only three months and took place at TVli\u00ea, Luiz Fernando Carvalho's collaborative creative space, which operated at Projac between 2013 and 2017 and was known as Galp\u00e3o.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amarello.com.br/artigo/amarello-visita-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Amarello Visita: Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Tom\u00e1s Biagi Carvalho|publisher=Amarello|access-date=14 April 2017|quote=Para preparar os atores de seus projetos, construiu um galp\u00e3o: uma mistura de circo com escola de samba, mambembe, feito de material reciclado e resto de cen\u00e1rio; uma c\u00e9lula criativa dentro dos Est\u00fadios Globo.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/serafina/2016/03/1743767-atores-de-velho-chico-nova-novela-da-globo-fazem-experiencias-em-galpao.shtml|title=Atores de 'Velho Chico' fazem experi\u00eancias em galp\u00e3o|author=L\u00edgia Mesquita |publisher=Serafina|date=28 February 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Os personagens de todo o elenco da saga familiar escrita por Benedito Ruy Barbosa eram gestados em um espa\u00e7o coletivo de experimenta\u00e7\u00e3o idealizado pelo diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/03/lindo-capitulo-marca-volta-do-brasil-rural-21h.html|title=Lindo cap\u00edtulo marca a volta do Brasil rural \u00e0 TV|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=16 March 2016|quote=\"A estreia de ''Velho Chico'' teve mesmo o selo autoral do seu diretor, Luiz Fernando Carvalho.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/03/velho-chico-e-o-brasil-real-e-o-da-fantasia.html|title=Velho Chico e o Brasil real e o da fantasia|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=18 March 2016|quote=\"''Velho Chico'', de alguma forma, trouxe a f\u00e1bula de volta ao hor\u00e1rio nobre. (...) Mas a realiza\u00e7\u00e3o de Luiz Fernando Carvalho faz sonhar. E a hist\u00f3ria de Benedito Ruy Barbosa tem muitas chances de agradar com essa mistura de realidade \u00e1rida com estetiza\u00e7\u00e3o.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> The first phase, applauded by the critics, marked the return of actor [[Rodrigo Santoro]] to the Globo fold<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/rodrigo-santoro-volta-as-novelas-da-globo-17902522|title=Rodrigo Santoro volta \u00e0s novelas|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=28 October 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>  and revealed the hitherto undiscovered talent of [[Carol Castro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/novelas/sensacao-de-velho-chico-carol-castro-teve-de-fazer-teste-chorando-10725 |title=Sensa\u00e7\u00e3o de Velho Chico, Carol Castro teve de fazer teste chorando|author=Marcia Pereira|date=16 March 2016|publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> [[Tarc\u00edsio Meira]], in just two episodes, put in an impressive performance, as did actress Selma Egrei, who took part in both phases of the novela.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.correio24horas.com.br/single-entretenimento/noticia/selma-egrei-se-destaca-em-velho-chico-com-a-sofrida-e-poderosa-encarnacao/?cHash=87ff234ae84127b9c7650a9a82598eae|title=Selma Egrei se destaca em 'Velho Chico' com a sofrida e poderosa Encarna\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Roberto Midlej |publisher=Correio Popular|date=7 August 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The cast was selected after an extensive  search for actors from the Northeast and marked the debut in novelas of Lucy Alves, Renato G\u00f3es, Marina Nery, Barbara Reis, Diyo Coelho, Xangai, Veronica Cavalcanti, Lee Taylor, Zezita de Matos, Mariene de Castro, Yara Charry, Raiza Alc\u00e2ntara, Lucas Veloso, Sueli Bispo and the comedian Bator\u00e9.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/velho-chico-tera-60-do-elenco-composto-por-atores-nordestinos-18716574|title=Velho Chico' ter\u00e1 60% do elenco composto por atores nordestinos|author=Zean Bravo |publisher=Revista da TV|date=28 February 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,diretor-procura-atores-por-todo-o-pais-para-novela-das-9,1777455|title=Diretor procura atores por todo o pa\u00eds para a novela das 9|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The last chapters of the novela pay tribute to the actor [[Domingos Montagner]] (Santo), who drowned in the S\u00e3o Francisco river two weeks before the end of the serial. The character was maintained in the plot even after the actor's death through the language created by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, in which a single subjective camera interpreted Santo's viewpoint, so his presence was felt, engaging with all the other characters, to the end.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/camera-subjetiva-solucao-de-velho-chico-para-santo-e-linda/ |title=C\u00e2mera subjetiva: solu\u00e7\u00e3o de 'Velho Chico' para Santo \u00e9 linda|author=Marcia Carolina Maia|date=27 September 2016|publisher=Veja|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2016/09/30/obrigado-velho-chico/|title=Cr\u00edtica: Obrigado, \"Velho Chico\"|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=30 September 2016|publisher=UOL|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/09/presenca-incorporea-de-domingos-montagner-em-velho-chico.html|title=A Presen\u00e7a incorp\u00f3rea de Domingos Montagner em Velho Chico|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=28 September 2016|quote=\"Nem dubl\u00ea, nem truques rasteiros. V\u00edtima de uma trag\u00e9dia que entristeceu o Brasil \u2014 e mais ainda a equipe de ''Velho Chico'' \u2014, Domingos Montagner estava na novela anteontem. Luiz Fernando Carvalho recorreu a uma c\u00e2mera subjetiva para trazer a presen\u00e7a incorp\u00f3rea do ator a quase todas as sequ\u00eancias. Era, claro, um recurso t\u00e9cnico. Por\u00e9m, qualquer car\u00e1ter racional foi plenamente absorvido pela dramaturgia e dissolvido pela emo\u00e7\u00e3o vis\u00edvel que dominou o elenco e alcan\u00e7ou o p\u00fablico. (...) Carvalho chegou perto de fronteiras perigosas e acertou muito mesmo.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> The novela came under strong pressure from the Globo network's drama department, calling for modifications to the text, storyline and esthetics. The director and the author, [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]], stood firm and refused to make the changes to ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]''. The in-house crisis made the TV columns and was described as a form of public pressure on Luiz Fernando Carvalho. According to the critic Maur\u00edcio Stycer, ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' is a landmark in the recent history of Brazilian TV, on account of its esthetic ambition and cultural relevance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/mauriciostycer/2016/10/1818880-velho-chico-marcou-pela-ambicao-estetica-e-a-relevancia-cultural.shtml |title='Velho Chico' marcou pela ambi\u00e7\u00e3o est\u00e9tica e a relev\u00e2ncia cultural|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=1 October 2016|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to Nilson Xavier, the novela \u201chad incontestable technical and artistic quality, from the direction to the photography, sound track and the actors\u2019 performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nilsonxavier.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2016/09/30/o-maior-merito-de-velho-chico-foi-provocar-e-estimular-o-publico/|title=O maior m\u00e9rito de Velho Chico foi provocar e estimular o p\u00fablico|author=Nilson Xavier|publisher=UOL|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u00c9 de Boni (Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio de Oliveira Sobrinho) a frase: \u201cA televis\u00e3o deve andar sempre um passo \u00e0 frente do p\u00fablico.\u201d \u201cVelho Chico\u201d foi um bom exemplo\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/telinha/critica-sobre-fim-de-velho-chico-tintas-fortes-do-inicio-ao-fim-20212649.html|title=Cr\u00edtica de Velho Chico: tintas fortes do in\u00edcio ao fim|author=Carla Bittencourt|publisher=Extra|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\"Velho Chico\u201d sempre foi uma novela de atua\u00e7\u00f5es e cenas memor\u00e1veis (...). Tudo muito denso, pintado com tintas mais fortes do que o telespectador est\u00e1 acostumado a ver nesse hor\u00e1rio. Essas caracter\u00edsticas garantiram \u00e0 trama seu lugar na hist\u00f3ria da teledramaturgia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2016/09/final-de-velho-chico-emociona-com-brilhante-atuacao-de-antonio-fagundes|title=Final de Velho Chico emociona com brilhante atua\u00e7\u00e3o de Antonio Fagundes|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio de Televis\u00e3o|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noblat.oglobo.globo.com/cronicas/noticia/2016/05/miss-bumbum.html|title=Noveleiro|publisher=O Globo|author=Luis Fernando Verissimo|date=1 May 2016|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=\"Eu j\u00e1 tentava ver tudo o que Luiz Fernando Carvalho fazia, e n\u00e3o apenas por solidariedade de xar\u00e1. O que ele est\u00e1 fazendo no ''Velho Chico'' ultrapassa tudo o que j\u00e1 fez na TV - com a poss\u00edvel exce\u00e7\u00e3o de ''Os Maias''. Ele \u00e9 incapaz de um enquadramento que n\u00e3o seja perfeito, e teve tamb\u00e9m o talento de escolher um elenco perfeito.\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201032703/http://noblat.oglobo.globo.com/cronicas/noticia/2016/05/miss-bumbum.html|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> It competed for the [[International Emmy Award for Best Telenovela]] of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://upload.iemmys.tv/public/iemmys/Nominees.aspx?nc=I|title=Nominees Categories|publisher=Iemmys.tv|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/kenneth-branagh-anna-friel-international-emmy-nominations-1202574242/|title=Kenneth Branagh, Anna Friel Receive International Emmy Nominations|publisher=Variety|author=Stewart Clarke|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4854403/emmy-nominations-2017/|title=Here Are the 2017 Emmy Nominations|publisher=Time|author=Kate Samuelson |date=13 July 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/velho-chico-justica-concorrem-ao-emmy-internacional-21876053|title=Velho Chico e Justi\u00e7a concorrem ao Emmy Internacional|publisher=Revista da TV,O Globo|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gshow.globo.com/programas/video-show/noticia/justica-ta-no-ar-velho-chico-totalmente-demais-e-alemao-concorrem-ao-emmy-internacional.ghtml|title=Justi\u00e7a, T\u00e1 no ar, Velho Chico, Totalmente Demais e Alem\u00e3o concorrem ao Emmy Internacional|publisher=GShow|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/a-contradicao-de-velho-chico-novela-e-finalista-ao-emmy-mas-nao-cabe-no-catalogo-de-vendas-internacionais/|title=A contradi\u00e7\u00e3o de Velho Chico: novela \u00e9 finalista ao Emmy mas n\u00e3o cabe no cat\u00e1logo de vendas internacionais|publisher=Telepadi|date=27 September 2017|quote=\u00c9 quase uma contradi\u00e7\u00e3o que o enredo n\u00e3o tenha apelo internacional e que, inscrito no Emmy Internacional, na categoria de novelas, esteja entre os cinco finalistas|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/coluna/noticia/2017/11/rodrigo-santoro-participara-do-emmy-com-equipe-de-velho-chico.html|title=Rodrigo Santoro participar\u00e1 do Emmy com equipe do Velho Chico|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=14 November 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, convidado pela Globo, n\u00e3o poder\u00e1 ir: est\u00e1 filmando em S\u00e3o Paulo|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Lavoura Arcaica, 15 years on'' ===\nTribute was paid to the film ''[[To the Left of the Father]]'' in 2017, 15 years after it was made and on account of it being hailed as one of the most important Brazilian films of all time, at the [[Rio International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/lavoura-arcaica-renasce-15-anos-apos-sua-estreia-no-festival-do-rio/|title='Lavoura Arcaica' renasce, 15 anos ap\u00f3s sua estreia, no Festival do Rio|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=23 September 2016|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Um monumento cinematogr\u00e1fico de nossa Retomada}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/gente-boa/post/barulhinho-bom-exibicao-de-lavoura-arcaica-em-pelicula-faz-felicidade-dos-nostalgicos-no-festival-do-rio.html|title=Exibi\u00e7\u00e3o de Lavoura Arcaica em pel\u00edcula faz a felicidade dos nost\u00e1lgicos no Festival do Rio |author=Cleo Guimaraes|date=15 October 2016|publisher=Gente Boa - OGlobo|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Para Selton Mello, que interpreta o protagonista Andr\u00e9, \"Foi uma aventura emocional radical, que me tirou o ch\u00e3o e me fez renascer. Esse filme me deu coragem e a verdadeira dimens\u00e3o da minha profiss\u00e3o\u201d}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,lavoura-arcaica-e-homenageado-no-festival-do-rio,10000081767|title='Lavoura Arcaica' \u00e9 homenageado no Festival do Rio |author=Luis Carlos Merten|date=12 October 2016|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> and the [[S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/lavoura-arcaica-com-presenca-de-radouan-nassar-poe-fim-a-mostra/|title='Lavoura Arcaica', com presen\u00e7a de Raduan Nassar, p\u00f5e fim \u00e0 Mostra|date=10 November 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|author=Luiz Zanin}}</ref> where a 35&nbsp;mm copy was shown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://revistacult.uol.com.br/home/lavoura-arcaica-e-a-utopia-por-um-mundo-melhor/|title=Lavoura Arcaica e a utopia por um mundo melhor|author=Eric Campi e Paulo Henrique Pompermaier|publisher=Revista Cult|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/lavoura-arcaica-15-anos-depois-dc69559029f7#.8409ildh4|title=Lavoura Arcaica, 15 anos depois|date=13 October 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo!|author=Almir de Freitas}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/lavoura-arcaica-completa-15-anos-e-segue-arrebatador/|title='Lavoura Arcaica' completa 15 anos\u2026 e segue arrebatador|date=26 June 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|author=Rodrigo Fonseca}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/filmes/quinze-anos-apos-estreia-lavoura-arcaica-dialoga-com-discussoes-atuais-20291697|title=Quinze anos ap\u00f3s a estreia, Lavoura Arcaica dialoga com discuss\u00f5es atuais |author=Suzana Velasco|date=15 October 2016|publisher=OGlobo|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> As part of the tribute at the [[Rio International Film Festival]], artist Raimundo Rodriguez created an installation that went on show for a month at the Esta\u00e7\u00e3o Net Botafogo, with memorabilia from the film, reviews and the director's notebooks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.poltronapop.com.br/2016/10/festival-do-rio-2016-lavoura-arcaica.html|title=\"Lavoura Arcaica\" ganha exibi\u00e7\u00e3o e instala\u00e7\u00e3o de Raimundo Rodriguez|date=23 September 2016|publisher=PoltronaPop|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> For Ismail Xavier and Ilana Feldman, Lavoura was born in 2001, emerging as a foreign body in the scenario of early 21st century Brazilian film, marked by its realism and its direct confrontation with Brazilian social and urban issues.<ref name=\"Ismail\"/>\n\n=== ''Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)'' ===\n{{Main|Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)}}\nScreened in 2017, the mini-series written by Maria Camargo based on the homonymous novel by [[Milton Hatoum]] was regarded by critics as another quality contribution to Brazilian television on account of the poetic style applied by the director to the adaptation of the novel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://literasutra.com/2017/03/13/duas-adaptacoes-para-dois-irmaos-entrevista-com-milton-hatoum/|title=Duas adapta\u00e7\u00f5es para Dois Irm\u00e3os: Entrevista com Milton Hatoum|publisher=Literasutra|author=Monalisa Marques|date=13 March 2017|access-date=20 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421001906/https://literasutra.com/2017/03/13/duas-adaptacoes-para-dois-irmaos-entrevista-com-milton-hatoum/|archive-date=21 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2017/01/dois-irmaos-faz-o-ano-comecar-muito-bem.html|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" \u00e9 um trabalho para ser louvado, uma grande contribui\u00e7\u00e3o de Carvalho para a televis\u00e3o brasileira|date=8 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=O Globo|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://operamundi.uol.com.br/conteudo/samuel/46161/em+adaptacao+de+dois+irmaos+para+tv+luiz+fernando+carvalho+transforma+prosa+de+milton+hatoum+em+poesia.shtml|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho conseguiu transformar a prosa de Hatoum em poesia|author=Vera Ceccarello |date=12 January 2017|publisher=OperaMundi|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffpostbrasil.com/edianez-parente/a-teatralidade-que-faz-de-dois-irmaos-uma-obra-prima-da-televi_a_21698413/|title=A teatralidade que faz de 'Dois Irm\u00e3os' uma obra prima da televis\u00e3o|author=Edianez Parente|date=13 January 2017|publisher=The Huffington Post|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/dois-irmaos-e-a-versao-amazonica-de-caim-e-abel/|title='Dois Irm\u00e3os' \u00e9 a vers\u00e3o amaz\u00f4nica de Caim e Abel|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=13 January 2017|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Pontuada por frases quase filos\u00f3ficas sobre a fala por vezes gaga do Tempo (outro muso de Carvalho), a vers\u00e3o de Maria Camargo para o romance de Hatoum deixa transbordante para o olhar quase teol\u00f3gico do aclamado diretor uma dimens\u00e3o b\u00edblica de fraternidade em f\u00faria, cindida na ponta da faca do ressentimento}}</ref> Direction of photography by Alexandre Fructuoso, costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie, scenography by Danielly Ramos, Juliana Carneiro and Mariana Villas-B\u00f4as, art production by Marco Cortez and Myriam Mendes. The production is part of the Quandrante Project and gained kudos with writer [[Milton Hatoum]]'s television debut.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://observador.pt/especiais/milton-hatoum-o-brasil-e-o-romance-da-desilusao/|title=Milton Hatoum: \"O Brasil \u00e9 o romance da desilus\u00e3o\"|author=Rita Cipriano |date=4 November 2017|publisher=Observador|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=Milton Hatoum: \"O Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u00e9 um dos grandes diretores brasileiros. Dirigiu a adapta\u00e7\u00e3o de Lavoura Arcaica, do Raduan Nassar, e novelas importantes. A linguagem dele \u00e9 muito inovadora. N\u00e3o \u00e9 aquele pastel\u00e3o, aquele soap opera previs\u00edvel. Ele trabalha com uma linguagem muito criativa e pensa em tudo \u2014 nos figurinos, na luz, em cada detalhe. \u00c9 impressionante.\"}}</ref> According to the publishing house [[Companhia das Letras]], the book sales increased by some 500% after the start of the mini-series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gente.ig.com.br/tvenovela/2017-01-18/minisserie-dois-irmaos.html|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\": miniss\u00e9rie aumenta vendas do livro em mais de 500%|date=18 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=iG}}</ref> Careers launched in Two Brothers include actors Matheus Abreu (Omar and Yaqub as an adolescent), the indigenous Zahy Guajajara (the \u00edndia Domingas) and the singer Bruna Caram (R\u00e2nia in the adult phase). The Lebanese actor [[Mounir Maasri]] made a guest appearance in the mini-series and was also responsible for the prosody (stress patterns) of the cast. The quality of the acting of the whole cast was stressed by the critics and also on social media and reached the worldwide and Brazilian Trending Topics throughout the series: [[Eliane Giardini]] and [[Juliana Paes]] as Zana; [[Antonio Fagundes]] and Antonio Calloni as Halim; and [[Cau\u00e3 Reymond]] and Matheus Abreu as the twins Omar and Yaqub. It was filmed in 2015, but at the request of the Globo network, the director agreed to make the novela ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' before he finished editing ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Dois Irm\u00e3os]]'', which was shown in January 2017. A number of innovative relevant points in the director's language were highlighted: the relation between literature and the transposition into images,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/a-linguagem-como-sonho-17e89674f18#.ue4tuyxkc|title=A Linguagem como Sonho|date=18 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo!|author=Almir de Freitas}}</ref> photography, framing, poetic language and sound track, which included hits from various decades to contextualize the period in which the mini-series was set. In addition, Luiz Fernando Carvalho inaugurated, on TV, the dialogue between the fictional scenes and images from the archives of Brazilian History, with the research of historical material done by Raquel Couto. \nAccording to the critic Maur\u00edcio Stycer, in an article published in the Folha de S.Paulo newspaper about Netflix's investment in Brazil, the miniseries was a startling revelation to those who normally only have access to terrestrial channels in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/mauriciostycer/2017/01/1852056-enquanto-netflix-avanca-na-conquista-do-mundo-globo-mostra-suas-armas.shtml|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" \u00e9 de uma qualidade espantosa para quem tem acesso apenas \u00e0 TV aberta no Brasil|date=21 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer}}</ref> For Luiz Zanin, the miniseries was about Brazil and the thwarted ideal of a multi-ethnic, sensual and carefree nation. \u201cAn elegant delicacy served up to the public, and which will leave it wanting more\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/o-som-e-a-furia-em-dois-irmaos/|title=O Som e a F\u00faria de Dois Irm\u00e3os|author=Luiz Zanin|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Uma hist\u00f3ria bem contada fala de si mesma e tamb\u00e9m de outras coisas. Esta nos falou do Brasil, de sua utopia frustrada de na\u00e7\u00e3o multi\u00e9tnica, sensual e feliz. Um fino biscoito oferecido ao p\u00fablico, e que vai deixar saudades}}</ref> Critic Carlos Alberto de Mattos wrote that what was seen in The Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os) \u201cwas not a realistic reflection, but an exuberant image, a mythical saga, a work of art\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carmattos.com/2017/01/09/arquetipos-e-epifanias-em-dois-irmaos/|title=Arqu\u00e9tipos e epifanias em Dois Irm\u00e3os|publisher=Rastros de Carmattos|author=Carlos Alberto Mattos|date=9 January 2017|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nilsonxavier.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2017/01/09/dois-irmaos-transmite-em-belas-imagens-um-crescente-clima-de-tragedia/|title='Dois Irm\u00e3os' transmite em belas imagens um crescente clima de trag\u00e9dia|author=Nilson Xavier|date=9 January 2017|publisher=UOL|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=(A miniss\u00e9rie) tem a assinatura de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, o que \u2013 j\u00e1 sabemos \u2013 significa esmero na est\u00e9tica, fotografia, tomadas, trilha sonora e dire\u00e7\u00e3o de atores.(...) Quem conhece a obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho sabe que cada produ\u00e7\u00e3o sua \u00e9 \u00fanica, mesmo dentro de seu estilo caracter\u00edstico de dire\u00e7\u00e3o}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://revistacaju.com.br/2017/01/13/a-lavoura-amazonense-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=A 'lavoura amazonense' de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Christiane Passafaro Guzzi|date=13 January 2017|publisher=Revista Caju|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=O que parece diferenciar Carvalho \u00e9 o estabelecimento de um estudo aprofundado da obra, da cr\u00edtica, da tradi\u00e7\u00e3o, e, principalmente, das reverbera\u00e7\u00f5es que a produ\u00e7\u00e3o dos escritores selecionados produzem no cen\u00e1rio ficcional}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/curioso-para-ver-dois-irmaos-ja-ha-3-episodios-no-globoplay-serie-vale-cada-minuto/|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" em duas palavras: n\u00e3o perca|date=6 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|author=Cristina Padiglione}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/dois-irmaos-tem-adaptacao-sensivel-e-poetica-na-globo/|title=Carvalho volta a exibir seu estilo teatral, sens\u00edvel e po\u00e9tico na adapta\u00e7\u00e3o|date=9 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Veja|author=Meire Kusumoto}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2017/01/intensa-e-inquietante-dois-irmaos-fisga-o-publico-a-critica-e-prova-que-nao-e-preciso-ritmo-frenetico-para-fazer-sucesso|title=Intensa e inquietante, Dois Irm\u00e3os fisga o p\u00fablico, a cr\u00edtica e prova que n\u00e3o \u00e9 preciso ritmo fren\u00e9tico para fazer sucesso|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio de Televis\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nexojornal.com.br/entrevista/2017/01/12/%E2%80%98Dois-irm%C3%A3os%E2%80%99-%C3%A9-sobre-o-colapso-de-uma-fam%C3%ADlia.-Mas-tamb%C3%A9m-de-um-projeto-de-pa%C3%ADs|title='Dois irm\u00e3os' \u00e9 sobre o colapso de uma fam\u00edlia. Mas tamb\u00e9m de um projeto de pa\u00eds|author=Juliana Domingos de Lima|date=12 January 2017|publisher=Nexo Jornal|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=\"A adapta\u00e7\u00e3o de \u201cDois irm\u00e3os\u201d, na verdade uma transposi\u00e7\u00e3o ou transcri\u00e7\u00e3o para o audiovisual, (...) oferece ao espectador brasileiro a possibilidade de alguns encontros fundamentais: encontro com cinquenta anos de hist\u00f3ria do pa\u00eds (...); com uma enorme diversidade humana e cultural (...); com uma forma expressiva que investe na sensibilidade e intelig\u00eancia do espectador (...); por fim, o encontro com um projeto de pa\u00eds, que se insinuava durante a Belle \u00c9poque amaz\u00f4nica, mas cuja promessa de futuro \u00e9 posta abaixo pela ditadura civil-militar e sua ideia destrutiva de \u201cprogresso\u201d. (...) \u00c9 importante perceber que, enquanto a literatura brasileira ganha relev\u00e2ncia e contund\u00eancia ao migrar para a TV, a pr\u00f3pria TV ganha tamb\u00e9m enorme prest\u00edgio art\u00edstico ao valorizar um produto liter\u00e1rio nacional, ainda mais sob a marca e o estilo barroco, marcado pelo ac\u00famulo de elementos e alta intensidade, do Luiz Fernando Carvalho\" (Ilana Feldman)}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, Luiz Fernando Carvalho left the Globo Network (Rede Globo) after 30 years of working for the TV station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/desgastes-de-bastidores-motivaram-fim-do-contrato-do-diretor-de-dois-irmaos-na-globo/|title=Um diretor fora da curva|date=24 February 2017|publisher=Telepadi|access-date=28 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valor.com.br/cultura/4911882/um-diretor-fora-da-curva|title=Um diretor fora da curva|author=Maria da Paz Trefaut|date=24 March 2017|publisher=Valor Econ\u00f4mico|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho construiu uma aura intelectual ao seu redor, uma imagem de profissional autoral que n\u00e3o se apega a conven\u00e7\u00f5es}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the director received the APCA Award for ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2017/12/1942551-apca-escolhe-os-melhores-de-2017.shtml|title=APCA escolhe os melhores de 2017|date=11 December 2017|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/juliana-paes-e-a-forca-do-querer-ganham-premio-da-associacao-paulista-de-criticos-de-artes-apca-veja-lista.ghtml|title=Juliana Paes e a For\u00e7a do Querer ganham pr\u00eamio da Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Artes (APCA); veja a lista|date=12 December 2017|publisher=G1|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref> the [[International Emmy Award for Best Telenovela]] Nomination for ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and the Bravo Award (Pr\u00eamio Bravo) for Artist of the Year, for his trajectory and esthetic renovation on television with ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' and the 15th anniversary of the film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''.\n\n== Personal life ==\nHe was married to the artist Sandra Burgos, with whom he has one son, Th\u00e9o Burgos Carvalho.\n\nHe was married to the actress [[Tereza Seiblitz]], with whom he has one son, Vitt\u00f3rio, born June 8, 2001.\n\nHe was married to the actress [[Let\u00edcia Persiles]], with whom he has one son, Ariel.\n\n== Bibliography ==\nThe following books written by Luiz Fernando Carvalho are references for this article. For the complete list of books about the director, see [[Luiz Fernando Carvalho Bibliography]]\n* {{cite book |first = Luiz Fernando |last = Carvalho | title = Sobre Lavour'Arcaica \u2013 O filme  | date = 2002  | publisher= Ateli\u00ea Editorial  | isbn = 9780815411833|url=https://books.google.com/?id=xNAed1GNO7QC&printsec=frontcover&dq=lavoura+arcaica#v=onepage&q=lavoura%20arcaica&f=false}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Abreu |first2=Luis Alberto |title=Hoje \u00e9 dia de Maria \u2013 Roteiros da 1a e 2a jornadas |publisher=Globo |date=2006 |isbn=9788525040985|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Qy8bAQAAIAAJ&q=Hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+Maria&dq=Hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+Maria}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho|title= Pedra do Reino - Estojo Ilustrado com 5 Cadernos de Filmagens + Di\u00e1rio de Elenco e Equipe |publisher=Globo |date=2007 |isbn=978-8525043375|url=http://www.saraiva.com.br/pedra-do-reino-estojo-ilustrado-com-5-cadernos-de-filmagens-diario-de-elenco-e-equipe-1968247.html}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho|title= O processo de Capitu |publisher= LeYa Casa da Palavra  |date=2008 |isbn=978-8577341023|url=https://books.google.com/?id=vaBaMQAACAAJ&dq=inauthor:%22Luiz+Fernando+Carvalho%22}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando|last=Carvalho |title= Livro - Quem \u00e9 Capitu?|publisher= Nova Fronteira |date=2008 |chapter=Capitu c\u2019est moi? |pages=17\u201320| isbn=9788520920831|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DuUdAQAAIAAJ&q=Quem+%C3%A9+Capitu?&dq=Quem+%C3%A9+Capitu?&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj0-9O0ktTTAhWJl5AKHcKSBIIQ6AEIJjAA}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Diniz |first2=Julio|title= Machado de Assis (1908-2008) |publisher= Contraponto |date=2008 |chapter=Capitu c\u2019est moi? |pages=80\u201383|isbn=978-85-7866-011-6|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Machado_de_Assis.html?id=cyyFPgAACAAJ&redir_esc=y}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Cuenca |first2=Jo\u00e3o Paulo |last3=Gianetti |first3=Cec\u00edlia |last4=Melamed |first4=Michel  |title= Afinal, o que querem as mulheres? |publisher= LeYa |date=2010 |isbn=9788580440300|url=https://books.google.com/?id=pwqCYgEACAAJ}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando |last2=Lins |first2=Paulo |last3=Franz |first3=Pedro |title=Suburbia |publisher=Aeroplano |date=2012 |isbn=9788578200916 |url=http://www.pedrofranz.com.br/suburbia |access-date=2017-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112022818/http://www.pedrofranz.com.br/suburbia |archive-date=2017-11-12 |url-status=dead }}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho |title= Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|publisher= LeYa Casa da Palavra |date=2013 |isbn=978-85-7734-525-0|url=https://books.google.com/?id=sHngjgEACAAJ}}\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Cinema\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''The Waiting (A Espera)'' \n| Director and Screenwriter\n| [[Short-film]] based on [[Roland Barthes]]\u00b4s Fragments d'un discours amoureux\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos|May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Ohos Sejam Atendidos)]]''\n| Director\n| [[Documentary film]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''\n|  Director and Screenwriter\n| [[Film]] based on the novel of [[Raduan Nassar]]\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+TV Series\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[:pt:Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas (miniss\u00e9rie)|Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]'' \n| Assistant director\n| Based on [[Guimar\u00e3es Rosa]]\u00b4s [[Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[:pt:Riacho Doce (miniss\u00e9rie)|Sweet River (Riacho Doce)]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|The Maias (Os Maias)]]''\n|  Director \n| Based on [[E\u00e7a de Queiroz]]\u00b4s [[Os Maias]]\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]], [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]] and [[Silvio Romero]]\u00b4s essay; Co-written with Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[:pt:Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria: Segunda Jornada|Today is Maria's Day: Second Journey (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria: Segunda Jornada)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]], [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]] and [[Silvio Romero]]\u00b4s essay; Co-written with Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[:pt:A Pedra do Reino|Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)]]''\n| Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel; Co-written with Braulio Tavares and Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Capitu]]''\n| Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[Machado de Assis]]\u00b4s [[Dom Casmurro]]\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[:pt:Afinal, o Que Querem as Mulheres?|After all, what does a woman want (Afinal, O Que Querem as Mulheres?)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Influenced by [[Sigmund Freud]]\u00b4s theory; Co-written with J.P. Cuenca and Michel Melamed\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[:pt:Sub\u00farbia|Suburbia]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Co-written with Paulo Lins\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Ladie's Mail (Correio Feminino)]]'' \n| Novelist e Diretor\n|  From [[Clarice Lispector]]\u00b4s chronicles\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on [[Milton Hatoum]]\u00b4s novel\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Soap Opera\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[:pt:Helena (1987)|Helena]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on the novel of [[Machado de Assis]]\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[:pt:Carmem (telenovela)|Carmen]]''\n|  Director\n| Written by [[Gl\u00f3ria Perez]]\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[:pt:Vida Nova|Vida Nova]]''\n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Tieta (telenovela)|Tieta]]''\n| Director\n| Based on the novel of [[Jorge Amado]]\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Pedra sobre Pedra|Stone on Stone (Pedra sobre Pedra)]]''\n| Director\n| Written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]]\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Renascer|Rebirth (Renascer)]]''\n| Director \n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[:pt:Irm\u00e3os Coragem (1995)|Irm\u00e3os Coragem]]''\n| Director\n| Remake of [[Janete Clair]]\u00b4s soap opera\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of Catlle (O Rei do Gado)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Esperan\u00e7a (telenovela)|Esperan\u00e7a]]'' \n| Director \n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa e Bruno Luperi\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Especiais para TV\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''Chit\u00e3ozinho e Xoror\u00f3 Especial'' \n| Director\n| Musical Show\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''The Cangaceiro's Revenge (Os Homens Querem Paz)'' \n| Director\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[:pt:Uma mulher vestida de sol|A Woman Clothed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)]]''\n|  Director\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)|The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)]]''\n|  Director\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)|Alexandre and Others Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)]]'' \n|  Diretor\n| Based on [[Graciliano Ramos]]\u00b4s short stories\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://luizfernandocarvalho.com/ Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Official website] {{in lang|pt}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0142461|name=Luiz Fernando Carvalho}}* \n* [http://40.mostra.org/en/filme/3902-TO-THE-LEFT-OF-THE-FATHER To The Left of The Father - Mostra de Cinema de SP]\n* [http://www.commeaucinema.com/critiques/a-la-gauche-du-pere,14209 A La Gauche du Pere - Comme au Cinema] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=46949.html A La Gauche du Pere - AlloCine] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://enciclopedia.itaucultural.org.br/pessoa466999/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Enciclopedia Ita\u00fa Cultural] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://topicos.estadao.com.br/noticias-sobre-luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Estad\u00e3o] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://www.atelie.com.br/publicacoes/autor/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Ateli\u00ea Editorial] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://40.mostra.org/br/diretores/3359-LUIZ-FERNANDO-CARVALHO Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Mostra de Cinema de SP] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.filmeb.com.br/quem-e-quem/diretor/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Filme B] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.adorocinema.com/personalidades/personalidade-78430/ Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Adoro Cinema] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.festivaldorio.com.br/br/filmes/lavoura-arcaica Lavoura Arcaica - Festival do Rio] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://twitter.com/luizfernandodir Luiz Fernando Carvalho] no [[Twitter]] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/LuizFernandoCarvalhoFanPage Luiz Fernando Carvalho] no [[Facebook]] {{in lang|pt}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carvalho, Luiz Fernando}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Rio de Janeiro (city)]]\n[[Category:Brazilian film directors]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox person\n| name = Luiz Fernando Carvalho\n| image    =\n| imagesize =\n| birth_name = Luiz Fernando Carvalho de Almeida\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1960|7|28|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality =\n| alias =\n| yearsactive = 1985\u2013present\n| occupation       = Film director, screenwriter, novelist\n| known_for        = [[Film]]s and [[Television program|TV series]] based on [[List of Brazilian writers|Brazilian writers]]\n| notable_works   =  ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'', ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|Os Maias]]'', ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Dois Irm\u00e3os]]''\n| children = \n}}\n\n'''Luiz Fernando Carvalho''' (born July 28, 1960 in [[Rio de Janeiro]]) is a [[Brazil]]ian filmmaker and television director, known for works closely linked to literature that constitute a renovation in Brazilian audiovisual aesthetics.<ref>Carter, Eli Lee [http://escholarship.org/uc/item/589368qf#page-3 \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho: An Auteur of Brazilian Television\"], ''UCLA Electronic Theses and Dissertations'', 2013. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref> He has already brought to the screen works by [[Ariano Suassuna]], [[Raduan Nassar]], [[Machado de Assis]], [[E\u00e7a de Queir\u00f3s]], [[Roland Barthes]], [[Clarice Lispector]], [[Milton Hatoum]], [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]] and [[Graciliano Ramos]], among others.\n\nSome critics compare Luiz Fernando Carvalho's productions to the Brazilian Cinema Novo<ref name=\"Sukman\">{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=lavoura+arcaica&anyword=&noword=&exactword=Mario+Peixoto&decadaSelecionada=&anoSelecionado=&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title=Um cineasta que est\u00e1 entrando para o clube dos poetas|author=Hugo Sukman|publisher=OGlobo|date=28 October 2001|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Com Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho respeita uma tradi\u00e7\u00e3o que vai de Mario Peixoto a Ruy Guerra}}</ref> and icons of film history such as [[Luchino Visconti]] and [[Andrei Tarkovski]].<ref name=\"Piza\">{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,lavoura-arcaica-estreia-sabado-no-canada,20010822p2443|title=\"Lavoura Arcaica\" estr\u00e9ia s\u00e1bado no Canad\u00e1|author=Daniel Piza|date=22 August 2001|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Um parentesco com o estilo e a espiritualidade do cinema dos russos Tarkovski e Sokurov}}</ref> His work is characterized by visual and linguistic experimentation<ref name=\"Ismail\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrissima/2016/10/1822788-quinze-anos-depois-filme-lavoura-arcaica-ainda-e-corpo-estranho.shtml|title=Quinze anos depois, filme \"Lavoura Arcaica\" ainda \u00e9 corpo estranho|author=Ilana Feldman e Ismail Xavier|date=16 October 2016|publisher=Ilustr\u00edssima/Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> and exploration of the multiplicity of Brazil's cultural identity.<ref>[http://www.lanacion.com.ar/395562-luiz-fernando-carvalho-talento-made-in-brasil \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho, talento made in Brasil\"], ''La N\u00e1cion'', 11 May 2002. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref><ref name=\"MariaRita\">{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/maria-rita-kehl-velho-chico-reinaugura-um-desejo-de-utopia-20210647|title='Velho Chico' reinaugura um desejo de utopia|author=Maria Rita Kehl|date=1 October 2016|publisher=OGlobo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=O Brasil de Benedito Ruy Barbosa e Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u00e9 agreste. \u00c9 pobre, remediado, devastado e esperan\u00e7oso}}</ref> The baroque style<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diplomatique.org.br/uma-novela-shakespeareana-neorrealista-e-barroca/|title='Uma Novela Shakespearana, neorrealista e barroca|author=Helcio Kovaleski|date=15 March 2016|publisher=Le Monde Diplomatique Brasil|access-date=13 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Coelho\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1411200117.htm|title='Lavoura' e os ind\u00edcios de uma obra prima|author=Marcelo Coelho|date=14 November 2001|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Lavoura Arcaica\" tem todas as raz\u00f5es para ser excessivo, barroco, quase ostentat\u00f3rio em sua riqueza estil\u00edstica. O filme consegue traduzir visualmente toda a beleza liter\u00e1ria do livro de Raduan Nassar}}</ref><ref name=\"Ilana\">{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/dois-irm%C3%A3os-arqueologia-da-mem%C3%B3ria-alegoria-da-destrui%C3%A7%C3%A3o-45b5723b88cd|title=Dois Irm\u00e3os: arqueologia da mem\u00f3ria, alegoria da destrui\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Ilana Feldman|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Na obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, o barroco \u00e9 um conceito norteador de uma pesquisa de linguagem: busca conceitual pela brasilidade presente nos opostos, nas contradi\u00e7\u00f5es e nos contrastes deste pa\u00eds}}</ref> of overlays and interlacing of narrative genres, the relation to the moment in Time,<ref name=\"Mata\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/critica/ult569u395.shtml|title=Em \"Lavoura Arcaica\", Carvalho faz retrato do tempo|author=Tiago Mata Machado|date=23 October 2001|publisher=FolhaOnline|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> the archetypal symbols of the Earth and the reflection on the language of social and family melodrama<ref name=\"Inacio\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1511200125.htm|title=Longa \u00e9 exce\u00e7\u00e3o exemplar no cinema do pa\u00eds|author=In\u00e1cio Ara\u00fajo|date=15 November 2001|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> are features of the director's poetic language.\n\nThe filmmaker's works have met with both critical and public acclaim. He directed the film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'' (2001), based on the homonymous novel by [[Raduan Nassar]], cited by the critic [[:fr:Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9]] in the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]] as a \"ground-breaking promise of renovation, of an upheaval not seen in Brazilian cinema since [[Glauber Rocha]],<ref name=\"Cahiers\">Tess\u00e9, Jean-Philippe [http://www.cineressources.net/articles_periodiques/resultat_f/index.php?pk=85803&param=F&textfield=a+la+gauche+du+pere&rech_type=F&rech_mode=exact&pageF=1&pageP=1&type=FOR&pk_recherche=85803 \" Les pieds dans la terre\"], ''Cahiers du Cin\u00e8ma'', July\u2013August 2003. Retrieved on 19 April 2017.</ref><ref>Tess\u00e9, Jean-Philippe [http://www.chronicart.com/cinema/a-la-gauche-du-pere/ \"On peut ais\u00e9ment voir dans cette grande fresque charnelle la plus belle d\u00e9couverte du cin\u00e9ma br\u00e9silien depuis Glauber Rocha, au moins parce que Luiz Fernando Carvalho partage avec le r\u00e9alisateur de Antonio das mortes un go\u00fbt pour la puissance du lyrisme\"], ''Chronicart'', 6 July 2003. Retrieved on 19 April 2017.</ref> which won over 50 national and international awards.<ref name=\"Montreal\">{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,montreal-premia-a-ousadia-de-lavoura-arcaica,20010905p2499 |title=Montreal premia a ousadia de \"Lavoura Arcaica\"|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=5 September 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The telenovelas ''[[Renascer|Renascer (Rebirth)]]'' (1993) and ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'' (1996), by screenwriter [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, are recognized as benchmarks of Brazilian television drama and achieved some of the highest audience ratings of the 1990s.<ref>Hopewell, John [https://variety.com/2016/tv/global/rodrigo-santoro-globo-velho-chico-1201725234/ \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho (\u2018The King of the Cattle\u2019) returns with a rural romantic saga packing political overtones\"], ''Variety'', 8 March 2016. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv-pesquisa.com.puc-rio.br/mostraregistro.asp?CodRegistro=23342&PageNo=25|title=Renascer deu aula de dire\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|date=6 November 1993|publisher=Jornal do Brasil|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nThere is a marked contrast between the director's television works: from the pop design of the 60s in the series ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Ladie's Mail (Correio Feminino)]]'' (2013) to the classic rigor of the mini-series ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|The Maias (Os Maias)]]'' (2001), the urban references of the working-class suburbs in the mini-series ''[[:pt:Suburbia|Suburbia]]'' (2012) to the playfulness of the soap ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' (2014), the aesthetic research of the Sert\u00e3o (backcountry) in ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' (2016) to the Brazilian fairytale of the mini-series ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]'' (2005) and the realistic universe of family tragedy in ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' (2017).<ref>Carter, Eli Lee [http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S1983-68212014000100004&script=sci_arttext&tlng=pt \"Rereading Dom Casmurro - aesthetic hybridity in Capitu\"], ''University of Virginia'', 2014. Retrieved on 18 April 2017.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1080/13569325.2014.958660| title=Afinal, o que Querem as Mulheres?: Luiz Fernando Carvalho's Metafictional Critique of Brazilian Television Fiction| journal=Journal of Latin American Cultural Studies| volume=23| issue=4| pages=363\u2013379| year=2014| last1=Carter| first1=Eli Lee}}</ref>\n\nThe director's production process is renowned for identifying new talent from all over Brazil and for training actors,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,freud-explica,635078|title=Freu Explica|author=Patricia Vilalba|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=11 November 2010|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Freud explica: \"O processo de ensaios para filmar com Luiz Fernando \u00e9 um dos diferenciais do diretor, que o p\u00f4s em posi\u00e7\u00e3o de sonho de consumo de qualquer ator comprometido com seu of\u00edcio\"}}</ref> revealing new stars of the dramatic arts such as [[Leticia Sabatella]], [[Eliane Giardini]], [[Bruna Linzmeyer]], Johnny Massaro, [[Irandhir Santos]], [[Simone Spoladore]], [[Caco Ciocler]], [[Marcello Antony]], Marco Ricca, [[Isabel Fillardis]], [[Giselle Iti\u00e9]], Emilio Orciollo Netto, Sheron Menezes, Jackson Antunes, [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]], [[Eduardo Moscovis]], Jackson Costa, [[Leonardo Vieira]], Cac\u00e1 Carvalho, Luciana Braga, Julia Dalavia, Renato G\u00f3es, Cyria Coentro, Marina Nery, J\u00falio Machado, B\u00e1rbara Reis, Lee Taylor, Zezita de Matos, Mariene de Castro and Lucy Alves, among others. The director's actor coaching technique has given rise to a method recounted in the book ''O processo de cria\u00e7\u00e3o dos atores de Dois Irm\u00e3os'' (''The creation process of the actors in Dois Irm\u00e3os''), by the photographer Leandro Pagliaro.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/entretenimento/tv/noticia/2017/01/dois-irmaos-livro-registra-cenas-da-preparacao-do-elenco-da-minisserie-9303834.html/|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\": livro registra cenas da prepara\u00e7\u00e3o do elenco da miniss\u00e9rie|author=Roger Lerina|date=12 January 2017|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/literatura,fotografo-registra-o-intenso-processo-de-ensaio-da-serie-dois-irmaos,10000098867|title=Fot\u00f3grafo registra o intenso processo de ensaio da s\u00e9rie 'Dois Irm\u00e3os'|author=Ubiratan Brasil|date=9 January 2017|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box|width=40%|align=right|quote=\"There is a concrete promise of renovation, of a palpitation not seen in Brazilian cinema since [[Glauber Rocha]]. (...) At first, one is left with nothing but fragments torn from a visual magma. But soon the chaos resolves itself, the film unrolls in all its richness like a barbaric poem verging on hallucination, of extraordinary power. (...) Never, however, does its return to the underlying myths obscure or accelerate the predominance of the sensations. If the film is possessed of such enchanting force, it is because Luiz Fernando Carvalho knows that everything starts there, in this first way of being born into the world, of allowing oneself to be ravished by it, to savor every twist of it...\"|source=\u2014Les Cahiers du Cin\u00e8ma, by [[:fr:Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9]] on his critic about ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''<ref name=\"Cahiers\"/>}}\n\n== Early Career: 1980s ==\nLuiz Fernando Carvalho studied architecture and literature. He started out in cinema at 18 in a number of roles: audio technician, assistant director, screenwriter, short film editor and director. His first TV work came in the early 80s, as assistant director of noteworthy mini-series, such as ''[[O Tempo e o Vento]]'', based on the work of [[\u00c9rico Ver\u00edssimo]], directed by [[Paulo Jos\u00e9]], and ''[[:pt:Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas|Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]'', from the work of [[Guimar\u00e3es Rosa|Jo\u00e3o Guimar\u00e3es Rosa]], in which he started to direct his first scenes, still as assistant director to Walter Avancini.\n\n=== ''The Waiting (A Espera)'' ===\nHe wrote and directed the short ''The Waiting (A Espera)'', based on the book ''[[A Lover's Discourse: Fragments]]'' (''Fragments d'un discours amoureux'') by [[Roland Barthes]]. Launched in 1986, the film collected the following awards: Best Short Film, Best Actress ([[Marieta Severo]]) and Best Cinematography ([[Walter Carvalho]]) at the 13th [[Festival de Gramado]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivaldegramado.net/vencedores?vencedores=30|title=Lista de vencedores do Festival de Gramado de 1986|publisher=FestivaldeGramado.net|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104050/http://www.festivaldegramado.net/vencedores?vencedores=30|archive-date=15 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Best Short Film ([[Golden Shell]]) at the [[San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival]] (Spain); and the Special Jury Award at the Ste Ther\u00e8se Festival (Canada).\n\n== 1990s ==\n=== ''Sweet River (Riacho Doce)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Riacho Doce (miniss\u00e9rie)}}\nEarly in the 90s, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed a 40-chapter mini-series written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]], based on the work of [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]] and starring [[Vera Fischer (actress)|Vera Fischer]], Osmar Prado, Sebasti\u00e3o Vasconcelos, [[Carlos Alberto Riccelli]] and [[Fernanda Montenegro]], with costumes by Beth Filipecki. The then inhospitable island of Fernando de Noronha (PE) served as the scene for the story, which is set in a small fishing village in the Northeast of Brazil.\n\n=== ''The Cangaceiro's Revenge (Os Homens Querem Paz)'' ===\nIn 1991, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed an adaptation of a script by Brazilian TV pioneer P\u00e9ricles Leal, with costumes by Beth Filipecki. The telefilm was shot in the town of Canind\u00e9, Cear\u00e1, and reached the finals of the 34th [[New York Television Festival]]. This marked the television debut of actress [[Leticia Sabatella]]. The critic Rodrigo Fonseca affirmed that his first memory of Let\u00edcia Sabatella on TV was also when he discovered the existence of the \"genius of direction that is Luiz Fernando\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mulheresdocinemabrasileiro.com.br/site/entrevistas_depoimentos/visualiza/164/Rodrigo-Fonseca-Leticia-Sabatella|title=Let\u00edcia Sabatella, por Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=Mulheres do Cinema Brasileiro|access-date=14 April 2017|quote=Foi quando eu tomei contato com a exist\u00eancia desse g\u00eanio da dire\u00e7\u00e3o que \u00e9 o Luiz Fernando}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Stone on Stone (Pedra Sobre Pedra)'' ===\n{{Main|Pedra Sobre Pedra}}\nIn 1992, he directed the telenovela written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]], considered to have reached the 6th largest audience in Brazilian television history.<ref name=\"Audiencia\">{{cite web|url=http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0,,EMI63532-9531,00.html |title=Aguinaldo Silva divulga lista das novelas com maior audi\u00eancia da hist\u00f3ria |date=10 March 2009 |publisher=Revista Quem |access-date=14 April 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304045233/http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0%2C%2CEMI63532-9531%2C00.html |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>  Notable cast members included: [[Lima Duarte]], [[Renata Sorrah]], Armando B\u00f3gus, [[Eva Wilma]], [[Paulo Betti]], [[Andr\u00e9a Beltr\u00e3o]], Pedro Paulo Rangel and [[Eduardo Moscovis]]. Certain characters are regarded as landmarks in TV drama: Sergio Cabeleira (Osmar Prado) and the photographer Jorge Tadeu ([[F\u00e1bio Jr.]]).\n\n=== ''The Tale of Our Lady of Light (O Auto de Nossa Senhora da Luz)'' ===\nWhile filming [[Pedra sobre Pedra]], Luiz Fernando Carvalho came up with a significant sequence inspired by [[Ariano Suassuna]]'s  Armorial Movement (Movimento Armorial) . The enormous success of the sequence, confirmed by the record number of requests by viewers for a rerun, was decisive in transformation of the material into a telefilm, with additional scenes written by Braulio Tavares and interpreted by the actor and musician [[Antonio N\u00f3brega]]. It competed for the [[International Emmy Award]] in 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/especiais/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz-curiosidades.htm|title=Curiosidades do Auto de Nossa Senhora da Luz|publisher=Mem\u00f3ria Globo|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104038/http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/especiais/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz-curiosidades.htm|archive-date=15 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Rebirth (Renascer)'' ===\n{{Main|Renascer}}\nThe 1993 soap, written by [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, met with critical and public acclaim and was the most watched in the 90s and 4th in audience ratings in the history of Brazilian television.<ref name=\"Audiencia\"/> It was also shown in several other countries. As directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, it is regarded as among the symbols of renovation of the aesthetics of the genre in the 90s.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KkJNHsGCYFkC&pg=PA219&lpg=PA219 |last=Jacob de Souza |first=Maria Carmen |title=Telenovela e representa\u00e7\u00e3o social: Benedito Ruy Barbosa e a representa\u00e7\u00e3o do popular na novela Renascer|publisher=E-papers|year=2004 |page=219 |isbn=978-85-87922-90-8|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, um dos mais expressivos representantes contempor\u00e2neos dessa tend\u00eancia autoral da dire\u00e7\u00e3o de telenovela, fez de Renascer seu sucesso mais exemplar}}</ref> The character Buba, interpreted by [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]], caused a national controversy, as it was the first time that the discussion of gender had been addressed in a telenovela. It received the APCA Award for Best Novela, Best Actor ([[Antonio Fagundes]]), Best Supporting Actor (Osmar Prado), Best Supporting Actress (Regina Dourado), Best Male Breakthrough Performance (Jackson Antunes).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/6/02/ilustrada/21.html/|title=\"Renascer\" domina premia\u00e7\u00e3o de cr\u00edticos|author=Ana Beatriz Brisola|date=2 June 1994|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> [[Leonardo Vieira]], Jackson Antunes, Cac\u00e1 Carvalho, Marco Ricca, [[Isabel Fillardis]] and [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]] were among the talents revealed in this work. The television entrepreneur [[:pt:Boni|Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio de Oliveira]], considered the plot \"well structured by Benedito, with a well-crafted first part, masterfully directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho\".<ref>{{cite book |last=Oliveira |first=Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio |date=2011 |title=O Livro do Boni |language=pt |location=S\u00e3o Paulo |publisher=Casa da Palavra |isbn=978-85-7734-226-6}}</ref> According to Marilia Martins, few novelas had a first chapter directed with such polish and skill as ''Rebirth''.\n\n=== ''A Woman Clothed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Uma mulher vestida de sol}}\nIn 1994, the telefilm directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho marked the first appearance of [[Ariano Suassuna]]'s works on television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/3/09/ilustrada/2.html|title=Ariano Suassuna prepara estr\u00e9ia na TV|author=Marcelo Migliaccio|date=9 March 1994|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=10 April 2017}}</ref> Based on the writer's unpublished novel of the same name, the script was the work of Ariano himself, in partnership with the director. Director of photography Dib Lufti, costumes by Luciana Buarque and art production by Lia Renha. Scenography by the artist Fernando Velloso, from the [[Grupo Corpo]] dance group, music by Ant\u00f4nio Madureira, a member of the Armorial Quintet (Quinteto Armorial). With ''A Woman dressed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'', the director commenced his exploration of the limits of television language, combining elements of the popular theater of the Northeast. Luiz Carlos Vasconcelos's Grupo Piolim participated and the cast included Tereza Seiblitz, Lineu Dias, Sebasti\u00e3o Vasconcelos, Ana L\u00facia Torre, [[Raul Cortez]] and the then novice actor Floriano Peixoto. According to the researcher of Literature H\u00e9lio Guimar\u00e3es, the work gave rise to an impasse at the TV station: was Lu\u00edz Fernando Carvalho too big for the Globo screen?<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/7/14/ilustrada/9.html|title=\"Mulher Vestida de Sol\" desafia o padr\u00e3o de realismo da Globo|author=H\u00e9lio Guimar\u00e3es|date=14 July 1994|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)}}\nOne year after ''A Woman dressed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'', in 1995, Luiz Fernando Carvalho resumed his connection with the writer [[Ariano Suassuna]], this time transforming the play ''[[:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)|The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)]]'' into a telefilm . The director continued his search for a hybrid language for television, as a way of criticizing the naturalism of the novelas. Art production and costumes by Yurika Yamasaki and the artist Dantas Suassuna, participation of [[Antonio N\u00f3brega]], [[Patr\u00edcia Fran\u00e7a]], [[Ary Fontoura]] and [[Marieta Severo]]. According to the critic Rog\u00e9rio Durst, the telefilm was a major feat of TV drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=artigo&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=A+Farsa+da+Boa+Pregui%C3%A7a&anyword=&noword=&exactword=sofisticada&decadaSelecionada=1990&anoSelecionado=&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title= Uma sofisticada op\u00e7\u00e3o popular|author=Rog\u00e9rio Durst|publisher=O Globo|date= 7 December 1995|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)'' ===\n{{Main Article|O Rei do Gado}}\n''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'', 1996, the director's next collaboration with the author [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/novela-de-forte-cunho-social-rei-do-gado-de-benedito-ruy-barbosa-volta-ao-ar-nesta-segunda-15009118|title= Novela de forte cunho social, 'O rei do gado', de Benedito Ruy Barbosa, volta ao ar nesta segunda|author=Nat\u00e1lia Borde |publisher=Revista da TV/OGlobo|date=12 January 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> became the novela with the 9th largest audience in Brazilian television history.<ref name=\"Audiencia\"/> It was rescreened three times,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2015/02/19/diretor-explica-por-que-terceira-reprise-de-rei-do-gado-faz-tanto-sucesso/|title=Diretor explica por que terceira reprise de \"Rei do Gado\" faz tanto sucesso|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=19 February 2015|publisher=UOL|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2015/02/1582950-reprise-de-o-rei-do-gado-chega-a-bater-novelas-ineditas-em-audiencia.shtml|title=Reprise de 'O Rei do Gado' chega a bater novelas in\u00e9ditas em audi\u00eancia|author=Fernanda Reis|date=1 February 2015|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> outrating other productions of the time, and was sold to over 30 countries. It marked the debut of [[Marcello Antony]], [[Caco Ciocler]], [[Mariana Lima]], Emilio Orciollo Netto and [[Lav\u00ednia Vlasak]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1996/10/20/revista_da_folha/3.html|title= Vidas com rumo|publisher=Revista da Folha|date=20 October 1996|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>  Other significant aspects of the novela were its social criticism and sensitive approach to the Landless Workers Movement (movimento dos sem-terra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/direto-da-fonte/a-televisao-brasileira-tem-dado-claros-sinais-de-esgotamento-de-seu-modelo/|title=A televis\u00e3o brasileira tem dado claros sinais de esgotamento de seu modelo|author=Thais Arbex|date=16 December 2013|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote= Rei do Gado foi a primeira novela a abordar o conflito dos sem-terra e a reforma agr\u00e1ria}}</ref> The actors Jackson Antunes and [[Ana Beatriz Nogueira]] stand out in this context. The cast included [[Antonio Fagundes]], [[Patricia Pillar]], [[Leticia Spiller]] and [[Raul Cortez]] with guest appearances in the early stages by [[Tarcisio Meira]], [[Eva Wilma]] and [[Vera Fischer (actress)|Vera Fischer]]. The character Ti\u00e3o Galinha, interpreted by Osmar Prado, is a landmark of his career. The novela received the Certificate of Merit at the [[San Francisco International Film Festival]] and the APCA Award for Best Actor ([[Raul Cortez]]), Best Supporting Actor (Leonardo Br\u00edcio), Best Supporting Actress (Walderez de Barros) and Best Male Breakthrough Performance ([[Caco Ciocler]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/novelas/o-rei-do-gado/premios.htm|title=Pr\u00eamios de'O Rei do Gado'|publisher=Mem\u00f3ria Globo|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328091627/http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/novelas/o-rei-do-gado/premios.htm|archive-date=28 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Fernando de Barros e Silva wrote, in the Folha de S.Paulo, \"The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado) swallows up Brazilian cinema\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.folha.uol.com.br/resultados/?q=O+Rei+do+Gado+engole+o+cinema+nacional+&site=&periodo=acervo&x=14&y=13|title=O Rei do Gado engole o cinema nacional |author=Fernando de Barros e Silva|date=7 July 1996|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to critic Rogerio Durst, the novela is \"a dramatic epic with first class special appearances and superb photography\".\n\nTiao Galinha belongs to another soap opera: \u201cRenascer\u201d.\n\n=== ''Giovanna and Henrico (Giovanna e Henrico)'' ===\nThe quality of the first seven chapters of ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'', showing the decline of the coffee cycle and Brazil's participation in World War II, prompted The Globo Network's International Division to transform the first part of the novela into the mini-series ''Giovanna and Henrico'', with [[Let\u00edcia Spiller]] and Leonardo Br\u00edcio playing the lead couple. The production was selected as hors-concours at the [[Banff World Media Festival]], in Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq150522.htm|title='O Rei do Gado' ganha pr\u00eamios em festivais|author=Cristina Padiglione|date=15 May 1997|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos)'' ===\n{{Main Article|:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos}}\nBefore the end of the 90s, Luiz Fernando Carvalho had already started on research for the feature film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''. Together with the author of the novel, [[Raduan Nassar]], he traveled to the Lebanon to familiarize himself with Mediterranean culture. The material collected during the trip was used to produce the documentary ''[[:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos|May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos)]]'', screened on GNT in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1997/12/14/tv_folha/16.html |title='Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos' estr\u00e9ia no GNT|author=Mariana Scalzo|date=14 December 1997 |access-date=29 March 2017}}</ref> In the opinion of critic Rodrigo Fonseca, the documentary \"honed to the limit of tragic fatality its investigation of time\".\n\n== 2000s ==\n=== ''To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)'' ===\n{{Main Article|To the Left of the Father}}\nIn 2001, the director made his first feature film, ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'', in which he was responsible for directing, screenplay and editing, with cinematography by Walter Carvalho, art direction by Yurika Yamazaki and costume design by Beth Filipecki.<ref name=\"Sukman\"/><ref name=\"Piza\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.almirdefreitas.com.br/almir/Lavoura_Arcaica___Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho.html|title=Com Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho vence o desafio de levar a literatura de Raduan Nassar para o cinema|author=Almir de Freitas|publisher=Revista Bravo!|access-date=17 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170418082444/http://www.almirdefreitas.com.br/almir/Lavoura_Arcaica___Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho.html|archive-date=18 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The cast included [[Selton Mello]], [[Raul Cortez]], [[Simone Spoladore]], [[Leonardo Medeiros]], [[Caio Blat]] and [[Juliana Carneiro da Cunha]]. Aiming to maintain the connection with the poetic prose of [[Raduan Nassar]]'s book, the director elected to film without a defined script, based entirely on the actors' improvisations on the theme.<ref name=\"Mata\"/><ref name=\"Coelho\"/><ref name=\"Inacio\"/> This involved intensive coaching of the cast, secluded on a farm for four months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1408200518.htm|title=Mergulho em Raduan Nassar conduz a pequena obra-prima|author=Jos\u00e9 Geraldo Couto|date=14 August 2005|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> The film's creation and production process was discussed in the book ''About To the Left of The Father'' (\"Sobre Lavoura Arcaica\"), in which the director is interviewed by Jos\u00e9 Carlos Avellar, Geraldo Sarno, Miguel Pereira, Ivana Bentes, Arnaldo Carrilho and Liliane Heynemann, launched in Portuguese, English and French by the publisher [[:pt:Ateli\u00ea Editorial|Ateli\u00ea Editorial]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.atelie.com.br/publicacoes/autor/luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title= Sobre Lavour'Arcaica \u2013 O filme|author=Luiz Fernando Carvalho |publisher=Atelier Cultural |year=2002|isbn=978-85-7480-140-7|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> It was success with the critics<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=pagina&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=Lavoura+Arcaica&anyword=&noword=&exactword=colheita&decadaSelecionada=2000&anoSelecionado=2001&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title=Uma colheita espl\u00eandida|author=Luciano Trigo|publisher=RioShow|date=28 October 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.folha.uol.com.br/resultados/?q=Filme+radicaliza+linguagem&site=&periodo=acervo&x=22&y=15|title=Filme radicaliza linguagem|author=Jos\u00e9 Geraldo Couto|publisher=Ilustrada/Folha de S.Paulo|date=24 September 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20011125-39485-spo-151-cd2-d3-not/busca/Lavoura+Arcaica|title=Convuls\u00f5es|author=Daniel Piza|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=25 November 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.lanacion.com.ar/395562-luiz-fernando-carvalho-talento-made-in-brasil|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, talento made in Brasil|author=Diego Batle|publisher=La Nacion|language=spanish|date=11 May 2002|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> and the public, reaching 300 thousand viewers with just two copies, one in Rio de Janeiro and the other in S\u00e3o Paulo. It is considered one of the [[Abraccine Top 100 Brazilian films|100 best Brazilian films of all times]], according to the Brazilian Film Critics Association (Abraccine).<ref>{{cite web |url= https://abraccine.org/2015/11/27/abraccine-organiza-ranking-dos-100-melhores-filmes-brasileiros/ |title= Abraccine organiza ranking dos 100 melhores filmes brasileiros |access-date= 26 October 2016 |author= Andr\u00e9 Dib |date= 27 November 2015 |publisher= abraccine.org}}</ref> It had a successful career in a number of national and international festivals, receiving over 50 awards at the [[Montreal World Film Festival]],<ref name=\"Montreal\"/><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.ffm-montreal.org/en/awards/16-awards-of-the-montreal-world-film-festival-2001.html/|title = 16 Awards of the Montreal World Film Festival 2001|website=FFMMontreal.org|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=n.d.|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Rio Film Festival]], the [[S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival]], the [[Grande Pr\u00eamio do Cinema Brasileiro|Grand Prix for Brazilian Film]], the [[Bras\u00edlia Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq2911200111.htm|title = Bras\u00edlia celebra \"Lavoura\" e \"Samba\"|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=29 November 2001|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Havana Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1512200135.htm|title = \"Lavoura\" ganha pr\u00eamios em Havana|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=15 December 2001|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Cartagena Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1103200214.htm|title = \"Lavoura Arcaica\" ganha Festival de Cartagena|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=11 March 2002|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Guadalajara International Film Festival]], the [[Buenos Aires International Festival of Independent Cinema]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pagina12.com.ar/diario/espectaculos/6-4799-2002-05-06.html|title=Una met\u00e1fora sobre los que no tienen lugar en la mesa social|author=Ana Bianco|language=spanish|publisher=P\u00e1gina 12|date=1 May 2002|access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> among others. In the opinion of writer and psychoanalyst Renato Tardivo, author of ''Porvir que vem antes de tudo \u2013 literatura e cinema em Lavoura Arcaica'', the film is one of the most important works of Brazilian cinema \u201cof all times\u201d.<ref>{{cite book |last=Tardivo |first=Renato Cury  |title=Porvir que vem antes de tudo: uma leitura de lavoura arcaica - literatura, cinema e a unidade dos sentidos |publisher=Universidade de S\u00e3o Paulo (USP)|date=2009 |url= http://www.teses.usp.br/teses/disponiveis/47/47134/tde-11122009-110032/pt-br.php}}</ref> The critic Carlos Alberto de Mattos described it as the first work of art of the Brazilian cinema in the 21st century.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carmattos.com/2016/10/13/festival-do-rio-lavoura-arcaica/|title=Festival do Rio: Lavoura Arcaica|author=Carlos Alberto de Mattos|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|date=25 November 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The film was acclaimed by the critics of various countries and, according to the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]], ''To the Left of the Father'' is a \"barbarous poem verging on hallucination, of extraordinary power\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.chronicart.com/cinema/a-la-gauche-du-pere/|title=Critique:A La Gauche du P\u00e8re|author=Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|language=French|publisher=Chronicart|date=6 July 2003|access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"allocine.fr\">{{cite web| url=http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=46949.html|title=Critiques:A La Gauche du P\u00e8re|publisher=AlloCin\u00e9|language=French|access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"allocine.fr\"/><ref>{{cite web| url=http://next.liberation.fr/cinema/2003/07/09/pere-de-tous-les-vices_439245|title=P\u00e9re de touts les vices. Relecture saisissante d'un monstre de la litt\u00e9rature br\u00e9silienne|author=Didier Peron|language=French|date=9 July 2003|publisher=Liber\u00e1cion|access-date=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The Maias (Os Maias)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)}}\nA 2001 production, this mini-series based on the homonymous novel by [[E\u00e7a de Queir\u00f3s]] and adapted by Maria Adelaide Amaral was another landmark in the director's career.<ref>Elena Corr\u00eaa, \"Linguagem po\u00e9tica que remete a outra \u00e9poca. Roteiro fiel e dire\u00e7\u00e3o inconfund\u00edvel\", em \"O Globo\" (11 de janeiro de 2001)</ref> The Maias portrays the decadent Portuguese aristocracy in the second half of the 19th century, through the tragic story of a traditional Lisbon family. Costumes by Beth Filipecki and direction of photography by Jos\u00e9 Tadeu Ribeiro. In the opinion of writer [[Luis Fernando Ver\u00edssimo]], \"the extraordinarily mobile camera of Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u201cvisited\u201d, more than portrayed, the frivolous Lisbon of the time and all the novel's atmospheres. But beneath it all, there was this majestic progression, from the first scene to the denouement, the moving camera conducting us like a slow tragic theme tune that recalls a symphony. No TV camera has ever been so complicit and seductive, never has TV been so romantic\".<ref>{{cite book |last=Wajnman |first=Solange  |title=Miniss\u00e9ries hist\u00f3ricas e a comunica\u00e7\u00e3o por objetos. Notas sobre os figurinos e cen\u00e1rios de 'Primo Bas\u00edlio' e \"Os Maias\"  |publisher=Universidade de Santa Maria (UFSM)|date=2011|url= https://periodicos.ufsm.br/animus/article/viewFile/4125/2624}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observatoriodaimprensa.com.br/artigos/qtv31012001991.htm|title=Os Maias|author=Luis Fernando Ver\u00edssimo|date=26 January 2001|publisher=Observat\u00f3riodaImprensa.com.br|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Para Os Maias, Carvalho escolheu um andamento que, na m\u00fasica, seria chamado de \u2018andante majestoso\u2019, que pode impacientar a gera\u00e7\u00e3o videoclipe, mas est\u00e1 perfeito, e era o ritmo preferido de Lean e Visconti.}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria)'' ===\n{{Main|Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria}}\nOver two seasons, ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]'' (2005), a mini-series in which he was also responsible for creation and script, consolidated the director's linguistic research.<ref>\"Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria - segunda jornada \u00e9 uma joia lapidada com meticulosidade por um artista barroco, que n\u00e3o tem medo de abra\u00e7ar o excesso de refer\u00eancias universais e regionais para recriar a realidade brasileira com rigor e paix\u00e3o\", in \"Correio Braziliense\" (15 October 2005)</ref>  His co-writers were Luis Alberto de Abreu and Carlos Alberto Soffredini, basing themselves on a selection of stories taken from popular Brazilian oral storytelling tradition,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq0901200511.htm|title=Carvalho invoca a cultura popular em micross\u00e9rie|author=Valmir Santos|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|date=9 January 2005|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\"\"Diretor associa \"Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria\" a uma busca pela identidade brasileira\"}}</ref> collected by the writers [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]], [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]] and [[Silvio Romero]]. Art direction by Lia Renha, guest artist Raimundo Rodriguez, direction of photography by Jos\u00e9 Tadeu Ribeiro and costumes by Luciana Buarque. The 60 marionettes that represented the animals were produced by the Grupo Giramundo, from Minas Gerais state. The work marked the start of the partnership between the director and psychoanalyst Carlos Byington, as advisor on the mythological dramatization of the text. The mini-series was conceived under a 360\u00ba dome, scrap from a rock show stage. The sound track, by Tim Rescala, was based on cirandas (traditional dances) by [[Heitor Villa-Lobos]], [[C\u00e9sar Guerra-Peixe]] and [[Francisco Mignone]]. Designer Jum Nakao was responsible for some of the costumes, with animation of the stop-motion scenes by Cesar Coelho, founder of the [[Anima Mundi (event)|Anima Mundi festival]]. It received the 2005 APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Critics' Choice Award, the ABC Best Photography Award, the Contigo Award for Best Director and Best Child Actress and the Brazil Quality Award (Pr\u00eamio Qualidade Brasil ) for Best Director, Television \u2013 Best Special Project, Best Author and Best Breakthrough Actress, and reached the finals of the 2005 [[International Emmy Award]], in the categories Best Mini-Series and Best Actress.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u54506.shtml|title=Atriz mirim de \"Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria\" \u00e9 indicada ao Emmy\"|publisher=Folha Online|date=21 October 2005|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> It was nominated Hors Concours by the [[Banff World Media Festival]], in Canada (2006), and the [[International Public Television Screening Conference|Input International Board Taipei]] (2005). Compared with ''To the Left of the Father'' on account of its innovative television language, it caught the attention of critics and public by its novel, theatrical and playful language in transporting the universe of popular culture to a sophisticated television production, without losing its authenticity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=pagina&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+maria&anyword=&noword=&exactword=&decadaSelecionada=2000&anoSelecionado=2005&mesSelecionado=10&revistaoglobo=on|title= Em Busca da nossa inf\u00e2ncia brasileira|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|publisher=Revista OGlobo|date=9 October 2005|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=As imagens de Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria s\u00e3o raras. Tudo escapa ao padr\u00e3o global: \u00e9 fic\u00e7\u00e3o que tem coragem de se revelar como fic\u00e7\u00e3o, \u00e9 uma TV que tem a ousadia de buscar nas origens do cinema a reinven\u00e7\u00e3o da linguagem}}</ref> The critic Nilson Xavier considers it one of the most poetic, original and beautiful productions of recent years.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.teledramaturgia.com.br/hoje-e-dia-de-maria/ |title=Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria|author=Nilson Xavier|publisher=Site Teledramaturgia |access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9, in the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]], the mini-series was very ambitious and formally very well produced, following other noteworthy projects such as ''The Maias (Os Maias)''.\n\n=== ''Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)'' ===\n{{Main Article|:pt:A Pedra do Reino}}\nIn 2007, the director's third production based on the works of [[Ariano Suassuna]] brought to the TV the ''Romance d'A Pedra do Reino e o Pr\u00edncipe do Sangue do Vai-e-Volta''. The mini-series is regarded as yet another aesthetic innovation by the director, as in ''To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)'' and ''Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria)''. The script was the work of Luiz Fernando Carvalho, in collaboration with Luis Alberto de Abreu and Braulio Tavares, direction of photography by Adrian Teijido, scenography by Jo\u00e3o Irenio Maia, editing by Marcio Hashimoto and costumes by Luciana Buarque. Colorist Sergio Pasqualino. Regional artists, coordinated by the artist Raimundo Rodriguez, assisted with the art production. Music by Ant\u00f4nio Madureira (Quinteto Armorial) and Marco Ant\u00f4nio Guimar\u00e3es ([[Uakti (band)|Uakti]]). The cast was the fruit of the director's extensive search for talent throughout the backcountry (sert\u00e3o) of the Northeast. Television debut of the actors [[Irandhir Santos]] and Mayana Neiva and the singer Renata Rosa, among many others. It was filmed in the town of Tapero\u00e1, where [[Ariano Suassuna]] spent his childhood. During the coaching process, the team and cast attended lectures, out in the sert\u00e3o, by the actress [[Fernanda Montenegro]], the psychoanalyst Carlos Byington and the writer himself. [[Ariano Suassuna]] affirmed that Luiz Fernando Carvalho's recreation of his ''Romance d\u2019A Pedra do Reino'' resulted in an \"extraordinarily beautiful work that moved him as author and individual, as a spectator\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.revistacinetica.com.br/pedradoreinoilana.htm|title=A Pedra do Reino:A opera mundi de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Ilana Felman|publisher=Revista Cin\u00e9tica|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://ricardocalil.ig.com.br/index.php/2007/06/06/triunfo-da-imaginao/comment-page-1|title=Triunfo da Imagina\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Ricardo Calil|publisher=iG |date=6 June 2007|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=A Pedra do Reino segue mesmo a l\u00f3gica dos sonhos, com del\u00edrios visuais de intenso brilho e elipses de tempo, com desorienta\u00e7\u00f5es espaciais e suspens\u00f5es de sentido}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/leia-critica-da-microsserie-pedra-do-reino-4182728|title=cr\u00edtica da micross\u00e9rie 'A Pedra do Reino|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=O Globo|date=16 June 2007|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=\u201cA Pedra do Reino\u201d eleva \u00e0 en\u00e9sima pot\u00eancia um questionamento autoral onipresente nas hist\u00f3rias de Carvalho desde que rodou \u201cOs homens querem paz\u201d, um especial, exibido em 1991}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/07/24/diretor-de-a-pedra-do-reino-adaptara-fernando-e-isaura-para-a-tv.amp.htm|title=Diretor de \"A Pedra do Reino\" adaptar\u00e1 \"Fernando e Isaura\" para a TV|author=Andr\u00e9ia Rocha|publisher=UOL|date=24 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2017/11/1934597-editora-lanca-dois-volumes-de-obra-postuma-de-ariano-suassuna.shtml|title=Nova Fronteira lan\u00e7a dois volumes de obra p\u00f3stuma de Ariano Suassuna|author=Claudio Leal |date=11 November 2017|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=\"Portando nomes reais ou acrescidos de sobrenomes ficcionais, amigos surgem em ep\u00edgrafes e s\u00e3o incorporados pelo escritor como personagens dos di\u00e1logos sobre a cultura brasileira e seu projeto liter\u00e1rio. As atrizes Inez Viana e Marieta Severo , os diretores Aderbal Freire Filho e Luiz Fernando Carvalho, os poetas Jos\u00e9 Laurenio de Melo e Ad\u00e9lia Prado se situam entre esses interlocutores de Dom Pantero na \"Autobiografia Musical, Dan\u00e7arina, Po\u00e9tica, Teatral e V\u00eddeo-CinematoGr\u00e1fica\"}}</ref>\n\n=== Quadrante Project (Projeto Quadrante) ===\nBased on ''[[:pt:A Pedra do Reino|Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)]]'' (2007), the director set up the Quadrante Project with the intention of making a series of regional drama programs to rediscover the Brazilian imaginary through adaptations of literary texts of authors from each Brazilian state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1712200617.htm|title=Sert\u00e3o \u00e9 \"semente\" de \"A Pedra do Reino\"|author=Esther Hamburguer|publisher=Revista Cult|date=17 December 2006|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> Similarly, local actors act out the texts. The richness of the project lay in the discovery of regional talent: authors, actors, composers, artists in general. The project recognized the human potential of each regional culture, looking beyond the simplistic image of a postcard. In addition to ''Stone of the Kingdom'', the Quadrante is made up of the mini-series [[Capitu]] (2008), based on the book ''[[Dom Casmurro]]'', by [[Machado de Assis]], and ''Dois Irm\u00e3os'' (2017), by [[Milton Hatoum]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2017/01/dois-irmaos-retoma-antigo-projeto-artistico-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-e-tem-primeiro-capitulo-deslumbrante|title=Dois Irm\u00e3os retoma antigo projeto art\u00edstico de Luiz Fernando Carvalho e tem primeiro cap\u00edtulo deslumbrante|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio da Televis\u00e3o|date=9 January 2017|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Capitu'' ===\n{{Main|Capitu}}\nIn 2008, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed and finalized the script for this adaptation of the book ''[[Dom Casmurro]]'', by [[Machado de Assis]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Carter |first=Eli Lee  |title=Rereading Dom Casmurro - aesthetic hybridity in Capitu  |publisher=University of Virginia|date=2014|url= http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S1983-68212014000100004&script=sci_arttext&tlng=pt}}</ref> The mini-series was written by Euclydes Marinho in collaboration with Daniel Piza, Luis Alberto de Abreu and Edna Palatnik. Art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez, photography by Adrian Teijido and costumes by Beth Filipecki. Colorist Sergio Pasqualino. It marked the TV debut of actors [[Let\u00edcia Persiles]] and Michel Melamed, among others. The mini-series was filmed in the abandoned Autom\u00f3vel Clube building, in downtown Rio de Janeiro, and the whole scenographic universe was created from newspaper and recycled material. The opening credits scene was conceived by the director and created by the designer Carlos B\u00eala.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/2475349/|title=Abertura de Capitu|author=Carlos B\u00eala|publisher=Vimeo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The production is part of the Quadrante Project and was the director's tribute to [[Machado de Assis]] on the centenary of his death. It received the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Critic's Choice Award (2009), ABC Best Photography Award  (from the Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Cinematografia) and the [[Creative Review]] award in the Best in Book and Design and Art Director categories. In the opinion of critic Gustavo Bernardo, the mini-series deserves \"to be viewed and reviewed countless times, at least because each fragment of a scene is precious for its beauty\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/prosa/post/a-capitu-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-145085.html|title=A Capitu de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Gustavo Bernardo|publisher=O Globo|date=9 December 2009|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to theatre director [[:pt:Gabriel Villela|Gabriel Villela]], Luiz Fernando Carvalho produces works of art on the screen, calls on the viewer's vivacity so that he accepts nothing masticated, but masticates along with Casmurro.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq0808200923.htm|title=\"Capitu\" traduz para TV modo de narrar de Machado de Assis|author=Gabriel Villela|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|date=8 August 2009|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> For Randall Johnson, director of the UCLA Latin American Institute, \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho is today, without doubt, the director whose work is the most authorial of all TV and cinema production in Brazil\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/curso-na-universidade-da-california-debate-obra-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-3144586|title=Curso na Universidade da Calif\u00f3rnia debate obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|publisher=Revista da TV/OGlobo|date=24 May 2009|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://renatofelix.wordpress.com/2009/08/27/entrevistas-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Entrevistas: Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Renato Felix|publisher=Blog do Renato Felix|date=27 August 2009|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Trata-se um ensaio sobre a d\u00favida. N\u00e3o absolvo Capitu e n\u00e3o a condeno}}</ref>\n\n== 2010s ==\n\n=== ''After all, what does a woman want (Afinal, O Que Querem as Mulheres?)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Afinal, o Que Querem as Mulheres?}}\nIn 2010, Luiz Fernando Carvalho created, directed and wrote the mini-series inspired by [[Sigmund Freud]]'s: famous question \"What does a woman want?\". [[Jo\u00e3o Paulo Cuenca]], Cecilia Giannetti and [[:pt:Michel Melamed|Michel Melamed]] collaborated on the script. As well as acting in the production, Melamed created the opening sound track. Direction of Photography Adrian Teijido, costumes by Beth Filipecki and art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez. The director launched actress [[Bruna Linzmeyer]]\u2019s career in this production. Osmar Prado shared the part of Freud with a model animated by Cesar Coelho, founder of the [[Anima Mundi (event)|Anima Mundi festival]], using the stop-motion technique.  The opening vignette features the work of German artist [[Olaf Hajek]], who also produced special illustrations for the mini-series by invitation of the director.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/17214632|title=Abertura da miniss\u00e9rie \"Afinal, o que querem as mulheres?\"|author=Alexandre Romano|publisher=V\u00edmeo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> It received the ABC award (Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Cinematografia) for Best Photography. According to columnist Patr\u00edcia Kogut, \"it is an oneiric journey, a visual poem that blends realities, full of references to times past, to what has been experienced, to what lingers in memory\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2010/11/critica-afinal-que-querem-as-mulheres-340331.html|title=Cr\u00edtica: Afinal, o que querem as mulheres?|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=13 November 2010|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Carter |first=Eli Lee  |title=Afinal, o que Querem as Mulheres?: Luiz Fernando Carvalho's Metafictional Critique of Brazilian Television Fiction |journal=Journal of Latin American Cultural Studies |volume=23 |issue=4 |pages=363\u2013379 |date=2014|doi=10.1080/13569325.2014.958660 }}</ref>\n\n=== ''Suburbia'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Suburbia}}\nIn 2012, Luiz Fernando Carvalho inaugurated in TV drama a production in which all the protagonists are of African descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://televisao.uol.com.br/critica/2012/11/01/seriado-olha-com-realismo-mas-carinho-para-a-dura-vida-no-suburbio.htm|title=Seriado olha com realismo, mas carinho para a dura vida no sub\u00farbio|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=1 November 2011|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/suburbia-uma-entrevista-com-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Suburbia: uma entrevista com Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Luiz Zanin|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=3 November 2012|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> The mini-series, created and written by the director in partnership with Paulo Lins, counted on the collaboration of Adrian Teijido (Photography), Luciana Buarque (Costumes), Marcio Hashimoto (Editing) and Sergio Pasqualino (Colorist). It also marked the start of another research cycle, in which the director focused on realist aesthetics, which influenced the language as a whole, but mainly in the choice of non-actors for the main parts. The nearly 40 actors launched in the mini-series include artists of the groups N\u00f3s do Morro and [[:pt:Afroreggae|Afroreggae]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2012/12/critica-naturalidade-e-ausencia-de-pose-o-mundo-de-suburbia.html|title=Naturalidade e aus\u00eancia de pose: o mundo de 'Suburbia'|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=3 December 2012|access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> \u00c9rika Januza, until then secretary of a school in the interior of Minas Gerais state, was chosen to play the main character of the story. Guest appearance by Fabr\u00edcio Boliveira, Rosa Marya Colin, Haroldo Costa, Maria Salvadora, Paulo Tiefenthaler and Dani Ornellas, among others. In 2012, the Globo network took the series up again for a second season in 2013 due to its satisfactory audience ratings. Later, however, the director Luiz Fernando Carvalho chose to cancel the new season. In the opinion of anthropologist Luiz Eduardo Soares, the work was a \"reconstructive reading of the carioca society, producing a superb result \".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/luiz-eduardo-soares-escreve-sobre-intensidade-da-forma-em-suburbia-6733970|title=Luiz Eduardo Soares escreve sobre a intensidade da forma em 'Suburbia'|author=Luiz Eduardo Soares|publisher=O Globo|date=15 November 2011|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Ladie\u2019s Mail (Correio Feminino)''===\n{{Main|:pt:Correio Feminino}}\nA mini-series in eight episodes, created and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho based on women's journals written by [[Clarice Lispector]] in the 1950s and 1960s, under the pseudonym Helen Palmer. The visual language and narrative were based on 60s pop art and design,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/quero-um-novo-ciclo-na-tv-diz-luiz-fernando-carvalho-10375021|title='Quero um novo ciclo na TV', diz Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=O Globo|date=16 October 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> from the costumes to the lighting and set; all filmed in a single light box, which changed color according to the subjects addressed. Adapted by Maria Camargo, the series was shown in 2013 as part of the program Fant\u00e1stico,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/luiz-fernando-carvalho-dirige-serie-correio-feminino-estreia-deste-domingo-do-fantastico-10543381|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho dirige s\u00e9rie Correio Feminino, estreia deste domingo do Fant\u00e1stico|author=Zean Bravo|publisher=O Globo|date=27 October 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> with costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie and Luciana Buarque, photography by Mikeas and edited by Marcio Hashimoto. The actress [[Maria Fernanda C\u00e2ndido]] played Helen Palmer narrating all the episodes. In the cast, [[Luiza Brunet]] interpreted the mature woman, and [[:pt:Alessandra Maestrini|Alessandra Maestrini]], the young woman. The adolescent is [[Cintia Dicker]], an international model whose acting career was launched in the mini-series. In the opinion of critic Patricia Kogut, the series is \"inspired, pleasant, in good taste and unpretentious, like Clarice's texts as Helen Palmer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2013/11/correio-feminino-faz-leitura-inspirada-de-clarice-lispector.html|title='Correio feminino' faz leitura inspirada de Clarice Lispector|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=5 November 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Alexandre and Other Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)}}\nA 2013 telefilm, with script by Luis Alberto de Abreu and Luiz Fernando Carvalho<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/prosa/post/a-consciencia-dos-sonhos-por-luiz-fernando-carvalho-518115.html|title=A consci\u00eancia dos sonhos - Diretor de 'Alexandre e outros her\u00f3is', especial de TV baseado nas hist\u00f3rias infantojuvenis de Graciliano Ramos, examina dimens\u00f5es m\u00edtica, ut\u00f3pica e humana na obra do alagoano|author=Luiz Fernando Carvalho|publisher=OGlobo|date=14 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> based on two stories by the Alagoan writer [[Graciliano Ramos]]. Luiz Fernando Carvalho's coaching and directing of the actors revealed a new code of interpretation to [[Marcelo Serrado]] and [[Ney Latorraca]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://atarde.uol.com.br/cultura/televisao/noticias/1555977-ney-latorraca-e-destaque-em-alexandre-e-outros-herois|title=Ney Latorraca \u00e9 destaque em 'Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is'|date=16 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=A Tarde|author=Roberta Pennafort}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/2013/12/1383371-ney-latorraca-renasce-em-especial-na-tv-alexandre-e-outros-herois.shtml|title=Ney Latorraca renasce em especial na TV 'Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is'|author=Gislaine Gutierre|publisher=Folha Online|date=10 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Ele (Luiz Fernando Carvalho) me tirou totalmente da zona de conforto}}</ref> as well as a harmony in the quality of the interpretations. Direction of photography by Mickeas, art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez and costumes by Luciana Buarque. Incidental sound track by Tim Rescala. Opening theme by the Pernambucan Siba. The cast of the TV special, a finalist in the 2014 [[International Emmy Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/finalista-do-emmy-internacional-alexandre-outros-herois-pode-ter-mais-episodios-em-2015-14233742|title=Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is \u00e9 finalista do Emmy Internacional|date=14 October 2014|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=Revista da TV|author=Nilton Carauta}}</ref> also included Fl\u00e1vio Bauraqui, Fl\u00e1vio Rocha, Marc\u00e9lia Cartaxo and Luci Pereira.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/opiniao/direcao-seca-faz-a-qualidade-tecnica-de-alexandre-e-outros-herois-1577#ixzz4dl00ba3T|title=Dire\u00e7\u00e3o 'seca' faz a qualidade t\u00e9cnica de Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is|date=19 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV|author=Raphael Scire}}</ref> Critic Patricia Kogut considered the telefilm a miniature work of art on television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2013/12/alexandre-e-outros-herois-uma-pequena-obra-prima-na-globo.html|title='Alexandre e outros her\u00f3is': uma pequena obra-prima na Globo|date=20 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=O Globo|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|quote=Trata-se de uma viagem horizontal pela cultura popular, sem o olhar estrangeiro, ou a entroniza\u00e7\u00e3o daquilo que \u00e9 simples. Essa \u00e9 uma das maiores virtudes do programa adaptado por Lu\u00eds Alberto de Abreu e com a clar\u00edssima assinatura de Luiz Fernando Carvalho. N\u00e3o vimos a alta cultura caindo na tenta\u00e7\u00e3o popularizante e sim uma produ\u00e7\u00e3o abertamente popular e ao mesmo tempo elegante e requintada, com ambi\u00e7\u00e3o art\u00edstica e dona de um universo est\u00e9tico pr\u00f3prio, original}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2013/12/25/luiz-fernando-carvalho-lembra-que-ha-lugar-para-graciliano-ramos-na-tv/|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho lembra que h\u00e1 lugar para Graciliano Ramos na TV|author=Mauricio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=25 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)'' ===\n{{Main|Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o}}\nThis 2014 production marked the director's return to the telenovela format after 12 years of dedicating himself to mini-series and more authorial projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/serafina/2014/04/1445086-luiz-fernando-carvalho-critica-novelas-tradicionais-e-cruza-conto-de-fadas-e-hq.shtml|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho critica novelas tradicionais e cruza conto de fadas e HQ|author=Sylvia Colombo|publisher=Serafina|date=27 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://televisao.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/07/31/e-preciso-renovar-mais-e-copiar-menos-diz-diretor-de-meu-pedacinho.htm|title=\u00c9 preciso renovar mais e copiar menos, diz diretor de Meu Pedacinho|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' was written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, with art production by Marco Cortez, art work by Raimundo Rodriguez and costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie. The critics praised various aspects, from the harmony of the quality of acting to the editing, direction, costumes, scenography and aesthetics, inspired by Westerns and Japanese manga (comics).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/entretenimento/noticia/2014/07/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-estetica-que-deu-certo-4564521.html|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o: A Est\u00e9tica que deu certo|author=Vanessa Scalei|publisher=Zero Hora|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2014/08/01/meu-pedacinho-do-chao-fugiu-do-obvio-surpreendeu-e-encantou/|title=Meu Pedacinho do Ch\u00e3o fugiu do \u00f3bvio e surpreendeu|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=1 August 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/opiniao/cinco-motivos-para-tornar-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-inesquecivel-4268|title=Cinco motivos para tornar Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o inesquec\u00edvel|author=Raphael Scire|publisher=UOL|date=30 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/05/linda-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-dissolve-duvidas-da-estreia.html|title='Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o' dissolve d\u00favidas na estreia|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=27 May 2014|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o \u00e9 uma das grandes produ\u00e7\u00f5es da nossa TV. Segue linda, artesanal dentro do poss\u00edvel e \u00e9 carregada principalmente por sua hist\u00f3ria. Dentro daquele ambiente on\u00edrico e l\u00edrico, h\u00e1 dramas e conflitos s\u00e9rios. Eles capturam a aten\u00e7\u00e3o do p\u00fablico com for\u00e7a. E a beleza dos cen\u00e1rios e figurinos n\u00e3o dissimula nem diminui esses recados}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,meu-pedacinho-de-chao-nao-se-acomoda-e-faz-nevar-no-rio,1531589|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o n\u00e3o se acomoda e faz nevar no Rio|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=21 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Luiz Fernando Carvalho's direction of the actors revealed a new code of interpretation, noted by the critics, to actors such as [[Juliana Paes]] and [[Rodrigo Lombardi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/04/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-estreia-com-marca-do-diretor.html|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o estreia com marca do diretor|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o estreia com marca do diretor (...) Juliana Paes, madura, exuberante, respondeu bem \u00e0 m\u00e3o forte da dire\u00e7\u00e3o. Mostrou que avan\u00e7ou um passo na sua trajet\u00f3ria de atriz}}</ref> The team's creative process and cast coaching to shape the aesthetics of ''My Little Plot of Land'' took place at TVLi\u00ea, known as Galp\u00e3o, which operated from 2013 to 2017. The space brought together all the creative teams and was conceived by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, at Projac, for collaborative project creation and talent training. In addition to ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'', the works ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Female Messages (Correio Feminino)]]'', ''[[:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)|Alexander and Other Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)]]'', ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|The Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' were created in the Galp\u00e3o. The whole process of creation and production of the novela in the Galp\u00e3o is described by the journalist Melina Dalboni in the book ''Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o'', which has drawings, sketches and photos by the director and the team (published by Casa da Palavra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2015/02/13/livro-prolonga-a-experiencia-dos-fas-de-meu-pedacinho-de-chao/|title=Livro prolonga experi\u00eancia dos f\u00e3s do Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=13 February 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Sets and costumes were envisaged through the playful eye of childhood,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/conheca-detalhes-da-criacao-de-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-trama-com-universo-onirico-ar-de-fabula-12586431|title=Conhe\u00e7a detalhes da cria\u00e7\u00e3o de 'Meu pedacinho de ch\u00e3o', trama com universo on\u00edrico e ar de f\u00e1bula|author=Nat\u00e1lia Castro|publisher=Revista da TV|date=26 June 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> and according to the columnist Patr\u00edcia Kogut, contributed to a beautiful invented universe, far different from what we are used to seeing on TV.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/07/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-deixara-sua-marca-na-historia-da-televisao.html|title=Cr\u00edtica: Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o deixar\u00e1 sua marca na hist\u00f3ria da TV|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The houses were faced with recycled cans, based on the work of artist Raimundo Rodriguez. The costumes, the subject of an exhibition, mixed technological fabrics and plastic material.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2014/12/exposicao-exibe-figurino-da-novela-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-no-rio.html|title=Exposi\u00e7\u00e3o exibe figurinos de Meu Pedacinho do Ch\u00e3o|publisher=G1|date=27 December 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Cesar Coelho, of the Anima Mundi Festival, used stop-motion and time-lapse techniques for all the animation. The novela received the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Award for Best Actor ([[Irandhir Santos]]); Contigo Magazine Award for Best Child Actor (Tom\u00e1s Sampaio) and Best Director; the Extra television award  for Best Costumes and Best Makeup (Rubens Lib\u00f3rio); and the Quem Magazine award for Best Actor ([[Irandhir Santos]]), Best Supporting Actor (Johnny Massaro) and Best Author ([[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]]). The critic Cristina Padiglione regards the novela as worthy of a standing ovation, and in the opinion of Alexandra Moraes \"the images, at first sight childish, gain relevance with colors and effects of dramatic intent. Good performances and the firm hand of the director give the plot meaning\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/cristina-padiglione/isso-nao-e-um-pedacinho-de-chao-e-um-latifundio/|title=Isso n\u00e3o \u00e9 um 'pedacinho' de ch\u00e3o, \u00e9 um latif\u00fandio|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2014/04/1437903-critica-cores-e-filtros-reforcam-trama-em-meu-pedacinho-de-chao.shtml|title=Cr\u00edtica: Cores e filtros refor\u00e7am trama em 'Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o'|author=Alexandra Moraes|publisher=Ilustrada - Folha de S.Paulo|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Old River (Velho Chico)'' ===\n{{Main|Velho Chico (telenovela)}}\nIn 2016, ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' marked Luiz Fernando Carvalho's return to prime time,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/09/velho-chico-folhetim-classico-mas-com-muita-renovacao.html|title='Velho Chico': folhetim cl\u00e1ssico, mas com muita renova\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u201cVelho Chico, como outras obras de Carvalho, provou que a ind\u00fastria cultural da televis\u00e3o tamb\u00e9m pode ter ares de artesanato. N\u00e3o \u00e9 pouco\"}}</ref> directing the novela written by [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and Bruno Luperi, which again carried the imprint of the new esthetic in TV drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omelete.uol.com.br/series-tv/entrevista/velho-chico-stanley-kubrick-da-tv-brasileira-diretor-luiz-fernando-carvalho-fala-sobre-a-novela/|title=\"Stanley Kubrick da TV brasileira\", diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho fala sobre a novela|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=14 March 2016|publisher=Omelete.com.br|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2016/01/1734731-a-maior-funcao-da-televisao-e-criar-cidadaos-diz-luiz-fernando-carvalho.shtml|title='A maior fun\u00e7\u00e3o da televis\u00e3o \u00e9 criar cidad\u00e3os', diz Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=L\u00edgia Mesquita|date=31 January 2016|publisher=Ilustrada|work=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=24 February 2016}}</ref> The novela was divided into two phases,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/06/velho-chico-tem-cenas-para-amarrar-o-presente-ao-passado.html |title='Velho Chico' tem cenas para amarrar o presente e o passado|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|date=15 June 2016|publisher=O Globo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> with direction of photography by Alexandre Fructuoso and costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie. Highlights were the photography<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,diretor-luiz-fernando-carvalho-fala-sobre-a-fotografia-peculiar-da-novela-velho-chico,10000064739|title=Diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho fala sobre a fotografia peculiar da novela 'Velho Chico'|author=Luis Carlos Merten|date=25 July 2016|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho e a fotografia viscontiana da novela \u2018Velho Chico\u2019}}</ref> and acclaimed performances by the actors [[Antonio Fagundes]], Lucy Alves, [[Domingos Montagner]], Lee Taylor, [[Marcos Palmeira]], [[Chico Diaz]], Renato G\u00f3es, [[Rodrigo Lombardi]], [[Dira Paes]], [[Irandhir Santos]], [[Fabiula Nascimento]], Julia Dalavia, Cyria Coentro, Barbara Reis, Julio Machado, Umberto Magnani, [[Camila Pitanga]], [[Christiane Torloni]], [[Marcelo Serrado]], Gabriel Leone, Giulia Buscaccio, Mariene de Castro, G\u00e9sio Amadeu, Jos\u00e9 Dumont, Marc\u00e9lia Cartaxo and others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/coluna/noticia/2016/12/quem-fez-festa-dos-telespectadores-em-2016.html|title=Quem fez a festa dos telespectadores em 2016|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=29 December 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u201cVelho Chico trouxe um vento novo para a faixa das 21h (...) Entre os destaques desse elenco estiveram novatos e veteranos, numa mistura de atores que encantou o p\u00fablico. Domingos Montagner, tragicamente morto perto da loca\u00e7\u00e3o, impressionou mais uma vez, como o Santo. Marcos Palmeira esteve no melhor papel da sua carreira. Antonio Fagundes, depois de ajustes no personagem, fez um coronel grandioso. Chico Diaz, Lucy Alves, Fabiula Nascimento, Zezita Matos, Christiane Torloni, Julia Dalavia, Renato G\u00f3es e tantos outros brilharam\"}}</ref> The cast was of a uniformity rarely seen in novelas, resulting in countless awards for its actors, including the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Award for Best Actress for Selma Egrei and the Critics' Choice Award for [[Domingos Montagner]](posthumous) and the production also won Best Supporting Actress (Selma Egrei), Best Supporting Actor (Irandhir Santos), Best Breakthrough Actress (Lucy Alves) and Best Breakthrough Actor (Lee Taylor),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/velho-chico-justica-selma-egrei-e-marco-ricca-sao-premiados-na-apc|title='Velho Chico', 'Justi\u00e7a', Selma Egrei e Marco Ricca s\u00e3o premiados na APCA|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Telepadi|date=30 November 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2016/11/1837325-aquarius-velho-chico-rita-lee-e-montagner-levam-premios-da-apca.shtml|title='Aquarius', 'Velho Chico', Rita Lee e Montagner levam pr\u00eamios da APCA|publisher=Folha Online|date=30 November 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> with Veja Rio's Carioca of the Year Award going to Luiz Fernando Carvalho for the renovated aesthetic of prime time television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vejario.abril.com.br/cidades/luiz-fernando-carvalho-cria-uma-nova-estetica-para-o-horario-nobre/|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho cria uma nova est\u00e9tica para o hor\u00e1rio nobre|author=Sofia Cerqueira |publisher=Veja Rio|date=10 December 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The team's creative process and cast coaching lasted only three months and took place at TVli\u00ea, Luiz Fernando Carvalho's collaborative creative space, which operated at Projac between 2013 and 2017 and was known as Galp\u00e3o.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amarello.com.br/artigo/amarello-visita-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Amarello Visita: Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Tom\u00e1s Biagi Carvalho|publisher=Amarello|access-date=14 April 2017|quote=Para preparar os atores de seus projetos, construiu um galp\u00e3o: uma mistura de circo com escola de samba, mambembe, feito de material reciclado e resto de cen\u00e1rio; uma c\u00e9lula criativa dentro dos Est\u00fadios Globo.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/serafina/2016/03/1743767-atores-de-velho-chico-nova-novela-da-globo-fazem-experiencias-em-galpao.shtml|title=Atores de 'Velho Chico' fazem experi\u00eancias em galp\u00e3o|author=L\u00edgia Mesquita |publisher=Serafina|date=28 February 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Os personagens de todo o elenco da saga familiar escrita por Benedito Ruy Barbosa eram gestados em um espa\u00e7o coletivo de experimenta\u00e7\u00e3o idealizado pelo diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/03/lindo-capitulo-marca-volta-do-brasil-rural-21h.html|title=Lindo cap\u00edtulo marca a volta do Brasil rural \u00e0 TV|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=16 March 2016|quote=\"A estreia de ''Velho Chico'' teve mesmo o selo autoral do seu diretor, Luiz Fernando Carvalho.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/03/velho-chico-e-o-brasil-real-e-o-da-fantasia.html|title=Velho Chico e o Brasil real e o da fantasia|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=18 March 2016|quote=\"''Velho Chico'', de alguma forma, trouxe a f\u00e1bula de volta ao hor\u00e1rio nobre. (...) Mas a realiza\u00e7\u00e3o de Luiz Fernando Carvalho faz sonhar. E a hist\u00f3ria de Benedito Ruy Barbosa tem muitas chances de agradar com essa mistura de realidade \u00e1rida com estetiza\u00e7\u00e3o.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> The first phase, applauded by the critics, marked the return of actor [[Rodrigo Santoro]] to the Globo fold<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/rodrigo-santoro-volta-as-novelas-da-globo-17902522|title=Rodrigo Santoro volta \u00e0s novelas|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=28 October 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>  and revealed the hitherto undiscovered talent of [[Carol Castro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/novelas/sensacao-de-velho-chico-carol-castro-teve-de-fazer-teste-chorando-10725 |title=Sensa\u00e7\u00e3o de Velho Chico, Carol Castro teve de fazer teste chorando|author=Marcia Pereira|date=16 March 2016|publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> [[Tarc\u00edsio Meira]], in just two episodes, put in an impressive performance, as did actress Selma Egrei, who took part in both phases of the novela.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.correio24horas.com.br/single-entretenimento/noticia/selma-egrei-se-destaca-em-velho-chico-com-a-sofrida-e-poderosa-encarnacao/?cHash=87ff234ae84127b9c7650a9a82598eae|title=Selma Egrei se destaca em 'Velho Chico' com a sofrida e poderosa Encarna\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Roberto Midlej |publisher=Correio Popular|date=7 August 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The cast was selected after an extensive  search for actors from the Northeast and marked the debut in novelas of Lucy Alves, Renato G\u00f3es, Marina Nery, Barbara Reis, Diyo Coelho, Xangai, Veronica Cavalcanti, Lee Taylor, Zezita de Matos, Mariene de Castro, Yara Charry, Raiza Alc\u00e2ntara, Lucas Veloso, Sueli Bispo and the comedian Bator\u00e9.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/velho-chico-tera-60-do-elenco-composto-por-atores-nordestinos-18716574|title=Velho Chico' ter\u00e1 60% do elenco composto por atores nordestinos|author=Zean Bravo |publisher=Revista da TV|date=28 February 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,diretor-procura-atores-por-todo-o-pais-para-novela-das-9,1777455|title=Diretor procura atores por todo o pa\u00eds para a novela das 9|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The last chapters of the novela pay tribute to the actor [[Domingos Montagner]] (Santo), who drowned in the S\u00e3o Francisco river two weeks before the end of the serial. The character was maintained in the plot even after the actor's death through the language created by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, in which a single subjective camera interpreted Santo's viewpoint, so his presence was felt, engaging with all the other characters, to the end.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/camera-subjetiva-solucao-de-velho-chico-para-santo-e-linda/ |title=C\u00e2mera subjetiva: solu\u00e7\u00e3o de 'Velho Chico' para Santo \u00e9 linda|author=Marcia Carolina Maia|date=27 September 2016|publisher=Veja|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2016/09/30/obrigado-velho-chico/|title=Cr\u00edtica: Obrigado, \"Velho Chico\"|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=30 September 2016|publisher=UOL|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/09/presenca-incorporea-de-domingos-montagner-em-velho-chico.html|title=A Presen\u00e7a incorp\u00f3rea de Domingos Montagner em Velho Chico|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=28 September 2016|quote=\"Nem dubl\u00ea, nem truques rasteiros. V\u00edtima de uma trag\u00e9dia que entristeceu o Brasil \u2014 e mais ainda a equipe de ''Velho Chico'' \u2014, Domingos Montagner estava na novela anteontem. Luiz Fernando Carvalho recorreu a uma c\u00e2mera subjetiva para trazer a presen\u00e7a incorp\u00f3rea do ator a quase todas as sequ\u00eancias. Era, claro, um recurso t\u00e9cnico. Por\u00e9m, qualquer car\u00e1ter racional foi plenamente absorvido pela dramaturgia e dissolvido pela emo\u00e7\u00e3o vis\u00edvel que dominou o elenco e alcan\u00e7ou o p\u00fablico. (...) Carvalho chegou perto de fronteiras perigosas e acertou muito mesmo.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> The novela came under strong pressure from the Globo network's drama department, calling for modifications to the text, storyline and esthetics. The director and the author, [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]], stood firm and refused to make the changes to ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]''. The in-house crisis made the TV columns and was described as a form of public pressure on Luiz Fernando Carvalho. According to the critic Maur\u00edcio Stycer, ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' is a landmark in the recent history of Brazilian TV, on account of its esthetic ambition and cultural relevance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/mauriciostycer/2016/10/1818880-velho-chico-marcou-pela-ambicao-estetica-e-a-relevancia-cultural.shtml |title='Velho Chico' marcou pela ambi\u00e7\u00e3o est\u00e9tica e a relev\u00e2ncia cultural|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=1 October 2016|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to Nilson Xavier, the novela \u201chad incontestable technical and artistic quality, from the direction to the photography, sound track and the actors\u2019 performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nilsonxavier.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2016/09/30/o-maior-merito-de-velho-chico-foi-provocar-e-estimular-o-publico/|title=O maior m\u00e9rito de Velho Chico foi provocar e estimular o p\u00fablico|author=Nilson Xavier|publisher=UOL|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u00c9 de Boni (Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio de Oliveira Sobrinho) a frase: \u201cA televis\u00e3o deve andar sempre um passo \u00e0 frente do p\u00fablico.\u201d \u201cVelho Chico\u201d foi um bom exemplo\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/telinha/critica-sobre-fim-de-velho-chico-tintas-fortes-do-inicio-ao-fim-20212649.html|title=Cr\u00edtica de Velho Chico: tintas fortes do in\u00edcio ao fim|author=Carla Bittencourt|publisher=Extra|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\"Velho Chico\u201d sempre foi uma novela de atua\u00e7\u00f5es e cenas memor\u00e1veis (...). Tudo muito denso, pintado com tintas mais fortes do que o telespectador est\u00e1 acostumado a ver nesse hor\u00e1rio. Essas caracter\u00edsticas garantiram \u00e0 trama seu lugar na hist\u00f3ria da teledramaturgia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2016/09/final-de-velho-chico-emociona-com-brilhante-atuacao-de-antonio-fagundes|title=Final de Velho Chico emociona com brilhante atua\u00e7\u00e3o de Antonio Fagundes|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio de Televis\u00e3o|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noblat.oglobo.globo.com/cronicas/noticia/2016/05/miss-bumbum.html|title=Noveleiro|publisher=O Globo|author=Luis Fernando Verissimo|date=1 May 2016|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=\"Eu j\u00e1 tentava ver tudo o que Luiz Fernando Carvalho fazia, e n\u00e3o apenas por solidariedade de xar\u00e1. O que ele est\u00e1 fazendo no ''Velho Chico'' ultrapassa tudo o que j\u00e1 fez na TV - com a poss\u00edvel exce\u00e7\u00e3o de ''Os Maias''. Ele \u00e9 incapaz de um enquadramento que n\u00e3o seja perfeito, e teve tamb\u00e9m o talento de escolher um elenco perfeito.\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201032703/http://noblat.oglobo.globo.com/cronicas/noticia/2016/05/miss-bumbum.html|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> It competed for the [[International Emmy Award for Best Telenovela]] of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://upload.iemmys.tv/public/iemmys/Nominees.aspx?nc=I|title=Nominees Categories|publisher=Iemmys.tv|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/kenneth-branagh-anna-friel-international-emmy-nominations-1202574242/|title=Kenneth Branagh, Anna Friel Receive International Emmy Nominations|publisher=Variety|author=Stewart Clarke|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4854403/emmy-nominations-2017/|title=Here Are the 2017 Emmy Nominations|publisher=Time|author=Kate Samuelson |date=13 July 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/velho-chico-justica-concorrem-ao-emmy-internacional-21876053|title=Velho Chico e Justi\u00e7a concorrem ao Emmy Internacional|publisher=Revista da TV,O Globo|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gshow.globo.com/programas/video-show/noticia/justica-ta-no-ar-velho-chico-totalmente-demais-e-alemao-concorrem-ao-emmy-internacional.ghtml|title=Justi\u00e7a, T\u00e1 no ar, Velho Chico, Totalmente Demais e Alem\u00e3o concorrem ao Emmy Internacional|publisher=GShow|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/a-contradicao-de-velho-chico-novela-e-finalista-ao-emmy-mas-nao-cabe-no-catalogo-de-vendas-internacionais/|title=A contradi\u00e7\u00e3o de Velho Chico: novela \u00e9 finalista ao Emmy mas n\u00e3o cabe no cat\u00e1logo de vendas internacionais|publisher=Telepadi|date=27 September 2017|quote=\u00c9 quase uma contradi\u00e7\u00e3o que o enredo n\u00e3o tenha apelo internacional e que, inscrito no Emmy Internacional, na categoria de novelas, esteja entre os cinco finalistas|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/coluna/noticia/2017/11/rodrigo-santoro-participara-do-emmy-com-equipe-de-velho-chico.html|title=Rodrigo Santoro participar\u00e1 do Emmy com equipe do Velho Chico|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=14 November 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, convidado pela Globo, n\u00e3o poder\u00e1 ir: est\u00e1 filmando em S\u00e3o Paulo|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Lavoura Arcaica, 15 years on'' ===\nTribute was paid to the film ''[[To the Left of the Father]]'' in 2017, 15 years after it was made and on account of it being hailed as one of the most important Brazilian films of all time, at the [[Rio International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/lavoura-arcaica-renasce-15-anos-apos-sua-estreia-no-festival-do-rio/|title='Lavoura Arcaica' renasce, 15 anos ap\u00f3s sua estreia, no Festival do Rio|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=23 September 2016|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Um monumento cinematogr\u00e1fico de nossa Retomada}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/gente-boa/post/barulhinho-bom-exibicao-de-lavoura-arcaica-em-pelicula-faz-felicidade-dos-nostalgicos-no-festival-do-rio.html|title=Exibi\u00e7\u00e3o de Lavoura Arcaica em pel\u00edcula faz a felicidade dos nost\u00e1lgicos no Festival do Rio |author=Cleo Guimaraes|date=15 October 2016|publisher=Gente Boa - OGlobo|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Para Selton Mello, que interpreta o protagonista Andr\u00e9, \"Foi uma aventura emocional radical, que me tirou o ch\u00e3o e me fez renascer. Esse filme me deu coragem e a verdadeira dimens\u00e3o da minha profiss\u00e3o\u201d}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,lavoura-arcaica-e-homenageado-no-festival-do-rio,10000081767|title='Lavoura Arcaica' \u00e9 homenageado no Festival do Rio |author=Luis Carlos Merten|date=12 October 2016|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> and the [[S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/lavoura-arcaica-com-presenca-de-radouan-nassar-poe-fim-a-mostra/|title='Lavoura Arcaica', com presen\u00e7a de Raduan Nassar, p\u00f5e fim \u00e0 Mostra|date=10 November 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|author=Luiz Zanin}}</ref> where a 35&nbsp;mm copy was shown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://revistacult.uol.com.br/home/lavoura-arcaica-e-a-utopia-por-um-mundo-melhor/|title=Lavoura Arcaica e a utopia por um mundo melhor|author=Eric Campi e Paulo Henrique Pompermaier|publisher=Revista Cult|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/lavoura-arcaica-15-anos-depois-dc69559029f7#.8409ildh4|title=Lavoura Arcaica, 15 anos depois|date=13 October 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo!|author=Almir de Freitas}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/lavoura-arcaica-completa-15-anos-e-segue-arrebatador/|title='Lavoura Arcaica' completa 15 anos\u2026 e segue arrebatador|date=26 June 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|author=Rodrigo Fonseca}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/filmes/quinze-anos-apos-estreia-lavoura-arcaica-dialoga-com-discussoes-atuais-20291697|title=Quinze anos ap\u00f3s a estreia, Lavoura Arcaica dialoga com discuss\u00f5es atuais |author=Suzana Velasco|date=15 October 2016|publisher=OGlobo|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> As part of the tribute at the [[Rio International Film Festival]], artist Raimundo Rodriguez created an installation that went on show for a month at the Esta\u00e7\u00e3o Net Botafogo, with memorabilia from the film, reviews and the director's notebooks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.poltronapop.com.br/2016/10/festival-do-rio-2016-lavoura-arcaica.html|title=\"Lavoura Arcaica\" ganha exibi\u00e7\u00e3o e instala\u00e7\u00e3o de Raimundo Rodriguez|date=23 September 2016|publisher=PoltronaPop|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> For Ismail Xavier and Ilana Feldman, Lavoura was born in 2001, emerging as a foreign body in the scenario of early 21st century Brazilian film, marked by its realism and its direct confrontation with Brazilian social and urban issues.<ref name=\"Ismail\"/>\n\n=== ''Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)'' ===\n{{Main|Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)}}\nScreened in 2017, the mini-series written by Maria Camargo based on the homonymous novel by [[Milton Hatoum]] was regarded by critics as another quality contribution to Brazilian television on account of the poetic style applied by the director to the adaptation of the novel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://literasutra.com/2017/03/13/duas-adaptacoes-para-dois-irmaos-entrevista-com-milton-hatoum/|title=Duas adapta\u00e7\u00f5es para Dois Irm\u00e3os: Entrevista com Milton Hatoum|publisher=Literasutra|author=Monalisa Marques|date=13 March 2017|access-date=20 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421001906/https://literasutra.com/2017/03/13/duas-adaptacoes-para-dois-irmaos-entrevista-com-milton-hatoum/|archive-date=21 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2017/01/dois-irmaos-faz-o-ano-comecar-muito-bem.html|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" \u00e9 um trabalho para ser louvado, uma grande contribui\u00e7\u00e3o de Carvalho para a televis\u00e3o brasileira|date=8 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=O Globo|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://operamundi.uol.com.br/conteudo/samuel/46161/em+adaptacao+de+dois+irmaos+para+tv+luiz+fernando+carvalho+transforma+prosa+de+milton+hatoum+em+poesia.shtml|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho conseguiu transformar a prosa de Hatoum em poesia|author=Vera Ceccarello |date=12 January 2017|publisher=OperaMundi|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffpostbrasil.com/edianez-parente/a-teatralidade-que-faz-de-dois-irmaos-uma-obra-prima-da-televi_a_21698413/|title=A teatralidade que faz de 'Dois Irm\u00e3os' uma obra prima da televis\u00e3o|author=Edianez Parente|date=13 January 2017|publisher=The Huffington Post|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/dois-irmaos-e-a-versao-amazonica-de-caim-e-abel/|title='Dois Irm\u00e3os' \u00e9 a vers\u00e3o amaz\u00f4nica de Caim e Abel|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=13 January 2017|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Pontuada por frases quase filos\u00f3ficas sobre a fala por vezes gaga do Tempo (outro muso de Carvalho), a vers\u00e3o de Maria Camargo para o romance de Hatoum deixa transbordante para o olhar quase teol\u00f3gico do aclamado diretor uma dimens\u00e3o b\u00edblica de fraternidade em f\u00faria, cindida na ponta da faca do ressentimento}}</ref> Direction of photography by Alexandre Fructuoso, costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie, scenography by Danielly Ramos, Juliana Carneiro and Mariana Villas-B\u00f4as, art production by Marco Cortez and Myriam Mendes. The production is part of the Quandrante Project and gained kudos with writer [[Milton Hatoum]]'s television debut.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://observador.pt/especiais/milton-hatoum-o-brasil-e-o-romance-da-desilusao/|title=Milton Hatoum: \"O Brasil \u00e9 o romance da desilus\u00e3o\"|author=Rita Cipriano |date=4 November 2017|publisher=Observador|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=Milton Hatoum: \"O Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u00e9 um dos grandes diretores brasileiros. Dirigiu a adapta\u00e7\u00e3o de Lavoura Arcaica, do Raduan Nassar, e novelas importantes. A linguagem dele \u00e9 muito inovadora. N\u00e3o \u00e9 aquele pastel\u00e3o, aquele soap opera previs\u00edvel. Ele trabalha com uma linguagem muito criativa e pensa em tudo \u2014 nos figurinos, na luz, em cada detalhe. \u00c9 impressionante.\"}}</ref> According to the publishing house [[Companhia das Letras]], the book sales increased by some 500% after the start of the mini-series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gente.ig.com.br/tvenovela/2017-01-18/minisserie-dois-irmaos.html|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\": miniss\u00e9rie aumenta vendas do livro em mais de 500%|date=18 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=iG}}</ref> Careers launched in Two Brothers include actors Matheus Abreu (Omar and Yaqub as an adolescent), the indigenous Zahy Guajajara (the \u00edndia Domingas) and the singer Bruna Caram (R\u00e2nia in the adult phase). The Lebanese actor [[Mounir Maasri]] made a guest appearance in the mini-series and was also responsible for the prosody (stress patterns) of the cast. The quality of the acting of the whole cast was stressed by the critics and also on social media and reached the worldwide and Brazilian Trending Topics throughout the series: [[Eliane Giardini]] and [[Juliana Paes]] as Zana; [[Antonio Fagundes]] and Antonio Calloni as Halim; and [[Cau\u00e3 Reymond]] and Matheus Abreu as the twins Omar and Yaqub. It was filmed in 2015, but at the request of the Globo network, the director agreed to make the novela ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' before he finished editing ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Dois Irm\u00e3os]]'', which was shown in January 2017. A number of innovative relevant points in the director's language were highlighted: the relation between literature and the transposition into images,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/a-linguagem-como-sonho-17e89674f18#.ue4tuyxkc|title=A Linguagem como Sonho|date=18 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo!|author=Almir de Freitas}}</ref> photography, framing, poetic language and sound track, which included hits from various decades to contextualize the period in which the mini-series was set. In addition, Luiz Fernando Carvalho inaugurated, on TV, the dialogue between the fictional scenes and images from the archives of Brazilian History, with the research of historical material done by Raquel Couto. \nAccording to the critic Maur\u00edcio Stycer, in an article published in the Folha de S.Paulo newspaper about Netflix's investment in Brazil, the miniseries was a startling revelation to those who normally only have access to terrestrial channels in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/mauriciostycer/2017/01/1852056-enquanto-netflix-avanca-na-conquista-do-mundo-globo-mostra-suas-armas.shtml|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" \u00e9 de uma qualidade espantosa para quem tem acesso apenas \u00e0 TV aberta no Brasil|date=21 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer}}</ref> For Luiz Zanin, the miniseries was about Brazil and the thwarted ideal of a multi-ethnic, sensual and carefree nation. \u201cAn elegant delicacy served up to the public, and which will leave it wanting more\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/o-som-e-a-furia-em-dois-irmaos/|title=O Som e a F\u00faria de Dois Irm\u00e3os|author=Luiz Zanin|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Uma hist\u00f3ria bem contada fala de si mesma e tamb\u00e9m de outras coisas. Esta nos falou do Brasil, de sua utopia frustrada de na\u00e7\u00e3o multi\u00e9tnica, sensual e feliz. Um fino biscoito oferecido ao p\u00fablico, e que vai deixar saudades}}</ref> Critic Carlos Alberto de Mattos wrote that what was seen in The Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os) \u201cwas not a realistic reflection, but an exuberant image, a mythical saga, a work of art\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carmattos.com/2017/01/09/arquetipos-e-epifanias-em-dois-irmaos/|title=Arqu\u00e9tipos e epifanias em Dois Irm\u00e3os|publisher=Rastros de Carmattos|author=Carlos Alberto Mattos|date=9 January 2017|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nilsonxavier.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2017/01/09/dois-irmaos-transmite-em-belas-imagens-um-crescente-clima-de-tragedia/|title='Dois Irm\u00e3os' transmite em belas imagens um crescente clima de trag\u00e9dia|author=Nilson Xavier|date=9 January 2017|publisher=UOL|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=(A miniss\u00e9rie) tem a assinatura de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, o que \u2013 j\u00e1 sabemos \u2013 significa esmero na est\u00e9tica, fotografia, tomadas, trilha sonora e dire\u00e7\u00e3o de atores.(...) Quem conhece a obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho sabe que cada produ\u00e7\u00e3o sua \u00e9 \u00fanica, mesmo dentro de seu estilo caracter\u00edstico de dire\u00e7\u00e3o}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://revistacaju.com.br/2017/01/13/a-lavoura-amazonense-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=A 'lavoura amazonense' de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Christiane Passafaro Guzzi|date=13 January 2017|publisher=Revista Caju|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=O que parece diferenciar Carvalho \u00e9 o estabelecimento de um estudo aprofundado da obra, da cr\u00edtica, da tradi\u00e7\u00e3o, e, principalmente, das reverbera\u00e7\u00f5es que a produ\u00e7\u00e3o dos escritores selecionados produzem no cen\u00e1rio ficcional}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/curioso-para-ver-dois-irmaos-ja-ha-3-episodios-no-globoplay-serie-vale-cada-minuto/|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" em duas palavras: n\u00e3o perca|date=6 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|author=Cristina Padiglione}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/dois-irmaos-tem-adaptacao-sensivel-e-poetica-na-globo/|title=Carvalho volta a exibir seu estilo teatral, sens\u00edvel e po\u00e9tico na adapta\u00e7\u00e3o|date=9 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Veja|author=Meire Kusumoto}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2017/01/intensa-e-inquietante-dois-irmaos-fisga-o-publico-a-critica-e-prova-que-nao-e-preciso-ritmo-frenetico-para-fazer-sucesso|title=Intensa e inquietante, Dois Irm\u00e3os fisga o p\u00fablico, a cr\u00edtica e prova que n\u00e3o \u00e9 preciso ritmo fren\u00e9tico para fazer sucesso|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio de Televis\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nexojornal.com.br/entrevista/2017/01/12/%E2%80%98Dois-irm%C3%A3os%E2%80%99-%C3%A9-sobre-o-colapso-de-uma-fam%C3%ADlia.-Mas-tamb%C3%A9m-de-um-projeto-de-pa%C3%ADs|title='Dois irm\u00e3os' \u00e9 sobre o colapso de uma fam\u00edlia. Mas tamb\u00e9m de um projeto de pa\u00eds|author=Juliana Domingos de Lima|date=12 January 2017|publisher=Nexo Jornal|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=\"A adapta\u00e7\u00e3o de \u201cDois irm\u00e3os\u201d, na verdade uma transposi\u00e7\u00e3o ou transcri\u00e7\u00e3o para o audiovisual, (...) oferece ao espectador brasileiro a possibilidade de alguns encontros fundamentais: encontro com cinquenta anos de hist\u00f3ria do pa\u00eds (...); com uma enorme diversidade humana e cultural (...); com uma forma expressiva que investe na sensibilidade e intelig\u00eancia do espectador (...); por fim, o encontro com um projeto de pa\u00eds, que se insinuava durante a Belle \u00c9poque amaz\u00f4nica, mas cuja promessa de futuro \u00e9 posta abaixo pela ditadura civil-militar e sua ideia destrutiva de \u201cprogresso\u201d. (...) \u00c9 importante perceber que, enquanto a literatura brasileira ganha relev\u00e2ncia e contund\u00eancia ao migrar para a TV, a pr\u00f3pria TV ganha tamb\u00e9m enorme prest\u00edgio art\u00edstico ao valorizar um produto liter\u00e1rio nacional, ainda mais sob a marca e o estilo barroco, marcado pelo ac\u00famulo de elementos e alta intensidade, do Luiz Fernando Carvalho\" (Ilana Feldman)}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, Luiz Fernando Carvalho left the Globo Network (Rede Globo) after 30 years of working for the TV station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/desgastes-de-bastidores-motivaram-fim-do-contrato-do-diretor-de-dois-irmaos-na-globo/|title=Um diretor fora da curva|date=24 February 2017|publisher=Telepadi|access-date=28 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valor.com.br/cultura/4911882/um-diretor-fora-da-curva|title=Um diretor fora da curva|author=Maria da Paz Trefaut|date=24 March 2017|publisher=Valor Econ\u00f4mico|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho construiu uma aura intelectual ao seu redor, uma imagem de profissional autoral que n\u00e3o se apega a conven\u00e7\u00f5es}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the director received the APCA Award for ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2017/12/1942551-apca-escolhe-os-melhores-de-2017.shtml|title=APCA escolhe os melhores de 2017|date=11 December 2017|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/juliana-paes-e-a-forca-do-querer-ganham-premio-da-associacao-paulista-de-criticos-de-artes-apca-veja-lista.ghtml|title=Juliana Paes e a For\u00e7a do Querer ganham pr\u00eamio da Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Artes (APCA); veja a lista|date=12 December 2017|publisher=G1|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref> the [[International Emmy Award for Best Telenovela]] Nomination for ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and the Bravo Award (Pr\u00eamio Bravo) for Artist of the Year, for his trajectory and esthetic renovation on television with ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' and the 15th anniversary of the film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''.\n\n== Personal life ==\nHe was married to the artist Sandra Burgos, with whom he has one son, Th\u00e9o Burgos Carvalho.\n\nHe was married to the actress [[Tereza Seiblitz]], with whom he has one son, Vitt\u00f3rio, born June 8, 2001.\n\nHe was married to the actress [[Let\u00edcia Persiles]], with whom he has one son, Ariel.\n\n== Bibliography ==\nThe following books written by Luiz Fernando Carvalho are references for this article. For the complete list of books about the director, see [[Luiz Fernando Carvalho Bibliography]]\n* {{cite book |first = Luiz Fernando |last = Carvalho | title = Sobre Lavour'Arcaica \u2013 O filme  | date = 2002  | publisher= Ateli\u00ea Editorial  | isbn = 9780815411833|url=https://books.google.com/?id=xNAed1GNO7QC&printsec=frontcover&dq=lavoura+arcaica#v=onepage&q=lavoura%20arcaica&f=false}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Abreu |first2=Luis Alberto |title=Hoje \u00e9 dia de Maria \u2013 Roteiros da 1a e 2a jornadas |publisher=Globo |date=2006 |isbn=9788525040985|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Qy8bAQAAIAAJ&q=Hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+Maria&dq=Hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+Maria}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho|title= Pedra do Reino - Estojo Ilustrado com 5 Cadernos de Filmagens + Di\u00e1rio de Elenco e Equipe |publisher=Globo |date=2007 |isbn=978-8525043375|url=http://www.saraiva.com.br/pedra-do-reino-estojo-ilustrado-com-5-cadernos-de-filmagens-diario-de-elenco-e-equipe-1968247.html}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho|title= O processo de Capitu |publisher= LeYa Casa da Palavra  |date=2008 |isbn=978-8577341023|url=https://books.google.com/?id=vaBaMQAACAAJ&dq=inauthor:%22Luiz+Fernando+Carvalho%22}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando|last=Carvalho |title= Livro - Quem \u00e9 Capitu?|publisher= Nova Fronteira |date=2008 |chapter=Capitu c\u2019est moi? |pages=17\u201320| isbn=9788520920831|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DuUdAQAAIAAJ&q=Quem+%C3%A9+Capitu?&dq=Quem+%C3%A9+Capitu?&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj0-9O0ktTTAhWJl5AKHcKSBIIQ6AEIJjAA}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Diniz |first2=Julio|title= Machado de Assis (1908-2008) |publisher= Contraponto |date=2008 |chapter=Capitu c\u2019est moi? |pages=80\u201383|isbn=978-85-7866-011-6|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Machado_de_Assis.html?id=cyyFPgAACAAJ&redir_esc=y}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Cuenca |first2=Jo\u00e3o Paulo |last3=Gianetti |first3=Cec\u00edlia |last4=Melamed |first4=Michel  |title= Afinal, o que querem as mulheres? |publisher= LeYa |date=2010 |isbn=9788580440300|url=https://books.google.com/?id=pwqCYgEACAAJ}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando |last2=Lins |first2=Paulo |last3=Franz |first3=Pedro |title=Suburbia |publisher=Aeroplano |date=2012 |isbn=9788578200916 |url=http://www.pedrofranz.com.br/suburbia |access-date=2017-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112022818/http://www.pedrofranz.com.br/suburbia |archive-date=2017-11-12 |url-status=dead }}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho |title= Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|publisher= LeYa Casa da Palavra |date=2013 |isbn=978-85-7734-525-0|url=https://books.google.com/?id=sHngjgEACAAJ}}\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Cinema\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''The Waiting (A Espera)'' \n| Director and Screenwriter\n| [[Short-film]] based on [[Roland Barthes]]\u00b4s Fragments d'un discours amoureux\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos|May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Ohos Sejam Atendidos)]]''\n| Director\n| [[Documentary film]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''\n|  Director and Screenwriter\n| [[Film]] based on the novel of [[Raduan Nassar]]\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+TV Series\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[:pt:Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas (miniss\u00e9rie)|Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]'' \n| Assistant director\n| Based on [[Guimar\u00e3es Rosa]]\u00b4s [[Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[:pt:Riacho Doce (miniss\u00e9rie)|Sweet River (Riacho Doce)]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|The Maias (Os Maias)]]''\n|  Director \n| Based on [[E\u00e7a de Queiroz]]\u00b4s [[Os Maias]]\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]], [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]] and [[Silvio Romero]]\u00b4s essay; Co-written with Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[:pt:Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria: Segunda Jornada|Today is Maria's Day: Second Journey (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria: Segunda Jornada)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]], [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]] and [[Silvio Romero]]\u00b4s essay; Co-written with Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[:pt:A Pedra do Reino|Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)]]''\n| Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel; Co-written with Braulio Tavares and Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Capitu]]''\n| Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[Machado de Assis]]\u00b4s [[Dom Casmurro]]\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[:pt:Afinal, o Que Querem as Mulheres?|After all, what does a woman want (Afinal, O Que Querem as Mulheres?)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Influenced by [[Sigmund Freud]]\u00b4s theory; Co-written with J.P. Cuenca and Michel Melamed\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[:pt:Sub\u00farbia|Suburbia]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Co-written with Paulo Lins\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Ladie's Mail (Correio Feminino)]]'' \n| Novelist e Diretor\n|  From [[Clarice Lispector]]\u00b4s chronicles\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on [[Milton Hatoum]]\u00b4s novel\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Soap Opera\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[:pt:Helena (1987)|Helena]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on the novel of [[Machado de Assis]]\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[:pt:Carmem (telenovela)|Carmen]]''\n|  Director\n| Written by [[Gl\u00f3ria Perez]]\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[:pt:Vida Nova|Vida Nova]]''\n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Tieta (telenovela)|Tieta]]''\n| Director\n| Based on the novel of [[Jorge Amado]]\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Pedra sobre Pedra|Stone on Stone (Pedra sobre Pedra)]]''\n| Director\n| Written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]]\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Renascer|Rebirth (Renascer)]]''\n| Director \n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[:pt:Irm\u00e3os Coragem (1995)|Irm\u00e3os Coragem]]''\n| Director\n| Remake of [[Janete Clair]]\u00b4s soap opera\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of Catlle (O Rei do Gado)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Esperan\u00e7a (telenovela)|Esperan\u00e7a]]'' \n| Director \n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa e Bruno Luperi\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Especiais para TV\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''Chit\u00e3ozinho e Xoror\u00f3 Especial'' \n| Director\n| Musical Show\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''The Cangaceiro's Revenge (Os Homens Querem Paz)'' \n| Director\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[:pt:Uma mulher vestida de sol|A Woman Clothed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)]]''\n|  Director\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)|The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)]]''\n|  Director\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)|Alexandre and Others Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)]]'' \n|  Diretor\n| Based on [[Graciliano Ramos]]\u00b4s short stories\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://luizfernandocarvalho.com/ Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Official website] {{in lang|pt}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0142461|name=Luiz Fernando Carvalho}}* \n* [http://40.mostra.org/en/filme/3902-TO-THE-LEFT-OF-THE-FATHER To The Left of The Father - Mostra de Cinema de SP]\n* [http://www.commeaucinema.com/critiques/a-la-gauche-du-pere,14209 A La Gauche du Pere - Comme au Cinema] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=46949.html A La Gauche du Pere - AlloCine] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://enciclopedia.itaucultural.org.br/pessoa466999/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Enciclopedia Ita\u00fa Cultural] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://topicos.estadao.com.br/noticias-sobre-luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Estad\u00e3o] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://www.atelie.com.br/publicacoes/autor/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Ateli\u00ea Editorial] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://40.mostra.org/br/diretores/3359-LUIZ-FERNANDO-CARVALHO Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Mostra de Cinema de SP] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.filmeb.com.br/quem-e-quem/diretor/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Filme B] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.adorocinema.com/personalidades/personalidade-78430/ Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Adoro Cinema] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.festivaldorio.com.br/br/filmes/lavoura-arcaica Lavoura Arcaica - Festival do Rio] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://twitter.com/luizfernandodir Luiz Fernando Carvalho] no [[Twitter]] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/LuizFernandoCarvalhoFanPage Luiz Fernando Carvalho] no [[Facebook]] {{in lang|pt}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carvalho, Luiz Fernando}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Rio de Janeiro (city)]]\n[[Category:Brazilian film directors]]\n", "name_user": "Bia2017", "label": "safe", "comment": "include reference", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho"}
{"title_page": "Bill Lee (Tennessee politician)", "text_new": "{{About|the Governor of Tennessee|other people named Bill Lee|William Lee (disambiguation){{!}}William Lee}}\n{{short description|50th Governor of Tennessee}}\n{{infobox officeholder\n| name = Bill Lee\n| image = Bill Lee 2020.jpg\n| order = 50th [[Governor of Tennessee]]\n| lieutenant = [[Randy McNally]]\n| term_start = January 19, 2019\n| term_end = \n| predecessor = [[Bill Haslam]]\n| successor = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1959|10|9}}\n| birth_place = [[Franklin, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| party = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| spouse = {{marriage|Carol Ann Lee|1984|2000|end=died}}<br>{{marriage|Maria Lee|2008}}\n| children = 4\n| residence = [[Tennessee Governor's Mansion|Governor's Mansion]]\n| education = [[Auburn University]] ([[Bachelor of Science|BS]])\n}}\n'''William Byron Lee''' (born October 9, 1959)<ref>[https://www.nga.org/governors/tennessee/ Gov. Bill Lee: Tennessee], [[National Governors Association]].</ref> is an American businessman and \"politician\" serving as the [[List of Governors of Tennessee|50th]] and current [[governor of Tennessee]].<ref name=\"EbertAllison\">Joel Ebert & Natalie Allison, [https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/01/19/bill-lee-tennessee-governor-inauguration/2585557002/ Bill Lee sworn in as Tennessee's 50th governor, nearly 2 years after long-shot bid], ''Tennessean'' (January 19, 2019).</ref> Elected in [[2018 Tennessee gubernatorial election|2018]], Lee campaigned as a business-oriented member of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.knoxnews.com/story/opinion/editorials/2018/10/25/bill-lee-tennessee-governor-erndorsement-knoxville-news-sentinel/1742616002/|title=Bill Lee has potential to be an inspiring Tennessee governor {{!}} Opinion|work=Knoxville News Sentinel|access-date=November 8, 2018|language=en}}</ref> Before entering politics he held various positions at the Lee Company, an inherited family business; he was the company's president and CEO from 1992 to 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nashvillepost.com/business/article/20489307/bill-lee-stepping-down-as-ceo-of-lee-co|title=Bill Lee stepping down as CEO of Lee Co.|newspaper=Nashville Post|date=February 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and career==\nLee was raised on his family's {{convert|1000|acre|adj=on}} cattle farm started by his grandparents in [[Franklin, Tennessee]], the Triple L Ranch; the family raises [[Hereford cattle]].<ref name=\"Jett\">Tyler Jett, [https://www.timesfreepress.com/news/local/story/2018/jul/06/bill-lee-says-he-wcalled-run-governor/474433/ Who is Bill Lee? Bill Lee says he was called to run for governor], ''Chattanooga Times Free Press'' (July 6, 2018).</ref><ref>http://www.lllranch.com/about.html ''About LLL Ranch'' (Retrieved September 16, 2019).</ref>\n\nAfter graduating from [[Franklin High School (Tennessee)|Franklin High School]] in his hometown,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.williamsonhomepage.com/spring_hill/franklin-businessman-bill-lee-raises-million-for-governors-race/article_d22e8c5e-209c-5fa0-bc23-bc3dc6cffb1b.html|title=Franklin businessman Bill Lee raises $1.3 million for governors race|website=Williamson Home Page}}</ref> Lee entered [[Auburn University]] in [[Auburn, Alabama]] in 1977 and graduated in 1981<ref name=\"Allison\">Nathan Allison, [https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/02/20/tn-gov-bill-lee-kappa-alpha-old-south-party-auburn/2904953002/ Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee says he regrets participating in 'Old South' parties at Auburn University], ''Tennessee'' (January 21, 2019).</ref> with a bachelor's degree in [[mechanical engineering]].<ref name=\"Jett\"/> In college, Lee was a member of the [[Kappa Alpha Order]].\n\nLee was named president and CEO of his family's home-services and construction company, Lee Company, holding the position from 1992 until 2016.<ref name=\"Jett\"/><ref name = TNCom>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2017/04/23/republican-bill-lee-announces-run-governor-tennessee/100435486/|title = Republican Bill Lee announces run for governor of Tennessee|date = April 23, 2017|accessdate = August 3, 2018|website = [[The Tennesseean]]|last1 = Ebert|first1 = Joel|last2 = Garrison|first2 = Joey}}</ref> He briefly served as chairman.<ref name=TNCom/>\n\n==Governor of Tennessee==\n===2018 election===\n{{main|2018 Tennessee gubernatorial election}}\nIn April 2017 Lee announced his candidacy the [[2018 Tennessee gubernatorial election|2018 election]] for [[governor of Tennessee]].<ref name = TNCom/> A self-described [[social conservative]], Lee also targeted pro-business Republicans.<ref name = TNCom/> In the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] [[primary election]], he ran against Congresswoman [[Diane Black]], Knoxville businessman and former Tennessee Economic and Development Commissioner Randy Boyd, and [[Kentucky House of Representatives|state House]] speaker [[Beth Harwell]].<ref name = TNCom/><ref name = TNWin>{{cite news|last=Ebert|first=Joel|publisher=Tennessean|date=August 2, 2018 |title=Bill Lee wins Republican nomination for governor of Tennessee |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/tn-elections/2018/08/02/tn-governor-election-republican-primary-results/820705002/}}</ref> Originally considered a longshot, Lee rose in the polls as Boyd and Black launched [[Negative campaigning|negative advertising]] against each other.<ref name=\"EbertAllison\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ebert |first1=Joel |title=How Diane Black and Randy Boyd lost Tennessee's Republican primary for governor |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/how-diane-black-and-randy-boyd-lost-tennessees-republican-primary-for-governor/ar-BBLvX0u |website=Tennessean |accessdate=August 7, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918165516/https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/how-diane-black-and-randy-boyd-lost-tennessees-republican-primary-for-governor/ar-BBLvX0u |archive-date=September 18, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He won the August 2 primary with 291,414 votes (36.8%) to Boyd's 193,054 (24.3%), Black's 182,457 (23.0%), and Harwell's 121,484 (15.3%).<ref>[https://sos-tn-gov-files.tnsosfiles.com/180802_RepbyOffice.pdf August 2018 Primary Election Results], Secretary of State of Tennessee.</ref>\n\nLee defeated the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] nominee, former [[List of mayors of Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville mayor]] [[Karl Dean]], in the November 6 general election,<ref>Natalie Allison, [https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/tn-elections/2018/11/06/tennessee-election-governor-karl-dean-bill-lee/1734245002/ Republican Bill Lee wins race for Tennessee governor, defeating Democrat Karl Dean], ''Tennessean'' (November 7, 2018).</ref> receiving 1,336,106 votes (59.5%) to Dean's 864,863 (38.5%).<ref>[https://sos-tn-gov-files.tnsosfiles.com/Nov%202018%20General%20Totals.pdf November 2018 General Election Results], Secretary of State of Tennessee.</ref>\n\nLee previously chaired and served on the committee of the Tennessee Prayer Breakfast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/01/09/bill-lee-separation-church-and-state-tennessee-governor/2525435002/|title=Gov.-elect Bill Lee asks lawmakers for prayer, stresses his views on separation of church and state|website=The Tennessean|accessdate=21 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Tenure===\n====2019====\n[[File:Bill Lee swearing in.jpg|thumb|Governor Bill Lee taking the oath of office.]]\nLee was sworn in on January 19, 2019.<ref name=\"EbertAllison\"/> He issued five executive orders in his first two months in office; one addressed economically distressed rural counties in Tennessee, another addressed nondiscrimination in employment, and a third imposed a 90-day \"freeze\" on the issuance of new regulations by executive departments.<ref>Kathy Carlson, \"Lee's executive orders fit trend for new administrations,\" ''Tennessee Ledger'' (February 22, 2019).</ref> Lee announced that the governor's website would include a new feature to allow citizens to give feedback on bills that had passed through the General Assembly and were awaiting his signature or veto.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wreg.com/2019/02/19/tennessee-gov-site-to-take-input-on-bills-awaiting-signature/|title=Tennessee gov site to take input on bills awaiting signature|publisher=WREG|date=February 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAs governor, Lee has rejected [[Medicaid expansion|proposals to expand]] [[TennCare]], the state's [[Medicaid]] program.<ref>Chris Bundgaard, [https://www.localmemphis.com/news/local-news/tn-governor-bill-lee-on-democrats-calls-to-expand-tenncare/1794642383 TN Governor Bill Lee on Democrats' Calls to Expand TennCare] (February 19, 2019).</ref> He supports legislation introduced in the [[Tennessee General Assembly]] to [[Abortion ban|ban abortion]] as early as six weeks into pregnancy, in potential conflict with the Supreme Court decision in ''[[Roe v. Wade]]''.<ref>Jonathan Mattise, [https://apnews.com/1724a05e393e456e8aac7dd214ebc5cd Tennessee Governor Bill Lee, top GOP lawmakers back heartbeat abortion ban], Associated Press (January 30, 2019).</ref> In February 2019 Lee announced that his budget proposal for the 2020 fiscal year would include a repeal of the 10% amusement tax Tennessee levies on gyms, fitness centers, and health clubs. Lee argued that the tax discourages Tennesseans from being physically active. If enacted, the repeal would reduce state revenues by around $10 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wate.com/news/tennessee/tenn-gov-bill-lee-to-propose-repealing-gym-tax-in-2019-budget/1794065375|title=Tenn. Gov. Bill Lee to propose repealing 'gym tax' in 2019 budget|publisher=WATE|date=February 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn March 4, Lee delivered his first [[State of the State address]] to the [[Tennessee General Assembly]], talking about his plans for the future and how he believed that \"Tennessee can and should lead the nation.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Full speech: Read Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee's first State of the State address |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/03/05/governor-bill-lee-state-of-the-state-full-speech-tennessee/3028501002/ |accessdate=December 18, 2019 |publisher=Tennessean |date=March 4, 2019}}</ref> On March 7, Lee delivered a \"state of [[West Tennessee]]\" address at the [[University of Memphis]]. He is the first governor make a speech directed toward only West Tennessee; in the speech, he proposed creating more charter schools and that the state use $25 million to help traditional public schools when they lose students.<ref>{{cite news |title=Governor Lee delivers first-ever State of West Tennessee address in Memphis |url=https://wreg.com/news/governor-lee-delivers-first-ever-state-of-west-tennessee-address-in-memphis/ |accessdate=February 24, 2020 |work=WREG-TV |date=March 7, 2019}}</ref> On April 4, Lee announced that the state would temporarily reinstate paper-based assessments for students taking the TNReady test, an annual statewide assessment, during the 2019\u201320 school year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee: Tennessee to return to paper-based testing in 2019-20 school year |url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/gov-bill-lee-tennessee-to-return-to-paper-based-testing-in-2019-20-school-year/51-0b254a72-416c-43f4-9dae-be5ef59c157b |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=WBIR-TV |date=April 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn May 24, 2019, Lee signed into law a school voucher program that provides public funds to families so they can send their kids to private schools, effective at the beginning of the 2020\u201321 fiscal year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee signs his controversial school voucher bill into law |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/education/2019/05/24/gov-bill-lee-signs-his-controversial-tennessee-school-voucher-bill/1224748001/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=Tennessean |date=May 24, 2019}}</ref> On July 2, Lee signed into law House Bill 1158, a school safety bill that calls for school districts across the state to establish a threat assessment team.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee signs school safety bill into law to mitigate school threats |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/local/williamson/franklin/2019/07/03/bill-lee-signs-tennessee-school-safety-bill-into-law-modeled-after-williamson-schools-protocol/1639004001/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=The Tennessean |date=July 3, 2019}}</ref> Lee visited [[Lauderdale County, Tennessee|Lauderdale County]] in West Tennessee on July 17, to see how recent flooding from the remnants of [[Hurricane Barry (2019)|Hurricane Barry]] had affected the community.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee tours flood-affected areas in west Tennessee |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2019/07/17/gov-bill-lee-touring-flood-affected-areas-west-tennessee/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=WMC-TV |date=July 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn November 26, 2019, Lee, along with [[Comcast]], announced a $2.4 million fiber network expansion that will bring high-speed broadband internet connection to [[Tipton County, Tennessee|Tipton County]] in [[West Tennessee]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee announces rural broadband expansion in West Tennessee |url=https://www.timesfreepress.com/news/breakingnews/story/2019/nov/26/lee-announces-rural-broadband-expansion-west-tennessee/509190/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=Chattanooga Times Free Press |date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> On December 1, Lee proclaimed the first of December as [[Rosa Parks]] Day, which was the day that Parks refused to give up her seat on a bus in [[Montgomery, Alabama]] in 1955.<ref>{{cite news |title=Governor Bill Lee declares Dec. 1 as \u2018Rosa Parks Day\u2019 |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2019/12/02/governor-lee-declares-dec-rosa-parks-day/ |accessdate=December 19, 2019 |publisher=WMC-TV |date=December 1, 2019}}</ref> In early December 2019, Lee visited several high schools and colleges in [[East Tennessee]] to promote the GIVE program, which prioritizes learning opportunities in rural counties and enhances career and technical education statewide.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee visiting East Tennessee high schools, colleges to promote GIVE program |url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/local/gov-bill-lee-visiting-east-tennessee-high-schools-colleges-to-promote-give-program/51-39679ab6-8ce6-4e49-81fa-38943288c6ad |accessdate=December 18, 2019 |publisher=WBIR-TV |date=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 10, Lee appointed Kyle Hixson to serve as a criminal court judge for the 6th judicial district, filling the spot of Bob McGee.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee appoints Kyle Hixson 6th Judicial District Criminal Court Judge |url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/gov-bill-lee-appoints-kyle-hixson-6th-judicial-district-criminal-court-judge/51-208c17ef-772b-42be-88cf-a1037f554028 |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |agency=WBIR-TV |date=December 10, 2019}}</ref> On December 13, Lee announced that the global industrial company Hyosung Heavy Industries would invest $86.9 million and develop 410 jobs over the next seven years in [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Lee announces global industrial company to create 400 jobs in Memphis |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2019/12/13/gov-lee-commissioner-rolfe-memphis-make-economic-development-announcement/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |agency=WMC-TV |date=December 13, 2019}}</ref> On December 18, Lee announced that Tennessee would continue to accept refugees, and in a letter to Lieutenant Governor [[Randy McNally]] and Speaker of the [[Tennessee House of Representatives]] [[Cameron Sexton]] wrote, \"it is important to note that each and every refugee that might potentially be resettled in Tennessee under the President\u2019s Executive Order will have been individually approved by the Trump Administration for legal immigrant status.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee will continue accepting refugees, Gov. Bill Lee says, as legislative leaders signal disapproval |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/18/tennessee-refugee-resettlement-gov-bill-lee-announces-state-accept/2686574001/https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/18/tennessee-refugee-resettlement-gov-bill-lee-announces-state-accept/2686574001/https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/18/tennessee-refugee-resettlement-gov-bill-lee-announces-state-accept/2686574001/ |accessdate=December 19, 2019 |agency=Tennessean |date=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 19, [[Vanderbilt University]] released a poll of Tennesseans over the fall of 2019 that showed Lee's approval rating at 62%, the highest of any statewide politician.<ref>{{cite web |title=Vandy Poll: Trump, Lee, Congress, and Other Issues |url=https://www.memphisflyer.com/ |website=MemphisFlyer.com |accessdate=January 1, 2020}}</ref> On December 26, Lee appointed former state senator [[Mae Beavers]] to serve a six-year term on the state Board of Parole.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mae Beavers named to Tenn. Board of Parole by Gov. Bill Lee |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/26/mae-beavers-appointed-tennessee-parole-board-gov-bill-lee/2749943001/ |accessdate=2020-01-01 |publisher=Tennessean |date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n====2020====\nOn January 3, 2020, Lee visited [[Elizabethton, Tennessee|Elizabethton]] to announce a $1 million grant to the Elizabethton TCAT. During his trip, he was met with protests from people who disagreed with Lee's decision to continue resettling refugees in the state. One protester, Elizabeth Cox, said, \"We have homeless and veterans that are sleeping under boxcars and under bridges and freezing to death. We don\u2019t need to look out for foreigners first.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee met by protesters on Tri-Cities visit |url=https://www.wjhl.com/news/local/gov-bill-lee-met-with-protest-on-tri-cities-visit/ |accessdate=January 6, 2020 |publisher=WJHL-TV |date=January 3, 2020}}</ref> On January 7 Lee signed an executive order that offered state employees three months' paid leave for new parents and caregivers of sick relatives. He described it as \"one of the most cost-effective investments in the families of our state employees in recent history\". The order is to go into effect on March 1.<ref name=\"Tennessean\">{{cite news |title=Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee calls for 12 weeks paid leave for state employees who are new parents, caregivers |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2020/01/07/tennessee-fmla-paid-parental-leave-bill-lee-time-off-state-employees/2831754001/ |accessdate=January 7, 2020 |date=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn January 14, Lee announced that he would sign a measure into law that assures continued taxpayer funding of faith-based foster care and adoption agencies even if they exclude [[LGBT]] families and others based on religious beliefs. Supporters of the measure argued that such measures are needed to protect against potential lawsuits hostile to the group's religious beliefs.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee governor says he will sign anti-gay adoption bill |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/tennessee-governor-says-he-will-sign-anti-gay-adoption-bill-n1116266 |accessdate=January 17, 2020 |work=NBC News |date=January 15, 2020}}</ref> In response to this legislation, [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]], which announced in July 2019 that it would bring 5,000 jobs to Nashville, stated, \"Amazon does not support this legislation. We have a long history of supporting equality and we\u2019re opposed to laws that discriminate or encourage discrimination.\u201d<ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee Gov. Lee to sign anti-LGBTQ adoption bill despite Amazon, Nike opposition |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/01/17/tennessee-nears-anti-lgbtq-bill-despite-amazon-nike-opposition.html |accessdate=January 19, 2020 |work=CNBC |date=January 17, 2020}}</ref> To explain why he signed the bill, Lee said, \"I think equality is important and protection of rights is important and the rights of religious liberty are important. And that bill was centered around protection of religious liberty and that\u2019s why I signed it.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Lee says he signed LGBT adoption refusal bill to protect religious liberty |url=https://www.newschannel5.com/news/gov-lee-says-he-signed-lgbt-adoption-refusal-bill-to-protect-religious-liberty |accessdate=January 23, 2020 |work=WTVF-TV |date=January 20, 2020}}</ref> Lee signed the measure on January 24.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee signs bill allowing adoption agencies to deny gay couples |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/01/24/tennessee-gay-adoption-gov-bill-lee-signs-anti-lgbt-measure/4570788002/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020 |work=USA Today |date=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn January 23, Lee proposed a \"heartbeat bill\", which would ban [[abortion]] when a fetal heartbeat is detected, similar to legislation that has been blocked in other states. Lee said the bill was \"a monumental step forward in celebrating, cherishing and defending life.\" [[Tennessee Democratic Party]] Chair [[Mary Mancini]] responded, \"No politician should be in the middle of the decision to end a pregnancy, choose adoption, or raise a child.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee announces new fetal heartbeat bill, comprehensive abortion reform |url=https://www.newschannel5.com/news/gov-bill-lee-proposes-new-bill-that-would-ban-abortion-when-fetal-heartbeat-is-detected |accessdate=January 24, 2020 |work=WTVF |date=January 23, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee governor announces 'heartbeat' bill to restrict abortions |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/tennessee-governor-heartbeat-bill-restrict-abortions |accessdate=January 24, 2020 |work=Fox News |date=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn February 3, Lee delivered his second annual State of the State address. In the address, he outlined his vision for the state, which included creating a $250 million endowment to address mental health in K-12 education and extending [[TennCare]] to pregnant women who need dental care. Lee also proposed a $117 million investment to increase teacher salaries.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Lee and dentists push for more dental coverage for pregnant women |url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/local/pregnant-mom-dental-bill-lee-expecting-baby-teeth-birth-weight/51-17aa35d4-59c5-4754-a56a-4dfc96408835 |accessdate=February 12, 2020 |work=WBIR-TV |date=February 11, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=In second State of the State address, Gov. Bill Lee pushes major investments in education, raises for teachers and state workers |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2020/02/04/2020-state-of-state-gov-bill-lee-pushes-education/4625073002/ |accessdate=February 6, 2020 |work=Tennessean |date=February 3, 2020}}</ref> On February 13, Lee delivered his second annual \"state of West Tennessee\" address at [[Lane College]] in [[Jackson, Tennessee]]. In the address, he proposed investing $70 million to equip teachers with professional development, materials and other tools to help increase the state's literacy rate.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee delivers State of West Tennessee address |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2020/02/14/gov-bill-lee-delivers-state-west-tennessee-address/ |accessdate=February 24, 2020 |work=WMC-TV |date=February 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn February 19, Lee denied clemency for death row inmate Nicholas Sutton.<ref>https://www.nashvillescene.com/news/pith-in-the-wind/article/21117091/governor-denies-clemency-for-nick-sutton</ref> Sutton had saved three corrections officers' lives.<ref>https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/20/us/nick-sutton-execution/index.html</ref> Lee's statement read: \u201cAfter careful consideration of Nicholas Sutton\u2019s request for clemency and a thorough review of the case, I am upholding the sentence of the State of Tennessee and will not be intervening.\u201d<ref>https://www.tn.gov/governor/news/2020/2/19/statement-from-gov--bill-lee-on-nicholas-sutton.html</ref> Sutton was the third person to be put to death under Lee's tenure as governor. On February 22, Lee signed a bill making Tennessee's official nickname the \"Volunteer State.\" The name originated during the [[War of 1812]], when Tennessee sent 1,500 volunteer soldiers.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Lee signs bill making Tennessee the 'Volunteer State' |url=https://www.wvlt.tv/content/news/Gov-Lee-signs-bill-making-Tennessee-officially-the-Volunteer-State-568109471.html |accessdate=February  24, 2020 |work=WVLT-TV |date=February 22, 2020}}</ref>\n \nOn February 27, Lee announced his support for permitless carry legislation, which would allow lawful gun owners 21 and older to carry a firearm without a permit. Lee said, \"This legislation is about increasing freedom for law-abiding citizens and implementing harsher penalties for criminals. With the freedom and liberties granted to us in the Second Amendment also comes a great responsibility to steward them wisely and protect our citizens.\" Many people opposed this legislation, including some [[Second Amendment to the United States Constitution|Second Amendment]] supporters.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee announces support for permitless carry legislation |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2020/02/27/gov-bill-lee-announces-permitless-carry-legislation/ |accessdate=March 2, 2020 |work=WMC-TV |date=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn the night of March 2 and the morning of March 3, [[Tornado outbreak of March 2\u20133, 2020|a series of tornadoes]] touched down across Tennessee, killing 25 people and injuring 150. On March 3, Lee said, \"It\u2019s heartbreaking. We\u2019ve had loss of life across the state.\" Of the recovery effort, he said, \"We\u2019re doing everything that we can to respond to this. With that being said, this is a very difficult situation.\" Later that day, Lee surveyed the damage in Nashville, visiting Germantown and [[Tennessee State University]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee says search for survivors continues as individuals remain unaccounted for following overnight tornadoes |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2020/03/03/city-state-leaders-address-damages-after-tornadoes-hit-middle-tennessee-overnight/ |accessdate=March 4, 2020 |work=WMC-TV |date=March 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLee lives in [[Fernvale, Tennessee|Fernvale]] with his second wife, Maria, whom he married in 2008.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/tn-elections/2018/11/06/bill-lee-wife-tennessee-governor-midterm-elections-2018/1884722002/ |title=Midterm elections: Bill Lee wife next Tennessee first lady Maria Lee |last=Grigsby |first=Karen  |last2=Ebert |first2=Joel |publisher=Tennessean.com |access-date=November 8, 2018}}</ref> His first wife, Carol Ann, died in 2000 in a horseback riding accident.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2017/08/04/campaigning-tennessee-governor-what-life-like-road-republican-bill-lee/536131001/ |title=Campaigning for Tennessee governor: What life is like on the road with Republican Bill Lee |publisher=Tennessean.com |date=August 4, 2017 |accessdate=November 8, 2018}}</ref> After her death, Lee took extended time off from his construction company to raise his four children.<ref name=\"Jett\"/>\n\nLee attends Grace Chapel Church in [[Leiper's Fork, Tennessee|Leiper's Fork]].<ref name = TNCom/>\n\nLee previously served as a member of the board of trustees of [[Belmont University]], chairman of the YMCA of Middle Tennessee, president of the [[Associated Builders and Contractors]], and a board member of the Hope Clinic for Women and the Men of Valor [[Prison ministry|Prison Ministry]].<ref name=\"Jett\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Bill Lee (Tennessee politician)}}\n*[https://www.tn.gov/governor/ Official governor website]\n*[https://www.billlee.com/ Campaign website]\n*{{C-SPAN|Bill Lee 04}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bill Haslam]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] nominee for [[Governor of Tennessee]]|years=[[2018 Tennessee gubernatorial election|2018]]}}\n{{s-inc|recent}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bill Haslam]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Governor of Tennessee]]|years=2019\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Mike Pence]]|as=[[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=2|title=[[United States order of precedence|Order of Precedence of the United States]]|years=Within Tennessee}}\n{{s-aft|after=Mayor of city<br />in which event is held}}\n|-\n{{s-aft|after=Otherwise {{Incumbent U.S. House Speaker}}<br />{{nowrap|''as [[Speaker of the United States House of Representatives|Speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives]]''}}}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Andy Beshear]]|as=[[Governor of Kentucky]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States order of precedence|Order of Precedence of the United States]]|years=Outside Tennessee}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Mike DeWine]]|as=[[Governor of Ohio]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Governors of Tennessee}}\n{{U.S. Governors}}\n{{Tennessee statewide political officials}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lee, Bill}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:American construction businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Auburn University alumni]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Governors of Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Franklin, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Republican Party state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:Tennessee Republicans]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the Governor of Tennessee|other people named Bill Lee|William Lee (disambiguation){{!}}William Lee}}\n{{short description|50th Governor of Tennessee}}\n{{infobox officeholder\n| name = Bill Lee\n| image = Bill Lee 2020.jpg\n| order = 50th [[Governor of Tennessee]]\n| lieutenant = [[Randy McNally]]\n| term_start = January 19, 2019\n| term_end = \n| predecessor = [[Bill Haslam]]\n| successor = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1959|10|9}}\n| birth_place = [[Franklin, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| party = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| spouse = {{marriage|Carol Ann Lee|1984|2000|end=died}}<br>{{marriage|Maria Lee|2008}}\n| children = 4\n| residence = [[Tennessee Governor's Mansion|Governor's Mansion]]\n| education = [[Auburn University]] ([[Bachelor of Science|BS]])\n}}\n'''William Byron Lee''' (born October 9, 1959)<ref>[https://www.nga.org/governors/tennessee/ Gov. Bill Lee: Tennessee], [[National Governors Association]].</ref> is an American businessman and politician serving as the [[List of Governors of Tennessee|50th]] and current [[governor of Tennessee]].<ref name=\"EbertAllison\">Joel Ebert & Natalie Allison, [https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/01/19/bill-lee-tennessee-governor-inauguration/2585557002/ Bill Lee sworn in as Tennessee's 50th governor, nearly 2 years after long-shot bid], ''Tennessean'' (January 19, 2019).</ref> Elected in [[2018 Tennessee gubernatorial election|2018]], Lee campaigned as a business-oriented member of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.knoxnews.com/story/opinion/editorials/2018/10/25/bill-lee-tennessee-governor-erndorsement-knoxville-news-sentinel/1742616002/|title=Bill Lee has potential to be an inspiring Tennessee governor {{!}} Opinion|work=Knoxville News Sentinel|access-date=November 8, 2018|language=en}}</ref> Before entering politics he held various positions at the Lee Company, an inherited family business; he was the company's president and CEO from 1992 to 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nashvillepost.com/business/article/20489307/bill-lee-stepping-down-as-ceo-of-lee-co|title=Bill Lee stepping down as CEO of Lee Co.|newspaper=Nashville Post|date=February 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and career==\nLee was raised on his family's {{convert|1000|acre|adj=on}} cattle farm started by his grandparents in [[Franklin, Tennessee]], the Triple L Ranch; the family raises [[Hereford cattle]].<ref name=\"Jett\">Tyler Jett, [https://www.timesfreepress.com/news/local/story/2018/jul/06/bill-lee-says-he-wcalled-run-governor/474433/ Who is Bill Lee? Bill Lee says he was called to run for governor], ''Chattanooga Times Free Press'' (July 6, 2018).</ref><ref>http://www.lllranch.com/about.html ''About LLL Ranch'' (Retrieved September 16, 2019).</ref>\n\nAfter graduating from [[Franklin High School (Tennessee)|Franklin High School]] in his hometown,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.williamsonhomepage.com/spring_hill/franklin-businessman-bill-lee-raises-million-for-governors-race/article_d22e8c5e-209c-5fa0-bc23-bc3dc6cffb1b.html|title=Franklin businessman Bill Lee raises $1.3 million for governors race|website=Williamson Home Page}}</ref> Lee entered [[Auburn University]] in [[Auburn, Alabama]] in 1977 and graduated in 1981<ref name=\"Allison\">Nathan Allison, [https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/02/20/tn-gov-bill-lee-kappa-alpha-old-south-party-auburn/2904953002/ Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee says he regrets participating in 'Old South' parties at Auburn University], ''Tennessee'' (January 21, 2019).</ref> with a bachelor's degree in [[mechanical engineering]].<ref name=\"Jett\"/> In college, Lee was a member of the [[Kappa Alpha Order]].\n\nLee was named president and CEO of his family's home-services and construction company, Lee Company, holding the position from 1992 until 2016.<ref name=\"Jett\"/><ref name = TNCom>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2017/04/23/republican-bill-lee-announces-run-governor-tennessee/100435486/|title = Republican Bill Lee announces run for governor of Tennessee|date = April 23, 2017|accessdate = August 3, 2018|website = [[The Tennesseean]]|last1 = Ebert|first1 = Joel|last2 = Garrison|first2 = Joey}}</ref> He briefly served as chairman.<ref name=TNCom/>\n\n==Governor of Tennessee==\n===2018 election===\n{{main|2018 Tennessee gubernatorial election}}\nIn April 2017 Lee announced his candidacy the [[2018 Tennessee gubernatorial election|2018 election]] for [[governor of Tennessee]].<ref name = TNCom/> A self-described [[social conservative]], Lee also targeted pro-business Republicans.<ref name = TNCom/> In the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] [[primary election]], he ran against Congresswoman [[Diane Black]], Knoxville businessman and former Tennessee Economic and Development Commissioner Randy Boyd, and [[Kentucky House of Representatives|state House]] speaker [[Beth Harwell]].<ref name = TNCom/><ref name = TNWin>{{cite news|last=Ebert|first=Joel|publisher=Tennessean|date=August 2, 2018 |title=Bill Lee wins Republican nomination for governor of Tennessee |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/tn-elections/2018/08/02/tn-governor-election-republican-primary-results/820705002/}}</ref> Originally considered a longshot, Lee rose in the polls as Boyd and Black launched [[Negative campaigning|negative advertising]] against each other.<ref name=\"EbertAllison\"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ebert |first1=Joel |title=How Diane Black and Randy Boyd lost Tennessee's Republican primary for governor |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/how-diane-black-and-randy-boyd-lost-tennessees-republican-primary-for-governor/ar-BBLvX0u |website=Tennessean |accessdate=August 7, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918165516/https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/how-diane-black-and-randy-boyd-lost-tennessees-republican-primary-for-governor/ar-BBLvX0u |archive-date=September 18, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He won the August 2 primary with 291,414 votes (36.8%) to Boyd's 193,054 (24.3%), Black's 182,457 (23.0%), and Harwell's 121,484 (15.3%).<ref>[https://sos-tn-gov-files.tnsosfiles.com/180802_RepbyOffice.pdf August 2018 Primary Election Results], Secretary of State of Tennessee.</ref>\n\nLee defeated the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] nominee, former [[List of mayors of Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville mayor]] [[Karl Dean]], in the November 6 general election,<ref>Natalie Allison, [https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/tn-elections/2018/11/06/tennessee-election-governor-karl-dean-bill-lee/1734245002/ Republican Bill Lee wins race for Tennessee governor, defeating Democrat Karl Dean], ''Tennessean'' (November 7, 2018).</ref> receiving 1,336,106 votes (59.5%) to Dean's 864,863 (38.5%).<ref>[https://sos-tn-gov-files.tnsosfiles.com/Nov%202018%20General%20Totals.pdf November 2018 General Election Results], Secretary of State of Tennessee.</ref>\n\nLee previously chaired and served on the committee of the Tennessee Prayer Breakfast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/01/09/bill-lee-separation-church-and-state-tennessee-governor/2525435002/|title=Gov.-elect Bill Lee asks lawmakers for prayer, stresses his views on separation of church and state|website=The Tennessean|accessdate=21 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Tenure===\n====2019====\n[[File:Bill Lee swearing in.jpg|thumb|Governor Bill Lee taking the oath of office.]]\nLee was sworn in on January 19, 2019.<ref name=\"EbertAllison\"/> He issued five executive orders in his first two months in office; one addressed economically distressed rural counties in Tennessee, another addressed nondiscrimination in employment, and a third imposed a 90-day \"freeze\" on the issuance of new regulations by executive departments.<ref>Kathy Carlson, \"Lee's executive orders fit trend for new administrations,\" ''Tennessee Ledger'' (February 22, 2019).</ref> Lee announced that the governor's website would include a new feature to allow citizens to give feedback on bills that had passed through the General Assembly and were awaiting his signature or veto.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wreg.com/2019/02/19/tennessee-gov-site-to-take-input-on-bills-awaiting-signature/|title=Tennessee gov site to take input on bills awaiting signature|publisher=WREG|date=February 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAs governor, Lee has rejected [[Medicaid expansion|proposals to expand]] [[TennCare]], the state's [[Medicaid]] program.<ref>Chris Bundgaard, [https://www.localmemphis.com/news/local-news/tn-governor-bill-lee-on-democrats-calls-to-expand-tenncare/1794642383 TN Governor Bill Lee on Democrats' Calls to Expand TennCare] (February 19, 2019).</ref> He supports legislation introduced in the [[Tennessee General Assembly]] to [[Abortion ban|ban abortion]] as early as six weeks into pregnancy, in potential conflict with the Supreme Court decision in ''[[Roe v. Wade]]''.<ref>Jonathan Mattise, [https://apnews.com/1724a05e393e456e8aac7dd214ebc5cd Tennessee Governor Bill Lee, top GOP lawmakers back heartbeat abortion ban], Associated Press (January 30, 2019).</ref> In February 2019 Lee announced that his budget proposal for the 2020 fiscal year would include a repeal of the 10% amusement tax Tennessee levies on gyms, fitness centers, and health clubs. Lee argued that the tax discourages Tennesseans from being physically active. If enacted, the repeal would reduce state revenues by around $10 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wate.com/news/tennessee/tenn-gov-bill-lee-to-propose-repealing-gym-tax-in-2019-budget/1794065375|title=Tenn. Gov. Bill Lee to propose repealing 'gym tax' in 2019 budget|publisher=WATE|date=February 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn March 4, Lee delivered his first [[State of the State address]] to the [[Tennessee General Assembly]], talking about his plans for the future and how he believed that \"Tennessee can and should lead the nation.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Full speech: Read Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee's first State of the State address |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/03/05/governor-bill-lee-state-of-the-state-full-speech-tennessee/3028501002/ |accessdate=December 18, 2019 |publisher=Tennessean |date=March 4, 2019}}</ref> On March 7, Lee delivered a \"state of [[West Tennessee]]\" address at the [[University of Memphis]]. He is the first governor make a speech directed toward only West Tennessee; in the speech, he proposed creating more charter schools and that the state use $25 million to help traditional public schools when they lose students.<ref>{{cite news |title=Governor Lee delivers first-ever State of West Tennessee address in Memphis |url=https://wreg.com/news/governor-lee-delivers-first-ever-state-of-west-tennessee-address-in-memphis/ |accessdate=February 24, 2020 |work=WREG-TV |date=March 7, 2019}}</ref> On April 4, Lee announced that the state would temporarily reinstate paper-based assessments for students taking the TNReady test, an annual statewide assessment, during the 2019\u201320 school year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee: Tennessee to return to paper-based testing in 2019-20 school year |url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/gov-bill-lee-tennessee-to-return-to-paper-based-testing-in-2019-20-school-year/51-0b254a72-416c-43f4-9dae-be5ef59c157b |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=WBIR-TV |date=April 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn May 24, 2019, Lee signed into law a school voucher program that provides public funds to families so they can send their kids to private schools, effective at the beginning of the 2020\u201321 fiscal year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee signs his controversial school voucher bill into law |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/education/2019/05/24/gov-bill-lee-signs-his-controversial-tennessee-school-voucher-bill/1224748001/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=Tennessean |date=May 24, 2019}}</ref> On July 2, Lee signed into law House Bill 1158, a school safety bill that calls for school districts across the state to establish a threat assessment team.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee signs school safety bill into law to mitigate school threats |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/local/williamson/franklin/2019/07/03/bill-lee-signs-tennessee-school-safety-bill-into-law-modeled-after-williamson-schools-protocol/1639004001/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=The Tennessean |date=July 3, 2019}}</ref> Lee visited [[Lauderdale County, Tennessee|Lauderdale County]] in West Tennessee on July 17, to see how recent flooding from the remnants of [[Hurricane Barry (2019)|Hurricane Barry]] had affected the community.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee tours flood-affected areas in west Tennessee |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2019/07/17/gov-bill-lee-touring-flood-affected-areas-west-tennessee/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=WMC-TV |date=July 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn November 26, 2019, Lee, along with [[Comcast]], announced a $2.4 million fiber network expansion that will bring high-speed broadband internet connection to [[Tipton County, Tennessee|Tipton County]] in [[West Tennessee]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee announces rural broadband expansion in West Tennessee |url=https://www.timesfreepress.com/news/breakingnews/story/2019/nov/26/lee-announces-rural-broadband-expansion-west-tennessee/509190/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |publisher=Chattanooga Times Free Press |date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> On December 1, Lee proclaimed the first of December as [[Rosa Parks]] Day, which was the day that Parks refused to give up her seat on a bus in [[Montgomery, Alabama]] in 1955.<ref>{{cite news |title=Governor Bill Lee declares Dec. 1 as \u2018Rosa Parks Day\u2019 |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2019/12/02/governor-lee-declares-dec-rosa-parks-day/ |accessdate=December 19, 2019 |publisher=WMC-TV |date=December 1, 2019}}</ref> In early December 2019, Lee visited several high schools and colleges in [[East Tennessee]] to promote the GIVE program, which prioritizes learning opportunities in rural counties and enhances career and technical education statewide.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee visiting East Tennessee high schools, colleges to promote GIVE program |url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/local/gov-bill-lee-visiting-east-tennessee-high-schools-colleges-to-promote-give-program/51-39679ab6-8ce6-4e49-81fa-38943288c6ad |accessdate=December 18, 2019 |publisher=WBIR-TV |date=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 10, Lee appointed Kyle Hixson to serve as a criminal court judge for the 6th judicial district, filling the spot of Bob McGee.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee appoints Kyle Hixson 6th Judicial District Criminal Court Judge |url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/gov-bill-lee-appoints-kyle-hixson-6th-judicial-district-criminal-court-judge/51-208c17ef-772b-42be-88cf-a1037f554028 |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |agency=WBIR-TV |date=December 10, 2019}}</ref> On December 13, Lee announced that the global industrial company Hyosung Heavy Industries would invest $86.9 million and develop 410 jobs over the next seven years in [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Lee announces global industrial company to create 400 jobs in Memphis |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2019/12/13/gov-lee-commissioner-rolfe-memphis-make-economic-development-announcement/ |accessdate=December 16, 2019 |agency=WMC-TV |date=December 13, 2019}}</ref> On December 18, Lee announced that Tennessee would continue to accept refugees, and in a letter to Lieutenant Governor [[Randy McNally]] and Speaker of the [[Tennessee House of Representatives]] [[Cameron Sexton]] wrote, \"it is important to note that each and every refugee that might potentially be resettled in Tennessee under the President\u2019s Executive Order will have been individually approved by the Trump Administration for legal immigrant status.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee will continue accepting refugees, Gov. Bill Lee says, as legislative leaders signal disapproval |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/18/tennessee-refugee-resettlement-gov-bill-lee-announces-state-accept/2686574001/https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/18/tennessee-refugee-resettlement-gov-bill-lee-announces-state-accept/2686574001/https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/18/tennessee-refugee-resettlement-gov-bill-lee-announces-state-accept/2686574001/ |accessdate=December 19, 2019 |agency=Tennessean |date=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 19, [[Vanderbilt University]] released a poll of Tennesseans over the fall of 2019 that showed Lee's approval rating at 62%, the highest of any statewide politician.<ref>{{cite web |title=Vandy Poll: Trump, Lee, Congress, and Other Issues |url=https://www.memphisflyer.com/ |website=MemphisFlyer.com |accessdate=January 1, 2020}}</ref> On December 26, Lee appointed former state senator [[Mae Beavers]] to serve a six-year term on the state Board of Parole.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mae Beavers named to Tenn. Board of Parole by Gov. Bill Lee |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/26/mae-beavers-appointed-tennessee-parole-board-gov-bill-lee/2749943001/ |accessdate=2020-01-01 |publisher=Tennessean |date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n====2020====\nOn January 3, 2020, Lee visited [[Elizabethton, Tennessee|Elizabethton]] to announce a $1 million grant to the Elizabethton TCAT. During his trip, he was met with protests from people who disagreed with Lee's decision to continue resettling refugees in the state. One protester, Elizabeth Cox, said, \"We have homeless and veterans that are sleeping under boxcars and under bridges and freezing to death. We don\u2019t need to look out for foreigners first.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee met by protesters on Tri-Cities visit |url=https://www.wjhl.com/news/local/gov-bill-lee-met-with-protest-on-tri-cities-visit/ |accessdate=January 6, 2020 |publisher=WJHL-TV |date=January 3, 2020}}</ref> On January 7 Lee signed an executive order that offered state employees three months' paid leave for new parents and caregivers of sick relatives. He described it as \"one of the most cost-effective investments in the families of our state employees in recent history\". The order is to go into effect on March 1.<ref name=\"Tennessean\">{{cite news |title=Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee calls for 12 weeks paid leave for state employees who are new parents, caregivers |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2020/01/07/tennessee-fmla-paid-parental-leave-bill-lee-time-off-state-employees/2831754001/ |accessdate=January 7, 2020 |date=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn January 14, Lee announced that he would sign a measure into law that assures continued taxpayer funding of faith-based foster care and adoption agencies even if they exclude [[LGBT]] families and others based on religious beliefs. Supporters of the measure argued that such measures are needed to protect against potential lawsuits hostile to the group's religious beliefs.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee governor says he will sign anti-gay adoption bill |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/tennessee-governor-says-he-will-sign-anti-gay-adoption-bill-n1116266 |accessdate=January 17, 2020 |work=NBC News |date=January 15, 2020}}</ref> In response to this legislation, [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]], which announced in July 2019 that it would bring 5,000 jobs to Nashville, stated, \"Amazon does not support this legislation. We have a long history of supporting equality and we\u2019re opposed to laws that discriminate or encourage discrimination.\u201d<ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee Gov. Lee to sign anti-LGBTQ adoption bill despite Amazon, Nike opposition |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/01/17/tennessee-nears-anti-lgbtq-bill-despite-amazon-nike-opposition.html |accessdate=January 19, 2020 |work=CNBC |date=January 17, 2020}}</ref> To explain why he signed the bill, Lee said, \"I think equality is important and protection of rights is important and the rights of religious liberty are important. And that bill was centered around protection of religious liberty and that\u2019s why I signed it.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Lee says he signed LGBT adoption refusal bill to protect religious liberty |url=https://www.newschannel5.com/news/gov-lee-says-he-signed-lgbt-adoption-refusal-bill-to-protect-religious-liberty |accessdate=January 23, 2020 |work=WTVF-TV |date=January 20, 2020}}</ref> Lee signed the measure on January 24.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee signs bill allowing adoption agencies to deny gay couples |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/01/24/tennessee-gay-adoption-gov-bill-lee-signs-anti-lgbt-measure/4570788002/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020 |work=USA Today |date=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn January 23, Lee proposed a \"heartbeat bill\", which would ban [[abortion]] when a fetal heartbeat is detected, similar to legislation that has been blocked in other states. Lee said the bill was \"a monumental step forward in celebrating, cherishing and defending life.\" [[Tennessee Democratic Party]] Chair [[Mary Mancini]] responded, \"No politician should be in the middle of the decision to end a pregnancy, choose adoption, or raise a child.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee announces new fetal heartbeat bill, comprehensive abortion reform |url=https://www.newschannel5.com/news/gov-bill-lee-proposes-new-bill-that-would-ban-abortion-when-fetal-heartbeat-is-detected |accessdate=January 24, 2020 |work=WTVF |date=January 23, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Tennessee governor announces 'heartbeat' bill to restrict abortions |url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/tennessee-governor-heartbeat-bill-restrict-abortions |accessdate=January 24, 2020 |work=Fox News |date=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn February 3, Lee delivered his second annual State of the State address. In the address, he outlined his vision for the state, which included creating a $250 million endowment to address mental health in K-12 education and extending [[TennCare]] to pregnant women who need dental care. Lee also proposed a $117 million investment to increase teacher salaries.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Lee and dentists push for more dental coverage for pregnant women |url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/local/pregnant-mom-dental-bill-lee-expecting-baby-teeth-birth-weight/51-17aa35d4-59c5-4754-a56a-4dfc96408835 |accessdate=February 12, 2020 |work=WBIR-TV |date=February 11, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=In second State of the State address, Gov. Bill Lee pushes major investments in education, raises for teachers and state workers |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2020/02/04/2020-state-of-state-gov-bill-lee-pushes-education/4625073002/ |accessdate=February 6, 2020 |work=Tennessean |date=February 3, 2020}}</ref> On February 13, Lee delivered his second annual \"state of West Tennessee\" address at [[Lane College]] in [[Jackson, Tennessee]]. In the address, he proposed investing $70 million to equip teachers with professional development, materials and other tools to help increase the state's literacy rate.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee delivers State of West Tennessee address |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2020/02/14/gov-bill-lee-delivers-state-west-tennessee-address/ |accessdate=February 24, 2020 |work=WMC-TV |date=February 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn February 19, Lee denied clemency for death row inmate Nicholas Sutton.<ref>https://www.nashvillescene.com/news/pith-in-the-wind/article/21117091/governor-denies-clemency-for-nick-sutton</ref> Sutton had saved three corrections officers' lives.<ref>https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/20/us/nick-sutton-execution/index.html</ref> Lee's statement read: \u201cAfter careful consideration of Nicholas Sutton\u2019s request for clemency and a thorough review of the case, I am upholding the sentence of the State of Tennessee and will not be intervening.\u201d<ref>https://www.tn.gov/governor/news/2020/2/19/statement-from-gov--bill-lee-on-nicholas-sutton.html</ref> Sutton was the third person to be put to death under Lee's tenure as governor. On February 22, Lee signed a bill making Tennessee's official nickname the \"Volunteer State.\" The name originated during the [[War of 1812]], when Tennessee sent 1,500 volunteer soldiers.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Lee signs bill making Tennessee the 'Volunteer State' |url=https://www.wvlt.tv/content/news/Gov-Lee-signs-bill-making-Tennessee-officially-the-Volunteer-State-568109471.html |accessdate=February  24, 2020 |work=WVLT-TV |date=February 22, 2020}}</ref>\n \nOn February 27, Lee announced his support for permitless carry legislation, which would allow lawful gun owners 21 and older to carry a firearm without a permit. Lee said, \"This legislation is about increasing freedom for law-abiding citizens and implementing harsher penalties for criminals. With the freedom and liberties granted to us in the Second Amendment also comes a great responsibility to steward them wisely and protect our citizens.\" Many people opposed this legislation, including some [[Second Amendment to the United States Constitution|Second Amendment]] supporters.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee announces support for permitless carry legislation |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2020/02/27/gov-bill-lee-announces-permitless-carry-legislation/ |accessdate=March 2, 2020 |work=WMC-TV |date=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn the night of March 2 and the morning of March 3, [[Tornado outbreak of March 2\u20133, 2020|a series of tornadoes]] touched down across Tennessee, killing 25 people and injuring 150. On March 3, Lee said, \"It\u2019s heartbreaking. We\u2019ve had loss of life across the state.\" Of the recovery effort, he said, \"We\u2019re doing everything that we can to respond to this. With that being said, this is a very difficult situation.\" Later that day, Lee surveyed the damage in Nashville, visiting Germantown and [[Tennessee State University]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gov. Bill Lee says search for survivors continues as individuals remain unaccounted for following overnight tornadoes |url=https://www.wmcactionnews5.com/2020/03/03/city-state-leaders-address-damages-after-tornadoes-hit-middle-tennessee-overnight/ |accessdate=March 4, 2020 |work=WMC-TV |date=March 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLee lives in [[Fernvale, Tennessee|Fernvale]] with his second wife, Maria, whom he married in 2008.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/tn-elections/2018/11/06/bill-lee-wife-tennessee-governor-midterm-elections-2018/1884722002/ |title=Midterm elections: Bill Lee wife next Tennessee first lady Maria Lee |last=Grigsby |first=Karen  |last2=Ebert |first2=Joel |publisher=Tennessean.com |access-date=November 8, 2018}}</ref> His first wife, Carol Ann, died in 2000 in a horseback riding accident.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2017/08/04/campaigning-tennessee-governor-what-life-like-road-republican-bill-lee/536131001/ |title=Campaigning for Tennessee governor: What life is like on the road with Republican Bill Lee |publisher=Tennessean.com |date=August 4, 2017 |accessdate=November 8, 2018}}</ref> After her death, Lee took extended time off from his construction company to raise his four children.<ref name=\"Jett\"/>\n\nLee attends Grace Chapel Church in [[Leiper's Fork, Tennessee|Leiper's Fork]].<ref name = TNCom/>\n\nLee previously served as a member of the board of trustees of [[Belmont University]], chairman of the YMCA of Middle Tennessee, president of the [[Associated Builders and Contractors]], and a board member of the Hope Clinic for Women and the Men of Valor [[Prison ministry|Prison Ministry]].<ref name=\"Jett\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Bill Lee (Tennessee politician)}}\n*[https://www.tn.gov/governor/ Official governor website]\n*[https://www.billlee.com/ Campaign website]\n*{{C-SPAN|Bill Lee 04}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bill Haslam]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] nominee for [[Governor of Tennessee]]|years=[[2018 Tennessee gubernatorial election|2018]]}}\n{{s-inc|recent}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bill Haslam]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Governor of Tennessee]]|years=2019\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Mike Pence]]|as=[[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=2|title=[[United States order of precedence|Order of Precedence of the United States]]|years=Within Tennessee}}\n{{s-aft|after=Mayor of city<br />in which event is held}}\n|-\n{{s-aft|after=Otherwise {{Incumbent U.S. House Speaker}}<br />{{nowrap|''as [[Speaker of the United States House of Representatives|Speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives]]''}}}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Andy Beshear]]|as=[[Governor of Kentucky]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States order of precedence|Order of Precedence of the United States]]|years=Outside Tennessee}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Mike DeWine]]|as=[[Governor of Ohio]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Governors of Tennessee}}\n{{U.S. Governors}}\n{{Tennessee statewide political officials}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lee, Bill}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:American construction businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Auburn University alumni]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Governors of Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Franklin, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Republican Party state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:Tennessee Republicans]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n", "name_user": "2601:483:202:9e30:f4cf:878d:8010:dc1c", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Lee_(Tennessee_politician)"}
{"title_page": "Henry Farrell", "text_new": "{{about|the novelist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name           = Henry Farrell  \n| image          = Charles F Myers 5207.jpg \n| imagesize      = \n| caption        = Charles F. Myers c. 1952\n| birth_name     = Charles Farrell Myers\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date|1920|9|27}}\n| birth_place    = [[Madera County, California]], U.S.\n| death_date     = {{Death date and age|2006|3|29|1920|9|27}}\n| death_place    = [[Pacific Palisades, California]], U.S. \n| occupation     = Novelist, screenwriter\n| spouse         = [[Molly Dodd]] (19??-1981; her death)}}\n\n'''Henry Farrell''' (September 27, 1920 &ndash; March 29, 2006) was an American novelist and screenwriter, best known as the author of the renowned [[gothic horror]] story ''[[What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (novel)|What Ever Happened to Baby Jane?]]'', which was made into [[What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (film)|a film]] starring [[Bette Davis]] and [[Joan Crawford]].\n\n==Life and work==\n{{unreferenced section|date=April 2015}}\nHe was born '''Charles Farrell Myers''' in California, and grew up in Chowchilla, California. Under the name Charles F. Myer, he wrote the \"Toffee\" short stories. Later taking the pseudonym Henry Farrell, his first novel was ''The Hostage'', published in 1959.\n[[File:Fantastic adventures 195006.jpg|thumb|right|Myers's \"The Shades of Toffee\" was the cover story in the June 1950 issue of ''Fantastic Adventures]]\n[[File:Imagination 195207.jpg|thumb|Another Toffee story was cover-featured in ''[[Imagination (magazine)|Imagination]]'']]\nWith [[Lukas Heller]], he co-wrote the screenplay for ''[[Hush...Hush, Sweet Charlotte]]'' (1964), starring Davis and [[Olivia de Havilland]]. It was based on a story he wrote titled \"What Ever Happened to Cousin Charlotte?\", and the script earned Heller and Farrell a 1965 [[Edgar Award]] from the [[Mystery Writers of America]] for Best Motion Picture Screenplay. He wrote the original screenplay for ''[[What's the Matter with Helen?]]'' (1971), which starred [[Debbie Reynolds]] and [[Shelley Winters]].\n\nHis wife was actress [[Molly Dodd]], who died in 1981. Dodd appeared in small roles in two movies written by Farrell, the TV production ''[[How Awful About Allan]]'', starring [[Anthony Perkins]] and [[Julie Harris (American actress)|Julie Harris]] and ''What's the Matter with Helen?'' French director [[Fran\u00e7ois Truffaut]]'s 1972 movie ''[[Such a Gorgeous Kid Like Me]]'' was based on Farrell's 1967 novel of the same name.\n\n==Death ==\nHenry Farrell died in his home in Pacific Palisades, California at age 85. According to his obituary, he completed another novel, titled ''A Piece of Clarisse'', shortly before his death [https://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/04/books/04farrell.html]. There is currently no word on publication.\n\n==Novels==\n*''The Hostage'' (1959)\n*''[[What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (novel)|What Ever Happened to Baby Jane?]]'' (1960)\n*''Death on the Sixth Day'' (1961)\n*''How Awful About Allan'' (1963)\n*''Such a Gorgeous Kid Like Me'' (1967)\n\n==Short Stories==\n*\"What Ever Happened to Cousin Charlotte?\"\n*\"The Eyes of Charles Sand\"\n*\"Where Beauty Lies\"\n*\"The Do-Gooder\"\n\n==Filmography==\n====Films====\n* ''[[Hush...Hush, Sweet Charlotte]]'' (1964) (with [[Lukas Heller]])\n* ''[[How Awful About Allan]]'' (1970) (TV movie)\n* ''[[The House That Would Not Die]]'' (1970) (TV movie)\n* ''[[What's the Matter with Helen?]]'' (1971)\n* ''The Eyes of Charles Sand'' (1972) (TV movie)\n\n====TV series====\n* ''[[Bus Stop (TV series)|Bus Stop]]'' (1961) - 1 episode (\"Jaws of Darkness\")\n* ''[[Alfred Hitchcock Presents]]'' (1962) - 1 episode (\"Where Beauty Lies\")\n* ''[[Perry Mason (TV series)|Perry Mason]]'' (1965-66) - 2 episodes (\"The Case of the Wrathful Wraith\", \"The Case of the Bogus Buccaneers\")\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of horror fiction authors]]\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0268230}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Farrell, Henry}}\n[[Category:1920 births]]\n[[Category:2006 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American novelists]]\n[[Category:American horror writers]]\n[[Category:American male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:American male novelists]]\n[[Category:Disease-related deaths in California]]\n[[Category:Edgar Award winners]]\n[[Category:American male short story writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American short story writers]]\n[[Category:People from Madera County, California]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male writers]]\n[[Category:Novelists from California]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from California]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the novelist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name           = Henry Farrell  \n| image          = Charles F Myers 5207.jpg \n| imagesize      = \n| caption        = Charles F. Myers c. 1952\n| birth_name     = Charles Farrell Myers\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date|1920|9|27}}\n| birth_place    = [[Madera County, California]], U.S.\n| death_date     = {{Death date and age|2006|3|29|1920|9|27}}\n| death_place    = [[Pacific Palisades, California]], U.S. \n| occupation     = Novelist, screenwriter\n| spouse         = [[Molly Dodd]] (19??-1981; her death)}}\n\n'''Henry Farrell''' (September 27, 1920 &ndash; March 29, 2006) was an American novelist and screenwriter, best known as the author of the renowned [[gothic horror]] story ''[[What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (novel)|What Ever Happened to Baby Jane?]]'', which was made into [[What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (film)|a film]] starring [[Bette Davis]] and [[Joan Crawford]].\n\n==Life and work==\n{{unreferenced section|date=April 2015}}\nHe was born '''Charles Farrell Myers''' in California, and grew up in Chowchilla, California. Under the name Charles F. Myer, he wrote the \"Toffee\" short stories. Later taking the pseudonym Henry Farrell, his first novel was ''The Hostage'', published in 1959.\n[[File:Fantastic adventures 195006.jpg|thumb|right|Myers's \"The Shades of Toffee\" was the cover story in the June 1950 issue of ''Fantastic Adventures]]\n[[File:Imagination 195207.jpg|thumb|Another Toffee story was cover-featured in ''[[Imagination (magazine)|Imagination]]'']]\nWith [[Lukas Heller]], he co-wrote the screenplay for ''[[Hush...Hush, Sweet Charlotte]]'' (1964), starring Davis and [[Olivia de Havilland]]. It was based on a story he wrote titled \"What Ever Happened to Cousin Charlotte?\", and the script earned Heller and Farrell a 1965 [[Edgar Award]] from the [[Mystery Writers of America]] for Best Motion Picture Screenplay. He wrote the original screenplay for ''[[What's the Matter with Helen?]]'' (1971), which starred [[Debbie Reynolds]] and [[Shelley Winters]].\n\nHis wife was actress [[Molly Dodd]], who died in 1981. Dodd appeared in small roles in two movies written by Farrell, the TV production ''[[How Awful About Allan]]'', starring [[Anthony Perkins]] and [[Julie Harris (American actress)|Julie Harris]] and ''What's the Matter with Helen?'' French director [[Fran\u00e7ois Truffaut]]'s 1972 movie ''[[Such a Gorgeous Kid Like Me]]'' was based on Farrell's 1967 novel of the same name.\n\n==Death ==\nHenry Farrell died in his home in Pacific Palisades, California at age 85. According to his obituary, he completed another novel, titled ''A Piece of Clarisse'', shortly before his death [https://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/04/books/04farrell.html]. There is currently no word on publication.\n\n==Novels==\n*''The Hostage'' (1959)\n*''[[What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (novel)|What Ever Happened to Baby Jane?]]'' (1960)\n*''Death on the Sixth Day'' (1961)\n*''How Awful About Allan'' (1963)\n*''Such a Gorgeous Kid Like Me'' (1967)\n\n==Short Stories==\n*\"What Ever Happened to Cousin Charlotte?\"\n*\"The Eyes of Charles Sand\"\n*\"Where Beauty Lies\"\n*\"The Do-Gooder\"\n\n==Filmography==\n===Films===\n* ''[[Hush...Hush, Sweet Charlotte]]'' (1964) (with [[Lukas Heller]])\n* ''[[How Awful About Allan]]'' (1970) (TV movie)\n* ''[[The House That Would Not Die]]'' (1970) (TV movie)\n* ''[[What's the Matter with Helen?]]'' (1971)\n* ''The Eyes of Charles Sand'' (1972) (TV movie)\n\n===TV series===\n* ''[[Bus Stop (TV series)|Bus Stop]]'' (1961) - 1 episode (\"Jaws of Darkness\")\n* ''[[Alfred Hitchcock Presents]]'' (1962) - 1 episode (\"Where Beauty Lies\")\n* ''[[Perry Mason (TV series)|Perry Mason]]'' (1965-66) - 2 episodes (\"The Case of the Wrathful Wraith\", \"The Case of the Bogus Buccaneers\")\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of horror fiction authors]]\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0268230}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Farrell, Henry}}\n[[Category:1920 births]]\n[[Category:2006 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American novelists]]\n[[Category:American horror writers]]\n[[Category:American male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:American male novelists]]\n[[Category:Disease-related deaths in California]]\n[[Category:Edgar Award winners]]\n[[Category:American male short story writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American short story writers]]\n[[Category:People from Madera County, California]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male writers]]\n[[Category:Novelists from California]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from California]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFilmography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_Farrell"}
{"title_page": "Korean Demilitarized Zone", "text_new": "{{short description|Demilitarized zone running across the Korean Peninsula}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox military installation\n| name             = Korean DMZ\n| native_name      = {{lang|ko|\ud55c\ubc18\ub3c4 \ube44\ubb34\uc7a5 \uc9c0\ub300}}<br/>{{lang|ko|\u97d3\u534a\u5cf6\u975e\u6b66\u88dd\u5730\u5e36}}<br/>Hanbando Bimujang jidae<br/>Hanbando Pimujang chidae\n| image            = File:Korea DMZ sentry.jpg\n| caption          = A South Korean checkpoint at the Civilian Control Line, located outside of the DMZ\n| location         = [[Korean Peninsula]]\n| image_map        = Korea DMZ.svg\n| image_map_caption = The Korean DMZ denoted by the red highlighted area. The blue line indicates the international border.\n| type             = [[Demilitarised zone|DMZ]]\n| builder          = {{plainlist|\n*{{flag|Democratic People's Republic of Korea}}\n*{{flag|Republic of Korea}}\n*[[United Nations Command]]\n}}\n| length           = {{convert|250|km|mi}}\n| used             = since {{start date|1953|07|27|df=y}}\n| condition        = Fully manned and operational\n| open_to_public   = No; access only granted by the North or United Nations Command. \n| events           = [[Division of Korea]]\n}}\n{{Campaignbox Korean Cold War}}\nThe '''Korean Demilitarized Zone''' ('''DMZ'''; [[Hangul|Chos\u014fn'g\u016dl/Hangul]]: {{Korean|hangul=\ud55c\ubc18\ub3c4 \ube44\ubb34\uc7a5 \uc9c0\ub300|hanja=|rr=|mr=|labels=no|context=}}; [[Hanja]]: {{Lang|ko-Hani|\u97d3\u534a\u5cf6\u975e\u6b66\u88dd\u5730\u5e36}}) is a strip of land running across the [[Korean Peninsula]]. It is established by the provisions of the [[Korean Armistice Agreement]] to serve as a [[buffer zone]] between [[North Korea]] and [[South Korea]]. The [[demilitarized zone]] (DMZ) is a [[border barrier]] that divides the Korean Peninsula roughly in half.  It was created by agreement between North Korea, [[China]] and the [[United Nations Command]] in 1953. The DMZ is {{convert|250|km|mi|abbr=off}} long, and about {{convert|4|km|mi|abbr=off}} wide.\n\nWithin the DMZ is a meeting point between the two nations in the small [[Joint Security Area]] (JSA) near the western end of the zone, where negotiations take place. There have been various incidents in and around the DMZ, with military and civilian casualties on both sides. \n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Location==\nThe Korean Demilitarized Zone intersects but does not follow the [[38th parallel north]], which was the border before the [[Korean War]]. It crosses the parallel on an angle, with the west end of the DMZ lying south of the parallel and the east end lying north of it.\n[[File:Korea at night.png|thumb|right|The Korean Demilitarized Zone is visible at night from space due to a noticeable lack of lighting in the northern half of the Korean Peninsula]]\nThe DMZ is {{convert|250|km|mi|abbr=off}} long,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=3660 |title=Korean Demilitarized Zone: Image of the Day |publisher=NASA Earth Observatory |accessdate=2010-03-26 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100316031349/http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=3660 |archivedate=16 March 2010 }}</ref> approximately {{convert|4|km|mi|abbr=on}} wide. Though the zone is demilitarized, the border beyond that strip is one of the most heavily [[Militarization|militarized]] borders in the world.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2011/06/24/the-worlds-most-dangerous-borders/ |title=The world's most dangerous borders |first=Philip |last=Walker |magazine=Foreign Policy |date=24 June 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170308153821/http://foreignpolicy.com/2011/06/24/the-worlds-most-dangerous-borders/ |archivedate=8 March 2017 }}</ref> The [[Northern Limit Line]], or NLL, is the disputed maritime [[demarcation line]] between North and South Korea in the [[Yellow Sea]], not agreed in the armistice. The coastline and islands on both sides of the NLL are also heavily militarized.<ref>Elferink, Alex G. Oude. (1994). {{Google books|x-VYb-wida8C|''The Law of Maritime Boundary Delimitation: a Case Study of the Russian Federation''|page=314}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Korea demilitarized zone map - 1969.jpg|thumb|upright=1.4|Detail of the DMZ]]\n[[File:KPA3-2a.jpg|thumb|A portion of the North Korean DMZ seen from the [[Joint Security Area]] in January 1976]]\n{{main|Division of Korea}}\nThe [[38th parallel north]]\u2014which divides the Korean Peninsula roughly in half\u2014was the original boundary between the United States and Soviet Union's brief administration areas of Korea at the end of [[World War II]]. Upon the creation of the [[Democratic People's Republic of Korea]] (DPRK, informally \"North Korea\") and the [[Republic of Korea]] (ROK, informally \"South Korea\") in 1948, it became a ''[[de facto]]'' international border and one of the most tense fronts in the [[Cold War]].\n\nBoth the North and the South remained dependent on their sponsor states from 1948 to the outbreak of the [[Korean War]]. That conflict, which claimed over three million lives and divided the Korean Peninsula along ideological lines, commenced on 25 June 1950, with a full-front DPRK invasion across the 38th parallel, and ended in 1953 after international intervention pushed the [[Front (military)|front]] of the war back to near the 38th parallel.\n\nIn the [[Korean Armistice Agreement|Armistice Agreement]] of 27 July 1953, the DMZ was created as each side agreed to move their troops back {{convert|2000|m|mi|abbr=in}} from the front line, creating a buffer zone {{convert|4|km|mi|abbr=on}} wide. The [[Military Demarcation Line]] (MDL) goes through the center of the DMZ and indicates where the front was when the agreement was signed.\n\nOwing to this theoretical [[stalemate]], and genuine hostility between the North and the South, large numbers of troops are stationed along both sides of the line, each side guarding against potential aggression from the other side, even {{Age|1953|July|27}} years after its establishment. The armistice agreement explains exactly how many military personnel and what kind of weapons are allowed in the DMZ. Soldiers from both sides may patrol inside the DMZ, but they may not cross the MDL. However, heavily armed ROK soldiers patrol under the aegis of [[military police]], and have memorized each line of the armistice.<ref name=\"On Patrol in the DMZ\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/mar/21/north-korea-south-korea-dmz-landmines |title=On patrol in the DMZ: North Korean landmines, biting winds and tin cans: As tensions on the peninsula escalate, a former South Korean guard describes life at one of the world's most fortified borders. NK News reports |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2016-03-21 |accessdate=2016-04-18 |author=Ahn, JH |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416132851/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/mar/21/north-korea-south-korea-dmz-landmines |archivedate=16 April 2016 }}</ref>  [[List of border incidents involving North and South Korea|Sporadic outbreaks of violence]] have killed over 500 South Korean soldiers, 50 US soldiers and 250 soldiers from DPRK along the DMZ between 1953 and 1999.<ref>{{cite news|last=Potts |first=Rolf |title=Korea's no-man's-land |url=http://www.salon.com/1999/02/03/feature_115/ |work=Salon |accessdate=31 January 2013 |date=3 February 1999 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130215050040/http://www.salon.com/1999/02/03/feature_115/ |archivedate=15 February 2013 }}</ref>\n\n[[Daeseong-dong]] (also written ''Tae Sung Dong'') and [[Kijong-dong|Kij\u014fng-dong]] (also known as the \"Peace Village\") are the only settlements allowed by the armistice committee to remain within the boundaries of the DMZ.<ref name=\"Tae\">{{cite news|url=http://www.stripes.com/article.asp?section=104&article=52586 |title=DMZ sixth-graders become graduates |newspaper=[[Stars and Stripes (newspaper)|Stars and Stripes]] |date=2008-02-19 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090611232350/http://www.stripes.com/article.asp?section=104&article=52586 |archivedate=11 June 2009 }}</ref> Residents of Tae Sung Dong are governed and protected by the [[United Nations Command]] and are generally required to spend at least 240 nights per year in the village to maintain their residency.<ref name = \"Tae\"/> In 2008, the village had a population of 218 people.<ref name = \"Tae\"/> The villagers of Tae Sung Dong are direct descendants of people who owned the land before the 1950\u201353 Korean War.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.army.mil/-news/2009/01/26/16093-santa-mobbed-by-students-during-visit-to-joint-security-area/ |title=Santa mobbed by students during visit to Joint Security Area |publisher=army.mil.com -The Official U.S. Army Website |accessdate=2009-12-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091124043626/http://www.army.mil/-news/2009/01/26/16093-santa-mobbed-by-students-during-visit-to-joint-security-area/ |archivedate=24 November 2009 }}</ref>\n\nTo continue to deter North Korean incursion, in 2014 the United States government exempted the Korean DMZ from its pledge to eliminate [[Anti-personnel mine|anti-personnel landmines]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/korearealtime/2014/09/24/why-the-korean-peninsula-keeps-landmines/ |title=Why the Korean Peninsula Keeps Land Mines |last=Kwaak |first=Jeyup S |newspaper=Wall Street Journal |date=24 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924070350/https://blogs.wsj.com/korearealtime/2014/09/24/why-the-korean-peninsula-keeps-landmines/ |archivedate=24 September 2014 }}</ref> On 1 October 2018, however, a 20-day process began to remove landmines from both sides of the DMZ.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/10/01/north-south-korea-begin-removing-landmines-along-fortified-border/|title=North and South Korea begin removing landmines along fortified DMZ|last=Agency|first=Reuters News|date=2018-10-01|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref>\n\n==Joint Security Area==\n[[File:070401 Panmunjeom3.jpg|thumb|View of the North from the southern side of the [[Joint Security Area|JSA]]]]\n[[File:Joint Security Area from North Korea.jpg|thumb|Conference Row seen from the northern side of the [[Joint Security Area|JSA]]]]\n{{main|Joint Security Area}}\nInside the DMZ, near the western coast of the peninsula, [[Panmunjom]] is the home of the Joint Security Area (JSA). Originally, it was the only connection between North and South Korea<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imcom.korea.army.mil/imakoroweb/sites/local/news/020808_IMCOMK_DMZ.asp |title=Panmunjon |publisher=army.mil.com |accessdate=2009-12-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905081008/http://imcom.korea.army.mil/imakoroweb/sites/local/news/020808_IMCOMK_DMZ.asp |archivedate=5 September 2009 }}</ref> but that changed on 17 May 2007, when a [[Korail]] train went through the DMZ to the North on the new [[Donghae Bukbu Line]] built on the east coast of Korea. However, the resurrection of this line was short-lived, as it closed again in July 2008 following an incident in which a South Korean tourist was shot and killed.\n\nThere are several buildings on both the north and the south side of the [[Military Demarcation Line]] (MDL), and there have been some built on top of it. The JSA is the location where all [[Inter-Korean summits|negotiations]] since 1953 have been held, including statements of Korean solidarity, which have generally amounted to little except a slight decline of [[Inter-Korean conflict|tensions]]. The MDL goes through the conference rooms and down the middle of the conference tables where the North Koreans and the United Nations Command (primarily South Koreans and Americans) meet face to face.\n\nWithin the JSA are a number of buildings for joint meetings called Conference Rooms. These are used for direct talks between the Korean War participants and parties to the armistice. Facing the Conference Row buildings are the North Korean ''[[Panmungak]]'' ({{lang-en|Panmun Hall}}) and the South Korean [[Freedom House (Joint Security Area)|Freedom House]]. In 1994, North Korea enlarged Panmungak by adding a third floor. In 1998, South Korea built a new Freedom House for its [[Red Cross]] staff and to possibly host reunions of families separated by the [[Korean War]]. The new building incorporated the old Freedom House Pagoda within its design.\n\nSince 1953 there have been occasional confrontations and skirmishes within the JSA. The [[Korean axe murder incident|axe murder incident]] in August 1976 involved the attempted trimming of a tree which resulted in two deaths ([[Captain (United States O-3)|Captain]] Arthur Bonifas and [[First Lieutenant]] Mark Barrett). Another incident occurred on 23 November 1984, when a Soviet tourist named Vasily Matuzok (sometimes spelled Matusak), who was part of an official trip to the JSA (hosted by the North), ran across the MDL shouting that he wanted to [[defection|defect]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stripes.com/news/pacific/korea/general-revisits-deadly-1984-thanksgiving-firefight-at-dmz-1.161443 |title=General revisits deadly 1984 Thanksgiving firefight at DMZ |work=Stars and Stripes |accessdate=13 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309182210/http://www.stripes.com/news/pacific/korea/general-revisits-deadly-1984-thanksgiving-firefight-at-dmz-1.161443 |archivedate=9 March 2016 }}</ref> North Korean troops immediately chased after him, opening fire. Border guards on the South Korean side returned fire, eventually surrounding the North Koreans as they pursued Matusak. One South Korean and three North Korean soldiers were killed in the action, and Matusak was not captured.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/ops/dmz-list.htm |title=Korea Demilitarized Zone Incidents |date=2009-05-28 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100331152533/http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/ops/dmz-list.htm |archivedate=31 March 2010 }}</ref>\n\nIn late 2009, South Korean forces in conjunction with the [[United Nations Command]] began renovation of its three guard posts and two checkpoint buildings within the JSA compound. Construction was designed to enlarge and modernize the structures. Work was undertaken a year after North Korea finished replacing four JSA guard posts on its side of the MDL.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.stripes.com/article.asp?section=104&article=65534 |title=South Korea to revamp DMZ towers |newspaper=[[Stars and Stripes (newspaper)|Stars and Stripes]] |date=2009-10-22 |accessdate=2009-11-09 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091022163155/http://www.stripes.com/article.asp?section=104&article=65534 |archivedate=22 October 2009 }}</ref> On 15 October 2018, during the high-level talks in Panmunjom, military officials of the rank of [[colonel]] from the two Koreas and Burke Hamilton, Secretary of the [[United Nations Command, Military Armistice Commission, Korea|UNC Military Armistice Commission]], announced measures to reduce conventional military threats, such as creating buffer zones along their land and sea boundaries and a no-fly zone above the border, removing 11 front-line guard posts by December, and [[demining]] sections of the Demilitarized Zone.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kait8.com/2018/10/15/koreas-hold-high-level-peace-talks|title=Koreas agree to break ground on inter-Korean railroad|last=TONG-HYUNG|first=KIM|date=|work=Kait8.com|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Villages==\n[[File:Propagandavillage.JPG|thumb|North Korean [[Kij\u014fng-dong]], seen from South Korea]]\nBoth North and South Korea maintain ''peace villages'' in sight of each other's side of the DMZ. In the South, [[Daeseong-dong]] is administered under the terms of the DMZ. Villagers are classed as Republic of Korea citizens, but are [[Tax exemption|exempt]] from paying tax and other civic requirements such as [[Conscription in South Korea|military service]]. In the North, [[Kij\u014fng-dong]] features a number of brightly painted, poured-concrete multi-story buildings and apartments with electric lighting. These features represented an unheard-of level of luxury for rural Koreans, North or South, in the 1950s. The town was oriented so that the bright blue roofs and white sides of the buildings would be the most distinguishing features when viewed from the border. However, based on scrutiny with modern telescopic lenses, it has been claimed the buildings are mere concrete shells lacking window glass or even interior rooms,<ref name=\"potts\">{{Cite journal|last=Potts|first=Rolf|date=1999-02-03|title=Korea's No-man's-land|url=http://www.salon.com/1999/02/03/feature_115/|url-status=live|journal=[[Salon (magazine)|Salon]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130215050040/http://www.salon.com/1999/02/03/feature_115/|archivedate=15 February 2013}}</ref><ref>O'Neill, Tom. \"Korea's DMZ: Dangerous Divide\". ''National Geographic'', July 2003.</ref> with the building lights turned on and off at set times and the empty sidewalks swept by a [[skeleton crew]] of [[Property caretaker|caretaker]]s in an effort to preserve the illusion of activity.<ref>{{cite web |last=Silpasornprasit |first=Susan |url=http://imcom.korea.army.mil/imakoroweb/sites/local/news/020808_IMCOMK_DMZ.asp |title=Day trip to the DMZ: A look inside the Korean Demilitarized Zone |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090330022530/http://imcom.korea.army.mil/imakoroweb/sites/local/news/020808_IMCOMK_DMZ.asp |archive-date=30 March 2009 |publisher=IMCOM-Korea Region Public Affairs Office, US Army}}</ref>\n\n===Flagpoles===\n{{multiple image|image1=Daeseong-dong_Scene.jpg|caption1=South Korean [[Daeseong-dong]] and its flagpole|image2=Gijeong-ri Flag.jpg|caption2=The world's fourth-tallest flagpole (160m) flying a [[Flag of North Korea|North Korean flag]] over [[Kijong-dong|Kij\u014fng-dong]] near [[Panmunjom]]}}\nIn the 1980s, the South Korean government built a {{Convert|98.4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[flagpole|flag pole]] in Daeseong-dong, which flies a [[flag of South Korea|South Korean flag]] weighing {{Convert|130|kg|lb|0|abbr=off}}. In what some have called the \"flagpole war,\" the North Korean government responded by building the {{Convert|160|m|ft|0|abbr=on|sp=us}} [[Panmunjeom flagpole]] in Kij\u014fng-dong, only {{Convert|1.2|km|mi|1|abbr=on}} west of the border with South Korea. It flies a {{Convert|270|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} [[flag of North Korea]]. As of 2014, the Panmunjom flagpole is the fourth tallest in the world, after the [[Jeddah Flagpole]] in [[Jeddah]], [[Saudi Arabia]], at {{Convert|170|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}, the [[Dushanbe Flagpole]] in [[Dushanbe]], [[Tajikistan]], at {{Convert|165|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} and the pole at the [[National Flag Square]] in [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]], which is {{Convert|162|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/asiapcf/east/02/19/koreas.dmz/ |title=CNN.com \u2013 Korea's DMZ: 'Scariest place on Earth' |accessdate=2007-10-23 |date=2002-02-20 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012164210/http://edition.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/asiapcf/east/02/19/koreas.dmz/ |archivedate=12 October 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://economy.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_blogview.asp?at_code=370439 |script-title=ko:\uac1c\uc131\uc5d0 '\uad6c\uba4d\ud0c4' 5\ub9cc\uc7a5 \ubc30\ub2ec\ud588\uc2b5\ub2c8\ub2e4 |work=economy.ohmynews.com |accessdate=2006-12-06 |language=ko }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=Al83tito |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==DMZ-related incidents and incursions==\n{{Main|List of border incidents involving North and South Korea}}\nSince demarcation, the DMZ has had numerous cases of incidents and incursions by both sides, although the North Korean government typically never acknowledges direct responsibility for any of these incidents (there are exceptions, such as the axe incident).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fas.org/man/crs/RL30004.pdf |title=North Korea: Chronology of Provocations, 1950 \u2013 2003 |accessdate=2012-02-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060905062431/http://www.fas.org/man/crs/RL30004.pdf |archivedate=5 September 2006 }}</ref> This was particularly intense during the [[Korean DMZ Conflict (1966\u20131969)]] when a series of skirmishes along the DMZ resulted in the deaths of 43 [[US soldier|American]], 299 [[South Korean soldier|South Korean]] and 397 [[North Korean army|North Korean soldiers]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Bolger|first=Daniel|title=Scenes from an Unfinished War: Low intensity conflict in Korea 1966\u20131969|publisher=Diane Publishing Co|isbn=978-0-7881-1208-9|year=1991}}</ref> This included the [[Blue House raid|Blue House Raid]] in 1968, an attempt to [[Assassination|assassinate]] President [[Park Chung-hee|Park Chung Hee]] at the [[Blue House]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cgsc.leavenworth.army.mil/carl/download/csipubs/scenes/scen_c3.pdf |title=Scenes from an Unfinished War: Low-Intensity Conflict in Korea, 1966\u20131968 |publisher=Cgsc.leavenworth.army.mil |accessdate=2012-02-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090325103728/http://cgsc.leavenworth.army.mil/carl/download/csipubs/scenes/scen_c3.pdf |archivedate=25 March 2009 }}</ref>\n\nIn 1976, in now-[[Declassification|declassified]] meeting minutes, U.S. deputy secretary of defense [[William Clements]] told U.S. secretary of state [[Henry Kissinger]] that there had been 200 raids or incursions into North Korea from the south, though not by the U.S. military.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve12/d286 |title=Minutes of Washington Special Actions Group Meeting, Washington, 25 August 1976, 10:30 a.m. |date=25 August 1976 |accessdate=12 May 2012 |publisher=[[Office of the Historian]], US Department of State |quote=Clements: I like it. It doesn't have an overt character. I have been told that there have been 200 other such operations and that none of these have surfaced. Kissinger: It is different for us with the War Powers Act. I don't remember any such operations. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120925121535/http://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve12/d286 |archivedate=25 September 2012 }}</ref> Details of only a few of these incursions have become public, including raids by South Korean forces in 1967 that had sabotaged about 50 North Korean facilities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2011/02/116_80936.html |title=S. Korea raided North with captured agents in 1967 |newspaper=The Korea Times |author=Lee Tae-hoon |date=7 February 2011 |accessdate=12 May 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121001195904/http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2011/02/116_80936.html |archivedate=1 October 2012 }}</ref>\n\n===Incursion tunnels===\n{{See also|Tunnel warfare}}\nSince 15 November 1974, South Korea has discovered four tunnels crossing the DMZ that had been dug by North Korea. The orientation of the blasting lines within each tunnel indicated they were dug by North Korea. North Korea claimed that the tunnels were for [[coal mining]]; however, no coal was found in the tunnels, which were dug through granite. Some of the tunnel walls were painted black to give the appearance of [[anthracite]].<ref>{{cite book|first=Jim|last=Sides|title=Almost Home|publisher=Xulon Press|year=2009|isbn=978-1-60791-740-3|page=118}}</ref>\n\nThe tunnels are believed to have been planned as a military invasion route by North Korea. They run in a north\u2013south direction and do not have branches. Following each discovery, engineering within the tunnels has become progressively more advanced. For example, the third tunnel sloped slightly upwards as it progressed southward, to prevent [[water stagnation]]. Today, visitors from the south may visit the second, third and fourth tunnels through guided tours.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demilitarized Zone |publisher=GlobalSecurity.org |url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/ops/dmz.htm |accessdate=2007-11-09 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071105034940/http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/ops/dmz.htm |archivedate=5 November 2007 }}</ref>\n\n====First tunnel====\nThe first of the tunnels was discovered on 20 November 1974, by a South Korean Army patrol, noticing steam rising from the ground. The initial discovery was met with [[Automatic firearm|automatic fire]] from North Korean soldiers. Five days later, during a subsequent exploration of this tunnel, [[United States Navy|US Navy]] Commander Robert M. Ballinger and [[Republic of Korea Marine Corps|ROK Marine Corps]] Major Kim Hah-chul were killed in the tunnel by a North Korean explosive device. The blast also wounded five Americans and one South Korean from the United Nations Command.\n\nThe tunnel, which was about {{convert|3|by|4|ft|1|abbr=on|order=flip}}, extended more than {{convert|1|km|yd|abbr=on}} beyond the MDL into South Korea. The tunnel was reinforced with concrete slabs and had electric power and lighting. There were [[Weapon storage area|weapon storage]] and sleeping areas. A [[narrow-gauge railway]] with carts had also been installed. Estimates based on the tunnel's size suggest it would have allowed considerable numbers of soldiers to pass through it.<ref name=bermudez_js>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621051225/http://www.korean-war.com/Archives/2002/02/msg00289.html |archivedate=2013-06-21 |url=http://www.korean-war.com/Archives/2002/02/msg00289.html |title=Tunnels under the DMZ |author=Bermudez, Joseph S. Jr |accessdate=2010-03-26 |website=korean-war.com}}</ref>\n\n====Second tunnel====\n[[File:Entrance to the 4th Infiltration Tunnel, Korean DMZ.jpg|thumb|Entrance to the North Korean-dug 4th Infiltration Tunnel, Korean DMZ]]\nThe second tunnel was discovered on 19 March 1975. It is of similar length to the first tunnel. It is located between {{convert|50|and|160|m|ft|abbr=on}} below ground, but is larger than the first, approximately {{convert|2|by|2|m|ft|0|sp=us|abbr=in}}.\n\n====Third tunnel====\n{{main|Third Tunnel of Aggression}}\nThe third tunnel was discovered on 17 October 1978. Unlike the previous two, the third tunnel was discovered following a tip from a [[North Korean defectors|North Korean defector]]. This tunnel is about {{convert|1600|m|ft|abbr=on}} long and about {{convert|73|m|ft|abbr=on}} below ground.<ref>{{cite book|last=Robinson|first=Martin|title=Seoul|year=2009|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=978-1-74104-774-5|pages=162}}</ref> Foreign visitors touring the South Korean DMZ may view inside this tunnel using a sloped access shaft.\n\n====Fourth tunnel====\nA fourth tunnel was discovered on 3 March 1990, north of [[Haean]] town in the former [[Punchbowl, Korea|Punchbowl]] battlefield. The tunnel's dimensions are {{convert|2|by|2|m|ft|0|sp=us|abbr=in}}, and it is {{convert|145|m|ft}} deep. The method of construction is almost identical in structure to the second and the third tunnels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panmunjomtour.com/english/dmz/dmz_20.htm |title=The Fourth Infiltration Tunnel |publisher=Panmunjom Travel Center |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070309084651/http://www.panmunjomtour.com/english/dmz/dmz_20.htm |archivedate= 9 March 2007 }}</ref>\n\n===Korean wall===\n[[File:The Korean Wall in the DMZ.JPG|thumb|The Korean wall, or anti-tank barrier, in the [[demilitarized zone]] seen through binoculars from the North Korean side.]]\nAccording to North Korea, between 1977 and 1979 the South Korean and United States authorities constructed a concrete wall along the DMZ.<ref name=\"tetteroo\"/> North Korea, however, began to propagate information about the wall after the [[fall of the Berlin Wall]] in 1989, when the symbolism of a wall [[Injustice|unjustly]] dividing a people became more apparent.<ref>{{cite book|last=Salzinger|first=Caroline|translator-last=Lempinen|translator-first=Ulla|title=Terveisi\u00e4 pahan akselilta: Arkea ja politiikkaa maailman suljetuimmissa valtioissa|year=2008|publisher=Atena|location=Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4|language=fi|isbn=978-951-796-521-7|page=40}}</ref>\n\nVarious organizations, such as the North Korean tour guide company Korea Konsult, claimed a wall was dividing Korea, saying that:\n\n{{quote|In the area south of the Military Demarcation Line, which cuts across Korea at its waist, there is a concrete wall which ... stretches more than {{convert|240|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} from east to west, is {{convert|5|-|8|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} high, {{convert|10|-|19|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} thick at the bottom, and {{convert|3|-|7|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} wide in the upper part. It is set with wire entanglements and dotted with gun embrasures, look-outs and varieties of military establishments.<!-- not in citation: [...] the South Korean rulers built this wall over a period of many years from 1977.--><ref>{{cite web|title=DMZ: Demilitarized Zone|url=http://koreakonsult.net/Attraction_DMZ_eng.html|publisher=Korea Konsult|accessdate=16 April 2015}}</ref>}}\n\nIn December 1999, Chu Chang-jun, [[China\u2013North Korea relations|North Korea's ambassador to China]], repeated claims that a \"wall\" divided Korea. He said the south side of the wall is packed with soil, which permits access to the top of the wall and makes it effectively invisible from the south side. He also claimed that it served as a bridgehead for any northward [[invasion]].<ref name=\"Wall\">{{cite web|url=http://www.korean-war.com/Archives/2000/12/msg00041.html |title=New York Times, 1999 |publisher=Korean-war.com |accessdate=2012-02-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308122740/http://www.korean-war.com/Archives/2000/12/msg00041.html |archivedate= 8 March 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Tear Down the Korean Wall |url=http://www.kimsoft.com/1997/nk9912.htm |publisher=DPRK UN Mission |date=1999-12-03 |accessdate=2007-10-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060329064336/http://www.kimsoft.com/1997/nk9912.htm |archivedate=29 March 2006 }}</ref>\n\nThe United States and South Korea deny the wall's existence, although they do claim there are [[Anti-tank obstacles|anti-tank barriers]] along some sections of the DMZ.<ref>{{cite news|last=Eckholm |first=Erik |date=8 December 1999 |title=Where Most See Ramparts, North Korea Imagines a Wall |url=http://partners.nytimes.com/library/world/asia/120899nkorea-skorea.html |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=26 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816222047/http://partners.nytimes.com/library/world/asia/120899nkorea-skorea.html |archivedate=16 August 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn the [[RT (TV network)|RT]] documentary ''10 Days in North Korea'', the crew shot footage of a wall as seen from North Korea and described it as a \"5 metre high wall stretching from east to west\".<ref>{{cite web|title=10 Days in North Korea |url=http://rt.com/shows/documentary/203135-north-korea-kim-jongun/ |author=\u00c1ngela Gallardo Bernal |publisher=RT |accessdate=20 February 2017 |date=9 November 2014 |id=at 19:30 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222101514/https://www.rt.com/shows/documentary/203135-north-korea-kim-jongun/ |archivedate=22 December 2016 }}</ref> Dutch journalist and filmmaker [[Peter Tetteroo]] also shot footage of a barrier in 2001 which his North Korean guides said was the Korean Wall.<ref name=\"tetteroo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmakers.com/index.php?a=filmDetail&filmID=1138 |title=Welcome to North Korea: A film by Peter Tetteroo for KRO Television |accessdate=2009-12-29 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711001620/http://www.filmakers.com/index.php?a=filmDetail&filmID=1138 |archivedate=11 July 2011 }}</ref>\n\nA 2007 [[Reuters]] report revealed that there is no coast to coast wall located across the DMZ and that the pictures of a \"wall\" which have been used in North Korean propaganda have merely been pictures of concrete anti-tank barriers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-korea-north-wall/north-korea-asks-south-to-tear-down-imaginary-wall-idUSSEO20068620071231|title=North Korea asks South to tear down imaginary wall|first=Jon|last=Herskovitz|date=31 December 2007|work=Reuters|accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref> While 800,000 landmines were being removed in 2018, it was shown that the [[Joint Security Area]] along the Korean border was guarded by standard [[barbed wire]].<ref name=bbckoreaoct>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-45704909|title=Koreas begin clearing landmines from heavily fortified border|last=|first=|date=1 October 2018|work=BBC News|access-date=9 February 2019|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==North Korean side of the DMZ==\n[[File:Entrance_of_Joint_Security_Area,_Korean_Demilitarized_Zone,_DPRK_side.jpg|thumb|DMZ, North Korea. [[Electric fence]]s are used in the Korean Demilitarized Zone as a means to seal off North Korea from South Korea. Behind the fence, there is a strip which has [[land mine]]s hidden beneath it.]]\nThe North Korean side of the DMZ primarily serves to prevent North Korean citizens from leaving North Korea. It also serves a similar function as the [[Berlin Wall]] and the [[inner German border]] did against its own citizens in the former [[East Germany]] in that it stops North Korean citizens from defecting to South Korea.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.qsl.net/ah6hy/SKDMZ.html |title=Korea Border Area |accessdate=2017-03-12 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914011727/http://www.qsl.net/ah6hy/SKDMZ.html |archivedate=14 September 2016 }} Bottom of the page. Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1982/05/20/world/north-korea-blocks-defections-across-dmz.html |title=North Korea Blocks Defections Across DMZ |accessdate=2017-03-12 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312202845/http://www.nytimes.com/1982/05/20/world/north-korea-blocks-defections-across-dmz.html |archivedate=12 March 2017 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=20 May 1982 |last1=Stokes |first1=Henry Scott }} Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref>\n\nFrom the armistice until 1972, approximately 7,700 North Korean soldiers and agents infiltrated South Korea to sabotage military bases and industrial areas.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/02/15/world/south-korean-movie-unlocks-door-on-a-once-secret-past.html?_r=0|title=South Korean Movie Unlocks Door on a Once-Secret Past|newspaper=The New York Times|author=Norimitsu Onishi|date=15 February 2014|accessdate=13 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nNorth Korea has thousands of artillery pieces near the DMZ. According to a 2018 article in ''[[The Economist]]'', North Korea could bombard Seoul with over 10,000 rounds every minute.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.economist.com/news/leaders/21735586-how-shifts-technology-and-geopolitics-are-renewing-threat-growing-danger|title=The Growing Danger of Great-Power Conflict|last=|first=|date=|journal=The Economist|language=en|access-date=2018-02-05}}</ref> Experts believe that 60 percent of its total [[artillery]] is positioned within a few kilometers of the DMZ acting as a deterrent against any South Korean invasion.\n\n==Propaganda==\n{{See also|Propaganda|Psychological warfare}}\n\n===Loudspeaker installations===\nFrom 1953 until 2004, both sides broadcast audio propaganda across the DMZ.<ref name=bbc-20040615/> Massive loudspeakers mounted on several of the buildings delivered DPRK propaganda broadcasts directed towards the south as well as propaganda radio broadcasts across the border.<ref name=\"potts\"/> In 2004, the North and South agreed to end the broadcasts.<ref name=\"bbc-20040615\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/3807409.stm|title=Koreas Switch off Loudspeakers|date=15 June 2004|accessdate=7 May 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040615123223/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/3807409.stm|archivedate=15 June 2004|url-status=live|publisher=BBC}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 August 2015, a border incident occurred where two South Korean soldiers were wounded after stepping on landmines that had allegedly been laid on the southern side of the DMZ by North Korean forces near an ROK guard post.<ref name=\"Choe Sang-hun\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/11/world/asia/north-korea-placed-mines-that-maimed-2-south-korean-soldiers-at-dmz-seoul-says.html?_r=0 |title=South Korea Accuses the North After Land Mines Maim Two Soldiers in DMZ |author=Choe Sang-hun |newspaper=New York Times |date=10 August 2015 |accessdate=13 August 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150813125328/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/11/world/asia/north-korea-placed-mines-that-maimed-2-south-korean-soldiers-at-dmz-seoul-says.html?_r=0 |archivedate=13 August 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Park |first=Ju-Min |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/08/10/us-southkorea-northkorea-mines-idUSKCN0QF07A20150810 |title=South Korea condemns North over land mine blast, vows retaliation |location=Seoul |work=[[Reuters]] |date=2015-08-10 |accessdate=2015-08-10 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150810235643/http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/08/10/us-southkorea-northkorea-mines-idUSKCN0QF07A20150810 |archivedate=10 August 2015 }}</ref> Both North Korea and South Korea then resumed broadcasting propaganda by loudspeaker.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/21/world/asia/north-korea-and-south-korea-exchange-rocket-and-artillery-fire.html |title=North Korea and South Korea Trade Fire Across Border, Seoul Says |date=21 August 2015 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=13 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117145801/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/21/world/asia/north-korea-and-south-korea-exchange-rocket-and-artillery-fire.html |archivedate=17 January 2016 }}</ref>  After four days of negotiations, on 25 August 2015 South Korea agreed to discontinue the broadcasts following a statement from North Korea's government expressing regret for the landmine incident.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bostonherald.com/news_opinion/international/asia/2015/08/south_korea_turns_off_propaganda_as_koreas_reach_deal |title=South Korea turns off propaganda as Koreas reach deal |date=2015-08-25 |accessdate=2015-08-25 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924004726/http://www.bostonherald.com/news_opinion/international/asia/2015/08/south_korea_turns_off_propaganda_as_koreas_reach_deal |archivedate=24 September 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn 8 January 2016, in response to North Korea's supposed successful testing of a [[Thermonuclear weapon|hydrogen bomb]], South Korea resumed broadcasts directed at the North.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kim |first1=Sam |title=South Korea Punishes Kim Jong Un With K-Pop for Nuclear Test |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-01-07/south-korea-to-inflict-k-pop-blasts-on-kim-jong-un-for-nuke-test |accessdate=8 January 2016 |work=Bloomsberg |date=2016-01-07 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107213804/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-01-07/south-korea-to-inflict-k-pop-blasts-on-kim-jong-un-for-nuke-test |archivedate=7 January 2016 }}</ref>  On 15 April 2016, it was reported that the South Koreans purchased a new stereo system to combat the North's broadcasts.<ref name=thereg-20160415>{{cite news|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/04/15/south_korea_to_upgrade_national_stereo_system_at_cost_of_us16m/ |title=South Korea to upgrade national stereo defence system for US$16m |author=Simon Sharwood |newspaper=The Register |date=15 April 2016 |accessdate=22 April 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160419011741/http://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/04/15/south_korea_to_upgrade_national_stereo_system_at_cost_of_us16m/ |archivedate=19 April 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Balloons===\n{{main|Balloon propaganda campaigns in Korea}}\nBoth North and South Korea have held [[Airborne leaflet propaganda|balloon propaganda leaflet]] campaigns since the Korean War.{{sfn|Jung|2014|p=16}}\n\nIn recent years, mainly South Korean [[non-governmental organization]]s have been involved in launching balloons targeted at the DMZ and beyond.{{sfn|Jung|2014|p=9}} Due to the winds, the balloons tend to fall near the DMZ where there are mostly [[North Korean soldier]]s to see the leaflets.<ref name=\"Higginbotham2014\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2014-06-05/the-no-tech-tactics-of-north-koreas-target-zero-park-sang-hak#p4 |title=The No-Tech Tactics of North Korea's Most Wanted Defector |last=Higginbotham |first=Adam |date=5 June 2014 |website=[[Bloomberg News]] |access-date=1 July 2015 |page=4 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703211625/http://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2014-06-05/the-no-tech-tactics-of-north-koreas-target-zero-park-sang-hak |archivedate=3 July 2015 }}</ref> As with the loudspeakers, balloon operations were mutually agreed to be halted between 2004 and 2010.{{sfn|Jung|2014|p=23}} It has been assessed that the activists' balloons may contribute to the decay of remaining cooperation between the Korean governments,<ref name=\"Feffer2014\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ips-dc.org/koreas-balloon-war/ |title=Korea's Balloon War |last=Feffer |first=John |date=6 November 2014 |website=[[Institute for Policy Studies]] |publisher= |access-date=29 June 2015}}</ref> and the DMZ has become more [[Militarization|militarized]] in recent years.{{sfn|Jung|2014|p=31}}\n\nMany North Korean leaflets during the [[Cold War]] gave instructions and maps to help targeted South Korean soldiers in defecting. One of the leaflets found on the DMZ included a map of [[Cho Dae-hum]]'s route of [[South Korean defectors|defection to North Korea]] across the DMZ. In addition to using balloons as a means of delivery, North Koreans have also used [[rocket]]s to send leaflets to the DMZ.<ref name=\"Friedman2006\">{{cite web|url=http://www.psywarrior.com/NKoreaH.html |title=Communist Korean War Leaflets |last=Friedman |first=Herbert A. |date=5 January 2006 |website=www.psywarrior.com |access-date=28 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150711121501/http://www.psywarrior.com/NKoreaH.html |archivedate=11 July 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Dismantling===\nOn 23 April 2018, both North and South Korea officially cancelled their border propaganda broadcasts for the last time.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/04/23/asia/north-korea-south-korea-upcoming-summit-intl/index.html|title=South Korea stops blasting propaganda along DMZ as summit looms|author1=Joshua Berlinger |author2=Yoonjung Seo|work=CNN|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref> On 1 May 2018, the loudspeakers across the Korean border were dismantled.<ref name=may1>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2018/05/01/607399907/north-and-south-korea-dismantle-loudspeakers-blaring-propaganda-on-the-dmz |title=North And South Korea Dismantle Loudspeakers Blaring Propaganda On The DMZ : The Two-Way |publisher=NPR |date=2018-05-01 |accessdate=2018-10-01}}</ref> Both sides also committed to ending the balloon campaigns.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2018-05-05/south-korea-faces-decision-over-leaflets-ties-warm-north|title=South Korea faces a decision over leaflets as ties warm with the North|last=|first=|date=|work=Public Radio International|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref> On 5 May 2018, an attempt by North Korean defectors to disperse more balloon propaganda across the border from South Korea was halted by the South Korean government.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/05/05/south-korea-sabotages-anti-north-korea-leaflet-drop/|title=South Korean police stop protesters releasing balloons to the North, as ties thaw|first=Reuters News|last=Agency|date=5 May 2018|via=www.telegraph.co.uk|newspaper=The Telegraph}}</ref> The no-fly zone which was established on 1 November 2018 also designated a no-fly zone for all aircraft types above the MDL, and prohibits hot-air balloons from traveling within 25&nbsp;km of the Korean border's [[Military Demarcation Line]] (MDL).<ref name=\"nov1effect\">[https://www.ncnk.org/sites/default/files/Agreement%20on%20the%20Implementation%20of%20the%20Historic%20Panmunjom%20Declaration%20in%20the%20Military%20Domain.pdf Agreement on the Implementation of the Historic Panmunjom Declaration in the Military Domain] , 2018 (PDF)</ref>\n\n==Civilian Control Line==\n{{multiple image\n|total_width=478\n|image1=Civilian_Control_Line,_Imjingak,_Paju,_South_Korea_(3162648972).jpg\n|caption1=Civilian Control Line, Imjingak, Paju, South Korea\n|image2=Korea_Civilian_Control_Line2010(1).JPG\n|caption2=Civilian Control Line, South Korea\n}}\nThe Civilian Control Line (CCL), or the Civilian Control Zone (CCZ, [[:ko:\ubbfc\uac04\uc778\ucd9c\uc785\ud1b5\uc81c\uad6c\uc5ed|\ubbfc\uac04\uc778\ucd9c\uc785\ud1b5\uc81c\uad6c\uc5ed]]), is a line that designates an additional buffer zone to the DMZ within a distance of {{Convert|5|to|20|km|lk=|abbr=on}} from the Southern Limit Line of the DMZ. Its purpose is to limit and control the entrance of civilians into the area in order to protect and maintain the security of military facilities and operations near the DMZ. The commander of the [[Eighth United States Army|8th US Army]] ordered the creation of the CCL and it was activated and first became effective in February 1954.<ref>{{cite web | author=Panmunjom tour | title=DMZ - Terminology | website=tourdmz.com  | url=http://tourdmz.com/english/02dmz/p2-1.php | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305210517/http://tourdmz.com/english/02dmz/p2-1.php | archive-date=2016-03-05 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe buffer zone that falls south of the Southern Limit Line is called the Civilian Control Zone. Barbed wire fences and manned military [[Guardpost|guard posts]] mark the Civilian Control Line. The Civilian Control Zone is necessary for the military to monitor civilian travel to tourist destinations close to the Southern Limit Line of the DMZ like the discovered infiltration tunnels and tourist observatories. Usually when traveling within the Civilian Control Zone, South Korean soldiers accompany tourist buses and cars as armed guards to monitor the civilians as well as to protect them from North Korean intruders.\n\nRight after the [[Korean Armistice Agreement|ceasefire]], the Civilian Control Zone outside the DMZ encompassed 100 or so empty villages. The government implemented migration measures to attract settlers into the area. As a result, in 1983, when the area delineated by the Civilian Control Line was at its largest, a total of 39,725 residents in 8,799 households were living in the 81 villages located within the Civilian Control Zone.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreana.or.kr/user/0003/nd6245.do?View&boardNo=00000415&pubLang=English&pubYear=2016&pubMonth=AUTUMN&zineInfoNo=0003|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312071509/http://www.koreana.or.kr/user/0003/nd6245.do?View&boardNo=00000415&pubLang=English&pubYear=2016&pubMonth=AUTUMN&zineInfoNo=0003|url-status=dead|archive-date=2017-03-12|title=DMZ: The Forbidden Land Glimpsed through Barbed Wire Fences|website=Koreana: Korean culture & arts|language=ko|access-date=2017-03-17}}</ref>\n\nMost of the tourist and media photos of the \"DMZ fence\" are actually photos of the CCL fence. The actual DMZ fence on the Southern Limit Line is completely [[Limited-access road|off-limits]] to everybody except soldiers and it is illegal to take pictures of the DMZ fence. The CCL fence acts more as a deterrent for South Korean civilians from getting too close to the dangerous DMZ and is also the final barrier for North Korean [[Infiltration tactics|infiltrators]] if they get past the Southern Limit Line DMZ fence.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/figure/A-map-of-the-study-site-presenting-the-location-of-Military-Demarcation-LineMDL_fig1_277646914 |title =A map of the study site presenting the location of Military Demarcation Line(MDL), Southern Limit Line(SLL) and Civilian Control Line(CCL). Civilian Control Zone is located between SLL and CCL. Border Line(BL) is designated within 25km from CCL |via=Development of Evaluation Indices for Ecological Restoration of Degraded Environments Near DMZ in the Republic of Korea }}</ref>\n\n==Neutral Zone of the Han River Estuary==\nThe whole estuary of the [[Han River (Korea)|Han River]] is deemed a \"Neutral Zone\" and is off-limits to all civilian vessels and is treated like the rest of the DMZ. Only [[military vessel]]s are allowed within this neutral zone.\n\nAccording to the July 1953 [[Korean Armistice Agreement]] civil [[Freight transport|shipping]] was supposed to be permissible in the Han River estuary and allow Seoul to be connected to the [[Yellow Sea]] (West Sea) via the Han River.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.findlaw.com/cnn/docs/korea/kwarmagr072753.html |title=FindLaw Legal Blogs |accessdate=2014-04-14 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305164517/http://news.findlaw.com/cnn/docs/korea/kwarmagr072753.html |archivedate=5 March 2014 }} Article 1, Section 5. Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref> However, both Koreas and the UNC failed to make this happen. The South Korean government ordered the construction of the [[Ara Canal]] to finally connect [[Seoul]] to the Yellow Sea, which was completed in 2012. Seoul was effectively landlocked from the ocean until 2012. The biggest limitation of the Ara Canal is it is too narrow to handle any vessels except small tourist boats and recreational boats, so Seoul still cannot receive large commercial ships or passenger ships in its port.\n\nIn recent years [[China|Chinese]] fishing vessels have taken advantage of the tense situation in the [[Han River (Korea)|Han River]] Estuary Neutral Zone and illegally fished in this area due to both the [[Korean People's Navy|North Korean]] and [[Republic of Korea Navy|South Korean]] navies never patrolling this area due to the fear of naval battles breaking out. This has led to [[Naval combat|firefights]] and sinkings of boats between Chinese fishermen and the [[South Korean Coast Guard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maritime-executive.com/article/south-korea-to-respond-to-illegal-fishing-with-force |title=South Korea to Respond to Illegal Fishing with Force |accessdate=2017-03-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312070836/http://www.maritime-executive.com/article/south-korea-to-respond-to-illegal-fishing-with-force |archivedate=12 March 2017 }} Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiskerforum.dk/en/news/b/han-river-crackdown |title=Han River crackdown - FiskerForum |accessdate=2017-03-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312060747/http://www.fiskerforum.dk/en/news/b/han-river-crackdown |archivedate=12 March 2017 |date=13 June 2016 }} Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref>\n\nOn January 30, 2019 North Korean and South Korean military officials signed a landmark agreement that would open the Han River Estuary to civilian vessels for the first time since the Armistice Agreement in 1953. The agreement will take effect on April 1, 2019 on a trial basis for a few vessels at first and then later will increase in stages gradually until freedom of passage will be granted to any large private ship, like a large cruise or cargo ship, who wishes to travel to Seoul as a final destination via the Han River.<ref>{{cite web | title=S. Korea shares nautical charts of Han River estuary with N. Korea | website=English Edition | date=2019-01-31 | url=http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_national/880735.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | author=\uc1a1\uc0c1\ud638 | title=Koreas to open Han River estuary to civilian ships in April | website=Yonhap News Agency | date=2019-01-30 | url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20190130008700315}}</ref>\n\n==Castle of Gung Ye==\nWithin the DMZ itself, in the town of [[Cheorwon]], is the old capital of the kingdom of [[Taebong]] (901\u2013918), a regional upstart that became [[Goryeo]], the dynasty that ruled a [[History of Korea|united Korea]] from 918 to 1392.\n\n[[Taebong]] was founded by the charismatic leader [[Gung Ye]], a brilliant if tyrannical one-eyed ex-[[Buddhist monk]]. Rebelling against the kingdom of [[Silla]], Korea's then ruling dynasty, he proclaimed the kingdom of [[Taebong]]\u2014also called Later Goguryeo, in reference to the ancient kingdom of [[Goguryeo]] (37BCE-668CE)\u2014in 901, with himself as king. The kingdom consisted of much of central Korea, including areas around the DMZ. He placed his capital in [[Cheorwon]], a mountainous region that was easily defensible (in the Korean War, this same region would earn the name \"the [[Iron Triangle (Korea)|Iron Triangle]]\").\n\nAs a former Buddhist monk, [[Gung Ye]] actively promoted the religion of [[Buddhism]] and incorporated Buddhist ceremonies into the new kingdom. Even after Gung Ye was [[Dethroning|dethroned]] by his own generals and replaced by [[Wang Geon]], the man who would rule over a united Korea as the first king of [[Goryeo]], this Buddhist influence would continue, playing a major role in shaping the culture of medieval Korea.\n\nAs the ruins of Gung Ye's capital lie in the DMZ itself, visitors cannot see them. Moreover, excavation work and research have been hampered by political realities. In the future, inter-Korean peace may allow for proper archaeological studies to be conducted on the castle site and other historical sites within and underneath the DMZ.<ref>Koehler, Rober. (2011). {{Google books|8FatCQAAQBAJ|''The DMZ: Dividing the Two Koreas''|page=108}}</ref>\n\nThe ruins of the capital city of Taebong, the ruins of the castle of Gung Ye, and King Gung Ye's [[tomb]] all lie within the DMZ and are off-limits to everybody except soldiers who patrol the DMZ.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://leekihwan.khan.kr/368 |title=\ud734\uc804\uc120\uc774 \ucc22\uc5b4\ub193\uc740 \uad81\uc608\uc758 \uc57c\ub9dd |accessdate=2017-03-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312060535/http://leekihwan.khan.kr/368 |archivedate=12 March 2017 |date=27 October 2014 | language=ko }} Retrieved 10 March 2017. Many pictures, maps, and description of the old Taebong capital that is stuck in the middle of the DMZ.</ref>\n\n==Transportation==\n[[File:Donghae-bukbu line on Korean DMZ.JPG|thumb|The Donghae Bukbu Line on Korea's east coast. The road and rail link was built for South Koreans visiting the [[Mount Kumgang Tourist Region]] in the North.]]\n[[File:DMZ train Seoul to Dorasan.jpg|thumb|[[DMZ Train]] tour organized by Korail]]\n[[Panmunjeom]] is the site of the negotiations that ended the Korean War and is the main center of human activity in the DMZ. The village is located on the main highway and near a railroad connecting the two Koreas.\n\nThe railway, which connects Seoul and [[Pyongyang]], was called the [[Gyeongui Line]] before division in the 1940s.  Currently the South uses the original name, but the North refers to the route as the P'y\u014fngbu Line. The railway line has been mainly used to carry materials and South Korean workers to the [[Kaesong Industrial Region]]. Its reconnection has been seen as part of the general improvement in the relations between North and South in the early part of this century. However, in November 2008 North Korean authorities closed the railway amid growing tensions with the South.<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://news.scotsman.com/northkorea/Last-train-to-Kaesong-as.4744792.jp|title=Last train to Kaesong as Korean relations cool|date=2008-11-28|publisher=News.Scotman.Com|location=Edinburgh|first=Jae-Soon|last=Chang}}</ref> Following the death of former [[President of South Korea|South Korean President]] [[Kim Dae-jung]], conciliatory talks were held between South Korean officials and a North Korean delegation who attended Kim's funeral. In September 2009, the Kaesong rail and road crossing was reopened.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_northkorea/375550.html |title=Inter-Korean economic cooperation Kaesong office reopens |publisher=Englishhani |date=2009-09-07 |accessdate=2009-09-17 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722143648/http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_northkorea/375550.html |archivedate=22 July 2011 }}</ref>\n\nThe road at Panmunjeom, which was known historically as ''Highway One'' in the South, was originally the only access point between the two countries on the Korean Peninsula. Passage is comparable to the strict movements that occurred at [[Checkpoint Charlie]] in Berlin at the height of the [[Cold War]]. Both North and South Korea's roads end in the JSA; the highways do not quite join as there is a {{convert|20|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} concrete line that divides the entire site. People given the rare permission to cross this border must do so on foot before continuing their journey by road.\n\nIn 2007, on the east coast of Korea, the first train crossed the DMZ on the new [[Donghae Bukbu Line|Donghae Bukbu (Tonghae Pukpu) Line]]. The new rail crossing was built adjacent to the road which took South Koreans to [[Mount Kumgang Tourist Region]], a region of significant cultural importance for all Koreans. More than one million civilian visitors crossed the DMZ until the route was closed following the shooting of a 53-year-old South Korean tourist in July 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/world/2008-07/12/content_6839889.htm |title=ROK woman tourist shot dead at DPRK resort |newspaper=[[China Daily]] |date=2008-07-12 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120217140840/http://www2.chinadaily.com.cn/world/2008-07/12/content_6839889.htm |archivedate=17 February 2012 }}</ref> After a [[Joint investigation team|joint investigation]] was rebuffed by North Korea, the South Korean government suspended tours to the resort. Since then the resort and the Donghae Bukbu Line have effectively been closed by North Korea.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/7539368.stm |title=N Korea steps up row with South |publisher=BBC |date=2008-08-03 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090930093913/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/7539368.stm |archivedate=30 September 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/8639065.stm |title=North Korea 'to seize property at Kumgang resort' |publisher=BBC |date=2010-04-23}}</ref> Currently, the South Korean [[Korea Railroad Corporation]] (Korail) organizes tours to DMZ with special DMZ themed trains.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.letskorail.com/ebizbf/EbizBfAboutDmz_Train.do|title=Korail|website=www.letskorail.com}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 October 2018, North and South Korea, agreed to meet the summit's goal of restoring railway and road transportation which had been cut since the Korean War by either late November or early December 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-northkorea-southkorea-idUSKCN1MP0D0|title=Koreas to reconnect roads, rail, U.S. concerned over easing sanctions|date=15 October 2018|via=www.reuters.com|newspaper=Reuters}}</ref> Road and railway transportation along the DMZ was reconnected in November 2018.<ref name=nov22kr /><ref name=nov22 /><ref name=nov30 />\n\n==Nature reserve==\n[[File:DMZ in Goseong.jpg|thumb|Goesong lookout point]]\n[[File:President Moon Jaein Gangwondo 20190426 08.jpg|thumb|]]\nIn the past half century, the Korean DMZ has been a deadly place for humans, making habitation impossible. Only around the village of [[Panmunjom]] and more recently the Donghae Bukbu Line on Korea's east coast have there been regular incursions by people.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2012/apr/13/wildlife-thriving-korean-demilitarised-zone |title=How wildlife is thriving in the Korean peninsula's demilitarised zone |first=Lisa |last=Brady |date=13 April 2012 |via=The Guardian |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160905181630/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2012/apr/13/wildlife-thriving-korean-demilitarised-zone |archivedate=5 September 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.american.edu/TED/ice/DMZ.HTM |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-09-01 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520080629/http://www1.american.edu/TED/ice/DMZ.HTM |archivedate=20 May 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThis natural isolation along the {{convert|250|km|abbr=on}} length of the DMZ has created an [[involuntary park]] which is now recognized as one of the most well-preserved areas of temperate [[habitat]] in the world.<ref name=\"Green\"/> In 1966 it was first proposed that the DMZ be turned into a [[national park]].<ref name=\"Paige 1967\"/>\n\nSeveral [[Endangered species|endangered animal and plant species]] now exist among the heavily fortified fences, [[landmines]] and listening posts. These include the endangered [[red-crowned crane]] (a staple of Asian art), the [[white-naped crane]], critically endangered [[Korean Fox]]<ref>{{cite web | last=Shim | first=Elizabeth | title=South Korean fox crossed into North Korea, Seoul says | website=UPI | date=2016-02-01 | url=https://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2016/02/01/South-Korean-fox-crossed-into-North-Korea-Seoul-says/6521454354667/}}</ref> and [[Asiatic black bear]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-48214343|title=Rare Asiatic Black Bear spotted in DMZ|date=10 May 2019|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref> and, potentially, the extremely rare [[Siberian tiger]],<ref name=\"Green\">{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2003/WORLD/asiapcf/east/08/22/korea.bio.dmz/ |title=Korea's DMZ: The thin green line |publisher=CNN |accessdate=2009-07-30 |date=2003-08-22 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090805110227/http://edition.cnn.com/2003/WORLD/asiapcf/east/08/22/korea.bio.dmz/ |archivedate=5 August 2009 }}</ref> [[Amur leopard]], and endangered marine species such as Western [[Gray Whale]].<ref>Hall Healy, 2007, KOREAN DEMILITARIZED ZONE: PEACE AND NATURE PARK, International Journal on World Peace\nVol. 24, No. 4 (DECEMBER 2007), pp. 61-83\n</ref><ref>Hyun Woo Kim, Hawsun Sohn, Yasutaka Imai, 2018, Possible occurrence of a Gray Whale off Korea in 2015, International Whaling Commission, SC/67B/CMP/11 Rev1</ref> [[Ecologist]]s have identified some 2,900 plant species, 70 types of mammals and 320 kinds of birds within the narrow buffer zone.<ref name=\"Green\"/> Additional surveys are now being conducted throughout the region.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_view.asp?menu=c10400&no=199457&rel_no=1 |title=Korean 'Tigerman' Prowls the DMZ |publisher=International Korean News |accessdate=2009-07-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090813200543/http://english.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_view.asp?menu=c10400&no=199457&rel_no=1 |archivedate=13 August 2009 }}</ref>\n\nThe DMZ owes its varied [[biodiversity]] to its geography, which crosses mountains, prairies, swamps, lakes, and tidal marshes. [[Environmentalist]]s hope that the DMZ will be conserved as a [[nature reserve|wildlife refuge]], with a well-developed set of objective and management plans vetted and in place. In 2005, [[CNN]] founder and [[media mogul]] [[Ted Turner]], on a visit to North Korea, said that he would financially support any plans to turn the DMZ into a peace park and a UN-protected [[World Heritage Site]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2005-11-18-turnerdmz_x.htm |title=Ted Turner: Turn Korean DMZ into peace park |newspaper=USA TODAY |date=2005-11-18 |accessdate=2010-05-07 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091206190920/http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2005-11-18-turnerdmz_x.htm |archivedate=6 December 2009 }}</ref>\n\nIn September 2011, South Korea submitted a nomination form to [[Man and the Biosphere Programme]] (MAB) in [[UNESCO]] for designation of {{convert|435|km\u00b2|sqmi|abbr=on}} in the southern part of the DMZ below the Military Demarcation Line, as well as {{convert|2979|km\u00b2|sqmi|abbr=on}} in privately controlled areas, as a Biosphere Reserve according to the Statutory Framework of the World Network of Biosphere Reserves.<ref name=\"Nomination of Korea DMZ Biosphere Reserve\">{{cite web|last=Choi |first=Chungil |title=Nomination of Korea DMZ Biosphere Reserve |url=ftp://ftp.unesco.org/upload/sc/Advisory_Cttee2012/New%20BRs/Korea/DMZ/Letter%20of%20endorsement-DMZ.pdf |accessdate=3 October 2012 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=Al83tito |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The MAB National Committee of the Republic of Korea mentioned only the southern part of DMZ to be nominated since there was no response from [[Pyongyang]] when it requested Pyongyang to push jointly. North Korea is a member nation of the international coordinating council of UNESCO's Man and the Biosphere Programme, which designates Biosphere Reserves.<ref name=\"Seoul to seek UNESCO Biosphere Reserve status for DMZ\">{{cite news|last=Kim |first=Jeong-su |title=Seoul to seek UNESCO Biosphere Reserve status for DMZ |url=http://www.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_international/540913.html |accessdate=3 October 2012 |newspaper=Hankyoreh |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722081415/http://www.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_international/540913.html |archivedate=22 July 2012 }}</ref>\n\nNorth Korea opposed the application as a violation of the armistice agreement during the council's meeting in Paris on 9 to 13 July 2011. The South Korean government's attempt to designate the Demilitarized Zone (DMZ) a UNESCO Biosphere Reserve was turned down at UNESCO's MAB council meeting in Paris in July 2012. Pyongyang expressed its opposition by sending letters to 32 council member countries, except for South Korea, and the UNESCO headquarters a month prior to the meeting. At the council meeting, Pyongyang said the designation violated the Armistice Agreement.<ref name=\"Biosphere reserve status for the DMZ is urgent\">{{cite news|last=Cho |first=Do-soon |title=Biosphere reserve status for the DMZ is urgent |url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joinsmsn.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2957816 |accessdate=3 October 2012 |newspaper=JoonAng Daily |date=14 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621051310/http://koreajoongangdaily.joinsmsn.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2957816 |archivedate=21 June 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Destruction of guard posts==\nOn 26 October 2018, South Korean major general Kim Do-gyun and North Korean lieutenant general An Ik San met in [[Tongilgak]] (the \"Unification Pavilion\"), a North Korean building located within the DMZ's Joint Security Area (JSA). There, they began implementing new protocols which aim to reduce tension by requiring both North and South Korea to destroy 22 guard posts across the DMZ,<ref name=\"voaoct26\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.voanews.com/a/koreas-continue-tension-easing-talks-as-the-north-criticizes-us/4630152.html|title=Koreas Continue Tension-Easing Talks as the North Criticizes US|last=Miller|first=Steve|work=VOA|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref> among other steps. Both generals approved requirements for the guard posts to be destroyed by the end of November 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.apnews.com/9e3311a2c2a9431198032cdd6e7e86a2|title=2 Koreas to destroy 22 front-line guard posts by November|date=2018-10-26|work=AP NEWS|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref> The JSA's guard posts were destroyed on 25 October 2018.<ref name=voaoct26 /><ref name=\"independentoct25\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theindependent.com/news/world/koreas-un-finish-withdrawing-firearms-from-border-village/image_55ab50f5-8704-5770-812d-87c7832e0568.html|title=2 Koreas to destroy 22 front-line guard posts by November|last=Jin-man|first=Lee|work=The Grand Island Independent|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"yonhapoct25\">{{Cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2018/10/25/0200000000AEN20181025001351315.html|title=(LEAD) Two Koreas, UNC wrap up JSA disarmament|last=\uc1a1\uc0c1\ud638|date=2018-10-25|work=Yonhap News Agency|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref> North and South Korea agreed to dismantle 11 guard posts located within their individual country and deemed as \"front-line.\"<ref name=\"etoct26\">{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/2-koreas-to-destroy-11-front-line-guard-posts-by-november/articleshow/66377151.cms|title=2 Koreas to destroy 11 front-line guard posts by November|date=2018-10-26|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2018-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026222722/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/2-koreas-to-destroy-11-front-line-guard-posts-by-november/articleshow/66377151.cms|archive-date=26 October 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=reutersoct26 /><ref name=cgtnoct26 /> It was also agreed that after the posts are dismantled, both Koreas would also withdraw equipment and personnel stationed at each post as well.<ref name=\"reutersoct26\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-northkorea-southkorea/north-and-south-korea-agree-to-scrap-22-guard-posts-at-border-next-month-idUSKCN1N0082|title=North and South Korea agree to scrap 22 guard posts at border next...|last=Shin|first=Hyonhee|work=U.S.|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref> In tandem with the [[September 2018 inter-Korean summit#September 19 (Day 2)|September 2018 Pyongyang and Military Domain Agreements]],<ref name=etoct26 /><ref name=reutersoct26 /><ref name=cgtnoct26 /><ref>https://www.ncnk.org/sites/default/files/Agreement%20on%20the%20Implementation%20of%20the%20Historic%20Panmunjom%20Declaration%20in%20the%20Military%20Domain.pdf</ref> both sides also agreed to gradually remove all guard posts near the DMZ following verification in December 2018.<ref name=etoct26 /><ref name=reutersoct26 /><ref name=\"cgtnoct26\">{{Cite news|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d414e774d544d30457a6333566d54/share_p.html|title=Two Koreas agree to withdraw 11 guard posts in border area by late November|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref>\n\nHowever, all remaining troops and equipment, including weapons, were withdrawn from all of the 22 \"frontline\" guard posts before destruction began and both Koreas later agreed to individually destroy 10 of these guard posts instead of 11.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/north-and-south-korea-begin-destroying-border-guard-posts-10919016|title=North and South Korea begin destroying border guard posts|work=Channel NewsAsia|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=rappler11 /><ref name=latnov10 /><ref name=sfcnov10 />\n\nOn 4 November 2018, the North and South Korean governments hoisted a yellow flag above each of their 11 DMZ guard posts to publicly indicate that they all will be dismantled.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_northkorea/868900.html|title=South and North Korea begin trial dismantlement of guard posts surrounding DMZ|website=english.hani.co.kr}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\"/> On 10 November 2018, the withdrawal of military personnel and weapons from all of the DMZ's 22 \"front-line\" guard posts was completed.<ref name=\"latnov10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/world/la-fg-korea-guard-post-withdrawals-20181110-story.html|title=In latest trust-building step, North and South Korean military finish withdrawal from front-line guard posts|last=Press|first=Associated|website=latimes.com|access-date=2018-11-19|date=11 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"sfcnov10\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/world/article/North-South-dismantle-22-guard-posts-along-border-13380901.php|title=North, South dismantle 22 guard posts along border|date=2018-11-10|work=SFChronicle.com|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>http://www.hastingstribune.com/koreas-complete-the-disarming-of-guard-posts/article_bddc8489-3eb5-5982-b626-a4ed5d6e69dc.html{{Dead link|date=January 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The destruction of 20 guard posts officially began on 11 November 2018.<ref name=nov11kh>{{Cite web | url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20181111000255 |title = Koreas begin destroying 20 front-line guard posts|date = 11 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=yonhapnov11>http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2018/11/11/0200000000AEN20181111005200320.html</ref> However, both Koreas amended the original agreement and decided to preserve 2 of the 22 now demilitarized frontline guard posts.<ref name=nov11kh /><ref name=yonhapnov11 /> Both of the posts which were planned to be preserved are located on the opposite sides of the Korean border.<ref name=\"rappler11\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.rappler.com/world/regions/asia-pacific/216465-north-south-korea-begin-destroying-border-guard-posts|title=North and South Korea begin destroying border guard posts|work=Rappler|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 November 2018, destruction of two DMZ guard posts, one being located in South Korea and the other located in North Korea, was completed.<ref name=nov15>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2018/11/15/south-korea-destroys-guard-posts-along-border-with-north-korea.html|title=South Korea destroys guard posts along border with North Korea &#124; The Star|website=thestar.com}}</ref><ref name=mtnov15>{{Cite web|url=https://www.military.com/daily-news/2018/11/16/south-korea-dismantles-guard-posts-dynamite-excavators.html|title=South Korea Dismantles Guard Posts with Dynamite, Excavators|first=Hyung-jin|last=Kim|date=16 November 2018|website=Military.com}}</ref> Work was still ongoing to complete the destruction of other guard posts as well.<ref name=nov15 /><ref name=mtnov15 /> On 23 November 2018, it was revealed that South Korea was slowly destroying their guard posts with [[excavator]]s.<ref name=khnov23 />\n\nOn 20 November 2018, North Korea, hoping to further ease tensions with South Korea, destroyed all of their 10 remaining \"frontline\" guard posts.<ref name=abc11>{{Cite web|url=https://abc11.com/4726650/|title=North Korea detonates DMZ guard posts at southern border|date=21 November 2018|website=ABC11 Raleigh-Durham}}</ref><ref name=nov20>https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/seoul-north-korea-explodes-10-guard-posts-lower-59309949</ref> The South Korean Defense Ministry released photos confirming this and also released a statement stating that North Korea had informed them about the plans to demolish them before it took place.<ref name=nov20 /> This came in accordance with the earlier agreements.<ref name=abc11 /> South Korea also released videos of the guard posts being destroyed as well.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/north-korea-video-south-korea-dmz-guard-posts-explode-peace-agreement-border-a8643876.html |title = South Korea releases video of North Korea blowing up 10 guard posts in DMZ|date = 21 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 November 2018, both Koreas completed work to dismantle 10 of their \"frontline\" guard posts.<ref name=nov30 /><ref name=belarusnov30 /> However, the later agreement for each Korea to preserve one \"frontline\" post was upheld as well.<ref name=nov30 /> The \"frontline\" guard post which was preserved on the North Korean side of the DMZ was visited by Kim Jong Un in 2013 when tensions were rising between both Koreas.<ref name=khnov23>{{Cite web | url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20181120000703 |title = &#91;Video&#93; N. Korea destroys 10 DMZ guard posts|date = 20 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Establishment of buffer zones, no-fly zones and Yellow Sea peace zones==\nOn 1 November 2018, [[buffer zones]] were established across the DMZ by the North and South Korean militaries.<ref name=nov1 /> In compliance with the Comprehensive Military Agreement which was signed at the [[September 2018 inter-Korean summit]],<ref name=ncnkdirect /> the buffer zone helps ensure that both North and South Korea will effectively ban hostility on land, air, and sea.<ref name=nov1 /> Both Koreas are prohibited from conducting [[Live fire exercise|live-fire artillery drills]] and regiment-level field maneuvering exercises or those by bigger units within 5 kilometers of the Military Demarcation Line (MDL).<ref name=\"nov1\">{{Cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2018/11/01/0200000000AEN20181101002500315.html|title=Koreas halt all 'hostile' military acts near border|last=\uc774\uce58\ub3d9|date=2018-11-01|work=Yonhap News Agency|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref> The buffer zones stretch from the north of Deokjeok Island to the south of Cho Island in the West Sea and the north of [[Sokcho]] city and south of Tongchon County in the East (Yellow) Sea.<ref name=\"ncnkdirect\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nknews.org/2018/10/two-koreas-end-military-drills-begin-operation-of-no-fly-zone-near-mdl-mnd/|title=Two Koreas end military drills, begin operation of no-fly zone near MDL: MND {{!}} NK News - North Korea News|date=2018-10-31|work=NK News - North Korea News|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n[[No-fly zones]] have also been established along the DMZ to ban the operation of drones, helicopters and other aircraft over an area up to {{Convert|40|km||abbr=on}} away from the MDL.<ref name=nov1 /> For [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|UAVs]], within {{Convert|15|km||abbr=on}} from the MDL in the East and {{Convert|10|km||abbr=on}} from the MDL in the West.<ref name=nov1effect /> Hot-air balloons cannot travel within {{Convert|25|km||abbr=on}} of the DMZ as well.<ref name=nov1effect /> For fixed-wing aircraft, no fly zones are designated within {{Convert|40|km||abbr=on}} from the MDL in the East (between MDL Markers No. 0646 and 1292) and within {{Convert|20|km||abbr=on}} of the MDL in the West (between MDL Markers No. 0001 and 0646).<ref name=ncnkdirect /> For [[rotary-wing aircraft]], the no fly zones are designated within {{Convert|10|km||abbr=on}} of the MDL.<ref name=ncnkdirect />\n\nBoth Koreas also created \"peace zones\" near their [[Border dispute|disputed]] Yellow Sea border.<ref name=nov1 />\n\n==Reconnecting of MDL-crossing road==\nOn 22 November 2018, North and South Korea completed construction to connect a three kilometer road along the DMZ, 90&nbsp;km northeast of Seoul.<ref name=nov22kr>{{Cite web | url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20181122006452315?section=national/defense |title = (2nd LD) Koreas connect road inside heavily fortified DMZ|date = 21 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=nov22>{{Cite web | url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/politics/south-north-korea-connect-border-road-through-dmz/1318769 |title = South, North Korea connect border road through DMZ}}</ref> This road, which crosses the Korean MDL land border, consists of 1.7&nbsp;km in South Korea and 1.3&nbsp;km in North Korea.<ref name=nov22 /> The road was reconnected for the first time in 14 years in an effort to assist with a process at the DMZ's Arrowhead Hill involving the removal of landmines and exhumation of Korean War remains.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.asianews.it/news-en/After-14-years,-a-road-to-unite-the-Koreas-and-recover-the-remains-of-the-fallen-45545.html |title = After 14 years, a road to unite the Koreas and recover the remains of the fallen}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/north-south-korea-join-roads-124905264.html|title=North and South Korea join roads after 14 years|website=www.yahoo.com}}</ref><ref>https://www.cairnspost.com.au/news/national/north-and-south-korea-join-roads-after-14-years/video/af8a644187eb15024a900b16826ebd24</ref>\n\n==Presence of landmines and Korean War remains==\nOn 1 October 2018, North and South Korean military engineers began a scheduled 20 day removal process of landmines and other explosives planted across the DMZ's [[Joint Security Area]] of the (DMZ).<ref name=bbckoreaoct /><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/10/01/north-south-korea-begin-removing-landmines-along-fortified-border/ |title = North and South Korea begin removing landmines along fortified DMZ|newspaper = The Telegraph|date = October 2018|last1 = Agency|first1 = Reuters News}}</ref><ref name=oct1>{{Cite web | url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/north-korea-south-korea-removing-land-mines-dmz-panmunjom-arrow-head-hill/ |title = North and South Korea begin removing mines along DMZ}}</ref> Work to remove landmines from the Joint Security Area was completed on 25 October 2018.<ref name=bbckoreaoct /><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3054494 |title = In 19 days, land mines are cleared from JSA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2018/10/356_257291.html | title=Two Koreas finish landmine cleanup in JSA. What's next?| date=19 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://pulsenews.co.kr/view.php?year=2018&no=653231 |title = Two Koreas complete demining and on path to make JSA arms-free - Pulse by Maeil Business News Korea}}</ref> Demining had begun at the DMZ's Arrowhead Hill and resulted in the discovery of Korean War remains.<ref name=oct25nov30>https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/south-korea-finds-war-remains-border-demining-58732705</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.dailyherald.com/article/20181025/news/310259972 |title = South Korea finds likely war remains during border demining|date = 25 October 2018}}</ref> Work between both Koreas to remove landmines from Arrowhead Hill was completed on 30 November 2018.<ref name=belarusnov30>{{Cite web | url=https://eng.belta.by/society/view/koreas-complete-work-on-removing-some-guard-posts-land-mines-in-dmz-116996-2018/ | title=Koreas complete work on removing some guard posts, land mines in DMZ| date=30 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=nov30kr>{{Cite web | url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20181130002400315 |title = Koreas to complete work to remove some guard posts, land mines in DMZ|date = 30 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Inter-Korean transportation services==\nOn 30 November 2018, following the removal of the \"frontline\" guard posts and Arrowhead Hill landmines, railroad transportation between North and South Korea which ceased in November 2008 resumed.<ref name=nov30>{{Cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/11/30/first-train-decade-departs-south-korea-north-korea/ |title = First train in a decade departs South Korea for North Korea|newspaper = The Telegraph|date = 30 November 2018|last1 = Avagnina|first1 = Gianluca}}</ref> The same day, 30 officials from both North and South Korea started an 18-day survey of a 400-kilometre (248-mile) railroad section in North Korea alongside the DMZ between Kaesong and Sinuiju.<ref name=voanov30>{{Cite web | url=https://www.voanews.com/a/koreas-survey-railway-tracks-cut-since-the-korean-war/4681029.html |title = Koreas Survey Railway Tracks Cut Since the Korean War}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web | url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2018/11/356_259637.html | title=South Korean train starts joint survey of North Korean railways| date=30 November 2018}}</ref> Efforts to conduct the survey had previously been obstructed due to the presence of the guard posts and the Arrowhead Hill landmines.<ref name=nov30 /> The survey will then follow the groundbreaking of a new railroad along the DMZ.<ref name=\"auto\"/> The railway survey which involved the [[Gyeongui Line]] concluded on 5 December 2018.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20181205000785 |title = &#91;Newsmaker&#93; Koreas in consultations for joint road inspection|date = 5 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 December 2018, a South Korean bus crossed the DMZ into North Korea.<ref name=dec8 /> The same day, the officials who conducted the inter-Korean survey for the Gyeongui Line began surveying the [[Donghae Line]].<ref name=dec8>{{Cite web | url=http://world.kbs.co.kr/service/news_view.htm?lang=e&Seq_Code=141408 |title = Joint Inspection of N. Korea's Eastern Rail Line Begins l KBS WORLD Radio}}</ref>\n\n==Military Border Crossing==\nOn 12 December 2018, militaries from both Koreas crossed the DMZ's MDL into the opposition countries for the first time in history to inspect and verify the removal of \"frontline\" guard posts.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/north-korea-south-korea-troops-cross-demilitarized-zone-in-peace-first-time/ | title=Troops cross North-South Korea Demilitarized Zone in peace for 1st time ever}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/north-and-south-korean-soldiers-enter-each-others-territory/north-invades-the-south/slideshow/67057861.cms | title=North and South Korean soldiers enter each other's territory | date=12 December 2018 | newspaper=The Economic Times | accessdate=9 February 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==Meeting of Trump, Kim, and Moon at the DMZ==\n{{Main|2019 Koreas\u2013United States DMZ Summit}}\nOn 30 June 2019, U.S. president [[Donald Trump]] became the first sitting U.S. president to enter North Korea, doing so at the DMZ line.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/president-trump-travel-dmz-meet-kim-jong/story?id=64042883 | title=President Trump becomes 1st president to step inside North Korea ahead of meeting with Kim Jong Un}}</ref> After crossing into North Korea, Trump and Kim met and shook hands.<ref name=\"cnnjune30\" />  Kim stated, in English, \"It's good to see you again\", \"I never expected to meet you at this place\" and \"you are the first U.S. president to cross the border.\"<ref name=cnnjune30 /> Both men then briefly crossed the border line before crossing back into South Korea.<ref name=cnnjune30>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/29/politics/kim-jong-un-donald-trump-dmz-north-korea/index.html|title=Trump takes 20 steps into North Korea, making history as first sitting US leader to enter hermit nation|first=Kevin |last=Liptak|website=CNN}}</ref>\n\nOn the South Korean side of the DMZ, Kim, Moon, and Trump held a brief chat before holding an hour-long [[2019 Koreas\u2013United States DMZ Summit|meeting]] at the DMZ's [[Inter-Korean House of Freedom]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.9news.com.au/world/trump-offers-to-meet-n-korea-s-kim-in-dmz/a39ece8d-fc6b-4ab8-81c8-af8b28f89415|title=Talks to reopen after Trump-Kim meeting - 9News|website=www.9news.com.au}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/06/30/trumps-press-secretary-bruised-after-jostling-with-north-korea-security-over-media-report-says/|title=Trump's press secretary bruised after jostling with North Korea security over media, report says|first=Hannah Knowles closeHannah KnowlesGeneral assignment|last=reporterEmailEmailBioBioFollowFollow|website=Washington Post}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bamboo Curtain]]\n* [[Iron Curtain]]\n* [[Neutral Nations Supervisory Commission]]\n* [[North Korea\u2013South Korea relations]]\n* [[Peace lines]]\n* [[United Nations Buffer Zone in Cyprus]]\n* [[Vietnamese Demilitarized Zone]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Paige 1967\">{{cite journal |last=Paige |first= Glenn D. |authorlink=Glenn D. Paige |date=January 1967 |title= 1966: Korea Creates the Future |jstor=  2642450|journal= Asian Survey - A Survey of Asia in 1966: Part I|volume= 7|issue=1 |pages=21\u201330 |doi= 10.2307/2642450}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |title=Shield of the Great Leader. The Armed Forces of North Korea |last=Bermudez |first=Joseph S. |authorlink= |year=2001 |publisher=[[Allen & Unwin]] |location=Sydney |series=The Armed Forces of Asia |isbn=978-1-86448-582-0 |pages= }}\n*{{cite web |publisher=[[CNN World News]]  |title=South Korea warns North will pay 'harsh price' over DMZ landmine blasts|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/08/09/asia/koreas-tensions/ |first1=Jethro |last1=Mullen |first2=Kathy |last2=Novak |date=10 August 2015 |accessdate=24 February 2017}}\n* Elferink, Alex G. Oude, (1994). ''The Law of Maritime Boundary Delimitation: a Case Study of the Russian Federation.'' Dordrecht: [[Martinus Nijhoff]]. {{ISBN|9780792330820}}; [http://www.worldcat.org/title/law-of-maritime-boundary-delimitation-a-case-study-of-the-russian-federation/oclc/123566768 OCLC 123566768]\n*{{cite web |ref=harv |url=http://www.mmg.mpg.de/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/wp/WP_14-07_Jung%20Ballooning%20Evangelism.pdf |title=Ballooning Evangelism: Psychological Warfare and Christianity in the Divided Korea |last=Jung |first=Jin-Heon |date=2014 |website=[[Max Planck Institute]] |series=MMG Working Paper |issue=14\u201307 |pages=7\u201333 |access-date=27 June 2015 |issn=2192-2357 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150630054302/http://www.mmg.mpg.de/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/wp/WP_14-07_Jung%20Ballooning%20Evangelism.pdf |archive-date=30 June 2015 |url-status=dead }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons|Korean Demilitarized Zone}}\n{{wikivoyage|DMZ (Korea)}}\n* [https://www.chris-toone.com/blog/dmzsouthkorea/ Touring the DMZ in South Korea] What it's like to stand at the border, 2017\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/imcomkorea/sets/72157607715383952// U.S. Army official Korean Demilitarized Zone image archive]\n* [http://newsweek.washingtonpost.com/postglobal/america/2008/01/too_sexy_for_the_dmz.html Washington Post Correspondent Amar Bakshi travels to the Korean Demilitarized Zone... And uncovers the world's most dangerous tourist trap], January 2008.\n* [https://doi.org/10.1007%2Fs11355-005-0006-0 Status and ecological resource value of the Republic of Korea's De-militarized Zone]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l6cIUKOqPMI Tour Of DMZ on YouTube. Dec. 2007]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Ediz1vuwt0 Tour of DMZ from the DPRK on YouTube, 2016]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5XK4PPmi6AE 360 degree tour of DMZ from the DPRK on YouTube, 2016]\n* [http://www.dmzforum.org/ DMZ Forum: Collaborative international NGO focusing on promoting peace and conservation within the Korean DMZ region]\n* [https://news.yahoo.com/blogs/power-players-abc-news/inside-tour-scariest-place-earth-072912137.html ABCNews/Yahoo! report/blog on the DMZ]\n* [http://www.earthnutshell.com/the-worlds-most-dangerous-border-a-tour-of-north-koreas-dmz/ The World\u2019s Most Dangerous Border \u2013 A Tour of North Korea\u2019s DMZ] Visiting the DMZ from Pyongyang.\n*[http://worldbybike.com/goodbye-north-korea/#gallery/3432/15253 Photo of road linking DPRK to Paju, ROK]\n*[https://fall.law.fsu.edu/collection/LimitsinSeas/IBS022.pdf International Boundary Study No. 22 \u2013 May 24, 1963 Korea \u201cMilitary Demarcation Line\u201d Boundary]\n\n{{Korea topics|expanded=Geography}}\n{{Portal bar|North Korea|South Korea}}\n{{coords|38.329|127.250|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:1953 introductions]]\n[[Category:Korean Demilitarized Zone| ]]\n[[Category:North Korea\u2013South Korea border]]\n[[Category:Aftermath of the Korean War]]\n[[Category:Border barriers]]\n[[Category:Cold War terminology]]\n[[Category:Demilitarized zones]]\n[[Category:Government of North Korea]]\n[[Category:Military of North Korea]]\n[[Category:Military history of Korea]]\n[[Category:North Korea\u2013South Korea relations]]\n[[Category:Military installations established in 1953]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Demilitarized zone running across the Korean Peninsula}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox military installation\n| name             = Korean DMZ\n| native_name      = {{lang|ko|\ud55c\ubc18\ub3c4 \ube44\ubb34\uc7a5 \uc9c0\ub300}}<br/>{{lang|ko|\u97d3\u534a\u5cf6\u975e\u6b66\u88dd\u5730\u5e36}}<br/>Hanbando Bimujang jidae<br/>Hanbando Pimujang chidae\n| image            = File:Korea DMZ sentry.jpg\n| caption          = A South Korean checkpoint at the Civilian Control Line, located outside of the DMZ\n| location         = [[Korean Peninsula]]\n| image_map        = Korea DMZ.svg\n| image_map_caption = The Korean DMZ denoted by the red highlighted area. The blue line indicates the international border.\n| type             = [[Demilitarised zone|DMZ]]\n| builder          = {{plainlist|\n*{{flag|Democratic People's Republic of Korea}}\n*{{flag|Republic of Korea}}\n*[[United Nations Command]]\n}}\n| length           = {{convert|250|km|mi}}\n| used             = since {{start date|1953|07|27|df=y}}\n| condition        = Fully manned and operational\n| open_to_public   = No; access only granted by the North or United Nations Command. \n| events           = [[Division of Korea]]\n}}\n{{Campaignbox Korean Cold War}}\nThe '''Korean Demilitarized Zone''' ('''DMZ'''; [[Hangul|Chos\u014fn'g\u016dl/Hangul]]: {{Korean|hangul=\ud55c\ubc18\ub3c4 \ube44\ubb34\uc7a5 \uc9c0\ub300|hanja=|rr=|mr=|labels=no|context=}}; [[Hanja]]: {{Lang|ko-Hani|\u97d3\u534a\u5cf6\u975e\u6b66\u88dd\u5730\u5e36}}) is a strip of land running across the [[Korean Peninsula]]. It is established by the provisions of the [[Korean Armistice Agreement]] to serve as a [[buffer zone]] between [[North Korea]] and [[South Korea]]. The [[demilitarized zone]] (DMZ) is a [[border barrier]] that divides the Korean Peninsula roughly in half.  It was created by agreement between North Korea, [[China]] and the [[United Nations Command]] in 1953. The DMZ is {{convert|250|km|mi|abbr=off}} long, and about {{convert|4|km|mi|abbr=off}} wide.\n\nWithin the DMZ is a meeting point between the two nations in the small [[Joint Security Area]] (JSA) near the western end of the zone, where negotiations take place. There have been various incidents in and around the DMZ, with military and civilian casualties on both sides. \n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Location==\nThe Korean Demilitarized Zone intersects but does not follow the [[38th parallel north]], which was the border before the [[Korean War]]. It crosses the parallel on an angle, with the west end of the DMZ lying south of the parallel and the east end lying north of it.\n[[File:Korea at night.png|thumb|right|The Korean Demilitarized Zone is visible at night from space due to a noticeable lack of lighting in the northern half of the Korean Peninsula]]\nThe DMZ is {{convert|250|km|mi|abbr=off}} long,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=3660 |title=Korean Demilitarized Zone: Image of the Day |publisher=NASA Earth Observatory |accessdate=2010-03-26 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100316031349/http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=3660 |archivedate=16 March 2010 }}</ref> approximately {{convert|4|km|mi|abbr=on}} wide. Though the zone is demilitarized, the border beyond that strip is one of the most heavily [[Militarization|militarized]] borders in the world.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2011/06/24/the-worlds-most-dangerous-borders/ |title=The world's most dangerous borders |first=Philip |last=Walker |magazine=Foreign Policy |date=24 June 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170308153821/http://foreignpolicy.com/2011/06/24/the-worlds-most-dangerous-borders/ |archivedate=8 March 2017 }}</ref> The [[Northern Limit Line]], or NLL, is the disputed maritime [[demarcation line]] between North and South Korea in the [[Yellow Sea]], not agreed in the armistice. The coastline and islands on both sides of the NLL are also heavily militarized.<ref>Elferink, Alex G. Oude. (1994). {{Google books|x-VYb-wida8C|''The Law of Maritime Boundary Delimitation: a Case Study of the Russian Federation''|page=314}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Korea demilitarized zone map - 1969.jpg|thumb|upright=1.4|Detail of the DMZ]]\n[[File:KPA3-2a.jpg|thumb|A portion of the North Korean DMZ seen from the [[Joint Security Area]] in January 1976]]\n{{main|Division of Korea}}\nThe [[38th parallel north]]\u2014which divides the Korean Peninsula roughly in half\u2014was the original boundary between the United States and Soviet Union's brief administration areas of Korea at the end of [[World War II]]. Upon the creation of the [[Democratic People's Republic of Korea]] (DPRK, informally \"North Korea\") and the [[Republic of Korea]] (ROK, informally \"South Korea\") in 1948, it became a ''[[de facto]]'' international border and one of the most tense fronts in the [[Cold War]].\n\nBoth the North and the South remained dependent on their sponsor states from 1948 to the outbreak of the [[Korean War]]. That conflict, which claimed over three million lives and divided the Korean Peninsula along ideological lines, commenced on 25 June 1950, with a full-front DPRK invasion across the 38th parallel, and ended in 1953 after international intervention pushed the [[Front (military)|front]] of the war back to near the 38th parallel.\n\nIn the [[Korean Armistice Agreement|Armistice Agreement]] of 27 July 1953, the DMZ was created as each side agreed to move their troops back {{convert|2000|m|mi|abbr=in}} from the front line, creating a buffer zone {{convert|4|km|mi|abbr=on}} wide. The [[Military Demarcation Line]] (MDL) goes through the center of the DMZ and indicates where the front was when the agreement was signed.\n\nOwing to this theoretical [[stalemate]], and genuine hostility between the North and the South, large numbers of troops are stationed along both sides of the line, each side guarding against potential aggression from the other side, even {{Age|1953|July|27}} years after its establishment. The armistice agreement explains exactly how many military personnel and what kind of weapons are allowed in the DMZ. Soldiers from both sides may patrol inside the DMZ, but they may not cross the MDL. However, heavily armed ROK soldiers patrol under the aegis of [[military police]], and have memorized each line of the armistice.<ref name=\"On Patrol in the DMZ\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/mar/21/north-korea-south-korea-dmz-landmines |title=On patrol in the DMZ: North Korean landmines, biting winds and tin cans: As tensions on the peninsula escalate, a former South Korean guard describes life at one of the world's most fortified borders. NK News reports |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2016-03-21 |accessdate=2016-04-18 |author=Ahn, JH |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416132851/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/mar/21/north-korea-south-korea-dmz-landmines |archivedate=16 April 2016 }}</ref>  [[List of border incidents involving North and South Korea|Sporadic outbreaks of violence]] have killed over 500 South Korean soldiers, 50 US soldiers and 250 soldiers from DPRK along the DMZ between 1953 and 1999.<ref>{{cite news|last=Potts |first=Rolf |title=Korea's no-man's-land |url=http://www.salon.com/1999/02/03/feature_115/ |work=Salon |accessdate=31 January 2013 |date=3 February 1999 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130215050040/http://www.salon.com/1999/02/03/feature_115/ |archivedate=15 February 2013 }}</ref>\n\n[[Daeseong-dong]] (also written ''Tae Sung Dong'') and [[Kijong-dong|Kij\u014fng-dong]] (also known as the \"Peace Village\") are the only settlements allowed by the armistice committee to remain within the boundaries of the DMZ.<ref name=\"Tae\">{{cite news|url=http://www.stripes.com/article.asp?section=104&article=52586 |title=DMZ sixth-graders become graduates |newspaper=[[Stars and Stripes (newspaper)|Stars and Stripes]] |date=2008-02-19 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090611232350/http://www.stripes.com/article.asp?section=104&article=52586 |archivedate=11 June 2009 }}</ref> Residents of Tae Sung Dong are governed and protected by the [[United Nations Command]] and are generally required to spend at least 240 nights per year in the village to maintain their residency.<ref name = \"Tae\"/> In 2008, the village had a population of 218 people.<ref name = \"Tae\"/> The villagers of Tae Sung Dong are direct descendants of people who owned the land before the 1950\u201353 Korean War.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.army.mil/-news/2009/01/26/16093-santa-mobbed-by-students-during-visit-to-joint-security-area/ |title=Santa mobbed by students during visit to Joint Security Area |publisher=army.mil.com -The Official U.S. Army Website |accessdate=2009-12-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091124043626/http://www.army.mil/-news/2009/01/26/16093-santa-mobbed-by-students-during-visit-to-joint-security-area/ |archivedate=24 November 2009 }}</ref>\n\nTo continue to deter North Korean incursion, in 2014 the United States government exempted the Korean DMZ from its pledge to eliminate [[Anti-personnel mine|anti-personnel landmines]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/korearealtime/2014/09/24/why-the-korean-peninsula-keeps-landmines/ |title=Why the Korean Peninsula Keeps Land Mines |last=Kwaak |first=Jeyup S |newspaper=Wall Street Journal |date=24 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924070350/https://blogs.wsj.com/korearealtime/2014/09/24/why-the-korean-peninsula-keeps-landmines/ |archivedate=24 September 2014 }}</ref> On 1 October 2018, however, a 20-day process began to remove landmines from both sides of the DMZ.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/10/01/north-south-korea-begin-removing-landmines-along-fortified-border/|title=North and South Korea begin removing landmines along fortified DMZ|last=Agency|first=Reuters News|date=2018-10-01|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref>\n\n==Joint Security Area==\n[[File:070401 Panmunjeom3.jpg|thumb|View of the North from the southern side of the [[Joint Security Area|JSA]]]]\n[[File:Joint Security Area from North Korea.jpg|thumb|Conference Row seen from the northern side of the [[Joint Security Area|JSA]]]]\n{{main|Joint Security Area}}\nInside the DMZ, near the western coast of the peninsula, [[Panmunjom]] is the home of the Joint Security Area (JSA). Originally, it was the only connection between North and South Korea<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imcom.korea.army.mil/imakoroweb/sites/local/news/020808_IMCOMK_DMZ.asp |title=Panmunjon |publisher=army.mil.com |accessdate=2009-12-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905081008/http://imcom.korea.army.mil/imakoroweb/sites/local/news/020808_IMCOMK_DMZ.asp |archivedate=5 September 2009 }}</ref> but that changed on 17 May 2007, when a [[Korail]] train went through the DMZ to the North on the new [[Donghae Bukbu Line]] built on the east coast of Korea. However, the resurrection of this line was short-lived, as it closed again in July 2008 following an incident in which a South Korean tourist was shot and killed.\n\nThere are several buildings on both the north and the south side of the [[Military Demarcation Line]] (MDL), and there have been some built on top of it. The JSA is the location where all [[Inter-Korean summits|negotiations]] since 1953 have been held, including statements of Korean solidarity, which have generally amounted to little except a slight decline of [[Inter-Korean conflict|tensions]]. The MDL goes through the conference rooms and down the middle of the conference tables where the North Koreans and the United Nations Command (primarily South Koreans and Americans) meet face to face.\n\nWithin the JSA are a number of buildings for joint meetings called Conference Rooms. These are used for direct talks between the Korean War participants and parties to the armistice. Facing the Conference Row buildings are the North Korean ''[[Panmungak]]'' ({{lang-en|Panmun Hall}}) and the South Korean [[Freedom House (Joint Security Area)|Freedom House]]. In 1994, North Korea enlarged Panmungak by adding a third floor. In 1998, South Korea built a new Freedom House for its [[Red Cross]] staff and to possibly host reunions of families separated by the [[Korean War]]. The new building incorporated the old Freedom House Pagoda within its design.\n\nSince 1953 there have been occasional confrontations and skirmishes within the JSA. The [[Korean axe murder incident|axe murder incident]] in August 1976 involved the attempted trimming of a tree which resulted in two deaths ([[Captain (United States O-3)|Captain]] Arthur Bonifas and [[First Lieutenant]] Mark Barrett). Another incident occurred on 23 November 1984, when a Soviet tourist named Vasily Matuzok (sometimes spelled Matusak), who was part of an official trip to the JSA (hosted by the North), ran across the MDL shouting that he wanted to [[defection|defect]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stripes.com/news/pacific/korea/general-revisits-deadly-1984-thanksgiving-firefight-at-dmz-1.161443 |title=General revisits deadly 1984 Thanksgiving firefight at DMZ |work=Stars and Stripes |accessdate=13 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309182210/http://www.stripes.com/news/pacific/korea/general-revisits-deadly-1984-thanksgiving-firefight-at-dmz-1.161443 |archivedate=9 March 2016 }}</ref> North Korean troops immediately chased after him, opening fire. Border guards on the South Korean side returned fire, eventually surrounding the North Koreans as they pursued Matusak. One South Korean and three North Korean soldiers were killed in the action, and Matusak was not captured.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/ops/dmz-list.htm |title=Korea Demilitarized Zone Incidents |date=2009-05-28 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100331152533/http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/ops/dmz-list.htm |archivedate=31 March 2010 }}</ref>\n\nIn late 2009, South Korean forces in conjunction with the [[United Nations Command]] began renovation of its three guard posts and two checkpoint buildings within the JSA compound. Construction was designed to enlarge and modernize the structures. Work was undertaken a year after North Korea finished replacing four JSA guard posts on its side of the MDL.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.stripes.com/article.asp?section=104&article=65534 |title=South Korea to revamp DMZ towers |newspaper=[[Stars and Stripes (newspaper)|Stars and Stripes]] |date=2009-10-22 |accessdate=2009-11-09 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091022163155/http://www.stripes.com/article.asp?section=104&article=65534 |archivedate=22 October 2009 }}</ref> On 15 October 2018, during the high-level talks in Panmunjom, military officials of the rank of [[colonel]] from the two Koreas and Burke Hamilton, Secretary of the [[United Nations Command, Military Armistice Commission, Korea|UNC Military Armistice Commission]], announced measures to reduce conventional military threats, such as creating buffer zones along their land and sea boundaries and a no-fly zone above the border, removing 11 front-line guard posts by December, and [[demining]] sections of the Demilitarized Zone.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kait8.com/2018/10/15/koreas-hold-high-level-peace-talks|title=Koreas agree to break ground on inter-Korean railroad|last=TONG-HYUNG|first=KIM|date=|work=Kait8.com|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Villages==\n[[File:Propagandavillage.JPG|thumb|North Korean [[Kij\u014fng-dong]], seen from South Korea]]\nBoth North and South Korea maintain ''peace villages'' in sight of each other's side of the DMZ. In the South, [[Daeseong-dong]] is administered under the terms of the DMZ. Villagers are classed as Republic of Korea citizens, but are [[Tax exemption|exempt]] from paying tax and other civic requirements such as [[Conscription in South Korea|military service]]. In the North, [[Kij\u014fng-dong]] features a number of brightly painted, poured-concrete multi-story buildings and apartments with electric lighting. These features represented an unheard-of level of luxury for rural Koreans, North or South, in the 1950s. The town was oriented so that the bright blue roofs and white sides of the buildings would be the most distinguishing features when viewed from the border. However, based on scrutiny with modern telescopic lenses, it has been claimed the buildings are mere concrete shells lacking window glass or even interior rooms,<ref name=\"potts\">{{Cite journal|last=Potts|first=Rolf|date=1999-02-03|title=Korea's No-man's-land|url=http://www.salon.com/1999/02/03/feature_115/|url-status=live|journal=[[Salon (magazine)|Salon]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130215050040/http://www.salon.com/1999/02/03/feature_115/|archivedate=15 February 2013}}</ref><ref>O'Neill, Tom. \"Korea's DMZ: Dangerous Divide\". ''National Geographic'', July 2003.</ref> with the building lights turned on and off at set times and the empty sidewalks swept by a [[skeleton crew]] of [[Property caretaker|caretaker]]s in an effort to preserve the illusion of activity.<ref>{{cite web |last=Silpasornprasit |first=Susan |url=http://imcom.korea.army.mil/imakoroweb/sites/local/news/020808_IMCOMK_DMZ.asp |title=Day trip to the DMZ: A look inside the Korean Demilitarized Zone |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090330022530/http://imcom.korea.army.mil/imakoroweb/sites/local/news/020808_IMCOMK_DMZ.asp |archive-date=30 March 2009 |publisher=IMCOM-Korea Region Public Affairs Office, US Army}}</ref>\n\n===Flagpoles===\n{{multiple image|image1=Daeseong-dong_Scene.jpg|caption1=South Korean [[Daeseong-dong]] and its flagpole|image2=Gijeong-ri Flag.jpg|caption2=The world's fourth-tallest flagpole (160m) flying a [[Flag of North Korea|North Korean flag]] over [[Kijong-dong|Kij\u014fng-dong]] near [[Panmunjom]]}}\nIn the 1980s, the South Korean government built a {{Convert|98.4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[flagpole|flag pole]] in Daeseong-dong, which flies a [[flag of South Korea|South Korean flag]] weighing {{Convert|130|kg|lb|0|abbr=off}}. In what some have called the \"flagpole war,\" the North Korean government responded by building the {{Convert|160|m|ft|0|abbr=on|sp=us}} [[Panmunjeom flagpole]] in Kij\u014fng-dong, only {{Convert|1.2|km|mi|1|abbr=on}} west of the border with South Korea. It flies a {{Convert|270|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} [[flag of North Korea]]. As of 2014, the Panmunjom flagpole is the fourth tallest in the world, after the [[Jeddah Flagpole]] in [[Jeddah]], [[Saudi Arabia]], at {{Convert|170|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}, the [[Dushanbe Flagpole]] in [[Dushanbe]], [[Tajikistan]], at {{Convert|165|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} and the pole at the [[National Flag Square]] in [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]], which is {{Convert|162|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/asiapcf/east/02/19/koreas.dmz/ |title=CNN.com \u2013 Korea's DMZ: 'Scariest place on Earth' |accessdate=2007-10-23 |date=2002-02-20 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012164210/http://edition.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/asiapcf/east/02/19/koreas.dmz/ |archivedate=12 October 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://economy.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_blogview.asp?at_code=370439 |script-title=ko:\uac1c\uc131\uc5d0 '\uad6c\uba4d\ud0c4' 5\ub9cc\uc7a5 \ubc30\ub2ec\ud588\uc2b5\ub2c8\ub2e4 |work=economy.ohmynews.com |accessdate=2006-12-06 |language=ko }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=Al83tito |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==DMZ-related incidents and incursions==\n{{Main|List of border incidents involving North and South Korea}}\nSince demarcation, the DMZ has had numerous cases of incidents and incursions by both sides, although the North Korean government typically never acknowledges direct responsibility for any of these incidents (there are exceptions, such as the axe incident).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fas.org/man/crs/RL30004.pdf |title=North Korea: Chronology of Provocations, 1950 \u2013 2003 |accessdate=2012-02-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060905062431/http://www.fas.org/man/crs/RL30004.pdf |archivedate=5 September 2006 }}</ref> This was particularly intense during the [[Korean DMZ Conflict (1966\u20131969)]] when a series of skirmishes along the DMZ resulted in the deaths of 43 [[US soldier|American]], 299 [[South Korean soldier|South Korean]] and 397 [[North Korean army|North Korean soldiers]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Bolger|first=Daniel|title=Scenes from an Unfinished War: Low intensity conflict in Korea 1966\u20131969|publisher=Diane Publishing Co|isbn=978-0-7881-1208-9|year=1991}}</ref> This included the [[Blue House raid|Blue House Raid]] in 1968, an attempt to [[Assassination|assassinate]] President [[Park Chung-hee|Park Chung Hee]] at the [[Blue House]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cgsc.leavenworth.army.mil/carl/download/csipubs/scenes/scen_c3.pdf |title=Scenes from an Unfinished War: Low-Intensity Conflict in Korea, 1966\u20131968 |publisher=Cgsc.leavenworth.army.mil |accessdate=2012-02-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090325103728/http://cgsc.leavenworth.army.mil/carl/download/csipubs/scenes/scen_c3.pdf |archivedate=25 March 2009 }}</ref>\n\nIn 1976, in now-[[Declassification|declassified]] meeting minutes, U.S. deputy secretary of defense [[William Clements]] told U.S. secretary of state [[Henry Kissinger]] that there had been 200 raids or incursions into North Korea from the south, though not by the U.S. military.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve12/d286 |title=Minutes of Washington Special Actions Group Meeting, Washington, 25 August 1976, 10:30 a.m. |date=25 August 1976 |accessdate=12 May 2012 |publisher=[[Office of the Historian]], US Department of State |quote=Clements: I like it. It doesn't have an overt character. I have been told that there have been 200 other such operations and that none of these have surfaced. Kissinger: It is different for us with the War Powers Act. I don't remember any such operations. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120925121535/http://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve12/d286 |archivedate=25 September 2012 }}</ref> Details of only a few of these incursions have become public, including raids by South Korean forces in 1967 that had sabotaged about 50 North Korean facilities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2011/02/116_80936.html |title=S. Korea raided North with captured agents in 1967 |newspaper=The Korea Times |author=Lee Tae-hoon |date=7 February 2011 |accessdate=12 May 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121001195904/http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2011/02/116_80936.html |archivedate=1 October 2012 }}</ref>\n\n===Incursion tunnels===\n{{See also|Tunnel warfare}}\nSince 15 November 1974, South Korea has discovered four tunnels crossing the DMZ that had been dug by North Korea. The orientation of the blasting lines within each tunnel indicated they were dug by North Korea. North Korea claimed that the tunnels were for [[coal mining]]; however, no coal was found in the tunnels, which were dug through granite. Some of the tunnel walls were painted black to give the appearance of [[anthracite]].<ref>{{cite book|first=Jim|last=Sides|title=Almost Home|publisher=Xulon Press|year=2009|isbn=978-1-60791-740-3|page=118}}</ref>\n\nThe tunnels are believed to have been planned as a military invasion route by North Korea. They run in a north-south direction and do not have branches. Following each discovery, engineering within the tunnels has become progressively more advanced. For example, the third tunnel sloped slightly upwards as it progressed southward, to prevent [[water stagnation]]. Today, visitors from the south may visit the second, third and fourth tunnels through guided tours.<ref>{{cite web|title=Demilitarized Zone |publisher=GlobalSecurity.org |url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/ops/dmz.htm |accessdate=2007-11-09 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071105034940/http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/ops/dmz.htm |archivedate=5 November 2007 }}</ref>\n\n====First tunnel====\nThe first of the tunnels was discovered on 20 November 1974, by a South Korean Army patrol, noticing steam rising from the ground. The initial discovery was met with [[Automatic firearm|automatic fire]] from North Korean soldiers. Five days later, during a subsequent exploration of this tunnel, [[United States Navy|US Navy]] Commander Robert M. Ballinger and [[Republic of Korea Marine Corps|ROK Marine Corps]] Major Kim Hah-chul were killed in the tunnel by a North Korean explosive device. The blast also wounded five Americans and one South Korean from the United Nations Command.\n\nThe tunnel, which was about {{convert|3|by|4|ft|1|abbr=on|order=flip}}, extended more than {{convert|1|km|yd|abbr=on}} beyond the MDL into South Korea. The tunnel was reinforced with concrete slabs and had electric power and lighting. There were [[Weapon storage area|weapon storage]] and sleeping areas. A [[narrow-gauge railway]] with carts had also been installed. Estimates based on the tunnel's size suggest it would have allowed considerable numbers of soldiers to pass through it.<ref name=bermudez_js>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621051225/http://www.korean-war.com/Archives/2002/02/msg00289.html |archivedate=2013-06-21 |url=http://www.korean-war.com/Archives/2002/02/msg00289.html |title=Tunnels under the DMZ |author=Bermudez, Joseph S. Jr |accessdate=2010-03-26 |website=korean-war.com}}</ref>\n\n====Second tunnel====\n[[File:Entrance to the 4th Infiltration Tunnel, Korean DMZ.jpg|thumb|Entrance to the North Korean-dug 4th Infiltration Tunnel, Korean DMZ]]\nThe second tunnel was discovered on 19 March 1975. It is of similar length to the first tunnel. It is located between {{convert|50|and|160|m|ft|abbr=on}} below ground, but is larger than the first, approximately {{convert|2|by|2|m|ft|0|sp=us|abbr=in}}.\n\n====Third tunnel====\n{{main|Third Tunnel of Aggression}}\nThe third tunnel was discovered on 17 October 1978. Unlike the previous two, the third tunnel was discovered following a tip from a [[North Korean defectors|North Korean defector]]. This tunnel is about {{convert|1600|m|ft|abbr=on}} long and about {{convert|73|m|ft|abbr=on}} below ground.<ref>{{cite book|last=Robinson|first=Martin|title=Seoul|year=2009|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=978-1-74104-774-5|pages=162}}</ref> Foreign visitors touring the South Korean DMZ may view inside this tunnel using a sloped access shaft.\n\n====Fourth tunnel====\nA fourth tunnel was discovered on 3 March 1990, north of [[Haean]] town in the former [[Punchbowl, Korea|Punchbowl]] battlefield. The tunnel's dimensions are {{convert|2|by|2|m|ft|0|sp=us|abbr=in}}, and it is {{convert|145|m|ft}} deep. The method of construction is almost identical in structure to the second and the third tunnels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panmunjomtour.com/english/dmz/dmz_20.htm |title=The Fourth Infiltration Tunnel |publisher=Panmunjom Travel Center |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070309084651/http://www.panmunjomtour.com/english/dmz/dmz_20.htm |archivedate= 9 March 2007 }}</ref>\n\n===Korean wall===\n[[File:The Korean Wall in the DMZ.JPG|thumb|The Korean wall, or anti-tank barrier, in the [[demilitarized zone]] seen through binoculars from the North Korean side.]]\nAccording to North Korea, between 1977 and 1979 the South Korean and United States authorities constructed a concrete wall along the DMZ.<ref name=\"tetteroo\"/> North Korea, however, began to propagate information about the wall after the [[fall of the Berlin Wall]] in 1989, when the symbolism of a wall [[Injustice|unjustly]] dividing a people became more apparent.<ref>{{cite book|last=Salzinger|first=Caroline|translator-last=Lempinen|translator-first=Ulla|title=Terveisi\u00e4 pahan akselilta: Arkea ja politiikkaa maailman suljetuimmissa valtioissa|year=2008|publisher=Atena|location=Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4|language=fi|isbn=978-951-796-521-7|page=40}}</ref>\n\nVarious organizations, such as the North Korean tour guide company Korea Konsult, claimed a wall was dividing Korea, saying that:\n\n{{quote|In the area south of the Military Demarcation Line, which cuts across Korea at its waist, there is a concrete wall which ... stretches more than {{convert|240|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} from east to west, is {{convert|5|-|8|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} high, {{convert|10|-|19|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} thick at the bottom, and {{convert|3|-|7|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} wide in the upper part. It is set with wire entanglements and dotted with gun embrasures, look-outs and varieties of military establishments.<!-- not in citation: [...] the South Korean rulers built this wall over a period of many years from 1977.--><ref>{{cite web|title=DMZ: Demilitarized Zone|url=http://koreakonsult.net/Attraction_DMZ_eng.html|publisher=Korea Konsult|accessdate=16 April 2015}}</ref>}}\n\nIn December 1999, Chu Chang-jun, [[China\u2013North Korea relations|North Korea's ambassador to China]], repeated claims that a \"wall\" divided Korea. He said the south side of the wall is packed with soil, which permits access to the top of the wall and makes it effectively invisible from the south side. He also claimed that it served as a bridgehead for any northward [[invasion]].<ref name=\"Wall\">{{cite web|url=http://www.korean-war.com/Archives/2000/12/msg00041.html |title=New York Times, 1999 |publisher=Korean-war.com |accessdate=2012-02-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308122740/http://www.korean-war.com/Archives/2000/12/msg00041.html |archivedate= 8 March 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Tear Down the Korean Wall |url=http://www.kimsoft.com/1997/nk9912.htm |publisher=DPRK UN Mission |date=1999-12-03 |accessdate=2007-10-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060329064336/http://www.kimsoft.com/1997/nk9912.htm |archivedate=29 March 2006 }}</ref>\n\nThe United States and South Korea deny the wall's existence, although they do claim there are [[Anti-tank obstacles|anti-tank barriers]] along some sections of the DMZ.<ref>{{cite news|last=Eckholm |first=Erik |date=8 December 1999 |title=Where Most See Ramparts, North Korea Imagines a Wall |url=http://partners.nytimes.com/library/world/asia/120899nkorea-skorea.html |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=26 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816222047/http://partners.nytimes.com/library/world/asia/120899nkorea-skorea.html |archivedate=16 August 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn the [[RT (TV network)|RT]] documentary ''10 Days in North Korea'', the crew shot footage of a wall as seen from North Korea and described it as a \"5 metre high wall stretching from east to west\".<ref>{{cite web|title=10 Days in North Korea |url=http://rt.com/shows/documentary/203135-north-korea-kim-jongun/ |author=\u00c1ngela Gallardo Bernal |publisher=RT |accessdate=20 February 2017 |date=9 November 2014 |id=at 19:30 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222101514/https://www.rt.com/shows/documentary/203135-north-korea-kim-jongun/ |archivedate=22 December 2016 }}</ref> Dutch journalist and filmmaker [[Peter Tetteroo]] also shot footage of a barrier in 2001 which his North Korean guides said was the Korean Wall.<ref name=\"tetteroo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmakers.com/index.php?a=filmDetail&filmID=1138 |title=Welcome to North Korea: A film by Peter Tetteroo for KRO Television |accessdate=2009-12-29 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711001620/http://www.filmakers.com/index.php?a=filmDetail&filmID=1138 |archivedate=11 July 2011 }}</ref>\n\nA 2007 [[Reuters]] report revealed that there is no coast to coast wall located across the DMZ and that the pictures of a \"wall\" which have been used in North Korean propaganda have merely been pictures of concrete anti-tank barriers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-korea-north-wall/north-korea-asks-south-to-tear-down-imaginary-wall-idUSSEO20068620071231|title=North Korea asks South to tear down imaginary wall|first=Jon|last=Herskovitz|date=31 December 2007|work=Reuters|accessdate=1 October 2018}}</ref> While 800,000 landmines were being removed in 2018, it was shown that the [[Joint Security Area]] along the Korean border was guarded by standard [[barbed wire]].<ref name=bbckoreaoct>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-45704909|title=Koreas begin clearing landmines from heavily fortified border|last=|first=|date=1 October 2018|work=BBC News|access-date=9 February 2019|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==North Korean side of the DMZ==\n[[File:Entrance_of_Joint_Security_Area,_Korean_Demilitarized_Zone,_DPRK_side.jpg|thumb|DMZ, North Korea. [[Electric fence]]s are used in the Korean Demilitarized Zone as a means to seal off North Korea from South Korea. Behind the fence, there is a strip which has [[land mine]]s hidden beneath it.]]\nThe North Korean side of the DMZ primarily serves to prevent North Korean citizens from leaving North Korea. It also serves a similar function as the [[Berlin Wall]] and the [[inner German border]] did against its own citizens in the former [[East Germany]] in that it stops North Korean citizens from defecting to South Korea.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.qsl.net/ah6hy/SKDMZ.html |title=Korea Border Area |accessdate=2017-03-12 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914011727/http://www.qsl.net/ah6hy/SKDMZ.html |archivedate=14 September 2016 }} Bottom of the page. Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1982/05/20/world/north-korea-blocks-defections-across-dmz.html |title=North Korea Blocks Defections Across DMZ |accessdate=2017-03-12 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312202845/http://www.nytimes.com/1982/05/20/world/north-korea-blocks-defections-across-dmz.html |archivedate=12 March 2017 |newspaper=The New York Times |date=20 May 1982 |last1=Stokes |first1=Henry Scott }} Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref>\n\nFrom the armistice until 1972, approximately 7,700 North Korean soldiers and agents infiltrated South Korea to sabotage military bases and industrial areas.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/02/15/world/south-korean-movie-unlocks-door-on-a-once-secret-past.html?_r=0|title=South Korean Movie Unlocks Door on a Once-Secret Past|newspaper=The New York Times|author=Norimitsu Onishi|date=15 February 2014|accessdate=13 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nNorth Korea has thousands of artillery pieces near the DMZ. According to a 2018 article in ''[[The Economist]]'', North Korea could bombard Seoul with over 10,000 rounds every minute.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.economist.com/news/leaders/21735586-how-shifts-technology-and-geopolitics-are-renewing-threat-growing-danger|title=The Growing Danger of Great-Power Conflict|last=|first=|date=|journal=The Economist|language=en|access-date=2018-02-05}}</ref> Experts believe that 60 percent of its total [[artillery]] is positioned within a few kilometers of the DMZ acting as a deterrent against any South Korean invasion.\n\n==Propaganda==\n{{See also|Propaganda|Psychological warfare}}\n\n===Loudspeaker installations===\nFrom 1953 until 2004, both sides broadcast audio propaganda across the DMZ.<ref name=bbc-20040615/> Massive loudspeakers mounted on several of the buildings delivered DPRK propaganda broadcasts directed towards the south as well as propaganda radio broadcasts across the border.<ref name=\"potts\"/> In 2004, the North and South agreed to end the broadcasts.<ref name=\"bbc-20040615\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/3807409.stm|title=Koreas Switch off Loudspeakers|date=15 June 2004|accessdate=7 May 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040615123223/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/3807409.stm|archivedate=15 June 2004|url-status=live|publisher=BBC}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 August 2015, a border incident occurred where two South Korean soldiers were wounded after stepping on landmines that had allegedly been laid on the southern side of the DMZ by North Korean forces near an ROK guard post.<ref name=\"Choe Sang-hun\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/11/world/asia/north-korea-placed-mines-that-maimed-2-south-korean-soldiers-at-dmz-seoul-says.html?_r=0 |title=South Korea Accuses the North After Land Mines Maim Two Soldiers in DMZ |author=Choe Sang-hun |newspaper=New York Times |date=10 August 2015 |accessdate=13 August 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150813125328/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/11/world/asia/north-korea-placed-mines-that-maimed-2-south-korean-soldiers-at-dmz-seoul-says.html?_r=0 |archivedate=13 August 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Park |first=Ju-Min |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/08/10/us-southkorea-northkorea-mines-idUSKCN0QF07A20150810 |title=South Korea condemns North over land mine blast, vows retaliation |location=Seoul |work=[[Reuters]] |date=2015-08-10 |accessdate=2015-08-10 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150810235643/http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/08/10/us-southkorea-northkorea-mines-idUSKCN0QF07A20150810 |archivedate=10 August 2015 }}</ref> Both North Korea and South Korea then resumed broadcasting propaganda by loudspeaker.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/21/world/asia/north-korea-and-south-korea-exchange-rocket-and-artillery-fire.html |title=North Korea and South Korea Trade Fire Across Border, Seoul Says |date=21 August 2015 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=13 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117145801/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/21/world/asia/north-korea-and-south-korea-exchange-rocket-and-artillery-fire.html |archivedate=17 January 2016 }}</ref>  After four days of negotiations, on 25 August 2015 South Korea agreed to discontinue the broadcasts following a statement from North Korea's government expressing regret for the landmine incident.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bostonherald.com/news_opinion/international/asia/2015/08/south_korea_turns_off_propaganda_as_koreas_reach_deal |title=South Korea turns off propaganda as Koreas reach deal |date=2015-08-25 |accessdate=2015-08-25 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924004726/http://www.bostonherald.com/news_opinion/international/asia/2015/08/south_korea_turns_off_propaganda_as_koreas_reach_deal |archivedate=24 September 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn 8 January 2016, in response to North Korea's supposed successful testing of a [[Thermonuclear weapon|hydrogen bomb]], South Korea resumed broadcasts directed at the North.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kim |first1=Sam |title=South Korea Punishes Kim Jong Un With K-Pop for Nuclear Test |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-01-07/south-korea-to-inflict-k-pop-blasts-on-kim-jong-un-for-nuke-test |accessdate=8 January 2016 |work=Bloomsberg |date=2016-01-07 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107213804/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-01-07/south-korea-to-inflict-k-pop-blasts-on-kim-jong-un-for-nuke-test |archivedate=7 January 2016 }}</ref>  On 15 April 2016, it was reported that the South Koreans purchased a new stereo system to combat the North's broadcasts.<ref name=thereg-20160415>{{cite news|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/04/15/south_korea_to_upgrade_national_stereo_system_at_cost_of_us16m/ |title=South Korea to upgrade national stereo defence system for US$16m |author=Simon Sharwood |newspaper=The Register |date=15 April 2016 |accessdate=22 April 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160419011741/http://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/04/15/south_korea_to_upgrade_national_stereo_system_at_cost_of_us16m/ |archivedate=19 April 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Balloons===\n{{main|Balloon propaganda campaigns in Korea}}\nBoth North and South Korea have held [[Airborne leaflet propaganda|balloon propaganda leaflet]] campaigns since the Korean War.{{sfn|Jung|2014|p=16}}\n\nIn recent years, mainly South Korean [[non-governmental organization]]s have been involved in launching balloons targeted at the DMZ and beyond.{{sfn|Jung|2014|p=9}} Due to the winds, the balloons tend to fall near the DMZ where there are mostly [[North Korean soldier]]s to see the leaflets.<ref name=\"Higginbotham2014\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2014-06-05/the-no-tech-tactics-of-north-koreas-target-zero-park-sang-hak#p4 |title=The No-Tech Tactics of North Korea's Most Wanted Defector |last=Higginbotham |first=Adam |date=5 June 2014 |website=[[Bloomberg News]] |access-date=1 July 2015 |page=4 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703211625/http://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2014-06-05/the-no-tech-tactics-of-north-koreas-target-zero-park-sang-hak |archivedate=3 July 2015 }}</ref> As with the loudspeakers, balloon operations were mutually agreed to be halted between 2004 and 2010.{{sfn|Jung|2014|p=23}} It has been assessed that the activists' balloons may contribute to the decay of remaining cooperation between the Korean governments,<ref name=\"Feffer2014\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ips-dc.org/koreas-balloon-war/ |title=Korea's Balloon War |last=Feffer |first=John |date=6 November 2014 |website=[[Institute for Policy Studies]] |publisher= |access-date=29 June 2015}}</ref> and the DMZ has become more [[Militarization|militarized]] in recent years.{{sfn|Jung|2014|p=31}}\n\nMany North Korean leaflets during the [[Cold War]] gave instructions and maps to help targeted South Korean soldiers in defecting. One of the leaflets found on the DMZ included a map of [[Cho Dae-hum]]'s route of [[South Korean defectors|defection to North Korea]] across the DMZ. In addition to using balloons as a means of delivery, North Koreans have also used [[rocket]]s to send leaflets to the DMZ.<ref name=\"Friedman2006\">{{cite web|url=http://www.psywarrior.com/NKoreaH.html |title=Communist Korean War Leaflets |last=Friedman |first=Herbert A. |date=5 January 2006 |website=www.psywarrior.com |access-date=28 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150711121501/http://www.psywarrior.com/NKoreaH.html |archivedate=11 July 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Dismantling===\nOn 23 April 2018, both North and South Korea officially cancelled their border propaganda broadcasts for the last time.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/04/23/asia/north-korea-south-korea-upcoming-summit-intl/index.html|title=South Korea stops blasting propaganda along DMZ as summit looms|author1=Joshua Berlinger |author2=Yoonjung Seo|work=CNN|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref> On 1 May 2018, the loudspeakers across the Korean border were dismantled.<ref name=may1>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2018/05/01/607399907/north-and-south-korea-dismantle-loudspeakers-blaring-propaganda-on-the-dmz |title=North And South Korea Dismantle Loudspeakers Blaring Propaganda On The DMZ : The Two-Way |publisher=NPR |date=2018-05-01 |accessdate=2018-10-01}}</ref> Both sides also committed to ending the balloon campaigns.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2018-05-05/south-korea-faces-decision-over-leaflets-ties-warm-north|title=South Korea faces a decision over leaflets as ties warm with the North|last=|first=|date=|work=Public Radio International|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref> On 5 May 2018, an attempt by North Korean defectors to disperse more balloon propaganda across the border from South Korea was halted by the South Korean government.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/05/05/south-korea-sabotages-anti-north-korea-leaflet-drop/|title=South Korean police stop protesters releasing balloons to the North, as ties thaw|first=Reuters News|last=Agency|date=5 May 2018|via=www.telegraph.co.uk|newspaper=The Telegraph}}</ref> The no-fly zone which was established on 1 November 2018 also designated a no-fly zone for all aircraft types above the MDL, and prohibits hot-air balloons from traveling within 25&nbsp;km of the Korean border's [[Military Demarcation Line]] (MDL).<ref name=\"nov1effect\">[https://www.ncnk.org/sites/default/files/Agreement%20on%20the%20Implementation%20of%20the%20Historic%20Panmunjom%20Declaration%20in%20the%20Military%20Domain.pdf Agreement on the Implementation of the Historic Panmunjom Declaration in the Military Domain] , 2018 (PDF)</ref>\n\n==Civilian Control Line==\n{{multiple image\n|total_width=478\n|image1=Civilian_Control_Line,_Imjingak,_Paju,_South_Korea_(3162648972).jpg\n|caption1=Civilian Control Line, Imjingak, Paju, South Korea\n|image2=Korea_Civilian_Control_Line2010(1).JPG\n|caption2=Civilian Control Line, South Korea\n}}\nThe Civilian Control Line (CCL), or the Civilian Control Zone (CCZ, [[:ko:\ubbfc\uac04\uc778\ucd9c\uc785\ud1b5\uc81c\uad6c\uc5ed|\ubbfc\uac04\uc778\ucd9c\uc785\ud1b5\uc81c\uad6c\uc5ed]]), is a line that designates an additional buffer zone to the DMZ within a distance of {{Convert|5|to|20|km|lk=|abbr=on}} from the Southern Limit Line of the DMZ. Its purpose is to limit and control the entrance of civilians into the area in order to protect and maintain the security of military facilities and operations near the DMZ. The commander of the [[Eighth United States Army|8th US Army]] ordered the creation of the CCL and it was activated and first became effective in February 1954.<ref>{{cite web | author=Panmunjom tour | title=DMZ - Terminology | website=tourdmz.com  | url=http://tourdmz.com/english/02dmz/p2-1.php | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305210517/http://tourdmz.com/english/02dmz/p2-1.php | archive-date=2016-03-05 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe buffer zone that falls south of the Southern Limit Line is called the Civilian Control Zone. Barbed wire fences and manned military [[Guardpost|guard posts]] mark the Civilian Control Line. The Civilian Control Zone is necessary for the military to monitor civilian travel to tourist destinations close to the Southern Limit Line of the DMZ like the discovered infiltration tunnels and tourist observatories. Usually when traveling within the Civilian Control Zone, South Korean soldiers accompany tourist buses and cars as armed guards to monitor the civilians as well as to protect them from North Korean intruders.\n\nRight after the [[Korean Armistice Agreement|ceasefire]], the Civilian Control Zone outside the DMZ encompassed 100 or so empty villages. The government implemented migration measures to attract settlers into the area. As a result, in 1983, when the area delineated by the Civilian Control Line was at its largest, a total of 39,725 residents in 8,799 households were living in the 81 villages located within the Civilian Control Zone.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreana.or.kr/user/0003/nd6245.do?View&boardNo=00000415&pubLang=English&pubYear=2016&pubMonth=AUTUMN&zineInfoNo=0003|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312071509/http://www.koreana.or.kr/user/0003/nd6245.do?View&boardNo=00000415&pubLang=English&pubYear=2016&pubMonth=AUTUMN&zineInfoNo=0003|url-status=dead|archive-date=2017-03-12|title=DMZ: The Forbidden Land Glimpsed through Barbed Wire Fences|website=Koreana: Korean culture & arts|language=ko|access-date=2017-03-17}} </ref>\n\nMost of the tourist and media photos of the \"DMZ fence\" are actually photos of the CCL fence. The actual DMZ fence on the Southern Limit Line is completely [[Limited-access road|off-limits]] to everybody except soldiers and it is illegal to take pictures of the DMZ fence. The CCL fence acts more as a deterrent for South Korean civilians from getting too close to the dangerous DMZ and is also the final barrier for North Korean [[Infiltration tactics|infiltrators]] if they get past the Southern Limit Line DMZ fence.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/figure/A-map-of-the-study-site-presenting-the-location-of-Military-Demarcation-LineMDL_fig1_277646914 |title =A map of the study site presenting the location of Military Demarcation Line(MDL), Southern Limit Line(SLL) and Civilian Control Line(CCL). Civilian Control Zone is located between SLL and CCL. Border Line(BL) is designated within 25km from CCL |via=Development of Evaluation Indices for Ecological Restoration of Degraded Environments Near DMZ in the Republic of Korea }}</ref>\n\n==Neutral Zone of the Han River Estuary==\nThe whole estuary of the [[Han River (Korea)|Han River]] is deemed a \"Neutral Zone\" and is off-limits to all civilian vessels and is treated like the rest of the DMZ. Only [[military vessel]]s are allowed within this neutral zone.\n\nAccording to the July 1953 [[Korean Armistice Agreement]] civil [[Freight transport|shipping]] was supposed to be permissible in the Han River estuary and allow Seoul to be connected to the [[Yellow Sea]] (West Sea) via the Han River.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.findlaw.com/cnn/docs/korea/kwarmagr072753.html |title=FindLaw Legal Blogs |accessdate=2014-04-14 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305164517/http://news.findlaw.com/cnn/docs/korea/kwarmagr072753.html |archivedate=5 March 2014 }} Article 1, Section 5. Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref> However, both Koreas and the UNC failed to make this happen. The South Korean government ordered the construction of the [[Ara Canal]] to finally connect [[Seoul]] to the Yellow Sea, which was completed in 2012. Seoul was effectively landlocked from the ocean until 2012. The biggest limitation of the Ara Canal is it is too narrow to handle any vessels except small tourist boats and recreational boats, so Seoul still cannot receive large commercial ships or passenger ships in its port.\n\nIn recent years [[China|Chinese]] fishing vessels have taken advantage of the tense situation in the [[Han River (Korea)|Han River]] Estuary Neutral Zone and illegally fished in this area due to both the [[Korean People's Navy|North Korean]] and [[Republic of Korea Navy|South Korean]] navies never patrolling this area due to the fear of naval battles breaking out. This has led to [[Naval combat|firefights]] and sinkings of boats between Chinese fishermen and the [[South Korean Coast Guard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maritime-executive.com/article/south-korea-to-respond-to-illegal-fishing-with-force |title=South Korea to Respond to Illegal Fishing with Force |accessdate=2017-03-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312070836/http://www.maritime-executive.com/article/south-korea-to-respond-to-illegal-fishing-with-force |archivedate=12 March 2017 }} Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiskerforum.dk/en/news/b/han-river-crackdown |title=Han River crackdown - FiskerForum |accessdate=2017-03-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312060747/http://www.fiskerforum.dk/en/news/b/han-river-crackdown |archivedate=12 March 2017 |date=13 June 2016 }} Retrieved 11 March 2017</ref>\n\nOn January 30, 2019 North Korean and South Korean military officials signed a landmark agreement that would open the Han River Estuary to civilian vessels for the first time since the Armistice Agreement in 1953. The agreement will take effect on April 1, 2019 on a trial basis for a few vessels at first and then later will increase in stages gradually until freedom of passage will be granted to any large private ship, like a large cruise or cargo ship, who wishes to travel to Seoul as a final destination via the Han River.<ref>{{cite web | title=S. Korea shares nautical charts of Han River estuary with N. Korea | website=English Edition | date=2019-01-31 | url=http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_national/880735.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | author=\uc1a1\uc0c1\ud638 | title=Koreas to open Han River estuary to civilian ships in April | website=Yonhap News Agency | date=2019-01-30 | url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20190130008700315}}</ref>\n\n==Castle of Gung Ye==\nWithin the DMZ itself, in the town of [[Cheorwon]], is the old capital of the kingdom of [[Taebong]] (901\u2013918), a regional upstart that became [[Goryeo]], the dynasty that ruled a [[History of Korea|united Korea]] from 918 to 1392.\n\n[[Taebong]] was founded by the charismatic leader [[Gung Ye]], a brilliant if tyrannical one-eyed ex-[[Buddhist monk]]. Rebelling against the kingdom of [[Silla]], Korea's then ruling dynasty, he proclaimed the kingdom of [[Taebong]]\u2014also called Later Goguryeo, in reference to the ancient kingdom of [[Goguryeo]] (37BCE-668CE)\u2014in 901, with himself as king. The kingdom consisted of much of central Korea, including areas around the DMZ. He placed his capital in [[Cheorwon]], a mountainous region that was easily defensible (in the Korean War, this same region would earn the name \"the [[Iron Triangle (Korea)|Iron Triangle]]\").\n\nAs a former Buddhist monk, [[Gung Ye]] actively promoted the religion of [[Buddhism]] and incorporated Buddhist ceremonies into the new kingdom. Even after Gung Ye was [[Dethroning|dethroned]] by his own generals and replaced by [[Wang Geon]], the man who would rule over a united Korea as the first king of [[Goryeo]], this Buddhist influence would continue, playing a major role in shaping the culture of medieval Korea.\n\nAs the ruins of Gung Ye's capital lie in the DMZ itself, visitors cannot see them. Moreover, excavation work and research have been hampered by political realities. In the future, inter-Korean peace may allow for proper archaeological studies to be conducted on the castle site and other historical sites within and underneath the DMZ.<ref>Koehler, Rober. (2011). {{Google books|8FatCQAAQBAJ|''The DMZ: Dividing the Two Koreas''|page=108}}</ref>\n\nThe ruins of the capital city of Taebong, the ruins of the castle of Gung Ye, and King Gung Ye's [[tomb]] all lie within the DMZ and are off-limits to everybody except soldiers who patrol the DMZ.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://leekihwan.khan.kr/368 |title=\ud734\uc804\uc120\uc774 \ucc22\uc5b4\ub193\uc740 \uad81\uc608\uc758 \uc57c\ub9dd |accessdate=2017-03-11 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312060535/http://leekihwan.khan.kr/368 |archivedate=12 March 2017 |date=27 October 2014 | language=ko }} Retrieved 10 March 2017. Many pictures, maps, and description of the old Taebong capital that is stuck in the middle of the DMZ.</ref>\n\n==Transportation==\n[[File:Donghae-bukbu line on Korean DMZ.JPG|thumb|The Donghae Bukbu Line on Korea's east coast. The road and rail link was built for South Koreans visiting the [[Mount Kumgang Tourist Region]] in the North.]]\n[[File:DMZ train Seoul to Dorasan.jpg|thumb|[[DMZ Train]] tour organized by Korail]]\n[[Panmunjeom]] is the site of the negotiations that ended the Korean War and is the main center of human activity in the DMZ. The village is located on the main highway and near a railroad connecting the two Koreas.\n\nThe railway, which connects Seoul and [[Pyongyang]], was called the [[Gyeongui Line]] before division in the 1940s.  Currently the South uses the original name, but the North refers to the route as the P'y\u014fngbu Line. The railway line has been mainly used to carry materials and South Korean workers to the [[Kaesong Industrial Region]]. Its reconnection has been seen as part of the general improvement in the relations between North and South in the early part of this century. However, in November 2008 North Korean authorities closed the railway amid growing tensions with the South.<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://news.scotsman.com/northkorea/Last-train-to-Kaesong-as.4744792.jp|title=Last train to Kaesong as Korean relations cool|date=2008-11-28|publisher=News.Scotman.Com|location=Edinburgh|first=Jae-Soon|last=Chang}}</ref> Following the death of former [[President of South Korea|South Korean President]] [[Kim Dae-jung]], conciliatory talks were held between South Korean officials and a North Korean delegation who attended Kim's funeral. In September 2009, the Kaesong rail and road crossing was reopened.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_northkorea/375550.html |title=Inter-Korean economic cooperation Kaesong office reopens |publisher=Englishhani |date=2009-09-07 |accessdate=2009-09-17 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722143648/http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_northkorea/375550.html |archivedate=22 July 2011 }}</ref>\n\nThe road at Panmunjeom, which was known historically as ''Highway One'' in the South, was originally the only access point between the two countries on the Korean Peninsula. Passage is comparable to the strict movements that occurred at [[Checkpoint Charlie]] in Berlin at the height of the [[Cold War]]. Both North and South Korea's roads end in the JSA; the highways do not quite join as there is a {{convert|20|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} concrete line that divides the entire site. People given the rare permission to cross this border must do so on foot before continuing their journey by road.\n\nIn 2007, on the east coast of Korea, the first train crossed the DMZ on the new [[Donghae Bukbu Line|Donghae Bukbu (Tonghae Pukpu) Line]]. The new rail crossing was built adjacent to the road which took South Koreans to [[Mount Kumgang Tourist Region]], a region of significant cultural importance for all Koreans. More than one million civilian visitors crossed the DMZ until the route was closed following the shooting of a 53-year-old South Korean tourist in July 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/world/2008-07/12/content_6839889.htm |title=ROK woman tourist shot dead at DPRK resort |newspaper=[[China Daily]] |date=2008-07-12 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120217140840/http://www2.chinadaily.com.cn/world/2008-07/12/content_6839889.htm |archivedate=17 February 2012 }}</ref> After a [[Joint investigation team|joint investigation]] was rebuffed by North Korea, the South Korean government suspended tours to the resort. Since then the resort and the Donghae Bukbu Line have effectively been closed by North Korea.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/7539368.stm |title=N Korea steps up row with South |publisher=BBC |date=2008-08-03 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090930093913/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/7539368.stm |archivedate=30 September 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/8639065.stm |title=North Korea 'to seize property at Kumgang resort' |publisher=BBC |date=2010-04-23}}</ref> Currently, the South Korean [[Korea Railroad Corporation]] (Korail) organizes tours to DMZ with special DMZ themed trains.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.letskorail.com/ebizbf/EbizBfAboutDmz_Train.do|title=Korail|website=www.letskorail.com}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 October 2018, North and South Korea, agreed to meet the summit's goal of restoring railway and road transportation which had been cut since the Korean War by either late November or early December 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-northkorea-southkorea-idUSKCN1MP0D0|title=Koreas to reconnect roads, rail, U.S. concerned over easing sanctions|date=15 October 2018|via=www.reuters.com|newspaper=Reuters}}</ref> Road and railway transportation along the DMZ was reconnected in November 2018.<ref name=nov22kr /><ref name=nov22 /><ref name=nov30 />\n\n==Nature reserve==\n[[File:DMZ in Goseong.jpg|thumb|Goesong lookout point]]\n[[File:President Moon Jaein Gangwondo 20190426 08.jpg|thumb|]]\nIn the past half century, the Korean DMZ has been a deadly place for humans, making habitation impossible. Only around the village of [[Panmunjom]] and more recently the Donghae Bukbu Line on Korea's east coast have there been regular incursions by people.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2012/apr/13/wildlife-thriving-korean-demilitarised-zone |title=How wildlife is thriving in the Korean peninsula's demilitarised zone |first=Lisa |last=Brady |date=13 April 2012 |via=The Guardian |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160905181630/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2012/apr/13/wildlife-thriving-korean-demilitarised-zone |archivedate=5 September 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.american.edu/TED/ice/DMZ.HTM |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-09-01 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520080629/http://www1.american.edu/TED/ice/DMZ.HTM |archivedate=20 May 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThis natural isolation along the {{convert|250|km|abbr=on}} length of the DMZ has created an [[involuntary park]] which is now recognized as one of the most well-preserved areas of temperate [[habitat]] in the world.<ref name=\"Green\"/> In 1966 it was first proposed that the DMZ be turned into a [[national park]].<ref name=\"Paige 1967\"/>\n\nSeveral [[Endangered species|endangered animal and plant species]] now exist among the heavily fortified fences, [[landmines]] and listening posts. These include the endangered [[red-crowned crane]] (a staple of Asian art), the [[white-naped crane]], critically endangered [[Korean Fox]]<ref>{{cite web | last=Shim | first=Elizabeth | title=South Korean fox crossed into North Korea, Seoul says | website=UPI | date=2016-02-01 | url=https://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2016/02/01/South-Korean-fox-crossed-into-North-Korea-Seoul-says/6521454354667/}}</ref> and [[Asiatic black bear]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-48214343|title=Rare Asiatic Black Bear spotted in DMZ|date=10 May 2019|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref>, and, potentially, the extremely rare [[Siberian tiger]],<ref name=\"Green\">{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2003/WORLD/asiapcf/east/08/22/korea.bio.dmz/ |title=Korea's DMZ: The thin green line |publisher=CNN |accessdate=2009-07-30 |date=2003-08-22 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090805110227/http://edition.cnn.com/2003/WORLD/asiapcf/east/08/22/korea.bio.dmz/ |archivedate=5 August 2009 }}</ref> [[Amur leopard]], and endangered marine species such as Western [[Gray Whale]].<ref>Hall Healy, 2007, KOREAN DEMILITARIZED ZONE: PEACE AND NATURE PARK, International Journal on World Peace\nVol. 24, No. 4 (DECEMBER 2007), pp. 61-83\n</ref><ref>Hyun Woo Kim, Hawsun Sohn, Yasutaka Imai, 2018, Possible occurrence of a Gray Whale off Korea in 2015, International Whaling Commission, SC/67B/CMP/11 Rev1</ref> [[Ecologist]]s have identified some 2,900 plant species, 70 types of mammals and 320 kinds of birds within the narrow buffer zone.<ref name=\"Green\"/> Additional surveys are now being conducted throughout the region.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_view.asp?menu=c10400&no=199457&rel_no=1 |title=Korean 'Tigerman' Prowls the DMZ |publisher=International Korean News |accessdate=2009-07-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090813200543/http://english.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_view.asp?menu=c10400&no=199457&rel_no=1 |archivedate=13 August 2009 }}</ref>\n\nThe DMZ owes its varied [[biodiversity]] to its geography, which crosses mountains, prairies, swamps, lakes, and tidal marshes. [[Environmentalist]]s hope that the DMZ will be conserved as a [[nature reserve|wildlife refuge]], with a well-developed set of objective and management plans vetted and in place. In 2005, [[CNN]] founder and [[media mogul]] [[Ted Turner]], on a visit to North Korea, said that he would financially support any plans to turn the DMZ into a peace park and a UN-protected [[World Heritage Site]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2005-11-18-turnerdmz_x.htm |title=Ted Turner: Turn Korean DMZ into peace park |newspaper=USA TODAY |date=2005-11-18 |accessdate=2010-05-07 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091206190920/http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2005-11-18-turnerdmz_x.htm |archivedate=6 December 2009 }}</ref>\n\nIn September 2011, South Korea submitted a nomination form to [[Man and the Biosphere Programme]] (MAB) in [[UNESCO]] for designation of {{convert|435|km\u00b2|sqmi|abbr=on}} in the southern part of the DMZ below the Military Demarcation Line, as well as {{convert|2979|km\u00b2|sqmi|abbr=on}} in privately controlled areas, as a Biosphere Reserve according to the Statutory Framework of the World Network of Biosphere Reserves.<ref name=\"Nomination of Korea DMZ Biosphere Reserve\">{{cite web|last=Choi |first=Chungil |title=Nomination of Korea DMZ Biosphere Reserve |url=ftp://ftp.unesco.org/upload/sc/Advisory_Cttee2012/New%20BRs/Korea/DMZ/Letter%20of%20endorsement-DMZ.pdf |accessdate=3 October 2012 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=Al83tito |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The MAB National Committee of the Republic of Korea mentioned only the southern part of DMZ to be nominated since there was no response from [[Pyongyang]] when it requested Pyongyang to push jointly. North Korea is a member nation of the international coordinating council of UNESCO's Man and the Biosphere Programme, which designates Biosphere Reserves.<ref name=\"Seoul to seek UNESCO Biosphere Reserve status for DMZ\">{{cite news|last=Kim |first=Jeong-su |title=Seoul to seek UNESCO Biosphere Reserve status for DMZ |url=http://www.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_international/540913.html |accessdate=3 October 2012 |newspaper=Hankyoreh |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722081415/http://www.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_international/540913.html |archivedate=22 July 2012 }}</ref>\n\nNorth Korea opposed the application as a violation of the armistice agreement during the council's meeting in Paris on 9 to 13 July 2011. The South Korean government's attempt to designate the Demilitarized Zone (DMZ) a UNESCO Biosphere Reserve was turned down at UNESCO's MAB council meeting in Paris in July 2012. Pyongyang expressed its opposition by sending letters to 32 council member countries, except for South Korea, and the UNESCO headquarters a month prior to the meeting. At the council meeting, Pyongyang said the designation violated the Armistice Agreement.<ref name=\"Biosphere reserve status for the DMZ is urgent\">{{cite news|last=Cho |first=Do-soon |title=Biosphere reserve status for the DMZ is urgent |url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joinsmsn.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2957816 |accessdate=3 October 2012 |newspaper=JoonAng Daily |date=14 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621051310/http://koreajoongangdaily.joinsmsn.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2957816 |archivedate=21 June 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Destruction of guard posts==\nOn 26 October 2018, South Korean major general Kim Do-gyun and North Korean lieutenant general An Ik San met in [[Tongilgak]] (the \"Unification Pavilion\"), a North Korean building located within the DMZ's Joint Security Area (JSA). There, they began implementing new protocols which aim to reduce tension by requiring both North and South Korea to destroy 22 guard posts across the DMZ,<ref name=\"voaoct26\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.voanews.com/a/koreas-continue-tension-easing-talks-as-the-north-criticizes-us/4630152.html|title=Koreas Continue Tension-Easing Talks as the North Criticizes US|last=Miller|first=Steve|work=VOA|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref> among other steps. Both generals approved requirements for the guard posts to be destroyed by the end of November 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.apnews.com/9e3311a2c2a9431198032cdd6e7e86a2|title=2 Koreas to destroy 22 front-line guard posts by November|date=2018-10-26|work=AP NEWS|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref> The JSA's guard posts were destroyed on 25 October 2018.<ref name=voaoct26 /><ref name=\"independentoct25\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theindependent.com/news/world/koreas-un-finish-withdrawing-firearms-from-border-village/image_55ab50f5-8704-5770-812d-87c7832e0568.html|title=2 Koreas to destroy 22 front-line guard posts by November|last=Jin-man|first=Lee|work=The Grand Island Independent|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"yonhapoct25\">{{Cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2018/10/25/0200000000AEN20181025001351315.html|title=(LEAD) Two Koreas, UNC wrap up JSA disarmament|last=\uc1a1\uc0c1\ud638|date=2018-10-25|work=Yonhap News Agency|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref> North and South Korea agreed to dismantle 11 guard posts located within their individual country and deemed as \"front-line.\"<ref name=\"etoct26\">{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/2-koreas-to-destroy-11-front-line-guard-posts-by-november/articleshow/66377151.cms|title=2 Koreas to destroy 11 front-line guard posts by November|date=2018-10-26|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2018-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026222722/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/2-koreas-to-destroy-11-front-line-guard-posts-by-november/articleshow/66377151.cms|archive-date=26 October 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=reutersoct26 /><ref name=cgtnoct26 /> It was also agreed that after the posts are dismantled, both Koreas would also withdraw equipment and personnel stationed at each post as well.<ref name=\"reutersoct26\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-northkorea-southkorea/north-and-south-korea-agree-to-scrap-22-guard-posts-at-border-next-month-idUSKCN1N0082|title=North and South Korea agree to scrap 22 guard posts at border next...|last=Shin|first=Hyonhee|work=U.S.|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref> In tandem with the [[September 2018 inter-Korean summit#September 19 (Day 2)|September 2018 Pyongyang and Military Domain Agreements]],<ref name=etoct26 /><ref name=reutersoct26 /><ref name=cgtnoct26 /><ref>https://www.ncnk.org/sites/default/files/Agreement%20on%20the%20Implementation%20of%20the%20Historic%20Panmunjom%20Declaration%20in%20the%20Military%20Domain.pdf</ref> both sides also agreed to gradually remove all guard posts near the DMZ following verification in December 2018.<ref name=etoct26 /><ref name=reutersoct26 /><ref name=\"cgtnoct26\">{{Cite news|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d414e774d544d30457a6333566d54/share_p.html|title=Two Koreas agree to withdraw 11 guard posts in border area by late November|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref>\n\nHowever, all remaining troops and equipment, including weapons, were withdrawn from all of the 22 \"frontline\" guard posts before destruction began and both Koreas later agreed to individually destroy 10 of these guard posts instead of 11.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/north-and-south-korea-begin-destroying-border-guard-posts-10919016|title=North and South Korea begin destroying border guard posts|work=Channel NewsAsia|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=rappler11 /><ref name=latnov10 /><ref name=sfcnov10 />\n\nOn 4 November 2018, the North and South Korean governments hoisted a yellow flag above each of their 11 DMZ guard posts to publicly indicate that they all will be dismantled.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_northkorea/868900.html|title=South and North Korea begin trial dismantlement of guard posts surrounding DMZ|website=english.hani.co.kr}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\"/> On 10 November 2018, the withdrawal of military personnel and weapons from all of the DMZ's 22 \"front-line\" guard posts was completed.<ref name=\"latnov10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/world/la-fg-korea-guard-post-withdrawals-20181110-story.html|title=In latest trust-building step, North and South Korean military finish withdrawal from front-line guard posts|last=Press|first=Associated|website=latimes.com|access-date=2018-11-19|date=11 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"sfcnov10\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/world/article/North-South-dismantle-22-guard-posts-along-border-13380901.php|title=North, South dismantle 22 guard posts along border|date=2018-11-10|work=SFChronicle.com|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>http://www.hastingstribune.com/koreas-complete-the-disarming-of-guard-posts/article_bddc8489-3eb5-5982-b626-a4ed5d6e69dc.html{{Dead link|date=January 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The destruction of 20 guard posts officially began on 11 November 2018.<ref name=nov11kh>{{Cite web | url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20181111000255 |title = Koreas begin destroying 20 front-line guard posts|date = 11 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=yonhapnov11>http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2018/11/11/0200000000AEN20181111005200320.html</ref> However, both Koreas amended the original agreement and decided to preserve 2 of the 22 now demilitarized frontline guard posts.<ref name=nov11kh /><ref name=yonhapnov11 /> Both of the posts which were planned to be preserved are located on the opposite sides of the Korean border.<ref name=\"rappler11\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.rappler.com/world/regions/asia-pacific/216465-north-south-korea-begin-destroying-border-guard-posts|title=North and South Korea begin destroying border guard posts|work=Rappler|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 November 2018, destruction of two DMZ guard posts, one being located in South Korea and the other located in North Korea, was completed.<ref name=nov15>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2018/11/15/south-korea-destroys-guard-posts-along-border-with-north-korea.html|title=South Korea destroys guard posts along border with North Korea &#124; The Star|website=thestar.com}}</ref><ref name=mtnov15>{{Cite web|url=https://www.military.com/daily-news/2018/11/16/south-korea-dismantles-guard-posts-dynamite-excavators.html|title=South Korea Dismantles Guard Posts with Dynamite, Excavators|first=Hyung-jin|last=Kim|date=16 November 2018|website=Military.com}}</ref> Work was still ongoing to complete the destruction of other guard posts as well.<ref name=nov15 /><ref name=mtnov15 /> On 23 November 2018, it was revealed that South Korea was slowly destroying their guard posts with [[excavator]]s.<ref name=khnov23 />\n\nOn 20 November 2018, North Korea, hoping to further ease tensions with South Korea, destroyed all of their 10 remaining \"frontline\" guard posts.<ref name=abc11>{{Cite web|url=https://abc11.com/4726650/|title=North Korea detonates DMZ guard posts at southern border|date=21 November 2018|website=ABC11 Raleigh-Durham}}</ref><ref name=nov20>https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/seoul-north-korea-explodes-10-guard-posts-lower-59309949</ref> The South Korean Defense Ministry released photos confirming this and also released a statement stating that North Korea had informed them about the plans to demolish them before it took place.<ref name=nov20 /> This came in accordance with the earlier agreements.<ref name=abc11 /> South Korea also released videos of the guard posts being destroyed as well.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/north-korea-video-south-korea-dmz-guard-posts-explode-peace-agreement-border-a8643876.html |title = South Korea releases video of North Korea blowing up 10 guard posts in DMZ|date = 21 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 November 2018, both Koreas completed work to dismantle 10 of their \"frontline\" guard posts.<ref name=nov30 /><ref name=belarusnov30 /> However, the later agreement for each Korea to preserve one \"frontline\" post was upheld as well.<ref name=nov30 /> The \"frontline\" guard post which was preserved on the North Korean side of the DMZ was visited by Kim Jong Un in 2013 when tensions were rising between both Koreas.<ref name=khnov23>{{Cite web | url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20181120000703 |title = &#91;Video&#93; N. Korea destroys 10 DMZ guard posts|date = 20 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Establishment of buffer zones, no-fly zones and Yellow Sea peace zones==\nOn 1 November 2018, [[buffer zones]] were established across the DMZ by the North and South Korean militaries.<ref name=nov1 /> In compliance with the Comprehensive Military Agreement which was signed at the [[September 2018 inter-Korean summit]],<ref name=ncnkdirect /> the buffer zone helps ensure that both North and South Korea will effectively ban hostility on land, air, and sea.<ref name=nov1 /> Both Koreas are prohibited from conducting [[Live fire exercise|live-fire artillery drills]] and regiment-level field maneuvering exercises or those by bigger units within 5 kilometers of the Military Demarcation Line (MDL).<ref name=\"nov1\">{{Cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2018/11/01/0200000000AEN20181101002500315.html|title=Koreas halt all 'hostile' military acts near border|last=\uc774\uce58\ub3d9|date=2018-11-01|work=Yonhap News Agency|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en}}</ref> The buffer zones stretch from the north of Deokjeok Island to the south of Cho Island in the West Sea and the north of [[Sokcho]] city and south of Tongchon County in the East (Yellow) Sea.<ref name=\"ncnkdirect\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nknews.org/2018/10/two-koreas-end-military-drills-begin-operation-of-no-fly-zone-near-mdl-mnd/|title=Two Koreas end military drills, begin operation of no-fly zone near MDL: MND {{!}} NK News - North Korea News|date=2018-10-31|work=NK News - North Korea News|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n[[No-fly zones]] have also been established along the DMZ to ban the operation of drones, helicopters and other aircraft over an area up to {{Convert|40|km||abbr=on}} away from the MDL.<ref name=nov1 /> For [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|UAVs]], within {{Convert|15|km||abbr=on}} from the MDL in the East and {{Convert|10|km||abbr=on}} from the MDL in the West.<ref name=nov1effect /> Hot-air balloons cannot travel within {{Convert|25|km||abbr=on}} of the DMZ as well.<ref name=nov1effect /> For fixed-wing aircraft, no fly zones are designated within {{Convert|40|km||abbr=on}} from the MDL in the East (between MDL Markers No. 0646 and 1292) and within {{Convert|20|km||abbr=on}} of the MDL in the West (between MDL Markers No. 0001 and 0646).<ref name=ncnkdirect /> For [[rotary-wing aircraft]], the no fly zones are designated within {{Convert|10|km||abbr=on}} of the MDL.<ref name=ncnkdirect />\n\nBoth Koreas also created \"peace zones\" near their [[Border dispute|disputed]] Yellow Sea border.<ref name=nov1 />\n\n==Reconnecting of MDL-crossing road==\nOn 22 November 2018, North and South Korea completed construction to connect a three kilometer road along the DMZ, 90&nbsp;km northeast of Seoul.<ref name=nov22kr>{{Cite web | url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20181122006452315?section=national/defense |title = (2nd LD) Koreas connect road inside heavily fortified DMZ|date = 21 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=nov22>{{Cite web | url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/politics/south-north-korea-connect-border-road-through-dmz/1318769 |title = South, North Korea connect border road through DMZ}}</ref> This road, which crosses the Korean MDL land border, consists of 1.7&nbsp;km in South Korea and 1.3&nbsp;km in North Korea.<ref name=nov22 /> The road was reconnected for the first time in 14 years in an effort to assist with a process at the DMZ's Arrowhead Hill involving the removal of landmines and exhumation of Korean War remains.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.asianews.it/news-en/After-14-years,-a-road-to-unite-the-Koreas-and-recover-the-remains-of-the-fallen-45545.html |title = After 14 years, a road to unite the Koreas and recover the remains of the fallen}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/north-south-korea-join-roads-124905264.html|title=North and South Korea join roads after 14 years|website=www.yahoo.com}}</ref><ref>https://www.cairnspost.com.au/news/national/north-and-south-korea-join-roads-after-14-years/video/af8a644187eb15024a900b16826ebd24</ref>\n\n==Presence of landmines and Korean War remains==\nOn 1 October 2018, North and South Korean military engineers began a scheduled 20 day removal process of landmines and other explosives planted across the DMZ's [[Joint Security Area]] of the (DMZ).<ref name=bbckoreaoct /><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/10/01/north-south-korea-begin-removing-landmines-along-fortified-border/ |title = North and South Korea begin removing landmines along fortified DMZ|newspaper = The Telegraph|date = October 2018|last1 = Agency|first1 = Reuters News}}</ref><ref name=oct1>{{Cite web | url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/north-korea-south-korea-removing-land-mines-dmz-panmunjom-arrow-head-hill/ |title = North and South Korea begin removing mines along DMZ}}</ref> Work to remove landmines from the Joint Security Area was completed on 25 October 2018.<ref name=bbckoreaoct /><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3054494 |title = In 19 days, land mines are cleared from JSA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2018/10/356_257291.html | title=Two Koreas finish landmine cleanup in JSA. What's next?| date=19 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://pulsenews.co.kr/view.php?year=2018&no=653231 |title = Two Koreas complete demining and on path to make JSA arms-free - Pulse by Maeil Business News Korea}}</ref> Demining had begun at the DMZ's Arrowhead Hill and resulted in the discovery of Korean War remains.<ref name=oct25nov30>https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/south-korea-finds-war-remains-border-demining-58732705</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.dailyherald.com/article/20181025/news/310259972 |title = South Korea finds likely war remains during border demining|date = 25 October 2018}}</ref> Work between both Koreas to remove landmines from Arrowhead Hill was completed on 30 November 2018.<ref name=belarusnov30>{{Cite web | url=https://eng.belta.by/society/view/koreas-complete-work-on-removing-some-guard-posts-land-mines-in-dmz-116996-2018/ | title=Koreas complete work on removing some guard posts, land mines in DMZ| date=30 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=nov30kr>{{Cite web | url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20181130002400315 |title = Koreas to complete work to remove some guard posts, land mines in DMZ|date = 30 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Inter-Korean transportation services==\nOn 30 November 2018, following the removal of the \"frontline\" guard posts and Arrowhead Hill landmines, railroad transportation between North and South Korea which ceased in November 2008 resumed.<ref name=nov30>{{Cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/11/30/first-train-decade-departs-south-korea-north-korea/ |title = First train in a decade departs South Korea for North Korea|newspaper = The Telegraph|date = 30 November 2018|last1 = Avagnina|first1 = Gianluca}}</ref> The same day, 30 officials from both North and South Korea started an 18-day survey of a 400-kilometre (248-mile) railroad section in North Korea alongside the DMZ between Kaesong and Sinuiju.<ref name=voanov30>{{Cite web | url=https://www.voanews.com/a/koreas-survey-railway-tracks-cut-since-the-korean-war/4681029.html |title = Koreas Survey Railway Tracks Cut Since the Korean War}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web | url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2018/11/356_259637.html | title=South Korean train starts joint survey of North Korean railways| date=30 November 2018}}</ref> Efforts to conduct the survey had previously been obstructed due to the presence of the guard posts and the Arrowhead Hill landmines.<ref name=nov30 /> The survey will then follow the groundbreaking of a new railroad along the DMZ.<ref name=\"auto\"/> The railway survey which involved the [[Gyeongui Line]] concluded on 5 December 2018.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20181205000785 |title = &#91;Newsmaker&#93; Koreas in consultations for joint road inspection|date = 5 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 December 2018, a South Korean bus crossed the DMZ into North Korea.<ref name=dec8 /> The same day, the officials who conducted the inter-Korean survey for the Gyeongui Line began surveying the [[Donghae Line]].<ref name=dec8>{{Cite web | url=http://world.kbs.co.kr/service/news_view.htm?lang=e&Seq_Code=141408 |title = Joint Inspection of N. Korea's Eastern Rail Line Begins l KBS WORLD Radio}}</ref>\n\n==Military Border Crossing==\nOn 12 December 2018, militaries from both Koreas crossed the DMZ's MDL into the opposition countries for the first time in history to inspect and verify the removal of \"frontline\" guard posts.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/north-korea-south-korea-troops-cross-demilitarized-zone-in-peace-first-time/ | title=Troops cross North-South Korea Demilitarized Zone in peace for 1st time ever}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/north-and-south-korean-soldiers-enter-each-others-territory/north-invades-the-south/slideshow/67057861.cms | title=North and South Korean soldiers enter each other's territory | date=12 December 2018 | newspaper=The Economic Times | accessdate=9 February 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==Meeting of Trump, Kim, and Moon at the DMZ==\n{{Main|2019 Koreas\u2013United States DMZ Summit}}\nOn 30 June 2019, U.S. president [[Donald Trump]] became the first sitting U.S. president to enter North Korea, doing so at the DMZ line.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/president-trump-travel-dmz-meet-kim-jong/story?id=64042883 | title=President Trump becomes 1st president to step inside North Korea ahead of meeting with Kim Jong Un}}</ref> After crossing into North Korea, Trump and Kim met and shook hands.<ref name=\"cnnjune30\" />  Kim stated, in English, \"It's good to see you again\", \"I never expected to meet you at this place\" and \"you are the first U.S. president to cross the border.\"<ref name=cnnjune30 /> Both men then briefly crossed the border line before crossing back into South Korea.<ref name=cnnjune30>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/06/29/politics/kim-jong-un-donald-trump-dmz-north-korea/index.html|title=Trump takes 20 steps into North Korea, making history as first sitting US leader to enter hermit nation|first=Kevin |last=Liptak|website=CNN}}</ref>\n\nOn the South Korean side of the DMZ, Kim, Moon, and Trump held a brief chat before holding an hour-long [[2019 Koreas\u2013United States DMZ Summit|meeting]] at the DMZ's [[Inter-Korean House of Freedom]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.9news.com.au/world/trump-offers-to-meet-n-korea-s-kim-in-dmz/a39ece8d-fc6b-4ab8-81c8-af8b28f89415|title=Talks to reopen after Trump-Kim meeting - 9News|website=www.9news.com.au}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/06/30/trumps-press-secretary-bruised-after-jostling-with-north-korea-security-over-media-report-says/|title=Trump's press secretary bruised after jostling with North Korea security over media, report says|first=Hannah Knowles closeHannah KnowlesGeneral assignment|last=reporterEmailEmailBioBioFollowFollow|website=Washington Post}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Neutral Nations Supervisory Commission]]\n* [[Iron Curtain]]\n* [[Bamboo Curtain]]\n* [[United Nations Buffer Zone in Cyprus]]\n* [[Vietnamese Demilitarized Zone]]\n* [[Peace lines]]\n*[[North Korea\u2013South Korea relations]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Paige 1967\">{{cite journal |last=Paige |first= Glenn D. |authorlink=Glenn D. Paige |date=January 1967 |title= 1966: Korea Creates the Future |jstor=  2642450|journal= Asian Survey - A Survey of Asia in 1966: Part I|volume= 7|issue=1 |pages=21\u201330 |doi= 10.2307/2642450}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |title=Shield of the Great Leader. The Armed Forces of North Korea |last=Bermudez |first=Joseph S. |authorlink= |year=2001 |publisher=[[Allen & Unwin]] |location=Sydney |series=The Armed Forces of Asia |isbn=978-1-86448-582-0 |pages= }}\n*{{cite web |publisher=[[CNN World News]]  |title=South Korea warns North will pay 'harsh price' over DMZ landmine blasts|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/08/09/asia/koreas-tensions/ |first1=Jethro |last1=Mullen |first2=Kathy |last2=Novak |date=10 August 2015 |accessdate=24 February 2017}}\n* Elferink, Alex G. Oude, (1994). ''The Law of Maritime Boundary Delimitation: a Case Study of the Russian Federation.'' Dordrecht: [[Martinus Nijhoff]]. {{ISBN|9780792330820}}; [http://www.worldcat.org/title/law-of-maritime-boundary-delimitation-a-case-study-of-the-russian-federation/oclc/123566768 OCLC 123566768]\n*{{cite web |ref=harv |url=http://www.mmg.mpg.de/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/wp/WP_14-07_Jung%20Ballooning%20Evangelism.pdf |title=Ballooning Evangelism: Psychological Warfare and Christianity in the Divided Korea |last=Jung |first=Jin-Heon |date=2014 |website=[[Max Planck Institute]] |series=MMG Working Paper |issue=14\u201307 |pages=7\u201333 |access-date=27 June 2015 |issn=2192-2357 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150630054302/http://www.mmg.mpg.de/fileadmin/user_upload/documents/wp/WP_14-07_Jung%20Ballooning%20Evangelism.pdf |archive-date=30 June 2015 |url-status=dead }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons|Korean Demilitarized Zone}}\n{{wikivoyage|DMZ (Korea)}}\n* [https://www.chris-toone.com/blog/dmzsouthkorea/ Touring the DMZ in South Korea] What it's like to stand at the border, 2017\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/imcomkorea/sets/72157607715383952// U.S. Army official Korean Demilitarized Zone image archive]\n* [http://newsweek.washingtonpost.com/postglobal/america/2008/01/too_sexy_for_the_dmz.html Washington Post Correspondent Amar Bakshi travels to the Korean Demilitarized Zone... And uncovers the world's most dangerous tourist trap], January 2008.\n* [https://doi.org/10.1007%2Fs11355-005-0006-0 Status and ecological resource value of the Republic of Korea's De-militarized Zone]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l6cIUKOqPMI Tour Of DMZ on YouTube. Dec. 2007]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Ediz1vuwt0 Tour of DMZ from the DPRK on YouTube, 2016]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5XK4PPmi6AE 360 degree tour of DMZ from the DPRK on YouTube, 2016]\n* [http://www.dmzforum.org/ DMZ Forum: Collaborative international NGO focusing on promoting peace and conservation within the Korean DMZ region]\n* [https://news.yahoo.com/blogs/power-players-abc-news/inside-tour-scariest-place-earth-072912137.html ABCNews/Yahoo! report/blog on the DMZ]\n* [http://www.earthnutshell.com/the-worlds-most-dangerous-border-a-tour-of-north-koreas-dmz/ The World\u2019s Most Dangerous Border \u2013 A Tour of North Korea\u2019s DMZ] Visiting the DMZ from Pyongyang.\n*[http://worldbybike.com/goodbye-north-korea/#gallery/3432/15253 Photo of road linking DPRK to Paju, ROK]\n*[https://fall.law.fsu.edu/collection/LimitsinSeas/IBS022.pdf International Boundary Study No. 22 \u2013 May 24, 1963 Korea \u201cMilitary Demarcation Line\u201d Boundary]\n\n{{Korea topics|expanded=Geography}}\n{{Portal bar|North Korea|South Korea}}\n{{coords|38.329|127.250|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:1953 introductions]]\n[[Category:Korean Demilitarized Zone| ]]\n[[Category:North Korea\u2013South Korea border]]\n[[Category:Aftermath of the Korean War]]\n[[Category:Border barriers]]\n[[Category:Cold War terminology]]\n[[